betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKIg.name=§6§l§nYou'll Probably Need Quite a Few of These
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKIg.desc=It may not actually store any energy but it'll still be useful for some other endgame items.

# Quest: Stargate Command
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJQ.name=§6§l§nStargate Command
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJQ.desc=Okay so if you actually want to use the stargate you'll need these to power it and dial it up.

# Quest: What, How?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJg.name=§6§l§nWhat, How?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJg.desc=Congratulations, with this final quest, you'll have beaten the hardest challenge in GregTech: New Horizons yet! %n%nThe whole GT:NH Team thanks you for your time spent on this modpack. You are now part of the top 0.5%% of our community!%n%nNow that you made one gate, take this second gate and link them together! (Unless you want to craft the second yourself of course).%n%nDon't hesitate to share your base in #screenshot-brag channel of our Discord server, claim your stargate role, and if you have any feedback on the endgame progression, we will gladly appreciate it!%n%nI guess now it's time for you to go outside, touch grass, or... continue onwards?

# Quest: You Made It!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM4A.name=§4§l§nYou Made It!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM4A.desc=May Dreammaster have mercy on your soul. You have reached the highest craftable tier in the game!

# Quest: UXV Energy Hatch
betterquesting.quest.DGfri1njSxOeS79XXo4NIg.name=§4§l§nUXV Energy Hatch
betterquesting.quest.DGfri1njSxOeS79XXo4NIg.desc=The final energy hatch. You should make these wireless as soon as possible.

# Quest: Fabricating Solar Systems... in Parallel
betterquesting.quest.IGVryoMbRu28q08v4uwSuw.name=§4§l§nFabricating Solar Systems... in Parallel
betterquesting.quest.IGVryoMbRu28q08v4uwSuw.desc=As you've noticed, UXV components are extremely expensive compared to the amount of Universium you can currently produce.%n%nThe Astral Array Fabricator allows you to run EOH recipes in parallel. You can review the math in the second page of the tooltip.%n%nFor a direct answer, you can use this spreadsheet: [url]https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1FTFdfmY_UWbTbFOyNzARKeI90pbHvPBH6M3JHJmaC-E/edit?usp=sharing[/url]%n%n[warn]Be aware that the EOH will use Raw Stellar Plasma instead of Hydrogen and Helium if you use Astral Arrays.[/warn]%n%n[note]Make sure you are generating enough power.[/note]

# Quest: See You Next Time!
betterquesting.quest.KNM9ICNAQIa8NaFoXwCC9g.name=§6§l§nSee You Next Time!
betterquesting.quest.KNM9ICNAQIa8NaFoXwCC9g.desc=Still want more? Consider doing another run! Maybe even with some restrictions if you want to spice it up a bit. Check the first quest chapter for some recommendations!%n%nThere's also roles to be earned for completing the pack two or even three times if you want an extra incentive.%n%n[note]This quest and “The Factory Must Grow!” are mutually exclusive; completing one will lock the other.%n%nIf you are going for 100%% questbook completion, don't panic, finishing either quest still allows the tab to receive a green check (much like the previous XOR quests).[/note]

# Quest: It Gets to a Point
betterquesting.quest.Ni-YWTVjSz6Bk_MeC0hIiQ.name=§4§l§nIt Gets to a Point
betterquesting.quest.Ni-YWTVjSz6Bk_MeC0hIiQ.desc=You are not done with wafers. Ok well, now you are, kind of.%n%nInfinite Wafers are the final tier of raw wafer, forged directly in the God Forge. Who knew silicon could hold up for this long?%n%nYocto Power ICs are used in Magmatter Nanites, MAX circuits, and UXV Energy Hatches.%n%n
%n[note]You'll need a UXV Laser Engraver to cut these.
%n
%nYocto Power ICs need to be coated in Quark Gluon Plasma in an Exo-Foundry, overclocked to reach the MAX voltage required. This step cannot be done in a Mass Solidifier.[/note]

# Quest: The Factory Must Grow!
betterquesting.quest.OCv5OWo6Q9KDfqe1w0ET9w.name=§6§l§nThe Factory Must Grow!
betterquesting.quest.OCv5OWo6Q9KDfqe1w0ET9w.desc=A single stargate pair wasn't enough for you?%n%nWell then, time to build a network.%n%nWelcome to the post-stargate tier! %n%nNow that you successfully managed to make a stargate, what about crafting them in industrial quantities? Try to craft 5 pairs of gates in the least amount of time, then come in #screenshot-brag and post your time to see where your infrastructure stands in the community!%n%n[note]This quest and “See You Next Time!” are mutually exclusive; completing one will lock the other.%n%nIf you are going for 100%% questbook completion, don't panic, finishing either quest still allows the tab to receive a green check (much like the previous XOR quests).[/note]%n%n§dEnjoy your round of Minesweeper!

# Quest: Assembling on Space Steroids
betterquesting.quest.UVG21mYSQJex90gQWdkpIw.name=§4§l§nAssembling on Space Steroids
betterquesting.quest.UVG21mYSQJex90gQWdkpIw.desc=Has 64 parallels and consumes ~30b EU/t per module, expensive to run but absolutely worth it.

# Quest: Humongous Hatch
betterquesting.quest.Uj0PvsNCQw-aWaEOvlFpow.name=§4§l§nHumongous Hatch
betterquesting.quest.Uj0PvsNCQw-aWaEOvlFpow.desc=At last... salvation from the egregious EoH hatch input limitations!%n%nThis will reduce the waiting time between cycles to a fraction of what it was before. 

# Quest: Rule of Threes
betterquesting.quest.bHFEDKAiTwGxaiyZEsmdjg.name=§4§l§nRule of Threes
betterquesting.quest.bHFEDKAiTwGxaiyZEsmdjg.desc=The final external structural upgrade to the Forge requires the most advanced understanding of graviton shards and their applications in extreme environments. With this, the last 4 module slots of the Forge of the Gods are available to construct, ascending your operation to unseen heights of technological mastery.%n%n[note]Adding a third and final ring to your Godforge allows for 4 additional modules, as well as allowing you to pick all three paths in the split paths part of the upgrade tree, allowing for a fully upgraded Godforge.[/note]%n%n[note]Usage of a third ring requires the END upgrade.[/note]

# Quest: Simulating a Solar System
betterquesting.quest.hNdNrT_aSKaYi_TnT7cowA.name=§4§l§nSimulating a Solar System
betterquesting.quest.hNdNrT_aSKaYi_TnT7cowA.desc=Almost as expensive as the real one, right? Not to worry, this stargate and the current are only just the beginning.%n%n[note]Our journey reaches the current end, entering the UXV, aka EOH era.%n%nThe year is 2023, and the game continues to be pushed further and further. The EOH exists now, along with machine parts up to UXV. Multiblocks have gained endless amounts of quality of life, including sub 1-tick OC, batch mode, void protection, and numerous AE2 additions like Crafting Input Buses, Stocking Hatches, Level Maintainers and more. Automation has never been easier, yet the goal has never been placed farther. Naquadah Fuel now has many tiers and can compete into the late-game, even competing with (now fixed) Dyson, but outclassed by the huge amount of power a maximized EOH can make (12.8 TEU/t!).%n%nInitially the stargate recipe seemed impossible, requiring months of runtime on hundreds of maximized EOHs, requiring some adjustments to be more realistic to attain. After this was changed, the race began again, this time between §aJohny709§r and §aGDCloud§r. §aJohny§r burned out towards the end, and §aGDCloud§r was surpassed by a silent contender, §aStarStack§r, being the first to conquer this challenge on the §a26th of June, 2023§r.%n%nBeyond just the first, this era marked the beginning of the Group Run Era, with large runs such as §aBallers Run§r (setting this era into motion), §aBee Run§r (affecting wide change on the NH project and its management as a whole), and §aCell Run 2§r (the fastest ever Stargate run at the time, only 73 days, popularizing many automation techniques like Level Maintained lines).%n%nAdditionally, this version saw the first player achieve GTNH Gods, reaching Stargate in a 3rd run, earned by §aGDCloud§r as a part of §aCell Run 2§r on the §a23rd of June, 2024§r. Later this Stargate would see three others reach this goal, §aRamspace§r on the §a29th of September, 2024§r, and §aStaffiX§r and §aserenibyss§r in a group run on the §a17th of November, 2024§r.%n%nP.S.: Here's the list as usual:%n-Many new processing multiblocks like HILE, Fluid Shaper, Industrial Autoclave, etc.%n-Forge of the Gods, Black Hole Compressor, Antimatter power generation, Precise Assembler T4%n-DTPF Convergence, Component Assembly Line tiered bonuses, Mega Vac Subspace Cooling, MK5 fusion skips for Metastable Oganesson%n-Wireless Data Hatches, Wireless Optical Hatches, Uncertainty Resolution%n-Artificial Universe Cells, smart blocking mode[/note]

# Quest: T3 Exo-Foundry
betterquesting.quest.iLn_-6-LSk-wEOfi9muW3w.name=§4§l§nT3 Exo-Foundry
betterquesting.quest.iLn_-6-LSk-wEOfi9muW3w.desc=Now that you have your hands on Eternity you can upgrade your §nExo-Foundry§r to the final tier!%n%nThe §6§lCelestial Magnetic Chassis§r will allow your Foundry to have a maximum of four modules installed, unlocking the most powerful combinations.%n%n[note]Checkout the Wiki if you need ideas on which modules to choose [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Exo-Foundry[/url][/note]

# Quest: A Minor Roadblock
betterquesting.quest.itcSYyc3Tdq9Q1qrP5RoEg.name=§4§l§nA Minor Roadblock
betterquesting.quest.itcSYyc3Tdq9Q1qrP5RoEg.desc=MAX circuits huh... Is it really almost over?

# Quest: Your Lord and Saviour, UXV CoAL
betterquesting.quest.smCKxKkMSeyIAUeFInS4hQ.name=§4§l§nYour Lord and Saviour, UXV CoAL
betterquesting.quest.smCKxKkMSeyIAUeFInS4hQ.desc=You want to rush this as soon as possible.%n%nEvery L of Universium matters.


## Quest Line: Feeding Yourself
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACg.name=Feeding Yourself
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACg.desc=Don't worry. Papa-G will fix it.

# Quest: Hunger No More
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACWA.name=Hunger No More
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACWA.desc=The hunger is constantly following you, consuming you, never letting you rest. The world around you is full of nourishing fruits, vegetables and crafted meals. Use them to curb your insatiable hunger.

# Quest: Grain Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACcw.name=Grain Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACcw.desc=Crafting some nice grain bait for your animal trap.

# Quest: Fruit Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdA.name=Fruit Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdA.desc=Crafting some tasty fruit bait for your animal trap.

# Quest: Veggie Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdQ.name=Veggie Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdQ.desc=Crafting some veggie bait for your animal trap.

# Quest: Fish Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdg.name=Fish Bait
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdg.desc=Crafting some fish bait for your fish trap.

# Quest: Animal Trapping
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdw.name=Animal Trapping
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACdw.desc=Tired of hunting for cows, zombies or sheep? You can build a trap and hope some animal or monster drops will be caught by the netting inside.

# Quest: A Fisherman's Friend
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeA.name=A Fisherman's Friend
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeA.desc=Have you ever tried to catch a fish with your bare hands? It's time to craft a fishing rod and get some fish the easy way. Cast your fishing rod in some water and wait until the bobber dips below the surface. Then reel back in your line and hopefully you caught yourself something nice.

# Quest: Fish Trapping
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeQ.name=Fish Trapping
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeQ.desc=Fishing can be very boring. Why not automate it with a fish trap?

# Quest: Wheat Time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeg.name=Wheat Time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACeg.desc=It's time to plant some wheat to make some bread or to prepare grain bait for your animal traps.

# Quest: Floury Flurry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACew.name=Floury Flurry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACew.desc=The first step in making bread is to macerate your wheat into flour with a mortar or a macerator.%n%nFlour can be used in many food recipes for different Pam's HarvestCraft foods.

# Quest: First Handmade Bread
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfA.name=First Handmade Bread
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfA.desc=Baking your dough in a Furnace makes some tasty bread. Your first bread!

# Quest: Do'h!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfQ.name=Do'h!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfQ.desc=Water and flour makes a dough or two... Dough can be used in many different food recipes from Pam's HarvestCraft.%n%nDon't use the terrible NEI recipe, instead drop a stack of flour into a cauldron full of water. Celiacs beware!

# Quest: Tasty Toast
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfg.name=Tasty Toast
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACfg.desc=Smelt your bread again and you get some toast! It gives you more nutrition points, and unlocks more culinary potential!

# Quest: Kitchenware
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmQ.name=Kitchenware
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmQ.desc=To cook some healthy food you need a few tools crafted first.%nSaucepan,%npot,%nrolling pin,%nmortar,%nmixing bowl,%nsoft mallet,%nskillet,%nknife...

# Quest: Fish Trapping 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD8Q.name=Fish Trapping 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD8Q.desc=Fishing can be very boring. Why not automate it with a fish trap?%n%nThis is fish trap 2.0.

# Quest: Fresh Water and Milk
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD8g.name=Fresh Water and Milk
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD8g.desc=Many cooking recipes need milk and water. Crafting it in the crafting table can be very tedious.%n%nIt is much easier using a Forestry worktable. Move all your buckets into the worktable, and shift-click to craft them all at once.

# Quest: Chef Training
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADWg.name=Chef Training
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADWg.desc=I need some ingredients to help me train since they don't grow well where I am, could you provide some? I'll give you the results in return.%n%n[note]You only need to turn in one set each time you complete the quest.[/note]

# Quest: Wheaty Juice
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE-A.name=Wheaty Juice
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE-A.desc=The first step to brew beer or other alcoholic fluids is wheaty juice.

# Quest: Fake Jagermeister
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE-w.name=Fake Jagermeister
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE-w.desc=Jägermeister is a common drink in Germany, why don't you grab a bottle? This one seems to be a cheap fake tho...

# Quest: Juice
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEPg.name=Juice
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEPg.desc=Most of your berries can be extracted to juice form. This is a chance to get more food variants and the nutritional value is higher than eating the fruit directly.

# Quest: Potato Cakes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEPw.name=Potato Cakes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEPw.desc=Potatoes, onions, butter and a skillet make very tasty potato cakes.

# Quest: Fried Eggs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQA.name=Fried Eggs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQA.desc=So easy, skillet and an egg.... fried egg.

# Quest: Hearty Breakfast
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQQ.name=Hearty Breakfast
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQQ.desc=Now let's combine all the things together and make a healthy and delicious breakfast.%n%nSome cooked meat, potato cakes, toast, fried egg and a tasty juice provide you with a very nourishing meal.%n%nYou can use any cooked meat and any fruit juice here.

# Quest: Korn and Doppelkorn
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_A.name=Korn and Doppelkorn
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_A.desc=Korn is german for wheat. That's why this special alcoholic brew is named like this. Doppelkorn means double-wheat.

# Quest: Sugarcanes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_Q.name=Sugarcanes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_Q.desc=Sugarcanes are a source of sugar, and therefore alcohol. If you want some rum or sugar, you'll need these.

# Quest: Vodka
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_g.name=Vodka
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE_g.desc=Vodka is Russian for "small water". It is a rather high proof alcoholic fluid.

# Quest: Food 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEmg.name=Food 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEmg.desc=Forget everything you know about food and values. With your new canning machine you are able to fill tin cans with very nourishing food. This food can be consumed in milliseconds and makes you full and happy. And you can eat as much as you want without getting tired of the food.%n%nEating before you are starving restores saturation and conserves cans.

# Quest: Dezil's Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF0A.name=Dezil's Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF0A.desc=In the last step you need to infuse your Marshmallow with some epic food in the Thaumcraft infusion altar. Before you can do it you need to unlock the research.%n%nIs this worth it? Is there any enemy worthy of using the buffs this gives on? That's up to you.

# Quest: The industrial way
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAA.name=The industrial way
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAA.desc=Making rum can be automated, but you need to follow this industrial way for it.

# Quest: Rum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAQ.name=Rum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAQ.desc=Rum. Yummy!

# Quest: Sugar: The Gathering
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAg.name=Sugar: The Gathering
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAg.desc=Stockpiling sugar might be a good idea if you have a sweet tooth. Or not?

# Quest: Honey for sugar.
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAw.name=Honey for sugar.
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFAw.desc=Since honey contains a lot of sugar, it might be a good idea to get some honey.%n%n[note]Just having the fluid in cells or buckets in your inventory lets the quest detect and consume it.[/note]

# Quest: Wasps honey
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFBA.name=Wasps honey
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFBA.desc=Giant wasps can be found in the Nether. Quick! Sneak into their hive and steal some honey!%n%n[note]Just having the fluid in cells or buckets in your inventory lets the quest detect it.[/note]

# Quest: Really OP Food
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFyw.name=Really OP Food
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFyw.desc=You've heard about Dezil's Marshmallow, a really OP food which can be found from time to time in chests. What about I show you a way to cook this stuff yourself?%n%nAfter you've mastered the flowing spirit in the dream dimension (witchery), put a bit of flour, sugar, salis mundus and draconium dust in your IV Mixer.%nThe recipe starts when you give flowing spirit to it and gives you malformed slush, a very stinky and disgusting piece of...something.%n%nBe careful, you'll get blindness II when holding it in your hand.

# Quest: Uncooked Slush
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzA.name=Uncooked Slush
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzA.desc=Next step is to form this slush into the right shape. Use a Marshmallow Mold and press it with your IV forming press. Remember to sterilize it after using it.%n%nBe careful, you'll get blindness and hunger II holding it.

# Quest: Glowing Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzg.name=Glowing Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzg.desc=Next step is heating up your Marshmallow in an Electric Blast Furnace at 4500K with some noble gas and making it glow.%n%nNow you'll get a Paralysis II effect in addition to the others.

# Quest: Cooling Your Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzw.name=Cooling Your Marshmallow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFzw.desc=In the next step you cool your Glowing Marshmallow in an EV Vacuum Freezer to make it more stable.%n%nYou still get Weakness II and Nausea II.

# Quest: Kitchenware 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHLA.name=Kitchenware 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHLA.desc=GregTech tools like the knives get used up when crafting foods. Pam's Tool like the Cutting Board, Juicer or the Bakeware can last forever.%n%nAfter you reach stainless steel in HV you can make these tools that last forever.

# Quest: Just Like Mom Used to Make
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHPg.name=Just Like Mom Used to Make
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHPg.desc=Jelly sandwiches are a great food source with decent saturation and are easy to make. Almost any fruit can be converted to jelly with sugar and a saucepan. There are a few different nut butters available. Peanuts can be found in Ground Gardens in forest, mountain, or taiga style biomes. Cashews are trees located in jungles or swamps. Chestnuts can be found in warmer forests. Pistachios can be found in jungles. Many of these saplings are also available for trade from villagers.%n%nTo keep all your recipes together, you can use either a Kitchen multiblock if you want to see all recipes available to you, or a Forestry Worktable if you're fine with the limit of nine recipes.%n%nSome sandwiches have better saturation than others, so be sure to check before buying that sapling!

# Quest: I Like Big Sandwiches
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHPw.name=I Like Big Sandwiches
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHPw.desc=Now that you have dough, there are several options for large sandwiches. They offer great saturation restoration and are easy to make.%n%nThe veggie and cheese options aren't quite as good and need more work to produce.%n%nThere are also normal-sized varieties of these sandwiches if you need more diet choices.

# Quest: No Chicken Escapes!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHQQ.name=No Chicken Escapes!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHQQ.desc=Do you like pies? I sure do! There are many varieties of pies available for you. The chicken pot pie is one of the easiest to make. Just a chicken, potato, carrot, and some dough. The fruit pies are a little simpler, so they don't quite restore as much saturation, but are great for filling tummies while you wait for the best foods to wear off.

# Quest: Pumpkin Pie
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJhw.name=Pumpkin Pie
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJhw.desc=Pumpkin Pie is a traditional US dessert that is particularly popular for Halloween, Thanksgiving, and Christmas.%n%n1,5 Food Bars for just two Pumpkins and a three sugar. Bon Appétit.

# Quest: Barley Time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKpQ.name=Barley Time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKpQ.desc=It's time to plant some barley to make some bread. If you can't find wheat, barley is a good alternative source to make flour.

# Quest: Cooking for Blockheads
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTw.name=Cooking for Blockheads
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTw.desc=Say thanks to mitch for backporting this great mod. You can use it to help you craft new food items. All blocks connected to the kitchen floor (use it as walls too!) are considered part of the same multiblock. Countertops will search up two blocks for cabinets to include.%n%nItems stored in storages like the cabinet (or your inventory) can be used in recipes. All storage spaces for items are the same, so don't bother making a ton of fridges unless you really want to. Supply water to the sink to get water for recipes.%n%nYou can store some cooking tools in the oven. You can store the rest on tool racks to auto-use them all in recipes. This includes stuff like the GT soft mallet if you can't make all the Pam's tools yet.%n%nThe oven has 3 input slots and 3 output slots, and can work on 9 items at once. It's basically a furnace. You can request items be cooked from the cooking table too.%n%nThe Cooking Table will automatically show you all recipes that can be created with the existing ingredients, and you can click on them to craft them. Make all the food, and get all the hearts!%n%nYou can use dye to color the kitchen, except for the oven.%n%nNote that the implementation is not finished, so there are some problems. Upgrades like powering the oven with RF/EU are not in yet. And so on. But we finally have a toaster so you can make TOAST!%n%n[note]There is no cow in a jar, it will not come back.[/note]

# Quest: Crispy Rotten Flesh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUg.name=Crispy Rotten Flesh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUg.desc=Rotten Flesh is not really healthy. It doesn't satisfy your hunger. What if you try to dry it?

# Quest: A Magical Lunchbox?
betterquesting.quest.ogXyVJTpQ8ONbZthhrupqg.name=A Magical Lunchbox?
betterquesting.quest.ogXyVJTpQ8ONbZthhrupqg.desc=Given sufficient magical prowess, the Thaumaturgist need not waste their time physically consuming food. The Talisman of Nourishment can hold up to 1000 hunger and 1000 saturation points, and will feed you automatically. %n%nYou can fill it up by placing food items on your hotbar, the more valuable the food, the more points added.%n%n[note]Careful not to place food items you want to keep in your hotbar while you have it on you![/note]


## Quest Line: The Green Revolution
betterquesting.questline.GbGDSZsbQUekpRKT9ZPdjw.name=The Green Revolution
betterquesting.questline.GbGDSZsbQUekpRKT9ZPdjw.desc=And remember crawlers: Kill, Kill, Kill! But only plants.

# Quest: Auronia
betterquesting.quest.-9Qf3tBHQbKZrhhefIRApg.name=Auronia
betterquesting.quest.-9Qf3tBHQbKZrhhefIRApg.desc=A great source of gold.%n%nAuronia leaves will 4x your gold ore.

# Quest: Mutation Titration
betterquesting.quest.0P-0LIDsRa-0r0SDSfZTUg.name=Mutation Titration
betterquesting.quest.0P-0LIDsRa-0r0SDSfZTUg.desc=Before going any further you really should craft a lot,[note] and I mean a lot[/note], of crop sticks. Hope you like chopping trees and crafting saws! §o§oYou should've seen the old recipe...%n%n§o§rEach of the adjacent quest groupings represent a different category of crops found within the mod. If you haven't yet, I would highly recommend you review the in depth guide quests focusing on [warn]Crop Stats[/warn] and [warn]Crop Nutrients[/warn].%n%nWhile not every crop will produce a useful harvest, they very well may deterministically breed into a useful crop or open up a useful pool. So don't throw away new species just because they don't seem immediately useful.%n%nCertain crops need more than just two parents to breed. For those crops, simply surround a single double cropstick with all 3-4 crops needed and continue as normal.%n%n[note]Be free farmhand~![/note]

# Quest: Vanilla Agriculture
betterquesting.quest.0pG3BaWpTQWJLWKudvCdcw.name=Vanilla Agriculture
betterquesting.quest.0pG3BaWpTQWJLWKudvCdcw.desc=Most plants from vanilla Minecraft can simply be placed onto crop sticks to create their associated CropsNH crop. This is especially helpful when it comes to Bonsais, which will allow you to more easily (and less laggily) produce the hectares of wood you will need for your progression.%n%n[warn]Note the soil requirements for your bonsai in NEI, §nyou cannot plant§r these on normal tilled farmland.[/warn]

# Quest: Salty!
betterquesting.quest.1b0GPUIOTL2vkERs7LqFtg.name=Salty!
betterquesting.quest.1b0GPUIOTL2vkERs7LqFtg.desc=These Salty Roots will break down into bountiful materials once you're able to separate them in a Chemical Bath.%n%nYou'll need a multiblock in order to get your hands on the borax dust.

# Quest: Aluminium Berries
betterquesting.quest.1rhK6oRBQ-qc6YJxPn4CuQ.name=Aluminium Berries
betterquesting.quest.1rhK6oRBQ-qc6YJxPn4CuQ.desc=Maybe this will stop you from tearing down entire mesas worth of terracotta.

# Quest: Passive Production
betterquesting.quest.20MjFyzJQhWPEPkK0EZDeA.name=Passive Production
betterquesting.quest.20MjFyzJQhWPEPkK0EZDeA.desc=One of the main reasons for getting into CropsNH is the passive production of resources.%n%nThe many crops attached to this quest will generally provide you the direct resource you are looking for. This can be perfect for getting that extra bit of aluminium you need to push through MV, or for generating a passive amount of basic minerals long before any other techniques become available.%n%n§4Keep in mind the sub-soil requirements for these crops especially. §rTo passively produce aluminium, you will first need blocks of aluminium or bauxite ore.

# Quest: Controlled Breeding
betterquesting.quest.39AFOCfITcSl7WMmATD3Aw.name=Controlled Breeding
betterquesting.quest.39AFOCfITcSl7WMmATD3Aw.desc=With your Stone Lily in hand, get ready to breed all the other species of §oLilliums§r! You can use deterministic breeding of course, but with pools and some undersoil management it shouldn't take too long at all.%n%nRemember that whether by pools or determinism, new crops will only be produced if the environment of the relevant double crop sticks matches the required environment of the new crop.

# Quest: Oh-Oh-Oh-Olivia
betterquesting.quest.3GtBaKquRvWXh6S4VqcD3Q.name=Oh-Oh-Oh-Olivia
betterquesting.quest.3GtBaKquRvWXh6S4VqcD3Q.desc=You know-oh-oh Olivine?%n%n§mIf you or a loved one has put the output of this crop and some distilled water in an autoclave, you may be entitled to financial compensation.§r

# Quest: The Environmental Enhancement Unit
betterquesting.quest.3uJ9TqwJQ5K3UPUFmx06sQ.name=The Environmental Enhancement Unit
betterquesting.quest.3uJ9TqwJQ5K3UPUFmx06sQ.desc=If you don't want to use magic to change the biome for your IF, you will have to apply some advanced biome simulation technology to your Industrial Farm.%n%nEach Environmental Enhancement Unit allows you to insert an Environmental Module inside of your IF controller. (You can only have up to 2 of these upgrades at a time). Environmental Modules can only be inserted while the machine is powered off. Each one increases the power usage by 50%% (even if you don't have a module installed).%n%n%nAs with all upgrades, the tier of the upgrade must match the tier of the seedbed.

# Quest: Slimy Seeds
betterquesting.quest.4hn4bXWvSay8UYjckHDH4A.name=Slimy Seeds
betterquesting.quest.4hn4bXWvSay8UYjckHDH4A.desc=The slime plant represents yet another way to produce those sticky materials needed for rubber and therefore electronic components.

# Quest: Tine
betterquesting.quest.5K0m6kADSVqZuouYNTEYWw.name=Tine
betterquesting.quest.5K0m6kADSVqZuouYNTEYWw.desc=A great source of tin.%n%nTine leaves will 4x your tin ore.

# Quest: Nightshade
betterquesting.quest.5KieQ6A4R1CGnGQd4CuQXw.name=Nightshade
betterquesting.quest.5KieQ6A4R1CGnGQd4CuQXw.desc=With the intense amount of magical energy the Nightshade emanates, you will need an Industrial Farm to produce and harvest it.%n%n[note]You can optionally just right-click Magic Essence into a cropstick instead of breeding the seed.[/note]

# Quest: Environmental Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.5vhRsuqOTjeLbozeMGcweA.name=Environmental Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.5vhRsuqOTjeLbozeMGcweA.desc=These modules each simulate a single favored biome tag for the crops in your IF.

# Quest: Tools of the Trade 3 - Feeding(?) Your Crops
betterquesting.quest.6HEnaqUVQuWHhHc3MAgQnA.name=Tools of the Trade 3 - Feeding(?) Your Crops
betterquesting.quest.6HEnaqUVQuWHhHc3MAgQnA.desc=That water source block doesn't really do it for your little guys. They will need a bit more attention, so use a watering can to increase their water stat.

# Quest: Other Fruits
betterquesting.quest.7UxcGl38S4yX3bIg7EdN-Q.name=Other Fruits
betterquesting.quest.7UxcGl38S4yX3bIg7EdN-Q.desc=Yes, tomatoes and chillies are technically fruits.%n%nOne of these crops is not like the other...

# Quest: Don't Forget Your Veggies
betterquesting.quest.82cQe4FcTTS5D8SuprUeaw.name=Don't Forget Your Veggies
betterquesting.quest.82cQe4FcTTS5D8SuprUeaw.desc=Have you eaten your veggies today? That's what I thought.

# Quest: Seed Generator
betterquesting.quest.8VW6FtZZRf6SAviHhNftWg.name=Seed Generator
betterquesting.quest.8VW6FtZZRf6SAviHhNftWg.desc=The Seed Generator is a single-block machine that can clone §omost§r existing seeds (with some very rare exceptions).%n%nIn order to clone a seed, you'll need to provide the following:%n- 36L of §2Enriched Fertilizer§r per stat point; So a 31/31/31 seed will require just under 3.4KL of §2Enriched Fertilizer§r per seed.%n- Some crops may require an additional catalyst item based on the material produced by the seed.%n%nThe seed generator has an NEI tab so feel free to consult it.%n%nThe fluid storage capacity of the Seed Generator is §omuch smaller§r than most machines, [note]you'll need at least an §5HV§r machine to replicate crops with maxed stats.[/note]%n%n§oYou only need one of the machines for this quest.

# Quest: Not The Pipes
betterquesting.quest.8XwasO5LQDW-ynx3pu2Zeg.name=Not The Pipes
betterquesting.quest.8XwasO5LQDW-ynx3pu2Zeg.desc=Stop using this for your pipes please. I swear. It's like you don't want a working brain. The throughput of potin just isn't worth it!

# Quest: Primordial "Berries"
betterquesting.quest.8vumBDgBToW6ngAzW1qF2Q.name=Primordial "Berries"
betterquesting.quest.8vumBDgBToW6ngAzW1qF2Q.desc=These bad boys are the most advanced species you can imagine. They will require extensive technological investment to breed, and take extremely long to produce their harvest.%n%nThey will require an Industrial Farm to grow.%n%n[warn]Water, fertilizer and sky access alone won't cut it for this crop, you'll need at least 1 biome tag or a high humidity biome or else your crop will get sick.[/warn]

# Quest: Jack, is that you?
betterquesting.quest.9IaKfZelRA2GaWVUgFvJQg.name=Jack, is that you?
betterquesting.quest.9IaKfZelRA2GaWVUgFvJQg.desc=Magic beans! Unfortunately no stalks into the sky here though.

# Quest: Silver And... Silver
betterquesting.quest.9mlSMwwETgGeMJTOggJfvg.name=Silver And... Silver
betterquesting.quest.9mlSMwwETgGeMJTOggJfvg.desc=Silver dust! Exciting! (not)

# Quest: Rubber Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.A21peFIQTEKAgY7eH4tjLw.name=Rubber Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.A21peFIQTEKAgY7eH4tjLw.desc=Easy rubber wood and sticky resin! These bonsai present a more complicated alternative to other rubber production methods, while providing additional useful materials.

# Quest: Speed Up Your Plant Growth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC0g.name=Speed Up Your Plant Growth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC0g.desc=Fertilizer is a foundational resource to produce and consume when farming. It has two key features:%n%n1. Speeding up crop growth by boosting the nutrient score.%n%n2. Preventing stat loss during crop breeding. This simply prevents stat loss; it doesn't increase the likelihood of a stat increase.%n%n4 Seperate items can be used to apply fertilizer to your crops, each providing a different amount of fertilizer points:%n%n- Crops NH Fertilizer: 100 points%n- Forestry Compost: 50 points%n- Forestry Fertilizer: 25 points%n- Bone Meal: 5 points%n%n[note]While Bone Meal may seem weak, it's ability to still prevent stat loss when breeding is key if you intend to start crops before you can make a Chemical Reactor.[/note]%n%nThe Crop Managers and the Industrial Farm both also accept liquid fertilizers. Right now there is 2 of them:%n%n- Fertilizer: 1 point per L%n- Enriched Fertilizer: 10 points per L

# Quest: Becoming a Florist
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC1Q.name=Becoming a Florist
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC1Q.desc=Time to get in touch with your inner florist, arrange these flowers well and they will help you breed more useful species!%n%n[note]If you actually want these for dyes, go make the rainbow cactus instead.[/note]

# Quest: Tools of the Trade 1 - Less Dirty Hands
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE9g.name=Tools of the Trade 1 - Less Dirty Hands
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAE9g.desc=This tool is a combined Trowel, Hoe, and Shovel. The basic spade will allow you to easily clear weeds from your sticks, till soil, and potentially obtain bonus seeds from simply harvesting the crops (right-click) without breaking them. Each point of resistance increases the chance of getting a seed when harvesting with the basic spade as follows:%n%n1 Resist = 3%%%n10 Resist = 32%%%n31 Resist = 100%%%n%n[note]If you're removing a crop with your spade, sneaking will let you remove the crop without having to worry about the spade breaking the crop stick.[/note]

# Quest: Hops, The Source of Beer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFCA.name=Hops, The Source of Beer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFCA.desc=If you don't want pure alcohol, but beer, breed some hops!

# Quest: Babies First Harvest Automaton
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGBg.name=Babies First Harvest Automaton
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGBg.desc=The Crop Manager is a single-block machine that will monitor crops in an area around itself and automatically apply fertilizer (fluid or item), Weed-EX, and water as needed. The water, fertilizer, and Weed-Ex can be pumped in directly, or use IC2 Universal water cells, normal cells aren't returned when they're used.%n%nJust like any other single block machine, Crop Managers are NOT rainproof, but you can cover them with a water source block just fine!%n%nTilled dirt still requires a nearby water block to be hydrated as the Manager will only water the crop, not the soil. Try putting a lily pad on top so it isn't annoying to walk on.

# Quest: Weed-EX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGBw.name=Weed-EX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGBw.desc=Weed-EX is used to prevent the growth and spread of weeds on empty crop sticks.%n%nYou can either spray it manually using a spray can, or supply it to a Crop Manager to automatically apply it to all crops in range.

# Quest: Sticky Canes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQA.name=Sticky Canes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQA.desc=While Sugarcane alone is quite useful, its close relative Sticky Cane is even moreso! Thanks to its production of sticky resin, it is a near universally used crop for the production of rubber in all sorts of electronics.

# Quest: Feeling a Little Like a Noob?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQw.name=Feeling a Little Like a Noob?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGQw.desc=You should grow some essence berries to level up!

# Quest: Put the Petal to the Metal...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRA.name=Put the Petal to the Metal...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRA.desc=... with the Bio Diesel you produce from Canola!%n%n%nWhile some still see Canola as nothing but a younger brother to the Goldfish, maybe you will find something greater hiding behind its oily guise.

# Quest: Warts!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRQ.name=Warts!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRQ.desc=I haven't been feeling well lately. Would you grow me some Gaia Wart? They're better than milk, since they only remove negative effects, and stack to 64. Really nice when fighting that Alchemist infernal! Or moving super tanks.%n%nThey also have some quite rare essentia on them, very useful for the budding thaumaturge.%n%n[note]In order to get your hands on some Gaia Warts, you'll need to right-click some snow onto some Netherwart until it transforms[/note]

# Quest: Sweet Tooth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRg.name=Sweet Tooth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGRg.desc=Sugarcane not keeping up with your sugary needs? Sugar beets give 8 sugar per beet.%n%nHmm, now I want some candy. Give me some sugar from your beets. I'll share some with you.%n%n[note]Electrolyze the sugar into O2 for an easy source.[/note]

# Quest: More Red, Less Wheat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGyQ.name=More Red, Less Wheat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGyQ.desc=Simple, easy, redstone-girl.%n%n[note]Redstone torches are great to get the light level just right.[/note]

# Quest: Tools Of The Trade 5 - Electronic Scanning
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHAg.name=Tools Of The Trade 5 - Electronic Scanning
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHAg.desc=The portable scanner is a direct upgrade to the plant lens.%n%nJust like the lens, the scanner can tell you all the information about a crop growing inside of a crop stick, but unlike the plant lens it also displays the exact Nutrient Score provided by the crop stick.%n%n[note]The portable scanner isn't just for crops, it can tell you a lot of information about basically everything! Look for the Portable Scanner quest after the EBF quest in Multiblock Goals tab for more information![/note]

# Quest: New Threads
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBQ.name=New Threads
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBQ.desc=Tired of killing spiders for string? Grow some flax for an easy non-biting source of string, add in some cotton and weave them together and you're almost to tanned leather! Just need some Corium now...

# Quest: The Ground is Crying
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBg.name=The Ground is Crying
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBg.desc=Need an alternate source of Chlorine? Breed some Tearstalks to get Ghast Tears for making salt water.%n%n;-;

# Quest: Blazes Too Hard to Kill?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBw.name=Blazes Too Hard to Kill?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHBw.desc=Then grow some Blazereed to save yourself the trouble.

# Quest: A Proposal?!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCA.name=A Proposal?!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCA.desc=Need to impress a lady or gent? How about growing diamonds on reeds...

# Quest: Why Does My Plant Bawk Like a Chicken?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCQ.name=Why Does My Plant Bawk Like a Chicken?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCQ.desc=Because it can lay eggs!

# Quest: Void Berries
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCw.name=Void Berries
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHCw.desc=Like little mini black holes.%n%nDon't try to eat them, you'll never feel full again.

# Quest: Positively Glowing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHDg.name=Positively Glowing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHDg.desc=There are a number of different ways to produce that wonderous material known as glowstone dust, pick your poison. %n%nNo matter which crop you end up picking, the mass centrifuging of glowstone dust can produce a number of useful materials passively.

# Quest: Cover Crops? Who Needs Those?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEA.name=Cover Crops? Who Needs Those?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEA.desc=This crop can produce its own fertilizer! Alongside other byproducts, making it one of the best crops to get statted up early. Once you have infinite fertilizer, breeding for stats gets a lot easier.

# Quest: Renewable Oil - No Diagenesis Required
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEQ.name=Renewable Oil - No Diagenesis Required
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEQ.desc=Oil from crops? Makes as much sense as oil from bees!%n%nIf you're looking for passive oil before the §5MV§r Crop Breeder, there is another crop that can help but it is §omuch§r slower.%n%n[warn]You can't use an §5MV§r Crop Breeder or Seed Generator in order to breed 31/31/31 seeds since their fluid capacity is too low.[/warn]%n%nYou'll need to follow these steps in order to get your hands on oil-berry seeds if your parents have maxed stats:%n%n1. Down-stat one of the parents via manual breeding.%n2. Use a spade to get some spare seeds.%n3. Use the lower stat seeds to create an oil berry seed using the §5MV§r Crop Breeder.%n4. Max out the stats of the oil berry seed like you originally did when you got your first maxed crop.%n5. Use a spade to farm enough seeds to fill your fields.%n%nAlternatively, if you don't want to bother with this process you can just wait until you can get your hands on the §5HV§r Breeder and Seed Generator.%n%n[note]If you want to go with the §5MV§r route, using random breeding is the easiest way to get your hands on a mid-stat version of the parents. For oil berry, the simplest solution simply involves breeding withereed with a 1/1/1 sugar cane until you breed a new mid-stat withereed.[/note]

# Quest: Tools of the Trade 2 - Mendelian Identification
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHgA.name=Tools of the Trade 2 - Mendelian Identification
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHgA.desc=When breeding new crops, you will come upon hundreds of different species! While every species has a unique texture which a dedicated farmhand will be able to discern between, this tool will clear things up much quicker for you. %n%nAfter using it you can tell the following:%n- Species%n- Stats%n- Crop tier%n- Whether it can grow (many crops have special requirements)%n- Whether you can harvest it%n- Growth progress

# Quest: Wither Skulls Easy Style
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHhw.name=Wither Skulls Easy Style
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHhw.desc=Withereed is a rare species which produces coal but, rarely, can also produce fully formed wither skulls!

# Quest: Son of Odin One-Eye
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiA.name=Son of Odin One-Eye
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiA.desc=The God of Thunder crop lets you increase your Thorium ore from the Nether to 4x. It also will give you Uranium you can use for Reactoria crops.

# Quest: Reactoria
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiQ.name=Reactoria
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiQ.desc=A great source of uranium and Pitchblende.%n%nReactoria crops will drop Reactoria leaves which will 4x your Pitchblende ore.

# Quest: Vegan Leather?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiw.name=Vegan Leather?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHiw.desc=If you want to save your cows and horses for milk and... glue... you can use Corium to produce your leather instead.

# Quest: Explosive Growth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjA.name=Explosive Growth
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjA.desc=Creeperweed can supply your gunpowder without needing to deal with bothersome explosions.

# Quest: Plant Based Milk
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjQ.name=Plant Based Milk
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjQ.desc=Oat Milk? Nay.%nSoy Milk? Nay.%n%nWart Milk. Say goodbye to your cattle.

# Quest: Better Put On That Rubber Suit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHnQ.name=Better Put On That Rubber Suit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHnQ.desc=Troll plant! What does it do? Troll you! %n%n%nAnd give you cancer. Sorry!

# Quest: Who the Hell is Bob?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHng.name=Who the Hell is Bob?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHng.desc=Want some emeralds for trading or other uses? These are the source.

# Quest: Deep Blue Sea of Sapphires
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI2Q.name=Deep Blue Sea of Sapphires
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI2Q.desc=You'll need a block of Sapphire beneath these beauties to get them to maturity. They can be a good source of aluminium and oxygen in late LV once you've gotten your first EBF but there are better options...

# Quest: Red Touch Yellow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI2g.name=Red Touch Yellow
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI2g.desc=Garnets are actually more valuable than Sapphires. They're an early source of Chrome and Manganese, which you'll need for HV machines. You can also centrifuge Pyrope, Almandine, and Spessartine Dust with Nitric Acid to obtain a variety of additional passive resources. To reach maturity, you will need a block of Garnet (either type) beneath this crop. You can get Garnets from the HV macerator and Spessartine Ore, or you can use an Implosion Compressor to turn Garnet Sands into crystals to make blocks.%n%nTo process all products of Garnydiania, you may find those steam multiblock machines quite useful! Though, to be honest, it will likely be much longer until you can make the most of this crop with the chemicals required.

# Quest: Creeping Climbers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAA.name=Creeping Climbers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAA.desc=Here are a few crops to spice up your solarpunk base, or help you climb up a treehouse.%n%nNo thousand block treck to the nearest Temperate Rainforest required here!

# Quest: The Art of Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZQ.name=The Art of Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZQ.desc=By simply planting saplings onto crop sticks, you've found you can create miniature versions of the matching trees! How cute!%n%nBonsai trees will give you drops just like a regular tree, but without the wasted server processing time of placing all the tree blocks just to chop them down again. This can be significant overhead on a server, so if you want to be nice to your host, breed some bonsai. 

# Quest: Crop Stats
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK0g.name=Crop Stats
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK0g.desc=A key part of CropsNH is improving the stats of your crops. There is always a chance for this to occur whenever a new crop grows - whether by self propagation or crossing...%n%n§lGrowth§r:%n§2Improves growth speed§r%n- Increases the number of progress points per growth tick by up to about 525%% with some variation depending on the tier of the crop.%n§4Can cause weeds to spawn§r%n- When growth is above 23 (or 7 for Necrobloom), crops will begin spreading weeds and diseases to nearby crops.%n- You can prevent this by either using Weed-EX or by increasing the resistance stat so it's equal to or above the growth stat.%n%n§lGain§r:%n§2Improves harvest size§r%n- Up to 2.5x per harvest at 31 gain.%n- Has a gain/100 chance of increasing the stack size of any drop by 1.%n%n§lResistance§r:%n§2Improves seed harvest chances§r%n- A resistance of 10 will guarantee a seed drop when harvesting a mature crop with a reinforced spade.%n- This scales by rate of resistance/10:%n  - 20: 2 seeds%n  - 25: 2 seeds + 50%% chance for a 3rd%n  - 31: 3 seeds + 10%% chance for a 4th%n- A resistance of 31 will guarantee a seed drop even without a spade.%n§2Increases weed resistance§r%n- When a crop's growth is above 23, resistance will prevent weed spreading as long as it's greater than or equal to the growth stat.%n§2Improves a crop's resistance to diseases§r%n- Each point reduces a crop's chance of becoming infected.%n- With 31 resistance, crops are immune to diseases.%n§2This includes sickness from lack of Nutrient Score, however, the crop still will not grow without the necessary nutrient level being reached.%n

# Quest: Argentia
betterquesting.quest.APU0Ykh9RMae9R7XqkXTKQ.name=Argentia
betterquesting.quest.APU0Ykh9RMae9R7XqkXTKQ.desc=A great source of silver.%n%nArgentia leaves will 4x your silver ore.

# Quest: Pyrolusium
betterquesting.quest.BuV2ZuQvRIOJeRNH4xtvoA.name=Pyrolusium
betterquesting.quest.BuV2ZuQvRIOJeRNH4xtvoA.desc=A great source of manganese.%n%nPyrolusium leaves will 4x your manganese and tantalite ore.

# Quest: Soul Sand Lilies
betterquesting.quest.Bx86-2AfQKadFFMHdh3now.name=Soul Sand Lilies
betterquesting.quest.Bx86-2AfQKadFFMHdh3now.desc=Oh hey, don't void that stuff, centrifuge it into something useful? (◕‿↼)%n%n%nSeriously though, as soon as you can: use these and some enriched fertilizer to breed Oil Berries in the MV Crop Breeder.

# Quest: Lucky!
betterquesting.quest.E3P20_dFSUiPdVSkma2iTA.name=Lucky!
betterquesting.quest.E3P20_dFSUiPdVSkma2iTA.desc=Lazulia will produce Lapis Lazuli and Lapis Dust.

# Quest: Not A Mandrake
betterquesting.quest.ECvjvBNURz-spVF95wOiJw.name=Not A Mandrake
betterquesting.quest.ECvjvBNURz-spVF95wOiJw.desc=This live root won't scream when you harvest it. At least, I don't think it will.

# Quest: Platina
betterquesting.quest.ExzkZigMSNafnvdI-5apjg.name=Platina
betterquesting.quest.ExzkZigMSNafnvdI-5apjg.desc=A source of platinum.%n%nPlatina leaves will 4x your plat line ores.%n%n[note]Using Platina will create a surplus of aqua regia if you just use it in your existing plat line, you'll need some extra infrastructure to handle the excess.[/note]

# Quest: Basic Lilies
betterquesting.quest.FB6XbhKLRk-QQEo2PsjGjA.name=Basic Lilies
betterquesting.quest.FB6XbhKLRk-QQEo2PsjGjA.desc=These Liliums aren't the most useful, but if you're wanting to build with say Tuff or Andesite this should ease your search for resources somewhat.%n%nRemember that these crops can only be bred when their environmental requirements are met. In this case, use those stones from before as your sub-soil.

# Quest: Taking Pools Seriously
betterquesting.quest.FWt08gVmSWi7Wa5PX80kDg.name=Taking Pools Seriously
betterquesting.quest.FWt08gVmSWi7Wa5PX80kDg.desc=With that 31/31/31 seed now in hand you will (ideally) §lnever have to complete %nthe entire statting process again. §r%n%nOnce replicated, you can cross this perfect seed with itself (keep them fertilized!) to access the pools that it has access to! §c§c§4§nThis is the intended path for early game crop discovery. §rWhile it is much more random than deterministic breeding, it will let you collect a wider range of species quicker.%n%nKeep in mind that: when pool breeding occurs, the offspring has a chance to be any crop found within any of the pools shared by 2 or more of the parent crops.§lThe mutation selection occurs prior to the check for environment. §rIn practice this means that if you're searching for a specific species in say, the Food pool, it will take much longer to appear than one in the Reed pool because there are fewer alternative species. [warn]No matter the environment.[/warn]%n%nOnce you've gotten your hands on a solid number of species, deterministic breeding becomes a simpler and more effective method for obtaining new species.

# Quest: Golden Berries
betterquesting.quest.FXUYD5RRT4K7AHMMpnvOIw.name=Golden Berries
betterquesting.quest.FXUYD5RRT4K7AHMMpnvOIw.desc=It's like a golden goose but... not.

# Quest: Gem Crops
betterquesting.quest.F_Ef5AtKQbSGmM24_LottQ.name=Gem Crops
betterquesting.quest.F_Ef5AtKQbSGmM24_LottQ.desc=These crops crystalize and produce their related crystals and dusts straight from the soil.%n%n§4Most of these crops will need a sub-soil of their related material whether block or ore.

# Quest: Leafy... Grains?
betterquesting.quest.FugIhOU6Q12Iq764ZRoMEA.name=Leafy... Grains?
betterquesting.quest.FugIhOU6Q12Iq764ZRoMEA.desc=All of the above could be useful for the production of certain drinks. But really all you'll be using them for is getting to the next crop,

# Quest: End Stone Lilies
betterquesting.quest.GV1Cx5SnSyKETKjMO6FUcQ.name=End Stone Lilies
betterquesting.quest.GV1Cx5SnSyKETKjMO6FUcQ.desc=Once you can actually get your hands on some endstone, these babies will allow for a §olot §o§rof high level passive material production.%n%nSince Enderbloom requires End Stone Lily to be bred deterministically and End Stone Lily requires Enderbloom for its deterministic mutation, you'll need to use your mastery of the mutation pools to obtain either of them.%n%n[note]Tip #1: If you're lost and don't know what to do, remember that you can trigger pool mutation even when breeding 2 crops of the same species together.[/note]%n%n[note]Tip #2: Also remember that crops require all their growth requirements to be met in order to breed, even when breeding via mutation pools.[/note]%n%n[note]Tip #3: This requirement can actually be used to filter the outcome of a pool mutation so that only a subset of them may appear. Though this doesn't actually reduce number of crops that can be picked from the pools shared by the parents. (and therefore doesn't directly increase your chance of getting what you want).§r[/note]%n%n[note]Tip #4: If you want to properly increase your chance of getting something through mutation pools, try lowering the number of shared pools between the parents.[/note]

# Quest: Environmental Preferences
betterquesting.quest.Hgj_XYnbRj2JGb8I-8QnLQ.name=Environmental Preferences
betterquesting.quest.Hgj_XYnbRj2JGb8I-8QnLQ.desc=Each crop has a set of preferred biome tags. These can be viewed in NEI along with the other growth requirements.%n%nHaving the proper biome tags will provide a significant Nutrient Point boost to your crops (§l+14 Points§r per tag).%n%nYou can only benefit from up to 2 biome tags (§l+28 Points§r).%n%nIt is possible to emulate a single preferred biome tag by planting your crops in a high-humidity location. The bonus scales linearly with humidity between 50%% and 80%%. Values below 50%% provide no bonus, while values above 80%% will hit the cap at an equivalent of 1 preferred biome tag (§l+14 Points).%n%n§l§rIf any favored biome tag is present in the current biome, the high humidity bonus will be ignored.%n%n%n§4§n§n§r§4The Nature's Compass will allow you to view the tags of each biome as subtext within its menu. Sorting biomes by tags is the simplest method.

# Quest: Evil...
betterquesting.quest.If475S_dQ5y_f8KcSRHeXQ.name=Evil...
betterquesting.quest.If475S_dQ5y_f8KcSRHeXQ.desc=While it can't produce certus quartz crystals, it will give you plenty of the relevant nether crystal dusts as well as straight nether quartz.%n%n§2Only needs netherrack soil, no sub-soil necessary here.

# Quest: A Summary of Crossbreeding
betterquesting.quest.Ik4r-iNLSEK_uq5FXqspQA.name=A Summary of Crossbreeding
betterquesting.quest.Ik4r-iNLSEK_uq5FXqspQA.desc=When crops breed, the resulting stats are the average of the parents' stats plus a random value between -2 and 4.%n%nEssentially, the variation in stats is a fixed (-2 -> +4). If all parents have fertilizer in them, stat loss is prevented in all cases (0 -> 4). %n%nDeterministic breeding is similar to how bees work, where you must bring the right species together. Some situations require more than two parents.%n%n[note]Advanced crops (§5MV§r and above materials) will require the breeding machine.[/note]%n%nMost crops will also have access to breeding pools. Breeding pools are like a set of tags associated with each crop. When breeding, if none of the parents produce a deterministic mutation, but some share one or more breeding pools, a random mutation may occur. The resulting offspring will always be a species tagged with one of the shared pools.%n%n[note]Once you've obtained your first 31/31/31 seed, it can be helpful to use these random pool mutations to collect many different types of crops.[/note]

# Quest: Thauminite Berries
betterquesting.quest.J04fEo0DTReAF9BJlQZ9RA.name=Thauminite Berries
betterquesting.quest.J04fEo0DTReAF9BJlQZ9RA.desc=Less blue blueberries. Thauminite oreberries!

# Quest: Ardite Berries
betterquesting.quest.JTmxoCTLTG2QXt6LoJhsBA.name=Ardite Berries
betterquesting.quest.JTmxoCTLTG2QXt6LoJhsBA.desc=Ardite oreberries!

# Quest: Weeds
betterquesting.quest.JcFOAl5pTtKNnMY61dFV_w.name=Weeds
betterquesting.quest.JcFOAl5pTtKNnMY61dFV_w.desc=Weeds will show up from time to time on empty single or double crop sticks. They will spread from there and sicken all your precious crops, so clear weeds with your spade (or fist) before you start desiring to reload the last backup. %n%nUsing smaller fields will make things a lot easier, at least until you can make Weed-Ex, so if you forget about them you only lose one or two seeds. If your crops have already become sick, you'll need Plant-Cure to heal them. Otherwise you'll just have to risk breaking them if you want the seeds back before then.

# Quest: Plant Diseases
betterquesting.quest.JgfP8eDqS-mDGcjgk-m3Dg.name=Plant Diseases
betterquesting.quest.JgfP8eDqS-mDGcjgk-m3Dg.desc=Plant Cure is used to cure sickly crops. Crops will get sick in two scenarios:%n%n1. A weed has grown and overtaken the crop.%n2. A crop does not reach minimum environmental requirements.%n%nYou must spray the cure manually, it will apply a minimal amount of fertilizer so that crops don't immediately become sickly again.

# Quest: Iridine
betterquesting.quest.KPORP3a2Q6K6jrjXhgoksA.name=Iridine
betterquesting.quest.KPORP3a2Q6K6jrjXhgoksA.desc=A source of iridium.%n%nIridine leaves will 4x your iridium ore.

# Quest: Spruce Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.L-unyIeFSCmjU1szB1sXwg.name=Spruce Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.L-unyIeFSCmjU1szB1sXwg.desc=Easy spruce wood!

# Quest: Farming the Graveyard
betterquesting.quest.Lop-uKsMQMiGgodxs9pUjg.name=Farming the Graveyard
betterquesting.quest.Lop-uKsMQMiGgodxs9pUjg.desc=While surveying species in the wild, you found some unique sproutlings reaching from a corpse. I wonder what these will provide.

# Quest: Carrot Stock
betterquesting.quest.MDRmD3RyR8CIdqdpll_74w.name=Carrot Stock
betterquesting.quest.MDRmD3RyR8CIdqdpll_74w.desc=Now that you've stolen the food from your harmless neighbors, or found it in nature like a considerate person, you must now plant these carrots onto crop sticks. Wait until the crop is §3fully grown§r and left-click it for the best chance to obtain the seeds.%n%nNo, the undomesticated Wild Carrot won't work. What are you, a rabbit?

# Quest: Enriched Fertilizer
betterquesting.quest.Nu5EfJtNQ0qIUW0Lt0E4yA.name=Enriched Fertilizer
betterquesting.quest.Nu5EfJtNQ0qIUW0Lt0E4yA.desc=§2Enriched fertilizer§r allows you to advance to the next stage of crop technology! %n%nIt is used in countless ways moving forward, but just to list a few it will be:%n%n- Pumped into your crops for more efficient fertilization.%n- Used to breed novel crops in the §dCrop Breeder§r.%n- Used to synthesize new seeds in the §dSeed Generator§r.%n%n§2Enriched Fertilizer§r is 10 times more potent than regular Fertilizer.%n%n- When used in a §dCrop Manager§r, a single unit of fluid adds 10 fertilizer units to the machine's internal storage.%n- When used in an §dIndustrial Farm§r, you only need to provide 1/10th of the amount indicated on the tooltips. (Except when using a Fertilization Unit.)%n%nIt will always be superior to the item based Fertilizers of the past, so moving forward you should be using it whenever possible.%n%nWhen using the §dCrop Breeder§r or §dSeed Generator§r, the §2Enriched Fertilizer§r recipe costs scale with the stats of the resulting seeds. [warn]Keep this in mind as early tier machines all have a lower than usual fluid capacity.[/warn] You'll need at least §5HV§r machines in order to create maxed seeds. By default NEI shows you the costs for a maxed seed, so keep this in mind when looking up recipes.

# Quest: Crop Sticks
betterquesting.quest.O65QUnR0QuGSoQrsUMTB1g.name=Crop Sticks
betterquesting.quest.O65QUnR0QuGSoQrsUMTB1g.desc=To do anything in CropsNH, you first need crop sticks. These will act as the supports for your plants to grow upon. Empty crop sticks can be doubled by right-clicking another crop stick onto them. These double-crop sticks allow you to breed any adjacent mature crops.%n%nAs new species grow on your crop sticks, you can harvest them by right-clicking, which won't remove the seed. Left-clicking harvests the crop and removes it, potentially dropping a seed depending on the resistance. Spades will help you improve your chances of obtaining seeds when you do this, as will the Resistance trait.%n%n§r§r[note]§l§r§lThe chance to drop a seed from any crop §nwithout a spade§r§l is measured%nas resistance/31. §rSo crops with a maxed resistance stat will always drop a seed when broken.§r[/note]%n%n[warn]Note in NEI the varying types of soil, sub-soil, and environmental requirements for different crops![/warn]%n%n%n%n§oIf you're already an experienced farmhand, collect a single stonelily seed and I'll let you skip subsequent introductory trainings for now.

# Quest: Metallic Crops
betterquesting.quest.PR2T5CUTQ6-IaOQd132Mzg.name=Metallic Crops
betterquesting.quest.PR2T5CUTQ6-IaOQd132Mzg.desc=Metallic crops are probably the most useful crops for late game. Thanks to the leaves harvested from these species, you can create tons of raw resources and even multiply the yield of your ores.%n%nMost metallic crops can be thrown into a forge hammer with some acid to create raw resources, or used in a chemical reactor with dirty crushed ores in order to increase your ore yields by up to 400%%.

# Quest: Rubyne
betterquesting.quest.PdVbnToTRuKXlvTqSg9qxQ.name=Rubyne
betterquesting.quest.PdVbnToTRuKXlvTqSg9qxQ.desc=This new species will present a more direct route to the Chrome you need for Stainless Steel production. Just don't make any pies with it.

# Quest: Ore Berries
betterquesting.quest.Q-4QPu7wRDC1ph_0uzziXA.name=Ore Berries
betterquesting.quest.Q-4QPu7wRDC1ph_0uzziXA.desc=Ore Berries are a shockingly diverse and useful set of crops, a number of which you'll have already received from previous questbook rewards. However, they can give more than just the basic minerals.%n%nAll of these crops will only grow in dark enviroments, with a sub-soil of their related material whether block or ore.

# Quest: Paper
betterquesting.quest.Q5XreXK-TpG40Wa_pCiW7w.name=Paper
betterquesting.quest.Q5XreXK-TpG40Wa_pCiW7w.desc=Papyrus represents one of the easiest ways to automate paper production in the game, if you needed that for some reason.

# Quest: Potato Stock
betterquesting.quest.QEd1ziVERKOXjzUj80M7Ig.name=Potato Stock
betterquesting.quest.QEd1ziVERKOXjzUj80M7Ig.desc=Now that you've stolen the food from your harmless neighbors, or found it in nature like a considerate person, you must now plant these potatoes onto crop sticks. Wait until the crop is §3fully grown§r and left-click it for the best chance to obtain the seeds.

# Quest: Nickelback
betterquesting.quest.QkDDUfRUTNyspowtsQHJ7w.name=Nickelback
betterquesting.quest.QkDDUfRUTNyspowtsQHJ7w.desc=A great source of nickel, and a horrible source of auditory stimulation. Nickelback leaves will 4x your nickel ore.

# Quest: Oak Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.QvknAsqFQoKau7FK0ZPPSw.name=Oak Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.QvknAsqFQoKau7FK0ZPPSw.desc=No, they won't produce Bonsai scale apples as well.

# Quest: Crop Nutrients
betterquesting.quest.R7QRLmaJRHuxmNcGpjX0hQ.name=Crop Nutrients
betterquesting.quest.R7QRLmaJRHuxmNcGpjX0hQ.desc=The speed at which a crop grows is based on its Nutrient Score. There are a number of different ways to obtain Nutrient Points for your crops, but to keep your crops from getting sick try to make sure they are always receiving at least a couple of the below bonuses:%n%n§l- +10 Points§r can be gained from having water in your crop sticks (scales 1-10 based on hydration level).%n§l- +10 Points§r can be gained from having fertilizer in your crop sticks (scales 1-10 based on fertilizer level).%n§l- +2 Points§r can be gained from allowing the crop to see the sky.%n       - Crops in the Industrial Farm will always have this bonus.%n§l- +28 Points§r can be gained from preferred biome tags%n       - [warn]If no preferred tags are found[/warn], high humidity will §rgive up to §l+14 Points.§r %n       - See more on this in the Environmental Preferences quest.%n%nAll crops have a base Nutrient Score of 5.%n%nYou can check the Nutrient Score of a crop by using a Portable Scanner on any crop sticks or Industrial Farm controller, even if it's empty.%n%nCrop tier determines the Nutrient Score requirements for growth. %nThe following cutoffs apply:%n%n§lTier 4 §r- Last tier where crops can be planted anywhere%n%n§lTier 5 §r- Last tier where crops can be planted anywhere as long as they can see the sky%n%n§lTier 11 §r- Last tier where crop can be anywhere as long as crops are in an 80%%+ humidity biome%n%n§lTier 12 §r- Last tier where crops can be anywhere as long as crops are in a 80%%+ humidity biome and can see the sky

# Quest: Dark Oak Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.RNs9o33VRcSIxlGcQnApfA.name=Dark Oak Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.RNs9o33VRcSIxlGcQnApfA.desc=Easy dark oak wood!

# Quest: Keeping The Sprouts Healthy
betterquesting.quest.SeFoun3ZTYuJ16YNy-Bq3g.name=Keeping The Sprouts Healthy
betterquesting.quest.SeFoun3ZTYuJ16YNy-Bq3g.desc=Weeds are a constant threat, whether in large automated fields or small crossbreeding plots.%n%nLets deal with them.

# Quest: Breeding With Technology
betterquesting.quest.Sel7hC1hT9ij2KcPa2g5ow.name=Breeding With Technology
betterquesting.quest.Sel7hC1hT9ij2KcPa2g5ow.desc=The Crop Breeder is a single-block machine that allows you to breed new crops deterministically. It will consume the parent seeds, some §2Enriched Fertilizer§r and a catalyst item for material-based crops.%n%nThe stats of an offspring created by the breeder will always be the rounded down average of seeds that were consumed to create it. [note]Breeding two or more maxed-out crops will always give a maxed-out offspring.[/note]%n%nThe §2Enriched Fertilizer§r cost is 144L per tier of the offspring crop + 72L for each stat point on the new seed. So a 31/31/31 tier 5 offspring would cost roughly 7.4KL to breed.%n%nSome crops require a minimum machine tier to be bred:%n- Iridine, Osmianth and Stargatium are all §5IV§r recipes%n- Titania is §5EV§r%n- Bauxia is §5MV§r%n- An §5HV§r machine is required to breed 31/31/31%n%n[note]Success chance starts at 40%% and increases by 10%% for every tier past §5LV§r, meaning that at §5ZPM§r, it's guaranteed. A failed breed will void the parent seeds used.[/note]%n%nAs a final note: when two crops share breeding requirements (ie Tearstalks and Evil Ore), be careful to insert the seeds in the proper order as to not trigger the mutation with fewer parents.%n%n§r§oYou only need one of the machines for this quest.

# Quest: Jungle Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.SkvqyNIlQDmTBfLCsmDepQ.name=Jungle Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.SkvqyNIlQDmTBfLCsmDepQ.desc=Easy jungle wood!

# Quest: Caffeine
betterquesting.quest.T4bs_MnkTX6Ugox2AkwQtg.name=Caffeine
betterquesting.quest.T4bs_MnkTX6Ugox2AkwQtg.desc=I promise you won't be dissapointed, so try some coffee. Yes, more than one at a time.%n%n[warn]Just, don't drink too much[/warn]

# Quest: Pam's Who?
betterquesting.quest.UJX_NTRpQb-V2IW4_CbUlA.name=Pam's Who?
betterquesting.quest.UJX_NTRpQb-V2IW4_CbUlA.desc=Lots and lots of food crops. While they may be less useful than other species you can grow, when compared to basic food crops the ability to stat these guys should make them pretty nice no matter the reason you need them.

# Quest: Bamboo "Bonsai"
betterquesting.quest.UXgyj5YwReqPhaolpqlSdQ.name=Bamboo "Bonsai"
betterquesting.quest.UXgyj5YwReqPhaolpqlSdQ.desc=I mean, it's technically a grass, but close enough.

# Quest: Enderbloom
betterquesting.quest.UwvcwiLER7qQrbOY1M6iww.name=Enderbloom
betterquesting.quest.UwvcwiLER7qQrbOY1M6iww.desc=As soon as you've got some endstone to grow it above, Enderblooms can be a great source for passive Nitrogen.%n%n[note]If you're wondering how to get this crop through deterministic mutations, (as End Stone Lily also requires Enderbloom to breed deterministically) consider taking a look at the End Stone Lily quest for a quick primer on quasi-deterministic breeding through random pools.[/note]

# Quest: Thiosulfine
betterquesting.quest.WaN7I-xVSb2SAsDULnEBKg.name=Thiosulfine
betterquesting.quest.WaN7I-xVSb2SAsDULnEBKg.desc=Thiosulfine is a complicated crop. At its simplest it will 4x your sulfur ore!! However, you can further process it alongside Galvania or Plumbilia leaves you can obtain additional rare materials. Notably, with Galvania, you get a chance to produce gallium dust.

# Quest: Star Wart
betterquesting.quest.WhDCyghURhuNaGl_rwNzYA.name=Star Wart
betterquesting.quest.WhDCyghURhuNaGl_rwNzYA.desc=Passive Nether Stars?! Impossible. To grow crops which hold such immense power, you will require the Industrial Farm with high tier seed-beds, and maybe an upgrade or 2 as it's quite slow to grow.

# Quest: A Knightly Snack
betterquesting.quest.XAVtJOEOSyOPjeEKgo-eZg.name=A Knightly Snack
betterquesting.quest.XAVtJOEOSyOPjeEKgo-eZg.desc=Tired of raiding all those dungeons for your armor shards? Use these!

# Quest: Steelyamom
betterquesting.quest.XYUqo9nLQ3eN0NngoqS1uw.name=Steelyamom
betterquesting.quest.XYUqo9nLQ3eN0NngoqS1uw.desc=Get it?%n%n§2(つ▀^▀ )つ

# Quest: Marble Lilies
betterquesting.quest.Y4CDtA9eQT6tazZoiMvejg.name=Marble Lilies
betterquesting.quest.Y4CDtA9eQT6tazZoiMvejg.desc=For the Greko-Romans among us, lots of magnesium can be found in this dust.

# Quest: Hemp
betterquesting.quest.YEb68DnHSTC0hC9YBst8TQ.name=Hemp
betterquesting.quest.YEb68DnHSTC0hC9YBst8TQ.desc=Genuinely one of the most impressive crops in the world, this one plant can do nearly everything. From tea to clothing, rope to concrete. %nFor you, it will play a key role in the creation of Industrial Farm in MV.

# Quest: Magical Agriculture
betterquesting.quest.YOH935zwShmW42dkm0szlA.name=Magical Agriculture
betterquesting.quest.YOH935zwShmW42dkm0szlA.desc=These crops all stem from the magical side of our realm...%n%n... get it? Stem?

# Quest: Scheelinium
betterquesting.quest.Z4d2MWOOTyuBxdWVoaOMkQ.name=Scheelinium
betterquesting.quest.Z4d2MWOOTyuBxdWVoaOMkQ.desc=A great source of tungsten.%n%nScheelinium leaves will 4x your scheelite, tungsten, lithium, and more.

# Quest: Simple Propagation
betterquesting.quest.Z_aW8Q3aSq2pU9hVhFX2qw.name=Simple Propagation
betterquesting.quest.Z_aW8Q3aSq2pU9hVhFX2qw.desc=Propagating your plants is as easy as placing a double crop-stick adjacent to a mature plant and waiting. %n%nAs long as there are no other plants adjacent to the double cropstick, your plant should simply grow into it.%n%n[note]Just like crossbreeding, spreading also applies the usual stat variation to new offsprings. This can be especially useful when statting up crops.[/note]

# Quest: Flower Power!
betterquesting.quest._D2Fw1VcSoqeHHMb8aK5DA.name=Flower Power!
betterquesting.quest._D2Fw1VcSoqeHHMb8aK5DA.desc=It's time to collect them all~!%n%nWell, all 12 different basic flowers.

# Quest: More Tin
betterquesting.quest._JjNBHSbTwOBjf_8bpLCbA.name=More Tin
betterquesting.quest._JjNBHSbTwOBjf_8bpLCbA.desc=Some easy tin for your steam age machines.

# Quest: Free Torches!
betterquesting.quest._uN-zMguRyCEB1JCjdhbvA.name=Free Torches!
betterquesting.quest._uN-zMguRyCEB1JCjdhbvA.desc=The Torchberry! %nDoes it make sense? %nNot at all! %n%nIs it helpful? %nCertainly!

# Quest: Birch Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.aOf6WTOfRGS9nJ_zvc88iA.name=Birch Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.aOf6WTOfRGS9nJ_zvc88iA.desc=Easy birch wood!

# Quest: Acacia Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.aZzdGU5PTX6aTXsX1u9oIw.name=Acacia Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.aZzdGU5PTX6aTXsX1u9oIw.desc=Easy acacia wood!

# Quest: The Queen of Crops
betterquesting.quest.aso1-CdJS2atlhwWpHJEoQ.name=The Queen of Crops
betterquesting.quest.aso1-CdJS2atlhwWpHJEoQ.desc=A great source of titanium!%n%nTitania leaves will 4x your titanium ores (including Bauxite!).

# Quest: Growing Spiders
betterquesting.quest.bYpK8VXJRhaTX8uFj4m6fQ.name=Growing Spiders
betterquesting.quest.bYpK8VXJRhaTX8uFj4m6fQ.desc=There are two different species of crop able to produce the products of those pesky spiders. Definitely easier than building a two-block wide mob farm chute if you ask me.

# Quest: Bauxia
betterquesting.quest.bk4ciGlRT36a8QXeXtCzzQ.name=Bauxia
betterquesting.quest.bk4ciGlRT36a8QXeXtCzzQ.desc=A great source of bauxite.%n%nBauxia leaves will 4x your aluminum ore.

# Quest: Slimy Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.csLVpyIuRPGMCnsllcwyJQ.name=Slimy Bonsai
betterquesting.quest.csLVpyIuRPGMCnsllcwyJQ.desc=Easy slime blocks and therefore easy glue and rubber, no need to horse around anymore.

# Quest: Cindering Pearls
betterquesting.quest.d5i0cS7PSyeM5iWzktBlTw.name=Cindering Pearls
betterquesting.quest.d5i0cS7PSyeM5iWzktBlTw.desc=Cinderpearls make for a good source of blaze powder.

# Quest: Plant Based Meats
betterquesting.quest.dy3RvEtwSHKwc3yIQQWn2g.name=Plant Based Meats
betterquesting.quest.dy3RvEtwSHKwc3yIQQWn2g.desc=Somehow this plant has developed the ability to produce a number of different types of meat. Don't ask me how it does it, or how it smells.

# Quest: UU Berries
betterquesting.quest.easeEzZORC-0Ry6F6of0Kg.name=UU Berries
betterquesting.quest.easeEzZORC-0Ry6F6of0Kg.desc=These special berries somehow have gained the atomic properties of UU-Matter. Due to their inherent genetic instability, they will require the Industrial Farm to harvest with high tier seed-beds.

# Quest: Sand Lilies
betterquesting.quest.g4ES1uecSi2Bu_an38Hbgg.name=Sand Lilies
betterquesting.quest.g4ES1uecSi2Bu_an38Hbgg.desc=No longer will sand be such a difficult resource to obtain in bulk. Thank Greg.

# Quest: Getting Dusty
betterquesting.quest.gEC9Qy4fTouqNoHVUPg1dg.name=Getting Dusty
betterquesting.quest.gEC9Qy4fTouqNoHVUPg1dg.desc=These crops will all collect and produce certain mineral dusts from the soil like pollen for B**s.

# Quest: Tools of the Trade 4 - Reinforced Spade
betterquesting.quest.gUpUgwhUThKRPgMQOyZ7Zw.name=Tools of the Trade 4 - Reinforced Spade
betterquesting.quest.gUpUgwhUThKRPgMQOyZ7Zw.desc=The reinforced spade will do everything the basic spade does, but better. It further increases your chances of bonus seeds based on the resistance stat. Every ten points of resistance increases the MINIMUM seed drop by one. That means:%n%n1 Resist = 10%% seed drop%n10 Resist = 1 guaranteed seed drop%n15 Resist = 1 guaranteed seed drop + 50%% chance for a second seed drop!%n31 Resist = 3 guaranteed seed drops + 10%% chance for a fourth seed drop!!%n%nTime to scale up farmhand.%n%n[note]If you're removing a crop with your spade, sneaking will let you remove the crop without having to worry about the spade breaking the crop stick.[/note]

# Quest: Space Flowers!
betterquesting.quest.gukFWnMtTme0mcEh1VjuOw.name=Space Flowers!
betterquesting.quest.gukFWnMtTme0mcEh1VjuOw.desc=Space Flowers can be used to synthesize and 4x some intergalactic materials:%n- Meteoric Iron and Steel%n- Desh%n- Mytryl%n- Oriharukon%n- Ledox%n- Callisto Ice%n- Deep Iron%n- Mysterious Crystal%n- Black Plutonium

# Quest: Gene Extractor
betterquesting.quest.ho__TwPPRhyUmCbuUGHlkg.name=Gene Extractor
betterquesting.quest.ho__TwPPRhyUmCbuUGHlkg.desc=The Crop Gene Extractor and Crop Synthesizers can be made in §5EV§r and allows you to create new seeds using UU-Matter and a few Data Orbs.%n%n§lCrop Gene Extractor§r%nThe §nCrop Gene Extractor§r is used to extract "Genes" from a crop. You can control which gene is extracted from a crop by using a programmed circuit:%n1. Species%n2. Growth%n3. Gain%n4. Resistance%n%nExtracting will usually have a base recipe time of 150 seconds (with the exception of the species gene, taking 300 seconds at base)%n%n§lCrop Synthesizer§r§r%nThe §nCrop Synthesizer§r is used to create new seeds from the extracted genes at the cost of some UU-Matter.%n%nThe UU-Matter cost will depend on the stats and tier of the seed being synthesized.%n- 750L per crop tier.%n- 100L per stat point on the seed.%n%n[note]Using the Crop Synthesizer is the only way to obtain and replicate maxed out Primordial Berry seeds.[/note]

# Quest: Netherrack Lilies
betterquesting.quest.i0bdslLETVmLNrV1ZeCpRg.name=Netherrack Lilies
betterquesting.quest.i0bdslLETVmLNrV1ZeCpRg.desc=If you somehow don't already have enough netherrack from mining all that sulfur, this should help pad your coffers.

# Quest: The Advanced Harvesting Unit
betterquesting.quest.iYoJw2SDRJODYwujhBz1zQ.name=The Advanced Harvesting Unit
betterquesting.quest.iYoJw2SDRJODYwujhBz1zQ.desc=The Advanced Harvesting Unit increases the production rate of your Industrial Farm. Only two are allowed per Industrial Farm. Each one increases the number of drops by 20%%, and power usage by 50%%.%n%n[note]Unlike the bonuses given by the Seed Beds and Fertilization Units, the bonuses given by the Advanced Harvesting Unit is applied as a final multiplier. This means that each Advanced Harvesting Unit will always increase your overall production by 20 to 40%% depending on how many upgrades you're using.[/note]%n%nAs with all upgrades, the tier of the upgrade must match the tier of the Seed Bed.

# Quest: Ferrofern
betterquesting.quest.jT1g8KZvQYyx0_K3PYdMGw.name=Ferrofern
betterquesting.quest.jT1g8KZvQYyx0_K3PYdMGw.desc=A great source of iron.%n%nFerrofern leaves will 4x your iron ore.

# Quest: Is That Really a Flower?
betterquesting.quest.jXeGLpceTSGX7e12_-j5NA.name=Is That Really a Flower?
betterquesting.quest.jXeGLpceTSGX7e12_-j5NA.desc=Everything can be beautiful, even the mycolo...logical.

# Quest: Speedy Berries
betterquesting.quest.jwBDPo12SWSVbCGfvPicMg.name=Speedy Berries
betterquesting.quest.jwBDPo12SWSVbCGfvPicMg.desc=The BOP Berry crop plays a nice role as the fastest growing crop you will get access to.%n%nThis makes it the perfect crop for breeding up stats with before crossing to other species which share pools.

# Quest: Micadia
betterquesting.quest.k89ZVtvxRKeTgwgWFuMUdA.name=Micadia
betterquesting.quest.k89ZVtvxRKeTgwgWFuMUdA.desc=A great source of mica.%n%nMicadia leaves will 4x your mica ore. %n%n[note]Just like for the bee, Micadia also allows you to use a cupronickel coil as it's sub-soil block instead of a mica ore.[/note]

# Quest: Crops to Mobs
betterquesting.quest.kJvlJxTXRaKGJ2vK8X_IYg.name=Crops to Mobs
betterquesting.quest.kJvlJxTXRaKGJ2vK8X_IYg.desc=Save your serverhost a headache, crop a mob!... Mob a crop?%n%nOr don't, I'm not your parent.

# Quest: Galvania
betterquesting.quest.kLmdG_I9R66vS_ndq8wG0A.name=Galvania
betterquesting.quest.kLmdG_I9R66vS_ndq8wG0A.desc=A great source of zinc.%n%nGalvania leaves will 4x your zinc ore.

# Quest: Copper Berries
betterquesting.quest.lSGABROTT4WbuEpU8IPQBA.name=Copper Berries
betterquesting.quest.lSGABROTT4WbuEpU8IPQBA.desc=Copper oreberries!

# Quest: Evil Berries
betterquesting.quest.lfjH7l4SRGq-uQ1kuMVZQQ.name=Evil Berries
betterquesting.quest.lfjH7l4SRGq-uQ1kuMVZQQ.desc=Why you would want to grow these alludes me, but sure: go for it!

# Quest: Cacti
betterquesting.quest.mBShEiHBR5mEEOSDD8O8aQ.name=Cacti
betterquesting.quest.mBShEiHBR5mEEOSDD8O8aQ.desc=Surely you will be the one to reach Stargate on cactus power, surely.

# Quest: Genus Lilium
betterquesting.quest.mRxtl7s-QOq6DiNt5mmMMA.name=Genus Lilium
betterquesting.quest.mRxtl7s-QOq6DiNt5mmMMA.desc=Lilies are a key set of species in CropsNH. They produce the dusts and materials otherwise created by the stones beneath your feet. Even far beneath your feet, or far far far above your feet.

# Quest: Basalt Lilies
betterquesting.quest.mWk4moL8SwKogZ2_7dQO3w.name=Basalt Lilies
betterquesting.quest.mWk4moL8SwKogZ2_7dQO3w.desc=Basalt dust, as with Granite dusts, has lots of minerals within it. In this case, note the large amount of flint dust which for your glass needs.

# Quest: Not So Evil Berries
betterquesting.quest.mmNIDjClTYyKnhgdVsLiJg.name=Not So Evil Berries
betterquesting.quest.mmNIDjClTYyKnhgdVsLiJg.desc=Fruits are a key part of a balanced diet too y'know.

# Quest: Last Universal Common Seed
betterquesting.quest.mpKVpvTlRUaQIX1f6bo87Q.name=Last Universal Common Seed
betterquesting.quest.mpKVpvTlRUaQIX1f6bo87Q.desc=Before going further into CropsNH, there is but one chore I need you to do. §6To prevent future hardship, collect a fully statted 31/31/31 seed.§r%n%nThis may seem daunting at first, but with enough blood, sweat, and bonemeal (see the fertilizer quest), you can do it. I believe in you!%n%n§4Ensure you pick a species which is related via mutation pools and determinism to other Crops you want.§r If you don't know what to choose, may I suggest the Potato or Cactus crops which will give you access to the Root or Danger pools respectively.%n%nWhile there is a reason behind keeping some seeds low statted (lowering enriched fertilizer costs in machines), the time saved by working with max stat crops compared to low stat crops is just too significant to ignore.%n%n§oThis quest will accept any CropsNH seed with a perfect statline.

# Quest: Multiblock Farming
betterquesting.quest.nkcwXV0yRH-6xPEEeBWcDA.name=Multiblock Farming
betterquesting.quest.nkcwXV0yRH-6xPEEeBWcDA.desc=Now this... this is how you show those §6B**keepers§r what's what. %n%nThe Industrial Farm (IF) is a long term, scalable, solution to Crop production. At its most basic, it will grow, harvest, and hydrate your crops, but with several upgrades and tier based size scaling, it is not a simple machine to make use of. The IF has three modes:%n%n§lInput§r - Pulls seeds and sub-soil blocks into the machine from an Input Bus.%n§lFarm§r - Grows the seeds and pushes products into an Output Bus.%n§lOutput§r - Exports the seeds and undersoil blocks from the machine into an Output Bus.%n%nYou can cycle through them in the machine menu by clicking on the mode button.%n%nTo start, you should construct the most basic IF possible. Once you've done that, place your seeds (and any relevant sub-soil blocks) into the Input Bus. %n%n[warn]Seeds that have sub-soil requirements won't be inserted into the farm unless a block of the sub-soil is also available to the machine. The sub-soil block doesn't need to be in the same Input Bus as the seeds for it to work.[/warn]§r§r%n%nOnce you've input your seeds (and sub-soil blocks), you can begin using Farm mode to grow your crops.%n%nWhen you wish to switch out seeds, enter Output mode before re-inserting the new seeds via the Input mode.%n%nThe length of your IF is controlled by the tier of your Seed Bed. An MV farm will require MV Seed Beds and therefore can only have one row of Seed Beds. This also means you can only insert one upgrade block (by replacing the wooden frame on the top layer). Each subsequent tier of Seed Bed increases the length of the machine, the base power consumption, the number of upgrades you can install and the number of seeds that can be inserted into the controller.%n%n[note]The power, water and fertilizer consumption of the industrial farm do not scale with the number of seeds inside the farm, so there is no benefit to running the farm under capacity.[/note]%n%nCrops grown in the Industrial Farm are assumed to grow in the following environment:%n- They have sky access (§l+2 Nutrient Points§r)§r%n- They have 200 water (§l+10 Nutrient Points§r)§r%n- They have 200 fertilizer when using fertilizer (§l+10 Nutrient Points§r)%n- The biome at the location of the controller controls the biome tags and humidity with the biome tags added by the env modules (§lup to +28 Nutrient Points§r)

# Quest: Fish Oil Supplement
betterquesting.quest.oIWPaHKuRByUsrrO-ug2Mw.name=Fish Oil Supplement
betterquesting.quest.oIWPaHKuRByUsrrO-ug2Mw.desc=Just make sure you put in ear-plugs first. These guys can be surprisingly useful if you know what to do with them.

# Quest: Osmianth
betterquesting.quest.p8eOuc12RZaZUsz21zuOXw.name=Osmianth
betterquesting.quest.p8eOuc12RZaZUsz21zuOXw.desc=A source of osmium.%n%nOsmianth leaves will 4x your osmium ore.

# Quest: Thaumium Berries
betterquesting.quest.pShpNuYrTXGwFmlSMKOrqw.name=Thaumium Berries
betterquesting.quest.pShpNuYrTXGwFmlSMKOrqw.desc=Thaumium oreberries! No trapdoor-ed crucible required.

# Quest: Your First Deterministic Cross
betterquesting.quest.pTDi3ejJT0O0oXr7Mq5F_Q.name=Your First Deterministic Cross
betterquesting.quest.pTDi3ejJT0O0oXr7Mq5F_Q.desc=With both carrot and potato seeds in hand, you are now ready to deterministically breed your first new species. Sugarcane.%n%nPlant your potato and carrot seeds next to a double crop stick placed on one of the fitting soil types shown in NEI.%n%n[warn]Always check NEI for what soil to use when breeding a new crop.[/warn]%n%nWhen breeding, it's important to ensure that the crop stick that will contain the new crop meets all the growth requirements of said new crop. [warn]Crops with special growth requirements will not appear unless all their growth requirements are met.[/warn] This includes things like soil, sub-soil, and light level.

# Quest: The Fertilization Unit
betterquesting.quest.poVTqaEOSh-OPgPjEjIfww.name=The Fertilization Unit
betterquesting.quest.poVTqaEOSh-OPgPjEjIfww.desc=The Fertilization Unit provides a massive boost to production, but requires you to use §2Enriched Fertilizer§r, and disables its 10x potency bonus. You'll need a steady supply of it in order to use this upgrade. It also increases power usage by 50%%.%n%nIn exchange for the increased cost, the Fertilization Unit will increase the farm's harvest bonus by 50%% and §omultiply§r it's growth speed bonus by 50%%.%n%nOnly one Fertilization Unit is allowed per Industrial Farm%n%n[note]The growth speed increase is applied as a final multiplier. This means that it's even more effective when used in conjunction with other upgrades.[/note]%n%nAs with all upgrades, the tier of the upgrade must match the tier of the seed bed.

# Quest: Tin Berries
betterquesting.quest.puDhJX2FQSOCGMWwSF0wEg.name=Tin Berries
betterquesting.quest.puDhJX2FQSOCGMWwSF0wEg.desc=Tin oreberries!

# Quest: Clay Lilies
betterquesting.quest.qoABdlzUSEqiNR2MiDIxIg.name=Clay Lilies
betterquesting.quest.qoABdlzUSEqiNR2MiDIxIg.desc=These should help with building more BBFs, your local riverbeds and riparian zones will thank you.

# Quest: Iron Berries
betterquesting.quest.r3RHo-BcT7KBIgaZgG93Ig.name=Iron Berries
betterquesting.quest.r3RHo-BcT7KBIgaZgG93Ig.desc=Really they're closer to jawbreakers or gobsmackers than berries.

# Quest: Stargatium
betterquesting.quest.s2pEIvhuRwW0FrzqhWJabw.name=Stargatium
betterquesting.quest.s2pEIvhuRwW0FrzqhWJabw.desc=A great source of §mstargates§r naquadah.%n%nStargatium leaves will 4x your naquadah ore.

# Quest: Stone from the Soil
betterquesting.quest.sIXQIDgpQL6NweTPXL8SUw.name=Stone from the Soil
betterquesting.quest.sIXQIDgpQL6NweTPXL8SUw.desc=Now for something a bit more complicated, Stone Lilies.%n%nThis species from the clade §oLilium§o §rproduces stone dust from its petals.%n%nTo determine how you can breed it, just check the NEI page for Stone Lily Seeds. The required prerequisite species can be obtained either by breeding, or directly from the overworld (if you are [warn]boring[/warn])%n%n[note]Remember that deterministic breeding will always take priority over pool based breeding[/note]. So unless you have access to a small pool including the Stone Lily, it will likely be quicker to follow the direct path.

# Quest: More Flowers
betterquesting.quest.s_UZrRZySwi79jOnwZw3Xg.name=More Flowers
betterquesting.quest.s_UZrRZySwi79jOnwZw3Xg.desc=These flowers reach beyond the basics of the initial 12, and may have some slightly more niche uses.%n%n[warn]Necrobloom's poisonous thorns aren't the only thing you'll have to worry about, it also starts spreading weeds when its growth stat is above 7.[/warn]

# Quest: Plumbilia
betterquesting.quest.tle9KskbQMOJ2ZS1nVWNEA.name=Plumbilia
betterquesting.quest.tle9KskbQMOJ2ZS1nVWNEA.desc=A great source of lead.%n%nPlumbilia leaves will 4x your lead ore.

# Quest: Coppon
betterquesting.quest.twBLeVfZRsuVO-hHDFVIKQ.name=Coppon
betterquesting.quest.twBLeVfZRsuVO-hHDFVIKQ.desc=Coppon fiber, while it won't make a nice sweater, it will 4x your copper ore. It can also be processed directly to copper dust.

# Quest: More Copper
betterquesting.quest.uU7RWnAOTOigmH6eYivwog.name=More Copper
betterquesting.quest.uU7RWnAOTOigmH6eYivwog.desc=Some easy copper for your steam age machines.

# Quest: The Overclocked Growth Acceleration Unit
betterquesting.quest.vOZpJncURaq1H0pUzFNblw.name=The Overclocked Growth Acceleration Unit
betterquesting.quest.vOZpJncURaq1H0pUzFNblw.desc=The Overclocked Growth Acceleration Unit allows for the overclocking of the Industrial Farm as with other Multiblocks, and enables the use of a single Multi-Amp Energy Hatch. Each overclock doubles production and input costs.%n%n[warn]You cannot use regular Energy Hatches when using a Multi-Amp Energy Hatch.[/warn]%n%nYou may only install one of these units per Industrial Farm.%n%nThe Overclocked Growth Acceleration Unit will not work if a Growth Acceleration Unit is installed.%n%nAs with all upgrades, the tier of the upgrade must match the tier of the seedbed.

# Quest: Cobalt Berries
betterquesting.quest.vS-gZqlCSJiI6rVi0KTzxw.name=Cobalt Berries
betterquesting.quest.vS-gZqlCSJiI6rVi0KTzxw.desc=Too blue blueberries. Probably wouldn't want to eat these.

# Quest: Witchery Seeds
betterquesting.quest.vX0tDVpeSG67fojo-jPmjg.name=Witchery Seeds
betterquesting.quest.vX0tDVpeSG67fojo-jPmjg.desc=In case you needed to mass produce witchery crops... for some reason

# Quest: The Growth Acceleration Unit
betterquesting.quest.xlp2LlfIRdWzOoE9G_Vf0w.name=The Growth Acceleration Unit
betterquesting.quest.xlp2LlfIRdWzOoE9G_Vf0w.desc=The Growth Acceleration Unit increases the growth speed of the crops found within the Industrial Farm. Each one increases growth speed by 100%% and power usage by 125%%.%n%nThe Growth Acceleration Unit will not work if an Overclocked Growth Acceleration Unit is installed.%n%nAs with all upgrades, the tier of the upgrade must match the tier of the seedbed.

# Quest: Granitic Lilies
betterquesting.quest.xpow4mxBRT-zLKuXEYRndw.name=Granitic Lilies
betterquesting.quest.xpow4mxBRT-zLKuXEYRndw.desc=Granite dust has a hefty amount of minerals trapped within it, you just need enough processing power to actually separate them out.

# Quest: Shimmering Leaves
betterquesting.quest.yB0s8UpOR7yKRNb-b-InVA.name=Shimmering Leaves
betterquesting.quest.yB0s8UpOR7yKRNb-b-InVA.desc=Shimmerleaf can get you easy quicksilver, no Cinnabar required!

# Quest: Organic Materials
betterquesting.quest.z3RLaOumReeg-aZ906lPCg.name=Organic Materials
betterquesting.quest.z3RLaOumReeg-aZ906lPCg.desc=This is a wide ranging category, but each crop here has some amount of utility. Almost all will likely be helpful as you develop.


## Quest Line: Getting Around...
betterquesting.questline.bAal8kZ3R8eRTwaHgbYkKA.name=Getting Around...
betterquesting.questline.bAal8kZ3R8eRTwaHgbYkKA.desc=Movement can be slow initially. But with some technology or magic, that is easily overcome!

# Quest: Indestructible Vessel
betterquesting.quest.-MexGhcYQ0OUrr5xgriDXQ.name=Indestructible Vessel
betterquesting.quest.-MexGhcYQ0OUrr5xgriDXQ.desc=In light of your thaumaturgical research, you have come to the conclusion that Greatwood is, in fact, a great material for constructing a resilient boat. Utilizing this material to its fullest potential has allowed you to construct a boat that is slightly faster and will never break on collision.

# Quest: Basic Flight Potion
betterquesting.quest.4LY2S8QsSw-JdMGrF8FUsQ.name=Basic Flight Potion
betterquesting.quest.4LY2S8QsSw-JdMGrF8FUsQ.desc=Tired of jetpacks? Want normal flight with no strings attached? Look no further!%n%nUsing your brand new MV Assembler and a Chicken Trophy, you can craft a basic Potion of Flight from Blood Magic, giving you 7 minutes of Creative flight with 8 uses before you have to make a new one.%n%n[note]Chicken Trophies are a rare drop from killing chickens.[/note]%n%n[note]Once you unlock Blood Magic, you can craft your own Flight Potion Flasks with a duration of up to 19 minutes, and refill them with any Filling Agent in an Alchemic Chemistry set.[/note]

# Quest: Relocator
betterquesting.quest.8QSORTVOSOaUXC6mQurMgA.name=Relocator
betterquesting.quest.8QSORTVOSOaUXC6mQurMgA.desc=The relocator allows for teleportation to previously marked locations, even between dimensions.%n%n[note]Uses quite a lot of power so a GraviChestPlate or other energy sources are recommended.[/note]

# Quest: The Power of Endermen
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhQ.name=The Power of Endermen
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAhQ.desc=Elevators are nice, but they're limited to vertical teleportation, and their range is also highly limited. Travel anchors don't have a limitation on angle, you can teleport from one anchor to any other within 128 blocks. You do this by looking at the anchor you wish to travel to and pressing the shift button. You can also name them and even set them as private if you like. They have a 2s cooldown.

# Quest: Glider Wings
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAChQ.name=Glider Wings
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAChQ.desc=If for some reason you want to be able to jump down a cliff without getting the message "Player X fell from a high place", a great idea would be to find a way to slow your fall. The store was out of feather falling potions, so make a hang glider instead.

# Quest: Electrotine Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAChw.name=Electrotine Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAChw.desc=Your glider gets you to the ground safely but it does not have any method to get up. After you researched electrotine you discovered that it is powerful enough for your first jetpack.%n%nA diamond chestplate surrounded with 4 electrotine batteries is powerful enough to bring you up into the air.%n%nIt does not have a hover mode so you better take your glider with you.%n%nHint: This jetpack can't fly higher than Y-128.

# Quest: Refill Your Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiA.name=Refill Your Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiA.desc=GREAT.... you now have an empty jetpack. You need 25 electrotine dust to completely fill it. Let's craft an electrotine generator and a charging bench to use the power of electrotine.%n%nYou will very quickly discover that, while it is fast and cheap, it's empty in the blink of an eye. Despite this, it is useful in combination with the hang glider to get into the air and to get away from hairy situations.

# Quest: Coal Steam Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiQ.name=Coal Steam Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiQ.desc=Your coal jetpack needs coal and water to produce steam. After a short warm-up period you can go and take it for a ride. Keep in mind you will need your glider to make a soft landing.%n%nPut your jetpack on your back and hit Shift and the adventure backpack's action-key to start it.%n%nMax flying height for this jetpack is Y-185.%n%nVertical velocity decreases linearly with height after overcoming optimal height - 135 for jetpack and 100 for copter.

# Quest: Copterpack, More 'Hover' than 'Jet'
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACig.name=Copterpack, More 'Hover' than 'Jet'
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACig.desc=The copterpack is the first jetpack with a hover mode. It uses several different types of fuels to power it.%n%nBuckets of creosote, lava, oil, diesel, cetane, ethanol, and fuel will work.%n%nEquip your jetpack and hit Shift and the adventure backpack's action-key. You can also switch between hover and normal mode.%n%nMax flying height is limited to Y-200.%n%nVertical velocity decreases linearly with height after overcoming optimal height - 135 for jetpack and 100 for copter.%n%n[note]Dropped items will be pushed away from you, just like a helicopter pushes things away, so be careful in the End, or by cliffsides.[/note]

# Quest: Electric Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiw.name=Electric Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACiw.desc=Your first electrical jetpack, It can be charged in any LV machine. You need to hit the IC2 mode-switch key to toggle between normal mode and hover mode while holding down the jump key. When descending, remember to shut off hover mode or else you'll drain your jetpack.%n%nThe only limitation is that you can't fly higher than Y-185.%n%nFor charging on the go, you can craft a charging crystal from ic2 charging components. You have to take the backpack out of the armor slot and put it in your hotbar and activate the charger by sneak-clicking.%n%nLater on GT++ charge packs are belts that can charge everything in your inventory including armor. Check NEI for the recipe.%n%nFinally, the GT++ wireless charger will charge everything in your inventory, including the jetpack, from your base at long ranges. A quest is unlocked once you finish your nanosuit. Just remember when you are off world or in the Nether that your jetpack isn't charging!

# Quest: Fueled Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACjA.name=Fueled Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACjA.desc=This jetpack uses IC2 biogas and can fly up to Y-245. You can switch between hover and normal mode using the IC2 mode-switch key.%n%nAn empty jetpack can be (re-)fueled in a fluid tank filled with biogas.

# Quest: Advanced Electric Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACjQ.name=Advanced Electric Jetpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACjQ.desc=The advanced electric jetpack is an upgraded version of the electric jetpack.%nWhile worn in the chest armor slot and charged with EU, it allows the player to fly. It provides no armor protection, but will charge tools being used in the same manner as the advanced lappack from its 3,000,000 EU internal storage.%n%nThe advanced electric jetpack is limited to a maximum flying height of Y-256.%n%n[note]To turn it on, hit the fly key listed under gravisuite. You can then use space to fly up. To activate hover, hit the IC2 mode key while holding space. Will also recharge tools.[/note]

# Quest: Row, Row, Row Your Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmg.name=Row, Row, Row Your Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmg.desc=You live close to the water and don't have a boat? Man, get it together.%n%nYou need wooden planks, slabs and a knife to craft one. (This is also quest id 666, be careful, something is going on.)%n%n[note]We here at QuestBook, Inc. do not guarantee the usefulness of boats. The standard worldgen does not include oceans, so their usefulness is heavily curtailed. There are lots of rivers, but horses might be more useful if not on a server.[/note]

# Quest: Trainspotting
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmw.name=Trainspotting
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACmw.desc=The wooden tracks can be made without any machine, though always check NEI for assembler recipes for discounts. Functionally equivalent to normal rails, but with a lower maximum speed (for safety reasons).%n%n[note]Hint: You can use your wooden rails for Steve's Carts farms.[/note]

# Quest: Rubber Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnA.name=Rubber Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnA.desc=The rubber dinghy requires only a few rubber plates. Like the vanilla wooden boat, it will break and dismantle whenever it hits a surface, however instead of returning sticks and planks, it will return a damaged rubber dinghy, which can be re-crafted with two pieces of rubber back into a usable rubber dinghy!

# Quest: Inflatable Boot
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnQ.name=Inflatable Boot
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnQ.desc=I meant to say boat... The inflatable boat is the first boat that doesn't break on impact with a solid block.

# Quest: Carbon Fiber Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACng.name=Carbon Fiber Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACng.desc=Unlike all other boats, this amazing carbon fiber canoe is COMPLETELY INDESTRUCTIBLE!* This means that you can smash it into as many beaches, lily pads and alligators as you like, the carbon fiber canoe won't take a scratch!%n%nWarning: We are not held responsible for any damage caused by riding the carbon fiber canoe into a lava lake or the Void.%n%n*Therefore, warranty is NOT included.

# Quest: Electric Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnw.name=Electric Boat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACnw.desc=The electric boat works mostly like a vanilla boat, chugging through the water at a decent pace. It will hopefully drop itself once you crash, which is slightly nicer than the usual sticks. That's all well and good, but what if we utilize the electric engine? Wearing an energy storage device in your chestplate slot, like a batpack or energypack, will cause the boat to drain energy from it and propel you forward at supersonic speed! Doing this will consume about 100 EU per block traveled, so even a decent batpack won't last long!

# Quest: Boat Shape?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACoA.name=Boat Shape?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACoA.desc=Really? Yes for the more advanced boats you need a new shape form.%n%nYou need to make an Extruder first to progress further.

# Quest: Wooden Rail Variants
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACog.name=Wooden Rail Variants
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACog.desc=The wooden junction, wye and switch tracks need an assembling machine to craft. They allow you to join and switch to tracks going to different locations.%n%nNEI doesn't show the right recipe on the first page. Go through the recipes a bit to find the right one.

# Quest: Switch Lever
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACow.name=Switch Lever
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACow.desc=The switch lever is the manual version of the switch motor, requiring a player to operate it instead of a redstone signal.%n%nIt is used in various signaling systems, mainly to change the way switch tracks and wye tracks work.

# Quest: Crowbar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACpA.name=Crowbar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACpA.desc=The crowbar comes in a Railcraft (and thaumcraft versions of RC) and a gregtech variant. It is used to manipulate machines from railcraft, remove plates and any other covers (pumps, conveyor modules, etc.) from gregtech pipes and machines as well as breaking certain objects faster, such as tracks. This tool is also used to access certain inventories from Railcraft.%n%nHold a crowbar and shift-right-click to attach carts. Click the starting cart then continue to click to add more carts to the link. Carts will act slower the more connections are made.%n%nThe crowbar can be used as a weapon, though it costs twice as much durability on attack (just like any other non weapon tool...).

# Quest: Minecart
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACpQ.name=Minecart
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACpQ.desc=After you craft your first cart the journey can begin...%n%nWell, not really. You will need some kind of tracks first.%n%n[note]We here at QuestBook, Inc. do not guarantee the usefulness of minecarts or trains in any way. Especially since you can mine out a vein in a single session once you have a hammer and backpacks.[/note]%n%n[warn]WARNING: Unprotected carts can be knocked off their rails by lightning. Cover the area with blocks to prevent carts from disappearing.[/warn]%n%n[warn]Also, make sure to keep your cart in one chunk, or use chunkloaders covering the whole area the cart works within. Loading/unloading chunks may cause carts to disappear or duplicate.[/warn]%n%n[note]You should only make these if you want to have fun with them, as anything they can do is better done by other methods, including the Long Distance Fluid Pipeline. Excessive minecart and train use on servers may cause lag and you may be asked to switch later anyway.[/note]

# Quest: The Transcontinental Railroad
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADYg.name=The Transcontinental Railroad
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADYg.desc=All the different mining veins that have been found seem to be really far apart. One way to shorten the travel time is to create a railroad from your base to the different mines. Sadly this requires a large amount of both iron and creosote. Let's not forget to place the last symbolic rivet on one of your new train lines.

# Quest: Jetpack v.0.1 Alpha
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADag.name=Jetpack v.0.1 Alpha
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADag.desc=Do you like flying? Ok then, make a slimy bouncepad and enjoy the view.

# Quest: Minecart with Tank, Workbench or Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEnQ.name=Minecart with Tank, Workbench or Furnace
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEnQ.desc=Want to transport oil or other fluids, have a portable crafting table or a portable chest? Then you need to craft some minecarts with tanks, chests or crafting tables.

# Quest: Fluid Loader and Unloader
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEng.name=Fluid Loader and Unloader
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEng.desc=멀리 떨어진 유전에서 기름 수송을 자동화하려면 유체 적재기(fluid loader)와 하역기(unloader)가 필요합니다. 잠금 레일(locking track)은 기름을 적재하거나 하역하는 동안 열차를 정지시킵니다.%n%n[note]추신: 정말 기차를 좋아하지 않는 한, LV에서 만들 수 있게 되면 장거리 유체 파이프라인(Long Distance Fluid Pipeline)을 사용하는 것이 좋을 것입니다.[/note]%n%n사용 방법에 대한 자세한 내용은 온라인에서 추가로 찾아봐야 할 수도 있지만 (GTNH는 조합법을 변경하지만, 일반 레일크래프트 기능은 그대로입니다), 간단한 작업 목록은 다음과 같습니다:%n%n1. 기지에서 유정까지 레일 루프를 만듭니다.%n%n2. 유정 근처에 잠금 레일을 설치하고, 그 위로 두 블록 높이에 유체 적재기를 설치합니다. 레일은 잠금 모드(Locking Mode)여야 합니다. 쇠지레(crowbar)를 사용하여 변경하세요.%n%n3. 적재기의 필터에 탱크 차량(tank car)을 사용하고 즉시 모드(Immediate mode)로 설정합니다.%n%n4. 유정을 적재기에 평소처럼 연결합니다.%n%n5. 기지의 잠금 레일 아래에 유체 하역기를 설치하고 적재기와 동일하게 설정합니다.%n%n6. 기관차도 비슷하게 자동화합니다. 유체 적재기를 증기 기관차 위에 설치하고 수동(manual) 모드로 설정한 후 기관차로 필터링합니다.%n%n어쨌든 제대로 작동시키거나, 더 조사해야 하거나, 한 번에 32양동이씩 옮긴다는 것을 깨닫고 그냥 걸어가기로 결정하거나, Discord에 가서 왜 누가 기차를 만드는지 물어볼 수도 있습니다.%n%n아이템 적재기도 있지만, 주요 용도는 기관차에 연료를 보급하는 것일 수 있습니다.

# Quest: Locomotive 0.1 Alpha
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEnw.name=Locomotive 0.1 Alpha
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEnw.desc=The furnace cart is a cheap locomotive. Click with coal or charcoal on the cart and it will start moving.%n%nThis is a curiosity, and probably you will use the steam locomotive from the next quest for an actual train.

# Quest: Steam Locomotive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEoA.name=Steam Locomotive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEoA.desc=The steam locomotive is much better than the furnace cart. You can control the speed and the direction the locomotive will move. You need to put water and coal inside to make steam to power the locomotive.%n%nYou can use a water tank or other water source to refill this locomotive by placing a Fluid Loader above it at a stop. The loader can be placed either directly above the track, or a block higher to give you clearance when riding the train. (You can't actually ride a train unless you sit in a normal minecart.)%n%nThis locomotive runs on any fuel you can burn in a steam boiler, perhaps you will want to use compressed coal blocks or similar. You can use an Item Loader to refuel it.%n%nOnce you have stable electricity in MV, you will likely move to the Electric Locomotive.

# Quest: Electric Locomotive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEoQ.name=Electric Locomotive
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEoQ.desc=Electric Locomotives are much better than steam ones. You need electric rail for it.

# Quest: Boost Your Speed
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEog.name=Boost Your Speed
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEog.desc=If you decide to not use a locomotive and drive with one or two carts only, you can use some booster tracks. Activate them with a lever or a redstone torch. You can also use them to slow down, especially when doing corners!

# Quest: The Transcontinental Railroad - High-Speed
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEow.name=The Transcontinental Railroad - High-Speed
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEow.desc=Did you ever dream of driving in a railcart at high speeds? Well your dreams can come true with the high speed tracks. Be careful though; you need to lower the speed when your rails change direction or when the track ends.

# Quest: The Transcontinental Railroad - Creeper-Proof
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpA.name=The Transcontinental Railroad - Creeper-Proof
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpA.desc=Railroads in the nether are dangerous. The reinforced tracks are blast proof. Hopefully you're blast proof too?%n%nYou can move 25%% faster than with normal tracks.%n%nNEI doesn't show the right recipe on the first page. Go through the recipes a bit to find the right one.

# Quest: The Transcontinental Railroad - Electric
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpQ.name=The Transcontinental Railroad - Electric
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpQ.desc=Electrical tracks are used together with your electric locomotive. You need to power the rails with energy.%n%nNEI doesn't show the right recipe on the first page. Go through the recipes a bit to find the right one.%n%n[note]Alternatively you can use the search bar to search for a specific name, in this case electric tracks![/note]

# Quest: Electric Feeder Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpg.name=Electric Feeder Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEpg.desc=To get your tracks electrified you need an electric feeding unit, shunting wires and some support frames. You can use an MFE or a transformer to get GT energy into the feeder unit.

# Quest: Travelocity!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF5Q.name=Travelocity!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF5Q.desc=A staff of traveling can get you really moving around your base. Hold shift and right-click to teleport in that direction. If you've got travel anchors, just right-clicking will send you to them. The range is 16 blocks for normal TP, 128 to an anchor.

# Quest: Works like in anime!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPw.name=Works like in anime!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPw.desc=You want to fly. Badly. So go and ductape wings!

# Quest: Angel Wings
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFQA.name=Angel Wings
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFQA.desc=Since you have access to better materials than cardboard now, you wanted to make wings. Angel wings.

# Quest: Secret-Angel-Assasin
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFQQ.name=Secret-Angel-Assasin
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFQQ.desc=Infusing your Wings with nano technology seems to be the next step, to further improve them and combine magic and technology.

# Quest: Angel Wings - Ultra Force!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFSw.name=Angel Wings - Ultra Force!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFSw.desc=From ore to ingot, from nano to quantum, as you progress, your technology level increases, so should your wings as well.

# Quest: Cart With Chunkloader
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFYw.name=Cart With Chunkloader
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFYw.desc=When transporting oil from long distances, a train is going to need a chunk loader. Craft one, and I'll give you a second one for free.%n%n[note]This quest might not be completable in MP?[/note]

# Quest: Step Assistant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG8w.name=Step Assistant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG8w.desc=The Piston Boots are a bouncy pair of shoes for adventurers.%n%nIt functions as a piece of armor for the foot slot that gives a fun jump boost! They let the wearer jump up to THREE blocks in height and increase run speed. They also grant a Step-Up enchantment to allow the wearer to step up a single block without jumping while sprinting. You can repair them with leather using an anvil.%n%nBasically, make them ASAP.

# Quest: Boost Your Speed v2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEg.name=Boost Your Speed v2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHEg.desc=High speed transition and booster tracks get your carts moving at really ridiculous speeds. Do not use normal track without several transition tracks or else your cart will explode. Do not try turning at high speed or, you guessed it, your cart will explode.

# Quest: So Much Nicer Than Ladders
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwQ.name=So Much Nicer Than Ladders
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwQ.desc=Elevators are great for fast transportation vertically in your base. Leaving a tinted elevator will stop at the same color elevator. Use some Malisis doors for a nice "real" elevator effect.%nThe rotating elevator will turn the player as they go up or down to face a specific direction. Handy if your elevator shaft is on one side at a floor and a different side at another floor.

# Quest: Better Boots with a little pizzazz
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1A.name=Better Boots with a little pizzazz
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1A.desc=Electric Boots of the Traveller grant you a 2%% Vis Discount along with all the benefits of the regular Boots of the Traveller.%n%nIn addition, they come with a wide variety of new features thanks to our amazing magic devs:%n%n- Configurable Jump Boost: You can choose between 0%%, 25%%, 50%%, 75%%, or a 100%% jump boost.%n%n- Configurable Speed Boost: Similar to the jump boost, you can adjust the speed boost percentage to your preference.%n%n- Flight Inertia: When toggled on, this feature cancels inertia while flying, allowing for precise movement even when traveling at high speeds.%n%n- Omnidirectional Movement: This toggle lets you decide whether your speed boost applies in all directions or only while running straight ahead.%n%n[note]None of these keybinds are set by default. The easiest way to configure them is to go into Options -> Controls, turn on the "Category" button, and type "Thaumic Boots." Then, assign keys for the features as needed.[/note]%n%n[note]If you want to advance in the dark arts you can also make them voidwalker boots.[/note]

# Quest: Walk all over you
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1Q.name=Walk all over you
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1Q.desc=Nanosuit Boots of the Traveller provide all the benefits of the Nanosuit, plus a massive speed boost, higher jump, and improved Vis Discount. These are the perfect boots for the master magical engineer.%n%n[note]If you want to advance in the dark arts you can also make them voidwalker boots.[/note]

# Quest: Walking across the stars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1g.name=Walking across the stars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1g.desc=Quantum Boots of the Traveller, for when you really need to run as fast as the wind. Might cause you some problems standing still!%n%n[note]If you want to advance in the dark arts you can also make them voidwalker boots.[/note]

# Quest: Flying Like....Mary Poppins?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDA.name=Flying Like....Mary Poppins?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDA.desc=The Thaumostatic Harness grants you flight, using up Potentia from a jar. The speed isn't great though, so perhaps further research will yield some results.

# Quest: Flying With the Greatest of Ease
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDQ.name=Flying With the Greatest of Ease
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDQ.desc=Ahh, that's better. With this girdle you can really fly around like a true wizard. It does take a little extra potentia to use though, so keep an eye on your flying time.

# Quest: Working While Flying?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDg.name=Working While Flying?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDg.desc=With these devices you can now fly and work at the same time without penalty. They can be found in the Witching Gadgets tab of the book. You'll need a Swiftness potion for this device.

# Quest: Long Distance Power Delivery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDw.name=Long Distance Power Delivery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIDw.desc=No mage wants to be restricted to short flying times. With this spire from the Automagy discipline you can transmit magical energy directly to your flying harness. To get the correct Thaumium block, compress 9 ingots to get the GT Thaumium block and then chisel that block to get the correct type.%n%nThis multiblock requires centi-vis to operate. You can use 2-6 Thaumostatic Pylons, with additional pylons extending the range. Provide the construct Aer centi-vis to operate, and it will accept Potentia essentia to transfer to flyers. The construct will also accept Aer and Volatus essentia to increase the range and rate of transfer, respectively. Right-click the sides of the controller to control which type of essentia each side will accept.

# Quest: Flying Like a Eag - I Mean Raven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIEg.name=Flying Like a Eag - I Mean Raven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIEg.desc=This cloak is a nice substitute for the Glider. There are plenty of other magical items worth a look in the Witching Gadgets tab.%nIf you want to toggle gliding with a key - configure binding for "Hotkey for activating some worn items" in control settings.

# Quest: 'Easy' Teleportation
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJnQ.name='Easy' Teleportation
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJnQ.desc=They may be a pain to craft, but teleposers are very useful for teleporting. Use the Teleposition Focus to set the first Teleposer location and put it in the second. Apply a redstone signal, and it'll teleport you at the cost of LP. It can also move items or entities, with the size increasing with better foci.

# Quest: Flippers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUw.name=Flippers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUw.desc=Maybe you were lucky and found some Flippers in a loot chest or dungeon.%n%nFlippers allow the player to swim at the same speed as walking. The only problem is that it has 0 armor protection.%n%nIf you're doing underwater construction, or digging out some clay or gravel, you may find them useful.

# Quest: Travelocity²
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3Q.name=Travelocity²
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3Q.desc=Why walk when you can teleport? This upgrade to the staff of traveling can move you even further, even faster, and will never run out of energy.%n%nRight-click:%n * If targeting a travel anchor: teleport to it, 2048 range%n * If looking at a block: teleport to it, 512 range%n * If no block in range: teleport forward, 64 range%n * If looking at a block within 4 range: teleport to the other side of a wall, 16 range%n * No cooldown%n%nShift-right-click:%n * Same as right-click, but ignoring travel anchors%n * Travel anchors will be hidden from view while holding shift%n%n[note]Tip: You won't be able to see travel anchors that are far away, but can still teleport to them if they are in range and chunk-loaded. Try using JourneyMap waypoints to mark anchors![/note]%n%n[note]Note: The right-click and shift-right-click actions are fully configurable. Check the EnderIO Staff Settings configs!%nConfig action values:%n 0: Do nothing%n 1: Teleport to look / forward%n 2: Teleport to anchor%n 3: Teleport to anchor, or to look / forward if no anchor[/note]

# Quest: Let's Go Lava Surfing!
betterquesting.quest.BC7LS6iHTYW_U0-SuIA4Sg.name=Let's Go Lava Surfing!
betterquesting.quest.BC7LS6iHTYW_U0-SuIA4Sg.desc=The Thaumium Boat is an upgraded version of your Greatwood Boat. The experience you have gained from manufacturing boats made of magical materials allows you to create a boat that can go even faster. Additionally, the Thaumium coating allows it to sail not only in rivers but also lava streams! Take it with you on your vacation in the Nether and enjoy.

# Quest: Enhanced Charm of Dislocation
betterquesting.quest.G7ACOCTJRi-bk6XQxZVtIQ.name=Enhanced Charm of Dislocation
betterquesting.quest.G7ACOCTJRi-bk6XQxZVtIQ.desc=Very powerful.

# Quest: Charm of Dislocation
betterquesting.quest.SxCNz5_RSym0Q-uKaG2JRA.name=Charm of Dislocation
betterquesting.quest.SxCNz5_RSym0Q-uKaG2JRA.desc=They have limited durability. So either put them on a pedestal to avoid durability loss, or use a thaumic restorer.

# Quest: Planar Gateways
betterquesting.quest.U6wfKJSxTiyYvcz-f-76EA.name=Planar Gateways
betterquesting.quest.U6wfKJSxTiyYvcz-f-76EA.desc=A planar gateway from Thaumic Horizons lets you travel to a pocket dimension. Setting up multiple gateways (up to 4) to the pocket dimension even allows for travel to other dimensions!

# Quest: Chaos Locator
betterquesting.quest._D1VyrEFSICL70afdVd1YQ.name=Chaos Locator
betterquesting.quest._D1VyrEFSICL70afdVd1YQ.desc=This device is fashioned to greatly accelerate the hunt for chaos shards, by teleporting you straight to them! %n%nSimply enter any number from -1000 to 1000 in the coordinate fields, click the button and you will be teleported directly to a chaos island, even across dimensions. %nHow convenient!%n%n[note]You will still have to fight the chaos guardian though, this isn't a cosmic superweapon.[/note]

# Quest: Speed up with the Sash
betterquesting.quest.aXAQD7T1SnGCAu0L4iV64w.name=Speed up with the Sash
betterquesting.quest.aXAQD7T1SnGCAu0L4iV64w.desc=The Sashes from Botania improves your speed passively along with a jump boost and provide Step assist all while fitting in your belt slot, how convenient is that?%n%nYou will need a method of powering them with either the mana tablet or the mana mirror linked to a pool.%n%nThe Soujourner Sash provides the basic speed boost, jump boost and step assist while the Globetrotter provides double the jump height and speed boost.%n%nThe Planestrider is special since it provides a slowly increasing speed boost as long as you are moving. You can even reach up to 11 times the Soujourner Sash speed boost!%n%n[note]You only need to make one Sash to complete the quest.[/note]

# Quest: Alternative to blasting off!?
betterquesting.quest.iWmU5h_ZSPqAcObmxgW5bw.name=Alternative to blasting off!?
betterquesting.quest.iWmU5h_ZSPqAcObmxgW5bw.desc=Are you sick and tired of using the rocket to blast off every time and want an alternative and faster method? The EnderIO Telepad is a 3x3x1 structure that when powered with RF will teleport the player to a set coordinate.%n%nTo set the Coordinate you will need a Coordinate selector tool to mark an area by shift-right-clicking to mark. Then shift-right-click the middle of the EnderIO Telepad pad to set the desired location.%n%nThen stand on the pad and click teleport to be sent in style.

# Quest: Teleporter
betterquesting.quest.tJdwTeS6TOOFACQhNuUvEw.name=Teleporter
betterquesting.quest.tJdwTeS6TOOFACQhNuUvEw.desc=The IndustrialCraft2 Teleporter allows for teleportation between 2 connected teleporters.%nIt requires energy storing block right next to it due to the massive power demand.%n%n[note]The energy required is determined by the distance between the teleporters and amount of items in the inventory.[/note]%n%n[note]The teleporter is quite buggy according to the official wiki.[/note]

# Quest: Spare Battery
betterquesting.quest.vv296Z3mSUqkQEaiJqQcOw.name=Spare Battery
betterquesting.quest.vv296Z3mSUqkQEaiJqQcOw.desc=The Electric Jetpack may be useful for flight, but it doesn't seem to last very long. %n%nIf only there was an integrated upgradable battery pack you could keep on your player to extend its range...%n%nOh wait, there is!%n%nThe §5§lCharge Pack§r can be used as a battery pack for charging items both in your hotbar and armor equip to your person. Simply place it in the belt bauble slot and it should be fully functional! The HV one should serve you nicely for now.%n%n[note]You can upgrade the Charge Pack as you unlock items that require higher voltages for charging. The Charge Pack will charge anything of-tier or lower- but not higher.[/note]


## Quest Line: ...Without Dying
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACw.name=...Without Dying
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACw.desc=In order to not die constantly, you'll need weapons and armor. There's also utility stuff, adventure backpacks, and static defenses for your base.

# Quest: More Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.3Hob-CoJQ-CK3jmp4EHyqQ.name=More Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.3Hob-CoJQ-CK3jmp4EHyqQ.desc=A new energy core means more powerful augments. This quest lists all Tier 2 augments.%n%nSome standouts:%n%n-Milk Infusion (§dUtility§r, Helmet): Constantly clear negative status effects.%n-Astronaut's Equipment (§6Protection§r, Any): Gain space suit capability.%n-Adaptive Jetpack Stabilizers (§aMovement§r, Chestplate): Allow your jetpack to hover perfectly without descending.

# Quest: Protect Your Base: Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0A.name=§a§lProtect Your Base: Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0A.desc=The small parts for the powerful turrets.

# Quest: Make Love, Not War
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0Q.name=§a§lMake Love, Not War
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0Q.desc=For those who don't want to kill things. Just teleport them away, however this takes a large amount of power.

# Quest: Why Grenades...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0g.name=§a§lWhy Grenades...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0g.desc=...when you can use rockets? Yes, rockets! They search and destroy, and go off with a huge boom.

# Quest: Tier 4 Fence and Walls
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0w.name=§a§lTier 4 Fence and Walls
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA0w.desc=Another upgrade for your walls. One more to go!

# Quest: Almost Unbreakable
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA2w.name=§b§lAlmost Unbreakable
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA2w.desc=Probably not required any more, but you've made so many walls already. So why not get the best ones?

# Quest: Protect Your Base: Tier 5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3A.name=§b§lProtect Your Base: Tier 5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3A.desc=Tough materials, for tough weapons. Railguns, and lasers, and... stuff. I assume you want a lot of those soon.

# Quest: Turret Base Tier 5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3Q.name=§b§lTurret Base Tier 5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3Q.desc=The last one, I promise. Used for the most powerful turrets available. You wonder if they might help you take out some more... "Dangerous" enemies?

# Quest: PewPew!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3g.name=§b§lPewPew!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3g.desc=Requires no ammo, but still does a ton of damage. All you need to do is feed it power, a lot of power.

# Quest: Railguns, What Else
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3w.name=§b§lRailguns, What Else
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA3w.desc=Massive power, and a wonderful sound when they fire. I recommend to use upgrades to increase range and damage.

# Quest: Protect Your Base: Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeA.name=§5§lProtect Your Base: Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeA.desc=One needs proper protection for one's home. So why not get some turrets for safety? At the moment, 2 Turrets are available: "Potato" and "disposable item". I assume you can guess what they do and how they work...

# Quest: Passive Defence
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeQ.name=§5§lPassive Defence
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeQ.desc=A more "passive" approach to base defense are walls and fences. But seriously, where's the fun in that?

# Quest: Turret Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeg.name=§5§lTurret Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAeg.desc=Turrets must be placed on top of a turret base. Only the player who initially placed the base can access and configure the turret. So don't worry about people taking your ammunition.

# Quest: Who Needs That Dirt Anyway
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAew.name=§5§lWho Needs That Dirt Anyway
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAew.desc=You probably have a ton of items floating around in your base. So why not use them to kill your enemies?

# Quest: Don't Play With Your Food!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfA.name=§5§lDon't Play With Your Food!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfA.desc=Use it to kill zombies instead. Does only a little damage, but hey, who cares?

# Quest: Upgrading Intensifies
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfQ.name=§5§lUpgrading Intensifies
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAfQ.desc=Your turrets probably need more space to hold more ammunition, so why not get an upgrade for that?

# Quest: Luke, I'm Your Father
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiw.name=Luke, I'm Your Father
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiw.desc=With that dark steel you got, you may now craft yourself a new set of armor. While pretty basic at first, it can be upgraded later to unlock powerful features.

# Quest: Harder, Stronger, Faster
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAmw.name=§6§lHarder, Stronger, Faster
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAmw.desc=No, actually not faster. But more durable than tier 1.

# Quest: Protect Your Base: Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnA.name=§6§lProtect Your Base: Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnA.desc=Slightly better protection. Now with a real gun. No more wasting food.

# Quest: Tier 2 Turret Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnQ.name=§6§lTier 2 Turret Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnQ.desc=Nothing to see here. Proceed...

# Quest: Sometimes, a Bullet Will Do
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAng.name=§6§lSometimes, a Bullet Will Do
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAng.desc=They hit hard. You have been warned.

# Quest: Burn Them. Burn Them All!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnw.name=§6§lBurn Them. Burn Them All!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAnw.desc=Hmmm, crispy bacon. What would happen if you enable neutral mobs as targeting...?

# Quest: Almost Like Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAqw.name=§9§lAlmost Like Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAqw.desc=Next-gen protection against nasty zombies, creepers and other "stuff".

# Quest: Protect Your Base: Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArA.name=§9§lProtect Your Base: Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArA.desc=Now we're talking: Grenades! The next in big badda boom hardware.

# Quest: Tier 3 Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArQ.name=§9§lTier 3 Base
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArQ.desc=More storage, more power, and a lot more slots for possible upgrades.

# Quest: This is Relatively Useful
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArg.name=§9§lThis is Relatively Useful
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArg.desc=For... some things... maybe... At least it's fun to watch?

# Quest: Fire in the Hole
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArw.name=§9§lFire in the Hole
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAArw.desc=Ah, there's nothing like an explosion and the certainty that your enemies have been blasted into tiny pieces.

# Quest: Turret Base Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAzw.name=§a§lTurret Base Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAzw.desc=Even more range, power and upgrade slots.

# Quest: Iron Shields
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkA.name=§2§lIron Shields
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkA.desc=You've been using your hide shield long enough. After you make your first tools, grab a bit of iron ore and make a nice iron shield.

# Quest: Stone spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkQ.name=§2§lStone spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkQ.desc=Upgrade your wooden spear with a stone arrowhead and iron screws to a stone spear.%nThis spear has better durability than the wooden one.

# Quest: Iron Spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkg.name=§3§lIron Spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkg.desc=Upgrade your wooden spear with an iron arrowhead and two steel screws to an iron spear.%n%nThe iron spear has better durability than the stone variant.

# Quest: Diamond Spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkw.name=§6§lDiamond Spear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACkw.desc=At MV Tier you can upgrade your iron spear to a diamond one. Get a diamond arrowhead, two stainless steel screws and a wooden spear.%n%nThis spear has superior durability.

# Quest: Diamond Shield
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAClA.name=§6§lDiamond Shield
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAClA.desc=Your iron shield is old and worn out. With a shield made from diamond plates you can maintain block for up to 5 seconds.

# Quest: Bow, Arrows and Quiver
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAClQ.name=§5§lBow, Arrows and Quiver
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAClQ.desc=Wow, your first handmade §oehm§r machine made bow. Now it's time to make a quiver and maybe some arrows.%n%nTo place arrows in the quiver, put the quiver and the stack of arrows in a crafting grid. Make sure the Gameplay key Special doesn't conflict with other keybinds. By default, it is Z. When you have the bow selected, use Z to swap arrow slots in the quiver.%n%nWhile it seems like these might be worthless, these arrows do have special uses. You really want to share a cookie with friends, don't you?%n%nLet's go hunt a bit.

# Quest: Wet Dirt Armor?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACqw.name=Wet Dirt Armor?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACqw.desc=If you don't have any armor, "mud armor" is better than nothing. Mud can be found in some wet biomes, or crafted from dirt and water.

# Quest: Wooden Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrA.name=Wooden Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrA.desc=If you can't find mud you can make very poor armor out of wood. Cutting down a few trees to make a set should do. You will need a soft mallet too, so save a few logs for that.

# Quest: Armor 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrQ.name=Armor 2.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrQ.desc=Iron armor is much better than the leather armor. Especially when you have to go outside during the night.

# Quest: Leather Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrg.name=Leather Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrg.desc=Killing some cows will give you enough leather to craft a complete set of leather armor.%n%nHint: You are able to dye this armor.

# Quest: Bronze armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrw.name=Bronze armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACrw.desc=Bronze armor has the same abilities as iron armor. Same durability, same protection and same enchantment capability.

# Quest: "Nice to Have" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsA.name="Nice to Have" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsA.desc=The gold armor is a "nice to have" armor. The durability is very low but you look expensive when you wear it.

# Quest: "Ooo, Shiny" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsQ.name="Ooo, Shiny" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsQ.desc=Diamond armor is the best armor in Vanilla Minecraft, but over here there are much better armors available.

# Quest: Fancy Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsg.name=Fancy Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsg.desc=Not really better but fancier. The chain mail armor is made out of steel rings.

# Quest: Armor 2.5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsw.name=Armor 2.5
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACsw.desc=The steel armor has more durability than the iron/bronze or chainmail armor.

# Quest: Composite Vest
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACtA.name=Composite Vest
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACtA.desc=Combining the strength of advanced alloy plates with the steel chestplate makes your vest very hard. Now you have double the durability and increased armor points by 1.5.

# Quest: Dark Steel Armor Basic Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD3w.name=Dark Steel Armor Basic Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD3w.desc=In order to upgrade one armor item with basic upgrades, you need a vibrant crystal and 10 XP levels. Some upgrades can be applied directly, but more advanced ones will require empowering the armor first.

# Quest: Dark Steel Armor Advanced Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD5Q.name=Dark Steel Armor Advanced Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD5Q.desc=Your Dark Steel armor can be upgraded in various ways by combining it with various other items. You will need an anvil and a lot of XP.%n%nMake sure when making the potions to only do three at a time, so the NBT data matches.

# Quest: Carbon Parts
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADBw.name=Carbon Parts
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADBw.desc=These are the first parts you will need for your beloved nano armor.%n%n[note]To actually complete the nano armor, you will need EV circuits and nano crystals (see Storing and Transforming EU).[/note]%n%n[warn]IC2 is slowly being removed from the modpack! Check out the nearby quest "Modular Meddling" for the replacement.[/warn]

# Quest: Seeing Things Brighter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADCA.name=Seeing Things Brighter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADCA.desc=The nano helmet is a bit special. It will provide you with night vision as long as you have energy!%n%n[note]If you got these from a lootbag, hold these in your hand after completing the "Carbon Parts" quest to skip this quest.[/note]

# Quest: Carbon Skin
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADCw.name=Carbon Skin
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADCw.desc=You can stop worrying about some mobs for now. This will help you survive a bit and will give you some of that SWAG. Your journey doesn't stop here traveller, as quantum armor awaits you!%n%n[note]PS: The nano suit also acts as hazmat gear.[/note]

# Quest: Sensor Lens
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHA.name=Sensor Lens
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHA.desc=The night vision goggles need special sensor lenses to work.

# Quest: Advanced Heat Exchanger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHQ.name=Advanced Heat Exchanger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHQ.desc=The night vision goggles need advanced heat exchangers to work.

# Quest: Don't Try to Dive With It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHw.name=Don't Try to Dive With It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADHw.desc=Combining a scuba helmet with a nano helmet in an assembling machine will give you a nano scuba helmet. You'd better not try to dive with it because you can't. It is a part of the new quantum suit helmet.

# Quest: Plated Leggings - Better Not Try to Wear It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIA.name=Plated Leggings - Better Not Try to Wear It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIA.desc=Combining stainless steel platings with some nano leggings in the assembler gives you nano plated leggings. Better not try to wear them because you can't. They are part of the new quantum suit leggings.

# Quest: Don't Try to Walk With It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIQ.name=Don't Try to Walk With It
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIQ.desc=Combining some rubber boots with nano boots in the Assembler gives you Nano Rubber Boots. Better not try to put them on because you can't. They are part of the new quantum suit boots.

# Quest: Iridium Plated
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIg.name=Iridium Plated
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIg.desc=Plating all your armor parts with iridium alloy casings gives them a better durability. Before you can wear these quantum armor parts you need to activate them with some quantum crystals.

# Quest: Quantum Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIw.name=Quantum Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADIw.desc=The quantum armor is a high tier and very durable armor with a lot of features like night vision, fall damage reduction and running very fast.

# Quest: Better Bolts
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9A.name=§6§lBetter Bolts
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9A.desc=Now that you are in MV and have an EBF, you can make new bolts with vanadiumsteel-tipped magnalium. Your enemies will tremble at your might.%n%nCheck "fletching" under NEI for fletching options.%n%nGood hunting!

# Quest: Best Bolts?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9Q.name=§a§lBest Bolts?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9Q.desc=That meteoric iron you found on the moon, when sent through the EBF, turns into this amazing meteoric steel, able to keep a fine edge. Put some on an Energetic Alloy tool rod to make an awesome bolt. Your next bolt you'll have to figure out yourself.%n%nUse whatever fletching you want.

# Quest: Best Crossbow?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9g.name=§9§lBest Crossbow?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAF9g.desc=Energetic alloy has proven to be an amazing material. Its light weight and high stiffness makes it perfect for a crossbow limb. It is slightly slower to draw but still has amazing stopping power with its very high bolt speed. Durability is much improved over a carbon limb.%n%nThe material would also make an excellent bolt body. Perhaps you will find a suitable tip to match?

# Quest: Electrogoggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRQ.name=Electrogoggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRQ.desc=As you wander with your Goggles of Revealing you noticed that they tend to break easy. So craft yourself some electric ones that just need to be charged again!

# Quest: Nano Goggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRg.name=Nano Goggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRg.desc=The #1 product for spies and wanna-be-spies. Nano-Goggles. Don't you want one of these too? But they are sold out? Craft some!

# Quest: Quantum Goggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRw.name=Quantum Goggles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFRw.desc=As you continue to progress, you notice that your black goggles don't match your nice white and shiny armor. You decide to get a pair of white ones.

# Quest: Goggles > 9000
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFSA.name=Goggles > 9000
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFSA.desc=This special pair of goggles recharges itself while you wander in sunlight. How convenient.

# Quest: Compressed Steel Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFog.name=Compressed Steel Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFog.desc=The compressed steel armor has more durability than the steel armor.

# Quest: Compressed Desh Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFow.name=Compressed Desh Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFow.desc=The compressed desh armor has more durability than the compressed steel armor.

# Quest: Compressed Titanium Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFpA.name=Compressed Titanium Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFpA.desc=The compressed titanium armor has more durability than the compressed steel armor.

# Quest: Traveller's Wings Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-A.name=Traveller's Wings Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-A.desc=Your wings can be equipped with a few modifications such as feather falling and double jump. Place the wings in the center of a Crafting Station.%n%nFeather Fall allows you to glide down slowly in air.%nDouble Jump means you jump while in the air to jump again.%n%nHint:%nAutorepair can be added to the wings as well.%nEvery Armor part has 3 Slots for modification.

# Quest: Traveller's Gloves Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-Q.name=Traveller's Gloves Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-Q.desc=Putting redstone on my weapon makes it faster. So why don't I put it on my hands directly!%nThis will increase your mining speed.%n%nHint:%nEvery Armor part has 3 Slots for modification, aside from gloves, which have 5.

# Quest: Traveller's Gear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9Q.name=Traveller's Gear
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9Q.desc=The goggles, wings, shoes, vest, belt and boots itself are not really special.%n%nYou can zoom with the goggles, have an extra inventory hotbar with the belt, step-up assist with the shoes, jump boost with the wings and faster swimming ability with the vest.%n%nYou get protection like with normal armor too.%n%nLater on you can upgrade your items to become more powerful ones.

# Quest: Traveller's Goggles Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9g.name=Traveller's Goggles Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9g.desc=Nightvision is very useful. If you combine your Goggles with a night vision potion (3:00, make sure to make 3 at a time), a golden carrot, and a flint and steel inside the Tinkers Crafting Station you get Night Vision Goggles. Place the Goggles in the Center of the Crafting Station.%n%nHint: Autorepair can be added to the goggles as well.%n%nEvery Armor has 3 slots for modification.

# Quest: Traveller's Vest Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9w.name=Traveller's Vest Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG9w.desc=Your vest can be equipped with a few modifications like perfect dodge and stealth.%nPerfect dodge means you're harder to hit and can be stacked up to 3 times.%nStealth turns you invisible while sneaking. Place the vest in the center of a Tinker's Crafting Station.%n%nHint:%nAutorepair can be added to the vest as well.%nEvery Armor part has 3 Slots for modification.

# Quest: "Oh, Magic" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHLw.name="Oh, Magic" Armor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHLw.desc=Ironwood Armor is a magic armor with some special enchants. The Helm gives aqua affinity, the shoes feather falling, the plate and the legs extra protection.

# Quest: Armor of the Dead
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHOA.name=Armor of the Dead
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHOA.desc=I've found another use for Ectoplasm - making Spectral Iron. An armor made from it is better than diamond and highly enchantable.%n%nIt also will drop healing orbs that will heal the nearest player when picked up.%n%nUnfortunately, a side effect is that you'll become partially transparent. Side effect, I mean bonus feature!

# Quest: "Oh, Magic" Armor II
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAICQ.name="Oh, Magic" Armor II
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAICQ.desc=Steeleaf armor is the next level in Twilight Forest armor. It can be handy as a defense in the Nether.

# Quest: "Oh, Magic" Armor III
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAICg.name="Oh, Magic" Armor III
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAICg.desc=Knightmetal is the top tier Twilight Forest armor. It doesn't come with any free enchants but it has high durability and high armor rating.

# Quest: Sometimes Life is Scary and Dark - Bring a Backpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQA.name=Sometimes Life is Scary and Dark - Bring a Backpack
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQA.desc=Now that you are MV, you can make an Adventure Backpack. This very useful backpack can do many things. It can store 2 tools for quick access, has internal tanks for containing liquids - use the Hose to access them, a built in crafting table, and storage.%n%nWhen placed on your back, it can be accessed using a quick-access key, default is B. Check your controls for details.%n%nWhen placed on the ground, it can be accessed with a right-click. While on the ground, the bedroll can be deployed and used.%n%nThey can also be upgraded to add special abilities. For a full list, visit [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Adventure_Backpacks[/url].%n%n[note]It uses up the same slot as the Coal Jetpack and the Copterpack, so you'll either need to choose one, or swap them around.[/note]

# Quest: See Like a ... Bat?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQQ.name=See Like a ... Bat?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQQ.desc=Nightvision is a great backpack ability.

# Quest: Swim Like a .... Squid?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQg.name=Swim Like a .... Squid?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQg.desc=If you need to go deep or explore in the water, this is the backpack for you.

# Quest: Walk Through Fire
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQw.name=Walk Through Fire
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIQw.desc=The Pigman backpack will make the Nether ezpz with fire resistance. You'll have to figure out a way to get struck by lightning while wearing a Pig backpack to get it...

# Quest: Creeper Repellant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRA.name=Creeper Repellant
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRA.desc=An ocelot backpack will get those creepers running away from you. Nice protection against those drowning creepers! Don't get too close to them or else their repulsion will be overridden and they'll blow up!

# Quest: Milk Without the Cow?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRQ.name=Milk Without the Cow?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRQ.desc=A Cow backpack will generate milk from wheat placed in its inventory. Great for a lazy farmer!

# Quest: Here There be Dragons
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRg.name=Here There be Dragons
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIRg.desc=The Dragon backpack gives you Fire Resistance, Strength, Night Vision and Regeneration.%n%n[note]It may be really good, but also uses up a dragon egg, so be sure you want it, or can craft another.[/note]

# Quest: Oink!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIWw.name=Oink!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIWw.desc=While the Pig backpack is useless on its own, it can be turned into a pretty powerful tool with the right...motivation.

# Quest: Seeing Inside Your Chests
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJhQ.name=Seeing Inside Your Chests
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJhQ.desc=With the Holo Glasses you are able to look into Chests, Barrels and Drawers like a Holographic inventory.%n%n[note]If you lost your free one, you should be capable of making another now.[/note]

# Quest: Armor Molds
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMAw.name=Armor Molds
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMAw.desc=Why use plates when you can make your armor pieces out of molten metal?

# Quest: Quantum Chestplate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMRw.name=Quantum Chestplate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMRw.desc=QuantumSuit Bodyarmor allows for flight just like its predecessor, but when you hold shift+space instead of going down you will go slightly up.%nThe next tier - GraviChestPlate - will get rid of this problem altogether.

# Quest: Supreme Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.BFkQt-DcRhmReOUsVWtrqA.name=Supreme Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.BFkQt-DcRhmReOUsVWtrqA.desc=At ZPM, you've almost reached the peak of personal defense technology. New augments await!%n%nThe living energy core will allow your armor to charge at ZPM voltage and equip tier 3 augments.%n%nThe frames in this tier provide 7 augment slots. Pushing the limits of modularity, every frame now has at least one prismatic slot.

# Quest: Modular Meddling
betterquesting.quest.CQnbvvAiRY2e7CsShsCe1A.name=Modular Meddling
betterquesting.quest.CQnbvvAiRY2e7CsShsCe1A.desc=Interested in powerful, customizable armor that you can modify as you advance? Look no further than §6§r§l&z&zMechanical Armor§r!%n%nIn order to begin tinkering, you'll need a workspace for modifying modular equipment along with a set of Mechanical Armor. The armor is essentially useless on its own, but gains additional features through modification. Each piece of armor is composed of three parts:%n%n§nAugments: §rAugments add a wide variety of useful features to the armor. Augments are categorized into one of three types: §6Protection§r, §aMovement§r, and §dUtility§r. Augments can only be inserted into slots corresponding to their category.%n%n§nFrames:§r The armor's frame determines the protection value of the armor along with how many slots it contains for augments.%n%n§nEnergy Cores:§r The energy core determines how much energy the armor stores, its charging tier, and which augments can be equipped.

# Quest: Even More Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.HrZv5S5MRLS38lNV93yEnQ.name=Even More Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.HrZv5S5MRLS38lNV93yEnQ.desc=There are currently only three new augments available in Tier 3, but they are very powerful.%n%n-Energy Grid Defense (§6Protection§r, Chestplate): Gain a forcefield that can completely block most damage at the cost of a huge amount of EU.%n-Gravitational Control Module (§aMovement§r, Chestplate): Creative flight.%n-Inertial Dampeners (§aMovement§r, Chestplate): Enable inertia canceling, allowing you to stop instantly while flying.

# Quest: Basic Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.Ta-VKcQFSpejtRIkB650qg.name=Basic Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.Ta-VKcQFSpejtRIkB650qg.desc=To turn your mechanical exoskeleton from a hunk of useless metal into a power suit, you'll need a core and a frame.%n%nThe basic energy core will allow your armor to charge at HV voltage and equip tier 1 augments.%n%nThe first three frames all give 3 augment slots spread among the categories. Choose based on what augments you need to equip!

# Quest: Perfected Energy Core
betterquesting.quest.YXYbS-DuTuK7ISAjGV874A.name=Perfected Energy Core
betterquesting.quest.YXYbS-DuTuK7ISAjGV874A.desc=Sick of your Mechanical Armor running out of batteries? Try strapping a miniaturized singularity to your chest! It's entirely safe.%n%nThis final energy core will provide infinite energy to the Mechanical Armor and allow any augment to be equipped.

# Quest: Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.hwvNowyHS7WJOK4xDcUw0A.name=Augmentation
betterquesting.quest.hwvNowyHS7WJOK4xDcUw0A.desc=Now that you have a frame and a core, you can get to work adding new features to your Mechanical Armor. This quest lists all Tier 1 augments.%n%nSome standouts:%n%n-Optical Brightness Adjuster (§dUtility§r, Helmet): Enable toggleable night vision.%n-Protective Lining (§6Protection§r, Any): Gain full hazmat protection.%n-Electric Jetpack (§aMovement§r, Chestplate): Jetpack!

# Quest: Mob Repellators
betterquesting.quest.tgH86mIERWKIh8OAleKrSw.name=Mob Repellators
betterquesting.quest.tgH86mIERWKIh8OAleKrSw.desc=First available in LV, the Mob Repellator prevents mobs from spawning in its radius. It works without power, but with it has a higher range.%n%n[note]You only need one to complete the quest.[/note]

# Quest: Advanced Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.z7sXK-B1SSyRD9ukAs1JEw.name=Advanced Mechanical Armor
betterquesting.quest.z7sXK-B1SSyRD9ukAs1JEw.desc=Now that you're in IV, you can unlock the next set of upgrades for Mechanical Armor, gaining more slots and new augments.%n%nThe quantum energy core will allow your armor to charge at IV voltage and equip tier 2 augments.%n%nThe frames in this tier provide 5 augment slots. The adaptive frame uniquely has a §6Pri§asma§dtic§r slot that will accept an augment of any category!

# Quest: Perfected Armor Frame
betterquesting.quest.zWyFqJfWTGKjw63-EG7DDw.name=Perfected Armor Frame
betterquesting.quest.zWyFqJfWTGKjw63-EG7DDw.desc=Tired of being constrained by augment slots? The constantly shifting properties of Infinity make it an ideal material for a modular frame.%n%nThis final frame provides 5 slots of every category, including prismatic.


## Quest Line: Building Better Bases
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADQ.name=Building Better Bases
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADQ.desc=Tired of torches everywhere making your base look like a loser built it? Make your base look like a winner with these quests.

# Quest: Let it Glow!
betterquesting.quest.0w2-45C7TC6rzR04zSYe8A.name=§a§lLet it Glow!
betterquesting.quest.0w2-45C7TC6rzR04zSYe8A.desc=Chisel adds a couple new sets of glowing blocks to enhance your builds. %n%nIf you've ever seen a cool looking futuristic base on the loading screen, it likely used one of these blocks!%n%n[note]Unlike Neonite and Antiblocks, Lapis Caelestis blocks do emit light - and different colors emit different amounts of it.[/note]

# Quest: Barrel Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.5zyyh2tXQ8On53B0VtAHZw.name=§c§lBarrel Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.5zyyh2tXQ8On53B0VtAHZw.desc=Better Barrels have tiers which increase the amount of upgrades a barrel can hold. They are mainly used to increase their storage capacity, although there are a few upgrades which give the barrels extra functionality.%n%nBarrels can only be upgraded one tier at a time, so be prepared to make lots of lower tier structural upgrades if you plan to continue using Better Barrels for your storage needs!

# Quest: Building Made Easy
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACWQ.name=§c§lBuilding Made Easy
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACWQ.desc=Placing blocks by hand can be tedious. Wouldn't it be nice to be able to place blocks like "Another 9 here"? Well, good news. Get yourself some of the various building blocks, and I shall reward you with something nice.%n%nYou could also just craft it (or the better one) with unstable ingots yourself, too.%n%nYou can upgrade to the various other BBWs too.

# Quest: Base Too Big? I've Got a Fix For You!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADuA.name=§2§lBase Too Big? I've Got a Fix For You!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADuA.desc=Keeping a base spread apart for pollution or explosion prevention can really wear you out, so why not make some concrete to get around faster?%n%nHarvest some Marble and centrifuge it into Calcite, and mix up some concrete in your Mixer. Next output it into a Fluid Solidifier with a block mold to make concrete blocks.%n%nYou'll move faster on top of these blocks. They can even be turned into bricks to prevent unwanted spawns! Hint: 10 buckets of wet mix converts to exactly 160 blocks. These blocks can also be Chiseled into different varieties.

# Quest: Chisel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjw.name=§a§lChisel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHjw.desc=Chisel is one of the main building mods in this pack. It adds hundreds of new blocks which will help make your base beautiful!%n%nThe mod also adds different variants of many vanilla blocks. Make a chisel to check them out!

# Quest: The Right Tool for the Job
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkA.name=§a§lThe Right Tool for the Job
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkA.desc=Tinker's Construct has their own chisel tool variant, for converting Tinker blocks into different types. Not a lot of uses, but if you check NEI you can see what you can do.

# Quest: Tinker's Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkQ.name=§a§lTinker's Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkQ.desc=Tinker's Construct offers a couple of useful blocks from the smeltery. Rough Brownstone takes Tin and Gravel and makes a block that lets you move a little faster. Cobblestone can be turned into Seared Stone, usable in the smeltery walls to make it larger without having to use clay.

# Quest: Some Handy Uses
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkg.name=§a§lSome Handy Uses
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkg.desc=The TiCon chisel doesn't have a lot of uses, but here are a couple of interesting ones. Use NEI to see other options for more decorations. You can also slab these blocks if you want something monsters cannot spawn on.%n%nYou can also use the chisel in-world on Tinkers' blocks to change them into different variants - just be aware that sometimes you can't change them back!%n%n[note]Brownstone roads are slightly faster than rough brownstone.[/note]%n%n[note]Using the chisel on seared stone allows you to turn it into seared bricks.[/note]

# Quest: Chisel All the Things
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkw.name=§2§lChisel All the Things
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHkw.desc=If, for some reason, you need to chisel a large number of items, the autochisel is what you want.

# Quest: Chisel as Fast as You Can
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlA.name=§2§lChisel as Fast as You Can
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlA.desc=The autochisel speed is pretty slow. Craft some upgrades to make it faster.

# Quest: My Ancient Enemy
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlQ.name=§a§lMy Ancient Enemy
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlQ.desc=The one place Chisel is weak is in stairs. It would be nice to have more variety, but later I'll show you how to make any block into a custom stair.%n%nYou can also search NEI for "stairs" to find stairs from other mods.

# Quest: Basic Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlg.name=§a§lBasic Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlg.desc=Chisel offers a wide variety of blocks. Searching NEI for "chisel" gives pages and pages. Here's a small sample.

# Quest: Fun Party Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlw.name=§a§lFun Party Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHlw.desc=There's also some really funky blocks available.

# Quest: Concrete and GT Stones
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmA.name=§a§lConcrete and GT Stones
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmA.desc=Chisel can also transform Concrete and GT stones into new interesting blocks. Some of the GT stone blocks will even prevent mobs from spawning on top. Concrete will let you run faster.

# Quest: Basic Builder's Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmQ.name=§c§lBasic Builder's Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmQ.desc=The only thing going for the stone builder's wand is that it's cheap. It doesn't offer much in special modes, and doesn't last long either. But you can make a lot!%n%nTo use, right-click on a block while holding more of that block in your inventory. An outline will show you what it will do.%n%n[note]Tip: /wandoops will undo any block placements you make with the wand, just in case you misclick.[/note]

# Quest: Low-Tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmg.name=§c§lLow-Tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmg.desc=The Iron wand will last longer than the stone wand, and has a few modes.

# Quest: Mid-Tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmw.name=§6§lMid-Tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHmw.desc=The next tier up wand is the Diamond wand. Has all kinds of fun modes. Just be careful using it, would hate to place a bunch of blocks accidentally!

# Quest: Botany
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHoA.name=§a§lBotany
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHoA.desc=The Botany mod offers more colors for blocks and glass, and simple tile patterns or more complex patterns using a Tileworker. For now, we'll make an iron trowel.%n%nThis mod will make lots of butterflies, so make sure to do your gardening underground or under glass. The butterflies will spread and infect leaves around your area, making more butterflies, causing lag.

# Quest: Finding Flowers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHoQ.name=§a§lFinding Flowers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHoQ.desc=처음으로, 꽃을 찾아야 합니다. 그 다음에는 삽을 집어 흙 블록을 흙으로 변환합니다. 이어서 꽃을 흙 위에 올려 Botany 꽃으로 변환합니다. MV 단계에 도달했다면, Genetics에 대한 정보를 얻고 싶다면 어떻게 벌이 되는가 탭을 확인해보세요.

# Quest: Powder Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHow.name=§a§lPowder Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHow.desc=Botany uses various powders to enhance soil properties.%n%nRaise Ph - Ash Powder, Pulp Powder%nLower Ph - Mulch Powder, Sulphur Powder%nIncrease Nutrients - Fertilizer Powder, Compost Powder

# Quest: Killing Weeds and Growing Flowers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpA.name=§a§lKilling Weeds and Growing Flowers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpA.desc=Nobody likes weeds. Weedkiller will keep the weeds off your soil.%n%nBone meal can be applied to germling flowers to make them mature faster.

# Quest: Like Having a County Extension Office in Your Hand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpQ.name=§6§lLike Having a County Extension Office in Your Hand
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpQ.desc=The soil meter will tell you the soil stats - how dry, how many nutrients, etc. You can amend the soil with the various powders so that it matches the requirements for your flower.

# Quest: 80 New Colors to Play With
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpg.name=§a§l80 New Colors to Play With
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpg.desc=When you plant a vanilla flower, it is already mature. Cut it with shears to get a germling you can replant to make more. Break the flower to get a mature flower. Turn the flower into pigment using a crafting table.%n%nTo get crosses, plant flowers next to empty soil blocks. Keep an eye out for weeds. Eventually a small germling will start growing.%n%nRemember, do this underground or in an enclosure or your TPS will regret it.

# Quest: Glass of Many Colors
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpw.name=§a§lGlass of Many Colors
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHpw.desc=The pigments color an amazing variety of glass. Just one warning - unlike normal glass, this glass isn't fireproof.

# Quest: Ceramics
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqA.name=§a§lCeramics
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqA.desc=With some clay and pigments, you can make pigmented clay. Put the pigmented clay in a furnace to get basic ceramic blocks. These blocks are great if you want an area of nice even colors.

# Quest: Mortar and Tiles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqQ.name=§a§lMortar and Tiles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqQ.desc=To make ceramic tile patterns, you need to convert your blocks into tiles. First make mortar, and then use the mortar with your blocks in a 3 block + 1 mortar pattern in the crafting table to get ceramic tiles.

# Quest: Tile Patterns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqg.name=§a§lTile Patterns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqg.desc=Now that you have tiles, you can make simple tile patterns. A 2x2 of red/yellow and yellow/red makes a simple checkerboard. Using the checkerboard again in a 2x2 makes a checkerboard with smaller tiles. Use Binnie's Botany wiki page to find more patterns you can make with just tiles.

# Quest: Tileworker
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqw.name=§2§lTileworker
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHqw.desc=The tileworker can take the single-color ceramic blocks and turn them into pretty patterned blocks.%n%nAnd contrary to the name, you use ceramic blocks here, not tiles.

# Quest: Glassworker
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrQ.name=§2§lGlassworker
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrQ.desc=Want some custom glass shapes and configurations? A glassworker can provide some unique patterns to put in your windows. You'll need to make some glass fittings to hold the glass together.

# Quest: Mo' Hammers Mo' Problems
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrg.name=§2§lMo' Hammers Mo' Problems
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrg.desc=Yes indeed, time for another type of hammer. The master carpentry hammer will allow you to rotate the blocks from the various workers.%n%nSneak to rotate the blocks vertically.%n%nWhy is the lower tier hammer the master hammer? Who knows??

# Quest: Panels to Cover Your...Everything
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrw.name=§2§lPanels to Cover Your...Everything
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHrw.desc=The panelworker will create wood flooring pieces for you to use.

# Quest: Fancy Woods
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsA.name=§2§lFancy Woods
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsA.desc=With the woodworker, you can create fancy looking types of wood blocks. You can use wood planks from Vanilla, Forestry, and Extra Trees.

# Quest: Look Mom, No Torches!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsQ.name=§a§lLook Mom, No Torches!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsQ.desc=Tired of a base using nothing but torches? This set of quests will go through the various options available to light up your beautiful base.%n%nFirst up, Railcraft lanterns. These come in stone and metallic varieties. The stone varieties don't need much to craft. One plus/minus for these lanterns is that they are solid blocks - while you cannot walk through them, they also do not fall if the surrounding blocks are removed. Search "lantern" in NEI for more varieties. They are a bit annoying to craft now, but if you check NEI you can make them pretty easily with assemblers later.

# Quest: Second Saw
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsg.name=§a§lSecond Saw
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsg.desc=Forge Microblocks은 맞춤형 부품 제작에 매우 유용할 수 있습니다. 사용할 수 있는 다양한 톱 계층이 있습니다. 재작성하여 쇠로 만든 것을 제작하면 다이아몬드로 된 것을 드리겠습니다.

# Quest: Fancy Lanterns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsw.name=§c§lFancy Lanterns
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHsw.desc=Bibliocraft는 화려한 외관의 등불을 제공합니다. 촛불은 캔들베리나 벌집에서 만들 수 있습니다.

# Quest: Even small Glowstone shines bright
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtA.name=§c§lEven small Glowstone shines bright
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtA.desc=이제 당신이 네더로 가서 발광석을 수집한 후에는, 그것을 빛으로도 사용할 수 있습니다. 당신은 그것의 색깔을 변경하여 블록 색을 바꿀 수 있습니다(불행히도 1.7.10은 색깔 있는 불빛을 지원하지 않습니다) 또는 Forge Microblocks 톱을 사용하여 작은 구석구석을 밝히기 위해 그것을 작게 자를 수 있습니다.%n%n당신이 찾거나 번식시킬 수 있는 다양한 발광 식물들도 있습니다. 예를 들면, 발광화가 그러합니다.

# Quest: Basic ProjectRed Illumination
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtQ.name=§2§lBasic ProjectRed Illumination
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtQ.desc=기본적인 ProjectRed Illumination 램프는 제작하기 위해 LV 믹서만 필요합니다. 일반 버전은 레드스톤 신호가 있어야만 켜집니다. 반전 버전은 레드스톤 신호가 적용되지 않는 한 항상 켜져 있습니다.

# Quest: Fancier ProjectRed Illumination
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtg.name=§2§lFancier ProjectRed Illumination
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtg.desc=더 화려한 ProjectRed Illumination 램프, 랜턴, 조명기구를 만들려면 성형 프레스와 조립기가 필요합니다.

# Quest: ProjectRed Lights With a Purpose
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtw.name=§2§lProjectRed Lights With a Purpose
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHtw.desc=ProjectRed는 버튼으로 사용할 수 있는 몇 가지 특별한 빛을 제공합니다. 일반 버튼은 항상 불이 켜져 있습니다. 피드백 버튼은 레드스톤 신호로 전원을 공급받을 때 불이 켜집니다.

# Quest: Flat Lamps
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuA.name=§2§lFlat Lamps
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuA.desc=이 간단한 램프는 Ztones 모드에서 나온 차분하고 세련된 스타일의 램프입니다. 저는 "오피스" 스타일을 연출하기 위해 이 램프를 천장에 사용하는 것을 좋아합니다.

# Quest: Glowstone & Chisel torches, space rated
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuQ.name=§2§lGlowstone & Chisel torches, space rated
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuQ.desc=When traveling off-world, you want the best in torches. Torches that will work in no-oxygen environments like the Moon. For that, you need glowstone torches. You can chisel these torches into a variety of torch types, also proven to work in deep space.

# Quest: Lighting Up a Large Area, Without Electricity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHug.name=§6§lLighting Up a Large Area, Without Electricity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHug.desc=If you have a relatively large area you need to light up without using electricity, you can use these floodlights. They can take normal furnace fuels, including blocks and compressed blocks. They do require some electronic components to make, but can send out a beam a long ways, or various cone shapes a shorter distance. Use the wrench to change modes, and shift-right-click to invert.

# Quest: Lighting Up a Large Area, With Electricity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuw.name=§5§lLighting Up a Large Area, With Electricity
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHuw.desc=Now that you have a vacuum freezer, you can liquefy compressed air cells and centrifuge them for rare gases. You'll need those to make the incandescent bulb for these lights. As long as they have EU, these lights can shoot a beam or do narrow or wide cones. Use the wrench to change modes, and shift-right-click to invert.%n%nIt's better to provide power to an Ender IO capacitor and then power these machines with RF, instead of powering directly with GT EU, because they don't work well with GT's EU amp system, and will draw a whole EU packet for a single RF.

# Quest: EnderIO Lights
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvA.name=§2§lEnderIO Lights
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvA.desc=EnderIO also has its own lights. These lights have a radius of 8 blocks vs the normal 7.

# Quest: BetterIO?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvQ.name=더 나은 IO?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvQ.desc=The Powered and Wireless Powered lights from EnderIO provide light up to 10 blocks away vs the normal 7 for a torch. They will require centrifuging liquid air to get the bulbs.

# Quest: What's Behind Door #3?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvg.name=§2§lWhat's Behind Door #3?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvg.desc=The Malisis Door Factory lets you go crazy with all kinds of ideas for custom doors.%n%nA Player Sensor is a nice way of opening a door. Better than pushing a button or stepping on a plate!%n%nMaybe you can find a use for this block mixer, it's kinda weird and doesn't work right.%n%nThere are some craftable Malisis items as well, check them out in NEI.

# Quest: Build it Bigger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvw.name=§2§lBuild it Bigger
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHvw.desc=당신이 만들 수 있습니다! 건축 가이드는 단순한 기하학적 모양의 윤곽선을 보여주는데 도움이 됩니다. 레드스톤 신호를 제공하여 활성화하세요.

# Quest: Faster, Better, Buildi-er
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwA.name=§6§lFaster, Better, Buildi-er
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwA.desc=The Enhanced Building Guide offers more features than the standard model. Most importantly, you can right-click on any white part of the block with the item you want placed and the block will place in the world. It needs a redstone signal to activate.

# Quest: More Like Ouch-i-tect
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwg.name=§a§lMore Like Ouch-i-tect
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHwg.desc=톱상은 대부분의 완전한 입방체 블록을 다양한 종류의 놀라운 모양으로 변환할 수 있습니다.%n%n망치로 오른쪽 클릭하면 90도 회전합니다. 망치로 Shift-오른쪽 클릭하면 "아래쪽" 면의 방향을 변경합니다.%n%n끌은 블록의 구조를 여러 가지 방법으로 변경하는 데 사용됩니다. 일부 블록은 인접 블록과 자동으로 연결됩니다. 이러한 연결은 변형을 원하는 측면 쪽에서 끌로 오른쪽 클릭하여 비활성화하고 다시 활성화할 수 있습니다.%n%n일부 블록에는 보조 재료가 적용될 수 있습니다. 이 보조 재료는 블록 중앙에 끌로 오른쪽 클릭하여 제거할 수 있습니다.%n%n또한, 끌로 바닐라 유리, 유리 판, 발광석 또는 얼음 블록을 오른쪽 클릭하여 블록을 깨지 않고 수확할 수도 있습니다.

# Quest: Keeping Track of Your Findings (Flowers)
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIOQ.name=§6§lKeeping Track of Your Findings (Flowers)
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIOQ.desc=이 편리한 장치는 지금까지 발견한 꽃과 그들의 특성을 기록해줍니다.

# Quest: Making Sense of Spaghetti
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIWg.name=§a§lMaking Sense of Spaghetti
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIWg.desc=Nobody likes an untidy base. Why don't you use some color to organize things a little!
%nThe paint brush, painter, and spray cans can be used to color machines, wires, cables, pipes, wool, stained glass, and more!
%n
%nColored pipes, wires, and cables can only connect to uncolored cables/pipes/wires, or those of the same color.
%n
%nInput buses and hatches can also be colored, and multiblock machines will enforce input separation based on their colors. Inputs of the same color can only see each other, and un-colored inputs work with any color. While outbut buses and hatches can be colored as well, doing so will have no effect on where the machine sends outputs.
%n
%nAny painted block can be painted over with another color, but to remove the color entirely you need to break the block while sneaking or use a can of solvent.
%n
%nThe paint brush is the cheapest to make paint for, only requiring one piece of colored dye. 
%nThe painter requires distilled water and a chemical bath to create paint for. 
%nThe spray can uses chemical dye, which requires an MV chemical reactor to make.
%nThe color applicator uses paint balls and can store all 16 colors at once.
%n
%n[note]Sneaking while using a spray can or paint brush will color an entire line of blocks![/note]
%n
%n[note]The priority of colored hatches is the same as the order of vanilla dyes in NEI, from highest (black) to lowest (white).[/note]

# Quest: Carpenter's Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIcA.name=§a§lCarpenter's Blocks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIcA.desc=Yet another custom block system! Carpenter's blocks are crafted blank and placed in-world, and then plain block textures applied to them. The blocks must not be Tile Entities, so Botany blocks don't work correctly with them, but GT Stones like Red Granite, and any colored clay or vanilla glass block will work. Some Chisel glass types will work, and Ztones blocks and Tinted Glass also work.%n%nThe Garage Door requires a block at the top to hang "down" from, but can pretty much be any length. A redstone signal on any block next to the Garage Door blocks will open or close the door. The open/close will propagate across multiple vertical doors, so you can set up non-square doors. Sneaking and right-clicking with an empty hand will change the door's polarity.%n%nThe pressure plates are player-only activation, making them great for doors into your base.%n%nThe hatches must be clicked on the side of a block to place. They can be handy for protecting you from crucible...byproducts.%n%nThere is a lot more block shapes possible, check NEI for "Carpenter's" to see the options.%n%nThe Chisel allows you to chisel blocks while attached to a Carpenter's block.%n%nThe Hammer allows various functions.%n%nHammer on door - changes door shape type%nSneak Hammer on door - Changes from iron to wooden behavior%nSneak Hammer on lever - Changes polarity (which direction is on/off)

# Quest: Catwalks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3g.name=§c§lCatwalks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3g.desc=The Catwalks Mod adds several cosmetic blocks to deck out your factory.%n%nScaffolds and Builder's Scaffolds are useful for building up in the air before you get access to flight. They can be climbed like ladders, and break instantly when punched. You will also not fall off of them if you let go of movement keys while climbing. If you right-click the Builder's Scaffold with a solid block, the scaffold will be replaced by that block.%n%nCatwalks can connect to each other to form a wide passageway. You can decorate them by attaching Caution Tape or Rope Lights, the latter provide dim lighting.%n%nCaged Ladders give you a way to move up and down without a risk of falling off. Climbing them is much faster than vanilla ladders.%n%nSupport Columns are purely decorative. They connect to each other in all directions. They also work as ladders.%n%nSturdy Rails let you run minecart tracks across gaps without supports. Right-click the Sturdy Powered Rail with a Blowtorch to power it permanently, you don't need a redstone torch. If you don't have enough distractions already, use them to build a rollercoaster!%n%nThe Blowtorch lets you remove railings or even the floor from a catwalk by right-clicking. Use it to make an opening to let you walk onto the catwalk, or if you don't know what an "OSHA violation" is. The same function can be performed by a GT or Forge-compatible wrench, so you don't actually need to make this.

# Quest: Excavation Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.Avz75EgSTdG48xI3HPGUMA.name=§8§lExcavation Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.Avz75EgSTdG48xI3HPGUMA.desc=Mining out large chunks of stone can be a huge pain when it comes to creating bases. Why not craft the excavator upgrade for your Prototype Matter Manipulator so that you have the ability to remove blocks quickly?

# Quest: Crystal Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.DSkXvzhRSKiwFLJywGDMRg.name=§6§l수정 셜커 상자
betterquesting.quest.DSkXvzhRSKiwFLJywGDMRg.desc=다이아몬드 셜커 상자의 강화 버전으로, 내부 아이템을 투명하게 들여다볼 수 있습니다.%n%n§n108§r개의 슬롯을 가지고 있습니다.%n%n[note]염색이 가능합니다![/note]

# Quest: Let's get Building!
betterquesting.quest.DrqLzppgTRWyg_ZvlVlokg.name=§a§lLet's get Building!
betterquesting.quest.DrqLzppgTRWyg_ZvlVlokg.desc=This pack features many mods which add lots of new building blocks and/or QOL features which make building much easier.%n%nThis questline will go over a few of the major additions.

# Quest: Chests Had Quite the Glow-up!
betterquesting.quest.GenrHPJeREqkjJv6CfbeEQ.name=§c§l상자의 화려한 변신은 무죄!
betterquesting.quest.GenrHPJeREqkjJv6CfbeEQ.desc=칸막이 상자(Compartment)는 탐색을 편하게 해주는 유능한 고급 상자입니다.%n%n내부 저장 공간이 여러 개의 폴더로 나뉘어 있어 이름을 정하거나 색상별로 구분할 수 있고, 검색 기능을 통해 모든 폴더의 아이템을 한 번에 찾을 수도 있습니다.%n%n가장 큰 사이즈의 칸막이 상자는 아이템을 최대 400 슬롯까지 저장할 수 있습니다.%n%n[note]제작대 옆에 칸막이 상자를 배치하면, 제작 화면에서 저장 공간에 접근할 수 있어 굉장히 편리합니다![/note]

# Quest: Obsidian Barrel
betterquesting.quest.KfgATF33ToiE0aYS4pp04Q.name=§6§l흑요석 통
betterquesting.quest.KfgATF33ToiE0aYS4pp04Q.desc=The Obsidian barrel holds as many items as the Diamond one, and is also immune to explosions.

# Quest: Obsidian Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.MbFXZcovQ1GRxQCeS2PUuw.name=§6§lObsidian Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.MbFXZcovQ1GRxQCeS2PUuw.desc=The portable equivalent of the Obsidian Barrel that retains it's explosion-proof qualities.%n%nHas §n108§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: Manipulator Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.NKKa001sQ9qXBPAUEV4Vrg.name=§8§lManipulator Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.NKKa001sQ9qXBPAUEV4Vrg.desc=Now that you have a Matter Manipulator... why not make it better?%n%nThese upgrades will give huge quality of life improvements when using should you choose to craft them. %n%n[note]Pay attention to the applicable tier of MM before you do so![/note]

# Quest: Obsidian Chest
betterquesting.quest.QMlw6Z67T5-y_qflA7On2Q.name=§8Obsidian Chest
betterquesting.quest.QMlw6Z67T5-y_qflA7On2Q.desc=Combining diamond chest with obsidian allowed you to create a chest that is blast proof!%n%n[note]Just as with the previous chests you can also upgrade with a fitting upgrade item.[/note]

# Quest: Iron Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.StA9TvxxSi2n2c7wQdCAFA.name=§2§lIron Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.StA9TvxxSi2n2c7wQdCAFA.desc=The portable equivalent of the Iron Barrel.%n%nHas §n54§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: A Modern Technology
betterquesting.quest.VFVruPLHQAeDthuV-s7HGQ.name=§a§lA Modern Technology
betterquesting.quest.VFVruPLHQAeDthuV-s7HGQ.desc=Concrete. Eh sorry, Hempcrete! A new modern technology brought to you via the GTNH Chisel mod. All 16 colors.%n%nThere are a lot of other nice blocks in Chisel. Just type "@chisel" in NEI and look around.

# Quest: Gotta Go Fast!
betterquesting.quest.Whl2BVaRSlaTf-ky0Ih96A.name=§6§lGotta Go Fast!
betterquesting.quest.Whl2BVaRSlaTf-ky0Ih96A.desc=Yet another block you can use to get around your base much more efficiently. Unlike concrete, you don't have to fill your floor with these to get their full benefit.%n%nYou can also stack the speed boost from both boosters and concrete for an even bigger speed boost!%n%n[note]Place your boosters 18 blocks apart - or 33 blocks if you're using concrete - for optimal boosting.[/note]

# Quest: Gold Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.YFUK2QflT1G3_WC8XBp2Wg.name=§3§lGold Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.YFUK2QflT1G3_WC8XBp2Wg.desc=The portable equivalent of the Gold Barrel.%n%nHas §n81§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: Finally, Some Real Power!
betterquesting.quest.YxYz1jL6RSWHCxMlTHeJFw.name=§4§l§nFinally, Some Real Power!
betterquesting.quest.YxYz1jL6RSWHCxMlTHeJFw.desc=The Energy Tunnel Manipulator Upgrade is incredibly useful for the heavy potential Matter Manipulator usage in UHV+. %n%nYou can now link directly with either the §5§lQuantum Link§r or a §5§lLaser Target Hatch§r for much quicker recharging. No need to rely on those slow wireless chargers any longer!

# Quest: Shulker Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.Zza5BrD7TduqKby_b3wQsQ.name=§3§lShulker Upgrades
betterquesting.quest.Zza5BrD7TduqKby_b3wQsQ.desc=Shulker boxes in need of an upgrade? Now that you're in MV and have access to §dCrystalline Pink Slime§r dust they can be! No need to gather all new shells, there are 9 upgrade items available. They will preserve the inventory of your shulker so there is no need to empty it beforehand.%n%n§lAvailable Upgrades:§r%nVanilla -> Copper%nVanilla -> Iron%nCopper -> Iron%nCopper -> Silver%nIron -> Gold%nSilver -> Gold%nGold -> Diamond%nDiamond -> Crystal%nDiamond -> Obsidian

# Quest: Diamond Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.aIt1E54yQaSOg4CMz-Xegw.name=§5§lDiamond Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.aIt1E54yQaSOg4CMz-Xegw.desc=The portable equivalent of the Diamond Barrel, you'll need to either upgrade your wand or take advantage of the Gold to Diamond Shulker Box Upgrade.%n%nHas §n108§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: Advanced Concrete Backfiller
betterquesting.quest.b-YCbvcNT4uEjg2pN-H6jw.name=§8§lAdvanced Concrete Backfiller
betterquesting.quest.b-YCbvcNT4uEjg2pN-H6jw.desc=The §5Advanced Concrete Backfiller§r has the same general functionality as the regular one except it boasts an impressive §364§r block radius and operates at §24x§r the speed. %n%nIt's a good idea to consider using one of these as your base continues to expand across more area. Filled space saves TPS!

# Quest: Building with Style
betterquesting.quest.bIOPajWVTbiG-QQsF2Gqig.name=§a§lBuilding with Style
betterquesting.quest.bIOPajWVTbiG-QQsF2Gqig.desc=Ztones is another mod which adds loads of new building blocks. Each craftable block also has many variants which can be made using a chisel.%n%n§cUnlike many other decorative blocks, Ztones blocks do not prevent mob spawns. Make sure you are spawnproofing your builds when using them!

# Quest: High-tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.blDDaS09R_qylY284dfxzg.name=§9§lHigh-tier Wand
betterquesting.quest.blDDaS09R_qylY284dfxzg.desc=Do you ever wish that you were able to place 16,000 blocks with the click of a button? No??..%n%nWell now you can!%n%n[note]It's unbreakable too![/note]

# Quest: Dark Steel Barrel
betterquesting.quest.dNDuychlSiqlrMhfnEKK_w.name=§6§lDark Steel Barrel
betterquesting.quest.dNDuychlSiqlrMhfnEKK_w.desc=The Dark Steel barrel holds 135 items! And is also immune to explosions.

# Quest: Copper Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.dbax1OsmRpWMg6Pt4tE_ig.name=§2§lCopper Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.dbax1OsmRpWMg6Pt4tE_ig.desc=The portable equivalent of the Copper Barrel.%n%nHas §n45§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: Crystal Chest
betterquesting.quest.e-VLKN-JSRK3V2cmDbm6rw.name=§b§lCrystal Chest
betterquesting.quest.e-VLKN-JSRK3V2cmDbm6rw.desc=You've created a chest that allows you to see what's inside, isn't that useful?%n%n[note]Just as with the previous chests you can also upgrade with a fitting upgrade item.[/note]

# Quest: Advanced Filing Cabinet
betterquesting.quest.lM99qle-Q_uPETUSrZQDKw.name=§2§lAdvanced Filing Cabinet
betterquesting.quest.lM99qle-Q_uPETUSrZQDKw.desc=The advanced filing cabinet can store twice as many items as the regular one, and is much less restrictive on what can be stored inside.

# Quest: Silver Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.nc1Pqje3RIe_Yp6WoPOFzg.name=§3§lSilver Shulker Box
betterquesting.quest.nc1Pqje3RIe_Yp6WoPOFzg.desc=The portable equivalent of the Silver Barrel.%n%nHas §n72§r slots.%n%n[note]Can be dyed![/note]

# Quest: Draconic Chest
betterquesting.quest.njQqj1iCTK-64uA4HfSdVw.name=§6§lDraconic Chest
betterquesting.quest.njQqj1iCTK-64uA4HfSdVw.desc=The Draconic Chest is a special upgrade of the compressed chest. In addition to a large inventory size and being able to retain its contents, it has a crafting station and a furnace integrated directly into it. %n%nThe smelting module can be powered by EU or RF and has an internal buffer of its own. It can smelt up to 5 items at a time.

# Quest: Concrete Backfiller
betterquesting.quest.uYT4jmFtQhOo5PoJLDyh-w.name=§6§lConcrete Backfiller
betterquesting.quest.uYT4jmFtQhOo5PoJLDyh-w.desc=Tired of all those mob noises coming from the depths? Consider making the §5Concrete Backfiller§r. This multiblock will fill the area underneath it with concrete in a §316§r block radius; patching all caves and air spots that might be lying underneath. %n%nSimply provide it with Light Concrete and let it do the rest!

# Quest: Chiseling the Way Greg Intended
betterquesting.quest.wRh-bN4UTemsx4Wskrrb6w.name=§2§lChiseling the Way Greg Intended
betterquesting.quest.wRh-bN4UTemsx4Wskrrb6w.desc=Another way to automatically chisel blocks to your heart's content, this time sponsored by GregoriousT himself!

# Quest: The Beginnings of a Humble Chest Monster
betterquesting.quest.zOwLuytjTFS18_K1we6TOw.name=§9§lThe Beginnings of a Humble Chest Monster
betterquesting.quest.zOwLuytjTFS18_K1we6TOw.desc=Did you really think a single chest would suffice for your storage needs? Come back when you've made at least a few.%n%n[note]You can place chests next to each other by chiseling every other chest into a trapped chest![/note]


## Quest Line: Forestry and Multifarms
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEg.name=Forestry and Multifarms
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEg.desc=Automated Farms, tree breeding, and more.....

# Quest: THE RAINMAKER
betterquesting.quest.3N-sNy89SWawxdvYsFWk5A.name=THE RAINMAKER
betterquesting.quest.3N-sNy89SWawxdvYsFWk5A.desc=The Rainmaker is a Forestry block capable of stopping/producing rain & creating thunderstorms.%n%nThe Rainmaker has no GUI, but can be right clicked with §a3§r different capsules:%n%n§cIodine Capsule:§r Produces Rain%n%n§cPhosphoric Iodine Capsule:§r Produces a Thunderstorm%n%n§cDissipation Charge:§r Stops Rain%n%nThe Rainmaker requires around ~30 seconds after activation for the §9rain§r and §9thunderstorm§r to start.%n%nThe dissipation charge will stop the rain after a few seconds until the next activation. 

# Quest: Forestry Core Block
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQQ.name=Forestry Core Block
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQQ.desc=This sturdy casing is the basis for almost all machines in Forestry, essentially being the Forestry equivalent of a machine casing.

# Quest: The Carpenter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQg.name=목수
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQg.desc=카펜터는 자동 제작대와 비슷합니다. 아이템 입력 슬롯과 조합법을 보관할 저장 슬롯이 있습니다. 일부 조합법은 물, 크레오소트, 꿀, 녹은 레드스톤과 같은 추가 유체가 필요합니다. 카펜터으로 농장 블록, 직조 배낭, 벌 및 나무 분석기 등을 만들 수 있습니다.%n%n카펜터는 작동에 전력이 필요합니다. GT 케이블이나 배터리 상자를 기계에 연결하거나, 포레스트리, 레일크래프트, 빌드크래프트의 RF 엔진을 사용할 수 있습니다.%n%n[note]추신: 맞아요, 자동화하기는 정말 골치 아픕니다. 만들고 싶은 것마다 하나씩 만드세요.[/note]

# Quest: Thermionic Fabricator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRA.name=Thermionic Fabricator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRA.desc=The thermionic fabricator is used to craft electron tubes and stained glass. It requires redstone flux (RF) energy to run.%n%nIt is your first machine made in the carpenter. Once warmed up, it needs to maintain a certain heat level to operate. The amount of power supplied will determine how much heat will be generated. If you do not supply enough power to maintain the current temperature it will slowly drop. It will continuously draw power, so disconnect it if you don't need it.

# Quest: A Series of Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRQ.name=A Series of Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRQ.desc=Before you can craft your first farm block you need apatite tubes. Make some apatite rods first with a lathe, then use a forge hammer to join them into long apatite rods. You need golden bolts and a red alloy plate.%n%nPut some glass or sand into your thermionic fabricator and make your first tubes.%n%n[note]You can also use the circuit assembler for a better output. Why did we have you make the TF again?[/note]

# Quest: The Multifarm
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRg.name=The Multifarm
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRg.desc=The smallest farm you can build requires 36 farm blocks (3x4x3 - the largest is 5x4x5 or 100 farm blocks). Place the underlying blocks corresponding to the farm type you built. In this case, Stone Bricks. You can place these blocks beside or under the multi structure, but not the layer above. It will search 6 blocks above these for dirt/farmland/sand/soul sand/humus depending on farm type, with the appropriate crops, saplings, etc. on top of that.%n%nYou can use different modes to collect different crops. Arboretum for trees, infernal for nether wart and so on. You can even mix and match modes on the same farm - cutting trees down for wood in part, and collecting fruit from trees without destroying it in another, for example. So long as they're on different sides, at least.%n%nYou may need to experiment a bit to see what works, but [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Multifarm[/url] has a decent list, though it doesn't specify cotton for managed crop farms for example. It might be a GTNH change, I dunno. A number of crops have an added CropsNH crop version as well, so you may prefer those for the higher yield if you level them up. Orchard mode works with Pam's, and Witchery, just to save you some time. Pam's nether crops however don't seem to work at all though.

# Quest: Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRw.name=Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACRw.desc=This chip allows you to select the farm type (when combined with the right electron tubes), and not use the default of growing trees. Unless that's what you want, in which case you don't need it.%n%nFor each circuit tier, you can configure 1/4 more of your farm.

# Quest: Changing Your Foresty Circuit Configuration
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACSA.name=Changing Your Foresty Circuit Configuration
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACSA.desc=The (forestry) soldering iron is a tool used for attaching electron tubes to circuit boards in order to manipulate how an electrical engine works or to program multifarms, as well as upgrading the squeezer or centrifuge. Honestly, you'll probably only use it for the multifarm though.%n%nOnce electron tubes have been attached to a circuit board they cannot be removed, only replaced. The circuit board is automatically crafted as soon as the basic recipe requirements are met, so it's best practice to first place your electron tubes and then add the circuit board.%n%nThe soldering iron can also be used to remove the circuit board from electrical engines, multifarms, squeezers and centrifuges by opening the machine's GUI and left-clicking with the soldering iron on the circuit board slot.

# Quest: Heating Coils
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACSQ.name=Heating Coils
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACSQ.desc=Your thermionic fabricator needs heating coils to function. So combine some magnetized (requires polarizer) steel rods with some copper wire and make some.%n%n[note]Why is this a separate quest again?[/note]

# Quest: Finding Apatite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTA.name=Finding Apatite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTA.desc=It's now time to search for some ores. Apatite is the most important material in Forestry. You can make fertilizer, farm blocks and other things with it. The vein is found between Y 40-60.

# Quest: Multifarm: Hatch
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTQ.name=Multifarm: Hatch
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTQ.desc=You can supply and extract items from the farm by using farm hatches that are connected to pipe systems.%n%nSupplying items%nThe farm hatch is clever enough to know which item goes where. If an item isn't appropriate for the farm's configuration, the hatch will simply reject it.%n%nExtracting items%nAny item that is harvested by the Multifarm is automatically ejected by the farm hatches into inventories or pipes. Pipes can be used to extract from other sides. You may need more than one, or a better conveyor if it isn't extracting fast enough for you.

# Quest: Multifarm: Valve
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTg.name=Multifarm: Valve
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTg.desc=Most farms require water for hydration purposes. Although you can do it manually by supplying it through liquid containers (such as cans), you can also automate the process by using farm valves.%n%nBy connecting fluid pipes into the farm valve and supplying water, you can automatically fill the farm's water tank.%n%nIf it hasn't rained for a while, the required water will go up, up to 1500%%. Use an Everfull Urn, or Reservoir (RIO) for serious water needs.

# Quest: Multifarm: Control
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTw.name=Multifarm: Control
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACTw.desc=You can control which fields of your farm work by applying a redstone signal to the control block. You can either shut down the whole farm by applying a redstone signal from top or below or you can disable a specific side by applying a redstone signal on the matching side of the control block.

# Quest: Multifarm: Gearbox
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUA.name=Multifarm: Gearbox
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUA.desc=To power your farm and have it automatically harvest crops, you will need at least one farm gearbox to supply power. You can use either RF or EU. If you use EU, make sure to use a cable to allow conversion. Farm operations can be hastened with additional gearboxes.%n%nTesting has shown that splitting the amps to 4 gearboxes (4A ULV) works better than sending 1A LV to 4 gearboxes.%n%nA max sized CropsNH Crop farm (5x4x5) using all space possible with max stat seeds (31/31/31) on a fast crop needs only 6A ULV to keep up.%n%nSimilarly, a max sized small farm (3x4x3) using all space possible with max stat seeds (31/31/31) on a high tier, moderate speed crop needs only 4A ULV.%n%nSending more power to the same gearbox doesn't work. If it can get to max RF capacity but your farm can't keep up, sending more power won't help, so add more gearboxes.%n%nIn addition, you lose 2 EU from the energy emitting device for every Amp of ULV (which is only 8 to begin with), so it's not nearly as efficient as using LV or higher. Just keep in mind that more A to more gearboxes is better than to the same one.%n%nOf course, if you mix your slower crops with your faster ones, you aren't likely to need to min-max to this extent.

# Quest: Enhanced Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUQ.name=Enhanced Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUQ.desc=This circuit allows you to configure 2/4 areas of your farm.

# Quest: Refined Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUg.name=Refined Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUg.desc=This circuit allows you to configure 3/4 areas of your farm.

# Quest: Intricate Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUw.name=Intricate Farm Logic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACUw.desc=This circuit allows you to configure 4/4 areas of your farm. Honestly, you should probably just skip the others.

# Quest: The Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD4g.name=The Centrifuge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD4g.desc=The Forestry Centrifuge is able to centrifuge up to 9 items out of bee combs. It uses RF energy.%n%nLatter bee combs need the GT one though, so keep that in mind.

# Quest: Clockwork Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEvg.name=시계장치 엔진
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEvg.desc=손으로 RF 전력을 생산하는 것은 Forestry 기계에서 한 두 가지 레시피를 만드는 데 좋은 방법입니다. 터렛도 이를 이용해 충전할 수 있습니다.

# Quest: Bio Gas Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEvw.name=Bio Gas Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEvw.desc=Producing RF power with lava is possible with the help of the biogas engine. You need water, fruit juice, liquid honey, milk, seed oil, or forestry biomass in the other slot. After a brief warmup time, the engine outputs up to 50 RF/t depending on the fluid used.%n%nThe possible fluids give the following power:%n%nWater: 10 RF/t for 1k ticks%nFruit juice: 10 RF/t for 2.5k ticks%nLiquid honey: 20 RF/t for 2.5k ticks%nMilk: 10 RF/t for 10k ticks%nSeed oil: 30 RF/t for 2.5k ticks%nBiomass: 50 RF/t for 2.5k ticks

# Quest: Peat Fired Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwA.name=Peat Fired Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwA.desc=Peat fired engines use Peat or Bituminous Peat to run. Peat burns for 5000 ticks and produces 10 RF every tick, 1 peat makes 0.66 Ash, so you get 2 Ash for burning 3 peat. Bituminous Peat burns for 6000 ticks and produces 20 RF/tick.%n%nPeat Farms can be set up by using a managed farm with tin electron tubes. It is possible with a manual farm too.

# Quest: Copper, Tin, Bronze Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwQ.name=Copper, Tin, Bronze Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwQ.desc=Electron tubes are used to set farms to a special kind of crop and can be used in engines, alvearies and some crafting recipes.%n%nUse a soldering iron to attach an electron tube to a circuit board.

# Quest: Iron, Golden, Diamantine Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwg.name=Iron, Golden, Diamantine Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEwg.desc=Electron tubes are used to set farms to a special kind of crop and can be used in engines, alvearies and some crafting recipes.%n%nUse a soldering iron to attach an electron tube to a circuit board.

# Quest: Rubberised, Obsidian, Lapis Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEww.name=Rubberised, Obsidian, Lapis Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEww.desc=Electron tubes are used to set farms to a special kind of crop and can be used in engines, alvearies and some crafting recipes.%n%nUse a soldering iron to attach an electron tube to a circuit board.

# Quest: Blazing, Ender, Emerald Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAExA.name=Blazing, Ender, Emerald Tubes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAExA.desc=Electron tubes are used to set farms to a special kind of crop and can be used in engines, alvearies and some crafting recipes.%n%nUse a soldering iron to attach an electron tube to a circuit board.

# Quest: Brazil Nut
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI0A.name=Brazil Nut
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI0A.desc=Brazil Nuts don't give you much in the way of important attributes. Breed them from Common Beech and Jungle.

# Quest: Coconut
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI0Q.name=Coconut
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI0Q.desc=Coconut is King for seed oil production - 300L per nut. Breed them from Brazil Nut and Balsa.%n%n§eCoconut and Seed Oil Get!

# Quest: Industrial Grafter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1w.name=Industrial Grafter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI1w.desc=If you're tired of constantly replacing branch cutters, this Industrial Grafter is rechargeable.%n%n[note]Or you could just make better ones.[/note]

# Quest: Another Path to Ethanol
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAw.name=에탄올로 가는 또 다른 길
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAw.desc=과잉 묘목이나 기타 쓰레기를 포함하여 발효기를 사용하면 포레스트리 바이오매스를 얻을 수 있습니다. 나무에 높은 현무애봉 트레이트가 있을수록 더 좋은 결과를 얻을 수 있습니다.

# Quest: Why No, This is Not Fit For Human Consumption
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBA.name=Why No, This is Not Fit For Human Consumption
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBA.desc=Taking the biomass from the Fermenter and using it in a still will give you Ethanol. Not really worth it for power, but useful if you want to turn it into ethylene. You could set it up on an old steam setup with nothing better to do to get a more useful power source out of it, or use the Ethanol to power the setup and the forestry farm.

# Quest: Better Fermenter Outputs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBw.name=Better Fermenter Outputs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBw.desc=With a Squeezer you can boost the output from your fermenter, saving on Fertilizer or Mulch and getting more per sapling. There's a variety of crops you can use to make fruit juice, so have fun breeding.

# Quest: Such Pretty Leaves...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIIw.name=Such Pretty Leaves...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIIw.desc=Now that you have entered MV you can begin breeding Forestry trees the smart way. Start by getting a Treealyzer, and scan the vanilla trees. They will transform into the forestry versions. You will need to gather honey or honeydew drops from bee combs to power the Treealyzer.%n%nIf you want to bulk scan saplings, you can feed them through a GT scanner filled with honey.%n%nYou can also try the Genetics mod to modify them. It's on the first bee tab.

# Quest: Collecting the Hybrids
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIJA.name=Collecting the Hybrids
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIJA.desc=If you got lucky and found some bees in a village, put them in their houses next to some trees. Over time the bees will slowly pollinate the leaves of the trees. Using a grafter you can break the leaf blocks to retrieve a sapling 100%%, useful for getting the forestry saplings. This doesn't seem to work with magical trees though. You can trade with villagers to get proven grafters that have a longer lifetime. Also investigate magic, you have heard rumors of long lasting grafters available to magicians.%n%nGregTech also offers a really nice tool, the Branch Cutter.

# Quest: Seeing the Fruits of Your Labor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIJQ.name=Seeing the Fruits of Your Labor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIJQ.desc=It can be difficult to see which leafy blocks are pollinated. Craft a pair of spectacles to get a better view.

# Quest: Orchard Apple
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAINQ.name=Orchard Apple
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAINQ.desc=The Orchard Apple tree has a couple of nice traits. The Faster maturity trait means it will turn from sapling to tree quickly. The Higher yield is the best yield from any Forestry tree. Breed the Orchard Apple from an Apple Oak and Hill Cherry.%n%nIf you want Fastest maturity for quick tree farms, you can breed Golden Raspberry. Try and figure out the breeding chain yourself.%n%nHigher Yield Get!

# Quest: Keeping Track of All Those Trees
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIOw.name=나비를 이해하기
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIOw.desc=이 장치는 당신이 발견한 모든 나무를 기록해줍니다.

# Quest: Better Grafter Through Technology
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAISQ.name=Better Grafter Through Technology
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAISQ.desc=The GT Branch Cutter is much better than the forestry grafters. It can have much higher durability based upon which material you use to create it.

# Quest: Speak For the Trees
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAISg.name=Speak For the Trees
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAISg.desc=You'll need to find a bunch of vanilla trees to start your breeding program. To convert them directly to Forestry trees, you can use a Treealyzer - but you'll need a carpenter and aluminium from MV for that. Alternatively, you can just grow a bunch of vanilla trees and surround them by good pollination bees in bee housing. Spectacles will help you see the fertilized leaves to harvest with your Grafter or Branch Cutter.%n%nCompleting the quests will require scanned trees, but you can progress on breeding while waiting for your GT Scanner or Treealyzer to be made.

# Quest: Silver Lime
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITA.name=Silver Lime
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITA.desc=Silver Lime, a basic tree breed. Breed it by mating Silver Birch with Apple Oak.%n%nNote: For all tree breeding quests, the required tree must be a pure species, not a hybrid, and must be scanned.

# Quest: Teak
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITQ.name=Teak
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITQ.desc=Teak is the first step to Giant Sequoia, a true giant. Breed it by mating Dark Oak and Jungle.%n%nNote: For all tree breeding quests, the required tree must be a pure species, not a hybrid, and must be scanned.

# Quest: Balsa
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITg.name=Balsa
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITg.desc=Balsa has some pretty wood. Breed it by mating Teak and Acacia.%n%n§eHigh Fertility Get!

# Quest: Common Beech
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITw.name=Common Beech
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAITw.desc=Common Beech gives you access to the Faster maturity attribute. Breed them from Silver Birch and Apple Oak.%n%nNote: For all tree breeding quests, the required tree must be a pure species, not a hybrid, and must be scanned.

# Quest: Hill Cherry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUA.name=Hill Cherry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUA.desc=Hill Cherry is a key tree for breeding purposes. Breed it by mating Silver Lime with Apple Oak or Silver Birch.

# Quest: Mundane Larch
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUQ.name=Mundane Larch
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUQ.desc=You can breed a Mundane Larch by combining Red Spruce and Silver Birch or Apple Oak. You also need to do these to get Sequoias.%n%nNote: For all tree breeding quests, the required tree must be a pure species, not a hybrid, and must be scanned.

# Quest: Bull Pine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUg.name=Bull Pine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUg.desc=You can breed a Bull Pine by combining Red Spruce and Mundane Larch.

# Quest: Lemon
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUw.name=Lemon
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIUw.desc=Lemon trees are great for maximum fruit juice production. Breed it by mating Hill Cherry with Silver Lime.

# Quest: Plum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVA.name=Plum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVA.desc=The Plum is a great multipurpose tree. It has High yield and its fruit produces mulch with the highest chance. It also has decent sappiness for biomass production. Breed it by mating Hill Cherry with Lemon.%n%n§dPlum and Mulch Get!

# Quest: Desert Acacia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVQ.name=Desert Acacia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVQ.desc=Desert Acacia. Another step on the road. Breed it by mating Teak with Balsa.

# Quest: Cocobolo
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVg.name=Cocobolo
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVg.desc=The Cocobolo is a nice tall tree, perfect for mating into your other trees to maximize their yield. Breed it by mating Desert Acacia with Dark Oak.

# Quest: Blue Mahoe
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVw.name=Blue Mahoe
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIVw.desc=The Blue Mahoe has the most sappiness of any tree. It will vastly increase the efficiency of your biomass production with Fermenters. Breed it by mating Balsa with Desert Acacia.%n%n§6High Sappiness Get!

# Quest: U-238 Tu-Wait, Seriously?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK0w.name=U-238 Tu-Wait, Seriously?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK0w.desc=If you want CropsNH crops to work with the multifarm, you now need this. Get the U-238 from thorium, and the endereyes from either your crops, villagers, or the normal way in HV. It also only searches 6 blocks above the farm structure block to prevent lag. So goodbye MF stacking, you always looked dumb, and didn't make any sense.%n%nThe largest size supports ~1100 crops, while the smallest supports ~600 depending on your layout if you use it for crops. This is because it will look for crops up to 5 blocks out further than normal in this mode (In the cardinal directions, it's further out in the corners. Just try it out, it's hard to describe). They're the same size as in previous versions, so you don't need to rejigger them.

# Quest: Papaya
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKIA.name=Papaya
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKIA.desc=The Papaya tree produces Papayas, which produce the most Fruit Juice. Sluuuurp!%n%n§aPapaya and Fruit Juice Get!

# Quest: Combustion Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKw.name=Combustion Engine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKw.desc=The combustion engine combusts things for power like a car engine does. You need water in it if it's over 100 degrees, or it will explode. Don't run out of water! You turn it on with a redstone signal.%n%nYour options for fuel are:%nOil @30RF/t for a total of 150K%nEthanol @40RF/t for a total of 360K%nDiesel @60RF/t for a total of 1,500K%n%n[note]Make sure to use Oil, not raw, light, medium, or heavy oil.[/note]

# Quest: Kinesis Pipes
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLA.name=키네시스 파이프
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLA.desc=1 블록 이상의 RF 전력을 전송하려면, 키네시스 파이프가 필요할 것입니다. 파이프 네트워크에 연결하려면 우선 나무 파이프를 사용하고, 그 다음에는 다른 타입의 파이프를 사용하여 전송합니다. 그런데, 이들은 다소 손실이 발생하는 것으로 보여져, 비록 더 비싸더라도 컨듀잇이 더 나을 수 있습니다. 또한, 어차피 RF를 저장하기 위해서는 캐패시터가 필요합니다.

# Quest: Coast Sequoia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLg.name=Coast Sequoia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLg.desc=You can breed a Coast Sequoia by combining Mundane Larch and Bull Pine.%n%n[warn]Fireproof Wood Get! If you care.[/warn]

# Quest: Wenge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLw.name=Wenge
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALLw.desc=You can get Wenge by combining Balsa and Cocobolo.

# Quest: Grandidier's Baobab
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMA.name=Grandidier's Baobab
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMA.desc=You can get Grandidier's Baobab by combining Wenge and Balsa.%n%n§eAbility to grow trees on sand, Get! Like you care.

# Quest: Giant Sequoia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMQ.name=Giant Sequoia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMQ.desc=You can get Giant Sequoia by combining Coast Sequoia and Grandidier's Baobab.%n%n§dBoth Height and §bGirth, Get!§r%n%n[note]PS: If this doesn't work (NEI says yes, internet says no) you should also be able to trade a forestry villager for it.[/note]

# Quest: Common Alder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMg.name=Common Alder
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMg.desc=You can breed a Common Alder by combining Silver Birch and Common Beech.

# Quest: Aspen
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMw.name=Aspen
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALMw.desc=You can breed an Aspen by combining Common Alder and Common Beech.

# Quest: Elderberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNA.name=Elderberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNA.desc=You can breed an Elderberry by combining Common Alder and Aspen.

# Quest: Raspberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNQ.name=Raspberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNQ.desc=You can breed Raspberry by combining Hill Cherry and Elderberry.

# Quest: Pomelo
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNg.name=Pomelo
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNg.desc=You can breed a Pomelo by combining Hill Cherry and Lemon.

# Quest: Manderine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNw.name=Manderine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALNw.desc=You can get Manderine by combining Pomelo and Hill Cherry.

# Quest: Orange
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALOA.name=Orange
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALOA.desc=You can get Orange by combining Pomelo and Manderine.

# Quest: Golden Raspberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALOQ.name=Golden Raspberry
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALOQ.desc=You can get Golden Raspberry by combining Raspberry and Orange.%n%n[warn]Fastest Maturity Get![/warn]%n%n[note]That probably took forever, huh? BTW, it probably would've been faster to make more multifarms or farming stations instead.[/note]%n%n[note]Also, you still gotta create the ultimate hybrid, too.[/note]

# Quest: Forestry Core Block #2
betterquesting.quest.X54R4jrtQu2rI9j4eHC7lw.name=Forestry Core Block #2
betterquesting.quest.X54R4jrtQu2rI9j4eHC7lw.desc=The upgraded casing for Forestry, used in multiple recipes for endgame Gendustry items and the Rainmaker. 


## Quest Line: Multiblock Goals
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADA.name=Multiblock Goals
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADA.desc=This set is a global tracker for multiblock structure goals. As you can build several parts of many multiblocks way earlier than the respective tier. Check back often.

# Quest: Distill the Atmosphere
betterquesting.quest.7p2Sqx7dR8mfVCNUYEUIuQ.name=§6§lDistill the Atmosphere
betterquesting.quest.7p2Sqx7dR8mfVCNUYEUIuQ.desc=Using the Vacuum Freezer you can create Liquid Air. Liquid Air can be centrifuged into additional gases you won't get when centrifuging normal compressed air. If you can gather enough Liquid Air you can instead distill it into a larger quantity and variety of rare gases.%n%nMake these special hatches to hold and store the amounts required for this recipe.

# Quest: Collision Course
betterquesting.quest.9Pc7p99ASnybsIbWmmg0LQ.name=§6§lCollision Course
betterquesting.quest.9Pc7p99ASnybsIbWmmg0LQ.desc=Finally, to actually get some ICs, use your photons in a Target Chamber.%n%nNote that the EU/t value listed in TC recipes is only a minimum, as recipe time is entirely determined by the Amount of photons you give the multi.%n%nMore specifically, you can get the recipe time by dividing recipe Amount by your input beam Amount, then multiplying that by 5s.

# Quest: Multiblock Tanks... Railcraft Tanks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALQ.name=§6§lMultiblock Tanks... Railcraft Tanks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALQ.desc=576 buckets of fluid, that should be enough to store all the creosote you have accumulated thus far. If that isn't enough you can make this tank bigger. The smallest tanks are 3x4x3 while the biggest are 9x8x9.%n%nFluid will auto-output without any pumps if you place a valve on its bottom side at the center. The output rate is 1000 L/t so twice as fast as a GT HV Pump Cover. You can color the tank with Buildcraft paintbrushes and the GT spray can.%n%nIf you still use Railcraft tanks in later tiers, you boost the output rate by using pumps.

# Quest: You Are Now Prepared, Hopefully!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASg.name=§6§lYou Are Now Prepared, Hopefully!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASg.desc=No matter where you got this smeltery from, you have one now. Time for some casting!%n%nNote: The book says to make a 3x3 base, but you can make a smeltery with a smaller or wider base. Taller/wider smelteries can do more items at one time, conserving fuel.%n%n[note]The smeltery does not double ores in GTNH. Later machines will help you there.[/note]

# Quest: The Water Dilemma
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASw.name=§6§lThe Water Dilemma
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAASw.desc=Finite water is a problem. But fear not, there are solutions! I shall guide you to a steady supply of water. The Railcraft water siding tanks provides enough water to last the early game.%n%nThe humidity of a biome is very important and will increase the base fill rate. If it is raining, the tank will fill much quicker. One block of the water siding tank must see sky for the maximum output. The best part is that you don't need a pump to extract water. Tanks and pipes placed next to it will be autofilled by the water siding tank.

# Quest: Time to Get Some Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATA.name=§6§lTime to Get Some Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATA.desc=You need steel? Uhh... fine. Let's get busy...%n%nThe Bricked Blast Furnace (BBF) can share walls with other ones, just like most GT multiblocks. How will this affect the air quality though...%n%nIf you are short on Stone Dust, you can get more by macerating cobblestone.%n%nIf you spawn near a biome with Hardened Clay you can macerate it to get the clay dust you need. You can also use brick blocks from Villages to get brick dust in the macerator.%n%nCrafting the Worktable from Forestry can make it easier as you can use all the buckets for crafting in one click.

# Quest: More Heat - Kanthal Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATg.name=§6§lMore Heat - Kanthal Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATg.desc=Better materials need higher temperatures. You can just exchange the old coils with the new ones. Kanthal coils let you reach 2700K. You can even reuse the old coils in your Pyro or to make other machines, how fancy is that! If you don't have any other place to use them, you can macerate or arc furnace them too.%n%nIf you don't have a Vacuum Freezer yet, then cool the hot ingots in an MV Chemical Bath with Coolant.%n%nRemember that you can get an upgraded OC (4/4) instead of a regular OC (2/4) if your coils are 1800K above the recipe temperature, as well as an EU discount. In this notation, the first number is speed and the second is power. This applies to every 900K or 1800K above, so you should try to upgrade your coils as soon as you can.

# Quest: Nichrome Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATw.name=§6§lNichrome Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAATw.desc=To reach 3600K so you can process higher tier materials like tungsten, you need nichrome heating coils.

# Quest: Compress All the Things
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUA.name=§6§lCompress All the Things
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUA.desc=Martin's (DreamMasterXXL) favorite machine. Compress ALL the things! With explosives, of course. Boom today!%n%nNote: You might want to put this far from your living quarters, the pollution can get high really fast.

# Quest: At the End of...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUQ.name=§6§lAt the End of...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUQ.desc=...the universe everything freezes eventually. But waiting for the heat death of the universe might take too long. Therefore, we present you the vacuum freezer. It should be good enough to cool your hot stuff.%n%nIngots that go through the EBF above a certain temperature will come out as hot ingots that need to be cooled.%n%nYou will need a minimum of 16 frost proof machine casings, the rest depends on your setup.

# Quest: An Unexpected Bonus
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUg.name=§6§lAn Unexpected Bonus
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUg.desc=Because we're nice developers, we decided to add a little bonus if you happen to compress charcoal. Use it in the bricked blast furnace, or in a boiler, it yields 10 times the burn time of a piece of charcoal. So one charcoal for free. This bonus only occurs on the first compression step. (But for fanciness, you should definitely get a quintuple one!)%n%n[note]Of course they're kinda useless unless you're using BBFs or boilers, though you can use them to make industrial diamonds.[/note]

# Quest: High-Speed Charcoal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUw.name=§6§lHigh-Speed Charcoal
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAUw.desc=Sure, those coke ovens are nice, but they aren't even remotely fast enough to keep up with a large steam boiler. Luckily, there is an upgrade available! The creosote oil will not be produced, but the process will speed up dramatically. Who needs that nasty yellowish flammable stuff anyway...

# Quest: TPV Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVg.name=§6§lTPV Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVg.desc=To process more advanced materials like Tungstensteel, Enderium and Niobium-Titanium, you will need more than 3600K. Time to upgrade your EBF... again.

# Quest: Steel Multiblock Tanks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVw.name=§6§lSteel Multiblock Tanks
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVw.desc=Do you want to have tanks that can hold double the amount of the iron ones? Go ahead and make a steel tank. Everything else is the same.

# Quest: HSS-G Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB2w.name=§6§lHSS-G Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB2w.desc=To process more advanced materials like HSS-E, HSS-S and naquadah you need more than 4500K. Time to upgrade your EBF to 5400K.

# Quest: Naquadah Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB3A.name=§6§lNaquadah Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB3A.desc=To process more advanced materials like naquadah alloy you need more than 6300K. Upgrade your EBF to 7200K to increase the heat.

# Quest: Naquadah Alloy Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB3Q.name=§6§lNaquadah Alloy Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB3Q.desc=This one is optional now. But still very useful and recommended.

# Quest: An Industrial Mobfarm
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABdQ.name=§6§lAn Industrial Mobfarm
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABdQ.desc=§6§lExtreme Entity Crusher§r is your newest and probably §lbest§r spawner/grinder, with this you are not only able to get drops without any §lTPS§r issues but also with style and §lextreme§r efficiency.%n%nOf course that depends on the quality of your sword; damage, looting, and durability are the only stats that will translate towards the efficacy of the machine. §3(weapon is optional however, there are spikes in it after all!)§r%n%nWill occasionally spawn infernal mobs if possible and will use §2§lx8§r power with every infernal spawn so you need to take that into account!%n%nIf you are actively using the Blood Magic "§c§lWell of Suffering§r" ritual to power your altar, this multi may be used in combination with it to 'generate' and 'kill' mobs automatically for life essence, so you don't need a setup involving an actual spawner!%n%n§lNotes:§r%nWill generate §2§l120L§r of liquid XP with every cycle.%nIn case of any problems with multiblock animation just use §5soldering iron§r on the machine to disable it.%nRead the tooltip! There are a few unique quality of life settings that you may find of use.%n%n[warn]Enchanting the spikes in the structure does nothing to affect the machine.[/warn]

# Quest: Powderbarrels
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-Q.name=§6§lPowderbarrels
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-Q.desc=Powderbarrels are pretty bad in the implosion compressor. They are good for prospecting though. Craft one stack.

# Quest: TNT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-g.name=§6§lTNT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-g.desc=TNT is much more powerful than the powderbarrel but much harder to craft. There are LV and HV ways to craft. At LV you need heavy or light fuel to make some toluene which can be solidified to gelled toluene. Alternatively you can use sugar and plastic dust in a chemical reactor to make toluene more efficiently. Mix it with sulfuric acid to make TNT.%n%nThe HV petrol way requires an oil cracking unit to make all kinds of cracked fuel or cracked naphtha and a distillation tower to extract toluene from that.%nThough you can also go the wood tar route in mid-MV.

# Quest: iTNT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-w.name=§6§liTNT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC-w.desc=Industrial TNT is the HV variant of TNT. It explodes with more power, and you can't pick it up. Not by hand anyway

# Quest: Better Than Duct Tape
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC8w.name=§6§lBetter Than Duct Tape
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC8w.desc=Using a soldering iron tool to remove the "burned out circuits" message is cheaper than duct tape.%n%nThe soldering iron requires one soldering material item and 10,000 EU. Valid soldering materials are fine wires, rods, and ingots made from either tin, lead, or soldering alloy. The soldering iron will consume the first such material it finds in the player's inventory. Since you'll likely have more than enough, Fine Wires of Soldering Alloy are probably best.%n%nOther uses for the soldering iron:%n%n- It will adjust the redstone strength from weak to strong emitted by GT machines.%n- While holding it all pipes, wires, and cables will look very small, so that you can see everything past them, and also be sure of the exact connections.%n- Shift right-clicking on some machines with it will allow you to toggle multi-stack input, which can be very useful for automating certain assembler recipes.%n%nIn order to "complete" this quest you'll need to charge the soldering iron after you craft it.%n%nFor the other problems other tools are necessary. Keep in mind that you can put all needed tools in a toolbox to fix all problems in one click.%n%nPossible problems                Tool to fix%n"Pipe is loose."                    Wrench%n"Screws are loose."           Screwdriver%n"Something is stuck."            Soft Mallet%n"Platings are dented."           Hammer%n"Circuitry burned out."    Soldering Iron%n"That doesn't belong there."   Crowbar

# Quest: Less Power Loss
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC9A.name=§6§lLess Power Loss
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC9A.desc=When you reach MV tier you can make your own duct tape in case you have to move your multiblock machines around. Duct tape will fix all maintenance problems in any multiblock machine.

# Quest: Glyceryl Trini...... What?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACLA.name=§6§lGlyceryl Trini...... What?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACLA.desc=Kids, today we will make some glyceryl trinitrate (aka Nitroglycerin) with some glycerol.%n    - Chemistry 101

# Quest: Low-Pressure Boiler Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACLw.name=§6§lLow-Pressure Boiler Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACLw.desc=The low pressure boiler tank is the easiest way to make steam with an RC boiler. The firebox needs this tank on top to produce steam. The bigger the boiler the slower it heats up, but it will produce more steam when heated up.%n%nExtract steam by attaching a pipe to the boiler tank.%n%n[note]This variant is very useful for inconsistent operation. It has lower efficiency but heats up significantly faster than the high pressure variant meaning the fuel will be used more efficiently at the beginning of the operation, the drawback is that this variant is 50%% as efficient as the high pressure one is at max temperature. If instead you want to have a constant high-throughput steam generation use high pressure variant instead.[/note]%n%n[warn]Actual fuel usage depends on the machine size and other factors such as machine temperature, if you want to know the actual number you will need to test it on your own setup.[/warn]

# Quest: Railcraft Steam Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMA.name=§6§lRailcraft Steam Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMA.desc=As an alternative way to make steam you can use the railcraft boilers. They require at least one firebox.%n%nMore than one size is possible: (1x1 which the quest gets you to make) 2x2 and 3x3.%n%nProvide water and coal to the firebox. Make sure you don't run out of water or...BOOM.%n%nEach boiler needs 1, 2 or 3 layers of tanks on top, equal to the size (1x1x1, 2x2x2, or 3x3x3) - see the quests linked below.

# Quest: Liquid-Fuelled Firebox
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMQ.name=§6§lLiquid-Fuelled Firebox
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMQ.desc=Creosote oil into steam! After you make your first steel you are able to craft a liquid fueled firebox.%n%nDiesel, ethanol, creosote and Biodiesel all work well here. This will also require a boiler tank - see the quests linked below.

# Quest: High-Pressure Boiler Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMg.name=§6§lHigh-Pressure Boiler Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACMg.desc=After you make steel you are able to craft a high pressure boiler tank. The upgraded version increases the temperature and produces more steam than the low pressure version. It will take longer to warm up, so make sure to keep it well fed!%n%nExtract steam by attaching a pipe to the boiler tank.%n%n[note]This is better than the low pressure variant only if you keep it working for very long time, if you intend to turn it on and off all the time this will waste a lot of resources! If you keep it at top temperature it will use ~2x more fuel than low pressure and will give ~4x more steam per sec making it 100%% more efficient! If you can't sustain the fuel drain or want a more flexible power source instead use the low pressure variant.[/note]%n%n[warn]Actual fuel usage depends on the machine size and other factors such as machine temperature, if you want to know the actual number you will need to test it on your own setup.[/warn]

# Quest: Dynamite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_A.name=§6§lDynamite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_A.desc=Dynamite is the most basic explosive you can use in the implosion compressor.%nMix some paper, string and glyceryl trinitrate in a chemical reactor to get dynamite.

# Quest: Time to Drill for Oil!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_Q.name=§6§lTime to Drill for Oil!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_Q.desc=Pumps are nice but you're going to reach a point where you'll want MOOOOOOOOOOOOORE oil. This multiblock will help with that but you'll need to search for oil using a seismic prospector. You can find raw, light, medium, and heavy oil. There's also a chance to find natural gas.%n%nHigher tiers of power will drill faster. You need to upgrade the energy hatch corresponding to the power tier.%n%nLater you can upgrade the oil drilling rig so it extracts from more than one chunk at a time.%n%nYou need mining pipes in the controller. If you need more than 64, you can use an input bus.%n%nThese are GT machines, so remember to protect them (and their power sources!) from rain on any side. And set a waypoint with JourneyMaps so you don't forget where you placed it!%n%nSpace dims can also have fluids beneath bedrock. For info, check the Tips and Tricks tab.

# Quest: Let's Get Crackin!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_g.name=§6§lLet's Get Crackin!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAC_g.desc=Cracking oil products like light and heavy fuel with the oil cracker is faster and more efficient than using a chemical reactor, producing 25 to 50 percent more output, depending on which cracking method it's doing (steam does 50%%, hydro does 25%% but consumes 20%% less hydrogen). Cracked products will result in additional by-products in the distillation tower. It is a smart idea to get this multiblock since you are going to need TONS of industrial TNT from Toluene for advanced tier rockets.%n%nThe 16 coils form 2 vertical rings of 8 on either side of the controller. The casings between the rings can be replaced with a hatch for steam/hydrogen input. Energy hatch and maintenance hatch can replace any of the casings. The input product hatch and output product hatch must replace one of the casings outside of the coils.%n%nHint: Only GT/Railcraft steam can be used, not ic2 steam. You can use a fluid heater to make it instead of a boiler.%n%n[note]The circuit goes in the controller.[/note]%n%n[note]PS: I listed all the cracker recipes on the spreadsheet for you to look at in a convenient format. Now you can easily compare which oil path to take![/note]

# Quest: Automation, Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACtw.name=§6§lAutomation, Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACtw.desc=Do you want to automate your smeltery because you're planning to make stacks and stacks of glass blocks?%n%nNo problem, craft a large bronze pipe and place it under the faucet. Make sure to connect the pipe to the faucet using a wrench. Now the molten fluid will flow inside the pipe. Under or next to the pipe you have to place the casting basins or tables.%n%nA hopper and a chest underneath will auto-output products from the casting blocks.%n%nNOTE: Faucets will output precisely 144L each activation if you toggle it off immediately. That's going to have some uses later on...

# Quest: Automation, Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuA.name=§6§lAutomation, Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuA.desc=You want a better automation than using pipes? Sure, craft a comparator and link it with redstone dust placed on the ground. The redstone needs to be adjacent to the faucet to activate the crafting process.

# Quest: 2x Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuQ.name=§6§l2x Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuQ.desc=Steel production is so slow. If you got enough bricks and clay, build a second BBF. Build it attached to the first one, so they can share a wall and you will save some bricks, clay and concrete.%n%n[warn]Note that this will generate twice as much pollution in total - consider moving them further away.[/warn]

# Quest: 4x Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACug.name=§6§l4x Steel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACug.desc=Not even two BBFs are fast enough...Can you figure out how to save the most bricks making 4?%n%n[note]PS: If you can't, this pack may not be for you.[/note]%n%n[warn]Note that this will generate massive amounts of pollution - have you considered the Nether?[/warn]

# Quest: Why One Coke Oven When You Can Have Ten?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuw.name=§6§lWhy One Coke Oven When You Can Have Ten?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACuw.desc=벽돌 제련로(Bricked Blast Furnace)가 엄청난 양의 석탄을 소모하고, 증기 보일러도 마찬가지인가요? 이제 코크스 오븐을 더 많이 만들고 약간 자동화할 때입니다. 코크스 오븐 해치(Coke Oven Hatch), 나무 유체 파이프(Wooden Fluid Pipes), 그리고 주석 아이템 파이프(Tin Item Pipes)가 목표 달성에 도움을 줄 것입니다.%n%n이것은 GT 멀티블록이므로 벽돌과 해치를 벽면 공유(wallshare)할 수 있습니다. 이 퀘스트에 필요한 벽돌 수는 10개의 벽면 공유 코크스 오븐을 만드는 데 필요한 최소량입니다.%n%n주석 아이템 파이프는 분해할 때 강철 렌치(steel wrench)가 필요하다는 것을 기억하세요.%n%n[note]코크스 오븐 벽돌을 더 효율적으로 만드는 방법을 NEI에서 검색해 보세요.[/note]%n%n[warn]코크스 오븐 공정 전체에서 많은 오염이 발생하므로, 더 먼 곳에 배치하는 것을 고려하세요.[/warn]

# Quest: Still Not Enough Charcoal?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADDQ.name=§6§lStill Not Enough Charcoal?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADDQ.desc=This oven is the best way to get charcoal and creosote (x50 faster than the Coke Oven) and other byproducts. You will need tons of bronze, iron and steel to build it, but it's worth it. Finally, it will be possible to dismantle the charcoal pit.%n%nWith Cupronickel coils the oven is a bit slower. Each coil tier speeds up the charcoal production.

# Quest: It's Time to Get More Steam
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEA.name=§6§lIt's Time to Get More Steam
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEA.desc=As soon as you have the ability to store energy in large quantities, it would be necessary to have a way to generate energy in large quantities. You need a large bronze boiler. But in order to make this boiler, you will need a mountain of bronze. This boiler produces 800L of steam per tick. This is enough to run 10 basic steam turbines.%n%nThe large boiler can use either water or distilled water. Water is consumed at a rate of 1L of water per 160L of steam.%n%nTo make a large boiler you must make a 3x3x5 structure with Bronze Pipe Casings in the center of the middle 3 levels. The lowest level must contain at least 1 or 2 input hatches, 1 or 2 input buses, 3 or 4 fireboxes, 1 muffler, and one maintenance hatch. The lowest level can not contain any plated bricks. All hatches, buses, and mufflers must have their back side touching a firebox. The output hatch can be placed on any of the upper 4 levels.%n%n§cWarning: Different from other boilers, Large Boilers must contain water at all times while active. If at any point the Boiler runs out of water while it is active, it will explode.

# Quest: Steam is Never Enough
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEg.name=§6§l스팀은 결코 충분하지 않습니다
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEg.desc=이제 고급 회로를 제작할 수 있게 되었으므로, 대형 강철 보일러를 설치할 시간입니다. 각각의 보일러는 1000 EU/t의 증기를 생산하는데, 이를 모두 전력으로 변환하려면 여러 개의 증기 터빈이 필요하게 될 것입니다! MV 터빈은 효율성이 떨어지는 점을 명심하고, 당신의 설치 계획을 짤 때 손실을 계산하세요.

# Quest: Moooooore Steam
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEw.name=§6§lMoooooore Steam
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADEw.desc=The Titanium Large Boiler is a distant cousin to the Bronze and Steel Boilers, and it has a significant difference. Instead of accepting just about any burnable fuel, it will only accept specific ones and reject all others. You can see which ones are accepted by looking at the appropriate NEI tab, but the Solid Super Fuels are guaranteed to work.%n%nThis is a big downside, but the upside is that these boilers output respectable power even in these tiers. Without any other inputs, this boiler produces Superheated Steam at a flow rate matching 4000 EU/t, on turbines running at 100%% fuel efficiency. If this becomes 150%%, then the steam output will produce 6000 EU/t, almost the same as a boosted Large Combustion Engine!%n%nTo get all the power from this, though, you will need an HP Steam Turbine, followed by a regular Steam Turbine, or more than one of each if the flow rate is too big for the turbine material you've chosen. Make sure to send the Distilled Water back to the boilers!

# Quest: Even More Steam? Are You Sure?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADFA.name=§6§lEven More Steam? Are You Sure?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADFA.desc=The Large Tungstensteel Boiler is the biggest and baddest of the four. Like the Titanium one, it is a specialized boiler that only accepts specific fuels, mainly the Solid Super Fuels, but it will produce Superheated Steam at a rate equivalent to 16000 EU/t, at 100%% fuel efficiency. If you have good Steam Turbines, especially Oriharukon ones, you will get much more power than that, around 24000 EU/t or more.%n%nDepending on how many of these you build, you might need a huge amount of turbines. To solve that problem, consider going a bit above the optimal flow on each turbine, or even switching to Loose mode, although this is only a good choice if you can match the optimal flow in that mode.

# Quest: Cleanroom
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADrA.name=§6§lCleanroom
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADrA.desc=더 발전된 (그리고 더 저렴한!) 회로를 만들고 싶다면, 클린룸(Cleanroom)이 필요합니다. 클린룸은 흥미로운 멀티블록입니다. 방 §o내부§r에 다른 기계들을 배치하게 되기 때문입니다!%n%n클린룸은 3x4x3에서 15x15x15(가로x높이x세로) 블록 크기의 빈 멀티블록 구조입니다. 바닥은 정사각형일 필요 없으며, 직사각형 모양도 괜찮습니다. 최상층은 모서리를 제외하고 필터 기계 케이싱(Filter Machine Casing)으로 구성되며, 모서리는 플라스크리트 블록(Plascrete Block)으로 만듭니다. 컨트롤러는 최상층 중앙에 위치해야 합니다. 방의 가로 또는 세로 길이가 짝수인 경우, 중간에 있는 두 개(또는 네 개)의 블록 중 하나가 될 수 있습니다. 나머지 구조는 플라스크리트 블록으로 구성됩니다.%n%n이 플라스크리트 블록 중 최대 30%%는 다른 유효한 블록이나 재료로 대체할 수 있습니다:%n%n강화문(Reinforced Door)을 사용하면 클린룸에 출입할 수 있습니다. 문은 반드시 닫아 두어야 하며, 그렇지 않으면 클린룸의 효율이 급격히 떨어집니다. 이동 닻(Travel Anchor)이나 엘리베이터도 사용할 수 있으며, 원한다면 바닥에 매립할 수도 있습니다. 이네퍼블 글래스(Ineffable Glass)를 "문" 대신 사용할 수도 있습니다.%n%n벽을 통해 전력과 아이템 운송을 자동화하려면 케이블 다이오드(Cable Diode)나 기계 외피(Machine Hull)를 사용할 수 있습니다. 기계를 더 높은 전압으로 업그레이드할 때는 매우 주의하세요. 기계 외피와 다이오드를 제거하고 새 전력 등급으로 교체해야 하며, 그렇지 않으면 큰 문제가 발생할 수 있습니다. 아이템만 통과시키는 용도로 사용하는 경우에는 이 작업을 할 필요가 없습니다.%n%n내부를 보고 싶다면, EV+ 등급의 유리(예: 강화 유리(Reinforced Glass), 마나글래스(Managlass), 이네퍼블 글래스)를 사용할 수 있습니다. 클린룸이 구성되지 않는다면, 30%% 제한을 염두에 두세요. 종종 유리를 너무 많이 추가한 것이 문제입니다.%n%n마지막으로, 클린룸 자체를 가동하려면 유지보수 해치와 에너지 해치가 필요합니다. 이 멀티블록의 전력 소모는 다소 특이합니다. 40 EU/t로 시작하여 점차 감소합니다. 하지만 40 EU/t(보통 MV 수준)를 사용할 때도 LV 에너지 해치 하나로 충분합니다. LV 전력 2암페어를 받아들이기 때문입니다. 이는 클린룸이 예외적인 경우라는 점을 명심하세요.%n%n일단 5x5x5 방을 만들어 봅시다. 나중에 필요에 따라 확장할 수 있습니다. 전력을 공급하고 효율이 100%%에 도달할 때까지 가동하세요. 100%% 미만의 효율에서는 클린룸 내부 기계가 산출물을 버릴 확률이 있으므로, 항상 클린룸을 가동 상태로 유지해야 합니다!%n%n유지보수 문제가 발생하면 최대 효율이 10%%씩 감소합니다. 휴대용 스캐너(Hand Scanner), 산업 정보 패널(Industrial Information Panel), 또는 유지보수 필요 커버(Needs Maintenance Cover)와 레드스톤 조명등(Redstone Powered Light) 또는 경보기(Howler Alarm)를 사용하여 클린룸을 모니터링하세요.%n%n[note]대형 화학 반응기(Large Chemical Reactor)나 초고강도 레이저 각인기(Hyper-Intensity Laser Engraver)와 같은 멀티블록은 클린룸에 있을 필요가 없습니다. 하지만 바이오 연구실(Bio Lab)과 같은 다른 기계를 위해 나중에 클린룸이 여전히 필요할 것입니다.[/note]%n%n[note]기타 유용한 팁: 아이템 운송을 위해 기계 외피를 피하고 AE 무선 연결기(Wireless Connector)나 초공간 인터페이스(Transvector Interface)를 사용할 수 있으며, 더 높은 등급의 에너지 해치를 사용하여 100%% 효율에 더 빨리 도달할 수 있습니다.[/note]%n%n[warn]클린룸 내부에서는 오염을 유발하는 어떤 것도 사용할 수 없다는 점을 명심하세요. 그렇지 않으면 클린룸이 작동을 멈춥니다.[/warn]

# Quest: A Very Useful Scanner
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADrQ.name=§6§lA Very Useful Scanner
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADrQ.desc=The portable scanner is a tool capable of showing advanced information about almost every block in the game. In order to function, the tool needs to be charged first. It can hold up to 400k EU and accept 128 EU/t or less. This is MV tier.%n%nIt can scan crops by right-clicking it to fully scan it, unlike a cropnalyzer which needs a seed bag in your inventory, and takes multiple goes. Crops that were scanned in the world will drop a scanned seed bag.%n%nIt can scan machines from GregTech, giving information about current progress, the stored energy, efficiency, problems and CPU-load - be sure to check the full chat window for additional details.%n%nFor any block in the game it scans, it gives information about its ID, Metadata, position in the world and hardness value. It also gives information about pollution level in the chunk the scanned block belongs to.%n%nIn addition it shows when the cleanroom has reached its 100 percent efficiency level.

# Quest: The 'Water Problems' Are Solved
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADug.name=§6§lThe 'Water Problems' Are Solved
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADug.desc=After entering the HV age you've found a way of making a water reservoir which solves the finite water problem. Craft it with some fused quartz glass, HV pumps, and cauldrons.

# Quest: EBF Info
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEmw.name=§6§lEBF Info
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEmw.desc=You can use a scanner to manually check how your EBF works, or you can make an information panel from nuclear control and always see the status. Make a GT sensor kit and use it on the EBF controller. Place the sensor card in your info panel. Enable it with a redstone signal.%n%nThe GregTech sensor card can monitor GregTech machines like the EBF, Turbines, and Pyrolyse ovens. This is handy for keeping an eye on maintenance issues for multiblocks.%n%nIf you want to put the panels far from the machines they are monitoring, you will need range upgrades.%n%n[note]There's also a more advanced version.[/note]

# Quest: Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFhA.name=§6§lAssembly Line
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFhA.desc=The Assembly Line (or 'Assline') is an important machine for high tier components in LuV tier and above for making Motors, Pistons, Robot Arms, Pumps and many more.%n%nThe multiblock can be 5-16 blocks long. The minimum length required depends on the number of components and fluids required by the recipe it's crafting. A length of 11 blocks will fit 80 percent of all recipes in GTNH.%n%nThe bottom layer must have on one outer side all the Input Hatches for fluids (4), in the bottom middle layer Input Buses for items (10), and on the end 1 Output Bus. Also on the bottom outer layer must be one Maintenance Hatch. The rest is Solid Steel Machine Casings.%n%nThe second layer on the outer sides left and right are Reinforced Glass and in the middle center Assembly Line Casing.%n%nThe third layer has on the left and right Grate Machine Casings and in the middle Assembler Machine Casings (Note the name change!). The Assembly Line control block and Data Access Hatch are on the opposite edge from the Input Hatches - not at the end with the Output Bus.%n%nThe fourth layer is a single line of Solid Steel Machine Casings in the middle (11), with two Energy Hatches for power. Once you have it built, you can replace the two IV energy hatches with 1 LuV energy hatch.%n%nAutomating the assline is a difficult challenge! You can use advanced tools like SFM or OpenComputers, but maybe you can figure out how to do it with EnderIO or just AE2.%n%nFor more details on using the Assembly Line, check out the wiki page [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Assembly_Line[/url]%n%n[note]BTW the input buses are ULV to help with your automating, if you don't want to automate it, you can use higher tier ones, unlike the CAL.[/note]%n%n[note]You can have up to 16 input buses. If you use the full 16 you should put the output bus to the side.[/note]%n%n[note]When using buses of a higher tier than ULV it will look for items starting at the top left slot, down to the bottom right slot.[/note]

# Quest: Data Access Hatches
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-w.name=§6§lData Access Hatches
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG-w.desc=So, if you want to do more than one recipe in your Assline, you want a Data Access Hatch. There are 3+1 versions.%n%nData Access Hatch: It holds 4 data sticks, so 4 recipes.%n%nAdvanced Data Access Hatch: It holds 16 data sticks. Ironically, you can make this right away.%n%nAutomatable Data Access Hatch: It's UV, but it allows I/O of the sticks. Skip it.%n%nThe Data Bank Multi: Can be connected to multiple Asslines, and can contain more than 1 DAH. This is the best way, when you can do it. Look in ZPM for the quest.%n%n[note]You only need to make one.[/note]

# Quest: Time to Drill For Ore!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGCQ.name=§6§lTime to Drill For Ore!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGCQ.desc=Auto Miner도 좋지만, 언젠가는 광석이 더 많이 필요해지는 지점에 도달할 것입니다. 이 멀티블록이 그 문제를 해결하는 데 도움을 줄 것입니다. 또한 광석을 사전에 분쇄(macerate)해 주고 약간의 추가 분쇄 광석(crushed ores)도 제공합니다.%n%n더 높은 등급의 전력은 더 빠르게 시추합니다. 전력 등급에 맞춰 에너지 해치를 업그레이드해야 합니다. 또한 에너지 해치, 입력 해치, 출력 버스가 필요합니다. 최소 MV 등급이지만 선택할 수 있습니다.%n%n나중에 광석 시추 플랜트(Ore Drilling Plant)를 업그레이드하여 48블록 반경 이상에서도 추출할 수 있습니다. 너무 멀리까지 채굴하고 싶지 않다면, 드라이버(screwdriver)로 범위를 조정하세요. 컨트롤러 단계가 높아질수록 작은 광석에 대해 4단계부터 시작하여 보너스 행운(fortune) 1을 추가로 제공합니다. 단계 3이 되면 여러 개의 압축 상자(compressed chest)에 자원을 분산하여 보관하고 싶을 것입니다!%n%n멀티블록 광산 기계는 시추하는 영역을 청크 로드(chunkload)하도록 업그레이드되었습니다. 하지만 기계 자체는 청크 로드하지 않습니다. 일반적으로 자신이 위치한 청크에서 §o아래로§r 시추한 다음, 범위 내의 다른 청크에서 한 번에 한 청크씩 §o위로§r 시추합니다.%n%n컨트롤러에 시추 파이프(mining pipes)가 필요하고, 유체 해치에 시추 유체(drilling fluid)가 필요합니다. 시추 파이프를 입력 버스에 공급할 수도 있습니다.%n%n많은 양의 시추 유체를 만들어야 합니다. 64개는 시작하기엔 턱없이 부족한 양입니다! 수천 양동이를 계획하세요. 현장에서 만들거나, 장거리 유체 파이프(Long Distance Fluid Pipes)를 통해 펌핑하세요.%n%n이들은 GT 기계이므로, 비(와 유성!)로부터 기계(와 전원!)를 모든 면에서 보호하는 것을 잊지 마세요. 그리고 JourneyMap으로 위치를 표시해 어디에 설치했는지 잊지 마세요!

# Quest: Thermal Boiler - Lava you long time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH6w.name=§6§lThermal Boiler - Lava you long time
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH6w.desc=If you want energy from Lava and the byproducts, the Thermal Boiler is the perfect solution. It processes Lava super fast for Steam, and with a Lava Filter will provide some centrifuged lava byproducts as well. A great source of Copper, Silver, Gold, Tin, Tantalum, and Tungstate, better outputs than regular lava processing in a Centrifuge.%n%nYou can get even better efficiency pairing it with a Large Heat Exchanger. The LHE will turn normal vanilla Lava into Pahoehoe Lava, which will provide Steam and byproducts in the Thermal Boiler. Win/Win/Win!

# Quest: Electrum Flux Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHGQ.name=§6§lElectrum Flux Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHGQ.desc=To process more advanced materials like Cosmic Neutronium, Tritanium and Awakened Draconium you need more than 9000K. Upgrade your EBF to 9900K.

# Quest: Grinding With Wind
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHKA.name=§6§lGrinding With Wind
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHKA.desc=The Windmill is a grinder that uses the force of wind to macerate Items and Blocks. You will only get one crushed Ore from it sometimes. However it does give a bonus when you try to macerate other things. That bonus depends on the item inserted, for example Netherrack has a chance to give two instead of one dust and Wheat will always give one and a quarter flour.%n%nThe dispensers replace a clay block in the walls. Put anything you like in the interior - a bed, stairs, torches, etc.%n%nNormal multiblock rules apply - do not cross chunk boundaries with this multiblock.%n%nIf this is your first GregTech multiblock, as with all the rest you will need to whack the controller with a soft mallet to activate it.%n%nIf you have troubles forming the multiblock, try breaking and replacing the controller block.%n%nThe controller can be fed items via hoppers etc. to allow for larger batches. Just don't allow the dispenser to fill up or it will void outputs.%n%nThe rotor blades will run if the controller is disabled or has no recipe. Remove the blades when not in use or else they'll be used up.%n%nSpeed and output will be affected by wind speed, recipe, and rotor.%n%nMacerates 16 items at a time.%n%nHigh wind speeds will decrease output.%n%nThe durability will decrease according to the wind speed.

# Quest: Awakened Draconium Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHKQ.name=§6§lAwakened Draconium Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHKQ.desc=To process the most advanced materials like Infinity Catalyst or Infinity you need more than 9900K. Upgrade your EBF to 10800K.%n%n[note]With the heat adjustment included, you can get up to 11601K if you OC with UHV hatches. Not that you need it or anything.[/note]

# Quest: Helium is Not Just for Balloons
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHcA.name=§6§lHelium is Not Just for Balloons
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHcA.desc=Higher tier superconducting wires and energy hatches will require helium. Compressing air and liquefying it requires 1802 compressed air cells to get 1 He cell. It's probably better to get it from end stone dust or monazite from the Moon. Another option is to have a look at your oil processing and see how you can get Helium from there.%n%n[note]PS: If you've progressed far enough in the TF, you can also chip off parts of the snow queen's lair. She won't mind, right?[/note]

# Quest: Hot Hot Hot!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIFQ.name=§6§lHot Hot Hot!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIFQ.desc=Once you build your vacuum freezer, you're going to have to carry around hot ingots all the time (assuming you don't automate it). Your old gloves are falling apart, and take up both hands. I think there's a way to glue them together so you can carry hot items with just one hand. Give me some parts and I'll do it for you.

# Quest: Playing With the Big Boys, Chemically
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJXQ.name=§6§lPlaying With the Big Boys, Chemically
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJXQ.desc=This facility will process certain chemical recipes you'll need later on, like Rocket Fuels. Keep in mind that recipes can only be made after meeting the required Chemical Plant tier.%n%nIt will need a minecart load of resources, so start mining!%n%nCatalysts are needed in some recipes, place them in the Catalyst Housing. They use durability, this includes ones that don't look like it.%n%n[note]You can make Silicon Carbide in the mixer, you don't need the ABS.[/note]%n%nValid solid casings: (Determines CP Tier for recipes)%n1 Strong Bronze Machine Casing%n2 Solid Steel Machine Casing%n3 Sturdy Aluminium Machine Casing%n4 Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing%n5 Stable Titanium Machine Casing%n6 Robust Tungstensteel Casing%n7 Vigorous Laurenium Machine Casing%n8 Rugged Botmium Machine Casing%n%nValid machine casings: (Determines maximum hatch/bus tier)%nLV-UHV Machine Casing, UHV unlocks any hatch/bus.%n%nValid pipe casings: (+2 Parallels, -20%% chance to consume catalyst durability per pipe casing starting with 2 parallels and 100%% chance for the first one.)%nBronze%nSteel%nTitanium%nTungstensteel%n%nAll coils from Cupronickel to Eternal are valid. Each one increases speed by +50%%, starting at 50%% speed for Cupronickel.%n%n[note]Additionally: If you have at least Awakened Draconium Coils and Tungstensteel pipe casings, then no catalyst is consumed at all![/note]

# Quest: Better Glass Upgrade, EV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_A.name=§8§lBetter Glass Upgrade, EV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_A.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Titanium. Make it to allow higher tier recipes in the Bacterial Vat, higher tier Energy Hatches in the MBF, or better Capacitors in your LSC. Or just use it for machine recipes, whatever.

# Quest: IV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_Q.name=§9§lIV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_Q.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Tungstensteel. Make it to allow higher tier recipes in the Bacterial Vat, higher tier Energy Hatches in the MBF, or better Capacitors in your LSC. Or just use it for machine recipes, whatever.%n%n[note]PS: If you just want to use it to make machines, check out the Thorium Yttrium glass blocks.[/note]

# Quest: LuV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_g.name=§d§lLuV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_g.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Rhodium-Plated Palladium. Make it to allow higher tier recipes in the Bacterial Vat, higher tier Energy Hatches in the MBF, or better Capacitors in your LSC. Or just use it for machine recipes, whatever.

# Quest: ZPM Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_w.name=§b§lZPM Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ_w.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Iridium. Make it to allow higher tier recipes in the Bacterial Vat, higher tier Energy Hatches in the MBF, or better Capacitors in your LSC. Or just use it for machine recipes, whatever.

# Quest: UV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAA.name=§2§l§nUV Glass
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAA.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Osmium. Make it to allow higher tier recipes in the Bacterial Vat, higher tier Energy Hatches in the MBF, or better Capacitors in your LSC. Or just use it for machine recipes, whatever.

# Quest: Bacterial Vat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAQ.name=§6§lBacterial Vat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAQ.desc=The Bacterial Vat is a unique multiblock machine with its own recipes. But it also has advanced versions of many brewery recipes.%n%nThe Vat isn't mandatory in this tier, but there are many useful recipes and you'll need it later on, so let's build one!%n%nAll recipes require a §cculture§r, some recipes require a specific §cGlass-Tier.§r%n%nThe culture is made in a BioLab and §lput in the controller.§r%n%nThe Glass-Tier is calculated as LV = Tier 1, so this quest requires you to make tier 3 glass.

# Quest: Sievert for the Vat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAw.name=§6§lSievert for the Vat
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKAw.desc=Some Vat recipes require a certain Sievert (radioactivity) value. So attach this Radio Hatch to your Vat to input radioactive material!%n%nThe Radio Hatch holds rods/long rods of radioactive material and uses them to produce Sievert. The input item determines the Sievert value and how long it lasts. Items stored in the hatch will be used continuously even if machine not active, so make sure you want to craft something before putting items in.%n%nYou can check the stats of an inputted item with a portable scanner.%n%nSome recipes require [warn]exact[/warn] sievert, you can use the screwdriver to access the radiation shutter control to adjust how much sv is blocked from being sent to the vat. For example, you need 100sv to make Seaweed Broth, so you'd use Naquadah rods, and block off 30sv.%n%nRod Stats:%nMaterial-Sievert-Apprx. time until used up%nBismuth                 83sv   198s%nUranium 235           92sv    80s%nUranium 238           92sv    80s%nPlutonium 239         94sv    66s%nPlutonium 241         94sv    66s%nNaquadah             130sv   14.5s%nEnriched Naquadah 140sv   10.5s%nNaquadria            150sv     8s%n%nThere are more radioactive materials than these, but these are the main ones.

# Quest: Making the Vat More Efficient!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKBA.name=§6§lMaking the Vat More Efficient!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKBA.desc=Looking at the Vat's recipes you are likely discouraged by the small amount of fluid being produced per recipe. Don't worry! Fluid consumption and production shown in NEI are just the baseline for the lowest efficiency. The efficiency of Vat depends on the amount of fluid in the Output Hatch.%n%nThe efficiency gradually increases as the output hatch fills up and reaches maximum efficiency when it is §cexactly half-filled§r. If the hatch fills even more, the efficiency goes down again, so try to keep it close to half! At maximum efficiency the amount of fluid consumed and produced per recipe is multiplied by 1001. The items and culture are not affected.%n%nThere are different means to keep it at half, including OC (not SFM, it doesn't like BW fluids), fluid detector+machine controller, or a fluid regulator, as well as more off the wall ones such as frames or block-sharing. If you choose the fluid detector route, remember that using a larger output hatch will make it easier to keep it close to half-filled.

# Quest: Something From Nothing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKbA.name=§6§lSomething From Nothing
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKbA.desc=Void Miners are basically the same thing as regular ones, except that they draw from the whole pool of ores for the dimension without there having to be any nearby. In addition, you can speed them up by supplying Neon, Krypton, Xenon, or Oganesson.%n%nYou can get Neon reasonably easily from Bartimaeusnek Ore from Ross 128ba. Krypton and Xenon can be produced from centrifuging fuel rods. All three can be produced from the EV liquid air distillation method. Remember you need the Liquid Air Fluid Hatch to actually put in enough liquid air. If you want all the produced gasses from the first 4 slots, you'll need to use the Giant Output Hatch.%n%nTo get Oganesson, you'll need mk3 fusion.%n%nAll four fluids can be replicated, so you'll probably end up doing that.%n%n[note]If you want the Deep Dark's ores, you HAVE to use a Void Miner.[/note]

# Quest: Higher Precision
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKcA.name=§6§lHigher Precision
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKcA.desc=You can upgrade the precise casings to unlock more recipes in precise mode and gain more parallels in normal mode.%n%n[note]To make orundum check out the recipe for the orundum plate.[/note]

# Quest: TFFT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzQ.name=§6§lTFFT
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzQ.desc=The TFFT is very useful if you don't want to have a bunch of Super Tanks, it also has a modular structure so it can be up to x4.33 times bigger than numbers in this quest.%n%nWith the tier I storage field block, it consumes 27 EU/t but only has about 0.27x the storage capacity of a Super Tank I per fluid.%n%nWith the tier V storage field block it consumes 1134 EU/t and has about 0.54x the storage capacity of a QT III per fluid.%n%nWith the tier X storage field block it consumes 0EU/t (only tier X uses 0) and has about x3.3 capacity of T7 YOTTank (divide by 25 to get per 1 fluid)%n%nYou can use the multi hatch to access all the fluids at once with an ME Fluid Storage Bus or Fluid Ender Conduit.%n%n[note]Remember to turn auto-voiding on if you need it.[/note]

# Quest: Expert MB-Construction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL1g.name=§6§lExpert MB-Construction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL1g.desc=Right-click the controller while sneaking will invoke an action called §osurvival autoplace§r. This will attempt to build the multiblock with items from your inventory, provided the area this multi occupies is clear of obstacles. Again, like hologram spawning, multiblocks that accept multiple types of tiered components or has variable length, the number of MSHPs you hold in hand will decide which tier of blocks will be placed. It will place correct amount of hatches for you, but will usually orient the hatches towards you, not perpendicular to the surface. It will just place casings for you if you don't have any hatches in inventory, unless this spot requires the use of a hatch (e.g. the top center spot of EBF).%n%nSurvival autoplace can also take from your alternative inventories, or items that contain/link to an inventory. Currently, this includes:%n- adventure backpacks, either worn or as an item in inventory%n- AE2 portable cells%n- ME networks connected via any AE2 wireless terminal with item access capabilities%n- Forestry backpacks%n- ender chest inventory, if you have the Ender Backpack from Backpacks mod. Note: ordinary backpacks from the Backpacks mod are NOT supported at the moment.

# Quest: You Are Not Prepared!!!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL1w.name=§6§lYou Are Not Prepared!!!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL1w.desc=It's time for something really big: A smeltery! There's a lot to craft, so better gather some resources... or you could go try complete this with the help of some unhappy NPC friends, but that would void your quest rewards.%n%n[note]Note: This quest is mutually exclusive with the other smeltery quest.[/note]

# Quest: Getting Muddy With Monazite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4Q.name=§6§lGetting Muddy With Monazite
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4Q.desc=Pretty soon you're going to need lanthanide elements. A lot of them.%nThey're not that easy to separate, however...%n%nCraft up a Digester to unlock the questline in the IV tab.%n%nNote: This multiblock will not function correctly without a muffler hatch

# Quest: Dissolution Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4g.name=§6§lDissolution Tank
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4g.desc=Basically a mixing machine purposely made for dilution.%n%nYou'll need to take care in providing the inputs at the required ratios, else you'll get no output.%n%nAnyway, this plays a large part in the lanthanide line so craft it up.

# Quest: Advanced MB Construction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKA.name=§6§lAdvanced MB Construction
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKA.desc=The ability to rotate MBs and view a structure hologram has been sto-§oborrowed§r from §9Tec§1Tech§r, giving you greater freedom to build the way you want! §5(until we nerf wallsharing at least)§r%n%nUnlike TT, you can use a normal wrench for this, just aim at the front center of a controller (or one of the other sides if you want to. You just need to aim for the part of the grid with the mark) and right-click or shift-right-click. The first rotates it clockwise, the latter flips it. If you want to change the facing of the controller itself, do that the normal way.%n%nUse a Multiblock Structure Hologram Projector or MSHP to visualize the structure, pay attention to the bottom left for structure details. For multiblocks that accept multiple types of tiered components or have a variable size, the number of MSHPs you hold in your hand will decide which tier is shown in the hologram.%n%n[note]If you don't get it, try placing a controller, wrenching it, and using the MSHP on it.[/note]%n%nWhile it's now possible to build a sideways EBF, or even build one into the floor, not everything can be rotated.%n%n[note]PS: We did get permission, that was just a little joke.[/note]

# Quest: HSS-S Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTA.name=§6§lHSS-S Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTA.desc=Technically this coil tier can be skipped. But you need LuV to get the next one, so you should really get these coils for now.%n%nTo process more advanced materials like LuV Superconductor Base you need more than 5400K. Time to upgrade your EBF to 6300K.

# Quest: Trinium Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTQ.name=§6§lTrinium Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALTQ.desc=To process more advanced materials like neutronium or fluxed electrum you need more than 8100K. Upgrade your EBF to 9001K. (OVER 9000!!!)

# Quest: Neutron Activator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeA.name=§6§lNeutron Activator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeA.desc=The Neutron Activator is a unique machine that you will use for processing Naquadah, and eventually Naquadah Fuel should you choose to do so.%n%nUnlike traditional multis, instead of using a regular energy hatch, this machine relies on a Neutron Accelerator that will need to be regulated by a Sensor Hatch. §3(The Neutron Accelerator needs to be provided power just like an energy hatch)§r%n%nThe accelerator will increase its Neutron Kinetic Energy (NKE) and when the NKE is between the requested number which you can see in NEI, the machine will work and output the right products. However, if you turn on the Neutron Activator when NKE doesn't meet the requirement, it will still consume your input material but output trash. So be careful with the NKE when you run this machine.%n%nWhen all Neutron Accelerators aren't running, NKE will decrease 72keV/s.%n%nNeutron Activator will explode when NKE is over 1200MeV.%n%n§dYou can enable batch mode with wire cutters.§r%n%n[note]The more height/speed casings you have, the more inefficient the EU->eV conversion becomes, so you then need more power. The math is as follows: Multiply recipe time by 0.9 for each height above 4 and multiply eV you get from your input power by 0.95 for each height above 4.[/note]

# Quest: Neutron Sensor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeQ.name=§6§lNeutron Sensor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeQ.desc=The sensor will send redstone signals according to the NKE of the Neutron Activator.%n%nIt works like a cover: enter the threshold value in eV, and it will emit a redstone signal when the NKE is at least as high as the threshold.

# Quest: Neutron Accelerator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeg.name=§6§lNeutron Accelerator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALeg.desc=It is used to accelerate the NKE. You just need to connect a cable to it and it will keep consuming the energy.%n%n[note]PS: You can use a controller cover to stop it.[/note]

# Quest: Oops
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALew.name=§6§lOops
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALew.desc=If you failed to meet the NKE as NEI requested, you can recycle something useful in this place.

# Quest: Air-Filter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALpQ.name=§6§lAir-Filter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALpQ.desc=Electric Air Filter%n%nThis wonderful multiblock comes in 3 versions: T1 for LV, T2 for late HV and T3 for IV.%n%nIt has 2 modes:%n%n- a normal mode, where one chunk is processed at a time in the working area, in order, per pollution cleaning cycle.%n- a random mode, where the chunk being cleaned is picked randomly between all the polluted chunks in the working area.%n To cycle between the modes, right-click on the controller with a screwdriver.%n%nThe controller can change its working area from 1x1 to (2*tier+1) x (2*tier+1) chunks. To do that, right-click with a screwdriver on the controller while sneaking. The default size is the maximum working area.%n%nThe pollution removal calculation is equals (by default) to 30 * bonusMultiTier * Muffler Hatches * Turbine Eff * Multiblock Eff * 2.5 ^ Effective Tier where:%n%n- BonusMultiTier is a boost given by the multiblock tier. T1 is 1 (0%%), T2 is 1.05 (5%%) and T3 is 1.10 (10%%)%n%n- Muffler Hatches is the amount of muffler hatches on the multiblock (up to 8)%n%n- Turbine Eff is the efficiency of the turbine chosen to run the multi. It won't run if there is no turbine in the controller.%n%n- Multiblock Eff is the efficiency of the multiblock (100%% when no maintenance issue, -10%% per issue)%n%n- Effective Tier is the Effective Tier of the multi: the minimum tier between the electric tier of the multi and the tier of the muffler hatches.%n%nThe pollution cleaning is boosted by two (by default) when using an Absorption Filter. When added in the input bus, it will be consumed and used for 30 (by default) successful pollution cleaning cycle. If a chunk with no pollution in it is processed, that doesn't count as successful, and the multi decides that a chunk has no pollution if the pollution is below 10k gibbl (by default). After the 30th successful pollution cleaning cycle, the output bus will give a Dirty Absorption Filter.%n%nTo know if an Absorption Filter is present and how many remaining cycles there are, use a portable scanner on the controller.%n%nA pollution cycle lasts 10s, and the cleaning is done every second.%n%n[note]P.S. If you procrastinated making one of these and make a T2 or T3 instead, the quest will still complete![/note]

# Quest: Absorption Filter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALpg.name=§6§lAbsorption Filter
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALpg.desc=When you reach MV tier you can make your own Absorption Filter for the Air Filter to clean pollution much more efficiently. The Filter will be consumed and you get a dirty Filter back after 30 Cycles.

# Quest: You Are Not Prepared... But They Are
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALqQ.name=§6§lYou Are Not Prepared... But They Are
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALqQ.desc=Building a smeltery from the ground up can be really tedious and time consuming. How about borrowing one from the locals? They will surely be happy to share it with an unfriendly adventurer that just dismantled their bricked railway station.%n%nThe villagers are so dumb that they spent all their seared bricks without adding a few key components like faucets or drains. You still need to craft some smeltery bricks yourselves...%n%nTotally not useful tip: if you hold off building this long enough, you will be able to break down seared brick blocks into seared brick items with a forge hammer or extractor.%n%n[note]Unfortunately, going down this path means we will not give you quest rewards, since you are already getting this important multiblock for free. Check the checkbox to signify your consent.[/note]

# Quest: Focusing Science and Mystery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2A.name=§6§lFocusing Science and Mystery
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2A.desc=This mechanic is completely optional, and never required for crafting. However, it's greatly incentivized when the number of parallels is high and when crafting the unique items that unlock higher tiers. “Focusing”, in general, means to increase the chances of the outputs in a QFT recipe, and it can be done in two ways, possibly both at the same time. Each method uses a new plasma, both of which are crafted in a T4 Fusion Reactor by using other plasmas as the inputs, including one T3 plasma for each. These plasmas are Neptunium and Fermium and they can be used together, or individually.%n%nWhen Neptunium Plasma is present, the current recipe can have one of the outputs focused. The specific output is chosen with a circuit in the input bus (this is the only thing circuits do for this multi), where circuit 1 is for the 1st output visible in NEI, circuit 2 is for the 2nd output, and so on. It is up to the player to choose which output they want the most out of all the existing ones, and the fact that every recipe has multiple outputs is because of this mechanic.%n%nWhen an output is successfully focused with Neptunium, its chance increases by reducing the chance of all the other outputs. The logic for this change is as follows:%n%n-> Without focusing, the chance of each output is 100 / number of outputs;%n-> If the casing tier matches the recipe tier, the chance of all other outputs is halved and the sum of those halves is added to the focused output (for example, 20/20/20/20/20 becomes 60/10/10/10/10);%n-> If the casing tier is +1 over the recipe tier, halve the other outputs' chance again (for example, 60/10/10/10/10 becomes 80/5/5/5/5);%n-> If the casing tier is +2 or +3 over the recipe tier, set the focused output to 100%% and the rest to 0%%.%n%nIn general, this type of focusing doesn't increase the total amount of outputs, save for the new items added with this multi that will come out in smaller quantities. Instead, it allows the player to replace less useful outputs with the more useful ones, and this choice is completely up to them, as is the choice of focusing at all.%n%nWhen Fermium Plasma is present, the current recipe will have all of its output chances boosted, unless the chance for one of them is 100%%, in which case that chance is unchanged. This happens because the boost increases if the output chance before ferm focusing is smaller, and the maximum boost is achieved when the chance is 0%%, which happens with high-tier nep focusing.%n%nWhen an output is successfully focused with Fermium, its chance increases based on how far it is from 100%% chance. This applies to all the outputs at once, and the logic for this change is as follows:%n%n-> If the casing tier matches the recipe tier, each output gets increased by 1/4 of the "failure" chance (for example, a 50%% chance output has a 50%% chance of failure, so it gets boosted by 12.5%%, becoming 62.5%%)%n-> If the casing tier is +1 over the recipe tier, each output gets increased by 1/3 of the "failure" chance%n-> If the casing tier is +2 or +3 over the recipe tier, each output gets increased by 1/2 of the "failure" chance%n%nWith the two plasmas combined and a +2 or +3 over recipe tier, a 5-output recipe would normally have 20/20/20/20/20 chances, but it becomes 100/50/50/50/50.%n%nMany lategame multis have parallels, which means they complete the recipe several times at once every time the recipe time is completed, instead of only one, but they require extra EU to achieve this. This makes power the biggest constraint for those multiblocks, and the same happens with the QFT, given that recipe inputs are generally very cheap and simple. Throwing more power at the machine means more outputs, in general.%n%nGiven that, a player that wants a faster QFT will make more catalysts to unlock more parallels, but each added parallels adds to the other ones, to a cap of 64. Focusing, instead, changes output odds, which effectively multiplies the number of outputs per cycle. In terms of speed, a recipe with 4 outputs and 64 parallels runs at the speed of 256 parallels for the focused output if it's nep focused to the maximum of 100%%, since it was 25%% originally.%n%nThis is a lot of saved EU for high-tier, high-parallel QFTs, so it is the main reason for focusing, and both plasmas are useful here. However, plasma consumption is not the same regardless of parallels, it instead scales with the square root of the number of correct catalysts for the recipe, which is to say, the number of parallels.%n%nThis further applies to the 3 new items that are needed to upgrade the casing tiers. Since their output amount is much smaller than usual, they could get a further boost if focusing is being used, to incentivize the plasma mechanic when upgrading the multi.

# Quest: Catalyzing Miracles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2Q.name=§6§lCatalyzing Miracles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2Q.desc=The QFT uses the kind of catalyst that the Chemical Plant also does. However, like the plants that have Awakened Draconium coils or higher, it does not consume the catalyst's durability on recipe finish, behaving more like a real-life catalyst that is regenerated after being used. This makes the catalysts used here more expensive to craft, as was the case with the Infinite Mutation Catalyst for Mutated Living Solder, which is meant to be used only with those coils that make it last forever.%n%nGiven that there is no durability loss, it would seem only one catalyst needs to be crafted. However, there are two reasons for this to not be true: firstly, each QFT recipe uses a different catalyst; secondly, the QFT checks for parallels by counting the amount of catalysts it has in its Bulk Catalyst Housing for the recipe in question (limit of 2,147,483,647). This system makes it so that crafting 1 of the correct type of catalyst is required to unlock a recipe, but making more is completely optional and only changes the speed at which the multi crafts, provided it gets enough EU input.%n%nEvery catalyst needs some of the materials that it unlocks in the QFT, which is to say, the original processing line will have to be used to craft the catalyst that allows the player to skip it in the QFT. This applies to every recipe, and in turn every line that can be skipped.%n%nTo improve the general speed of processing, your one option is to get more parallels with catalysts. The other, more complicated way is to boost the chances of a successful output by adding more energy to the system, but in a special way: instead of using direct EU, using it to create a powerful plasma works to improve the QFT processing.%n%nIf the correct plasmas are added, the boosting will work, but it is also possible to upgrade the structure itself to perform chemistry skips that are not possible with the base QFT. These upgrades rely on more advanced and powerful materials, mainly in the material progression of DTPF recipes. However, those existing materials are not enough, because the quantum stabilization can't be maintained with those “foreign” substances. Luckily, the QFT itself can produce the items needed to build the upgraded casings, and these items are outputs of some of the skips performed in the multi. It begins by allowing the much simpler production of already-owned materials but, in this process, it unlocks entirely new materials that are useful to improve the structure itself.%n%nThere are three new items and four tiers in the structure. The first tier can be built without them, but every new tier needs a new item crafted in the tier before. These outputs are related to the recipe where they can be obtained, and they possess unique characteristics that, in real life, are only theoretical.%n%nThe first item you will need to craft is the Hyper-Stable Self-Healing Adhesive. To craft this material, proceed with the Glue/Solder recipe by using the Adhesion Promoter Catalyst. Additionally, make these other catalysts to prove you're well set in your QFT journey.

# Quest: Tier 2 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2g.name=§6§lTier 2 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2g.desc=Consider improving your QFT's focusing capabilities by replacing your §3Neutron Shielding Core§r casings with §3Cosmic Fabric Shielding Core§r casings. Like the tier 2 manipulators, these also require §3Hyper-Stable Self-Healing Adhesive§r.

# Quest: Tier 3 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2w.name=§6§lTier 3 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM2w.desc=Consider improving your QFT's focusing capabilities even further by replacing your §3Cosmic Fabric Shielding Core§r casings with §3Infinity Infused Shielding Core§r casings. Like the tier 3 manipulators, these also require §3Superconductor Rare-Earth Composite§r.

# Quest: Tier 4 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3A.name=§6§lTier 4 Shielding
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM3A.desc=Consider pushing your QFT's focusing capability to its final form by replacing your §3Infinity Infused Shielding Core§r casings with §3SpaceTime Bending Core§r casings. Like the tier 4 manipulators, these also require §3Black Body Naquadria Supersolid§r.

# Quest: Too much Indium?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMSA.name=§6§lToo much Indium?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMSA.desc=Milling process is an alternative way to produce Indium, designed for LuV and above. It does not void Aluminium and Galena for no reason, and you can extract Indium from Sphalerite efficiently. In exchange for machine cost and infrastructure needed to process.

# Quest: Infinity Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkQ.name=§6§lInfinity Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkQ.desc=Smelting with the ferocity of the universe itself.%n%nThis unbelievable material seemed impossible to manipulate into a coil block form, even though its properties made this desirable. It is incredibly stable even at extreme temperatures, but this also made it unable to pack together for coils.%n%nHowever, the situation changed when you thought about using something more intelligent. By integrating a Wetware or better UHV circuit, the Infinity Coil became a reality, controlled by the ever-watching eyes of the circuitry you've spent months to create. From now on, these eyes will watch over your multiblocks.%n%nProvides 11701K heat. You could upgrade your EBF, though at this point it's more likely to be for your MBFs or your DTPF.

# Quest: Algae Pond
betterquesting.quest.Ds_ok-hRS2ODJNs3LUP9kw.name=§6§lAlgae Pond
betterquesting.quest.Ds_ok-hRS2ODJNs3LUP9kw.desc=Sustainability. It's not the name of the game... but it could be!%n%nIf you've ever wanted to generate many chemicals from a single source, you've probably looked at Oil or Benzene. However, there's also the Algae Farm.%n%nEach tier, starting from ULV (at 50s per batch) through IV (25s per batch), reduces the time it takes to produce Algae by about 5 seconds, and then beyond that each tier will cut the duration in half. The production time can also randomly double or triple, but this happens relatively rarely.%n%nEach tier increase also adds to the amount of Algae you get in a single cycle, as well as the type of Algae produced. Each cycle gives out an exact amount as well as a bonus amount 10%% of the time. The Algae Farm also accepts Compost, which you can make from the algae itself, to boost the multi's tier by one. This might be expensive at the start, but it's heavily recommended in most cases. You can get regular Algae and Green Algae starting at ULV; Brown Algae starts appearing at HV, Golden-Brown Algae at EV, and Red Algae at IV, though higher tier algae appears in very small quantities at first.%n%nTo find out more about the exact output quantities and timings, please see the wiki: [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Algae_Farm[/url]%n%nThe Algae can be used for various chemicals like Methane, Ammonia, Sulfuric Acid, Sodium Carbonate, Ethylene, Lithium Chloride, and even some power-generating fluids. You typically need a Chemical Plant for that. In IV tier you can also combine Green Algae with Glowstone to get Glowing Coral and make Sunnarium from that. If you're curious about all the processing chains, look them up on NEI: quests to cover them are coming up, possibly with more recipes that don't need the Chemical Plant.

# Quest: Tier 2 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.Mf1D7e-LTaW3rbBRYmxBAQ.name=§6§lTier 2 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.Mf1D7e-LTaW3rbBRYmxBAQ.desc=After significant progression, you'll be able to upgrade the QFT to tier 2 by replacing the §3Neutron Pulse Manipulator§r casings with §3Cosmic Fabric Manipulator§r casings. Once installed, the QFT can perform the §6monaline skip§r, the §6first two naqline skips§r, and the §6netherite line skip§r.%n%nThese casings require more advanced materials, including §3Hyper-Stable Self-Healing Adhesive§r, which can only be crafted in a tier 1 QFT. This adhesive isn’t just excellent at sticking things together - it’s also built to withstand the intense energy flow of a tier 2, 3, or even tier 4 QFT! §o%n%nWho knows what kinds of materials you’ll need after this?!

# Quest: A Beginner's Guide to Particle Physics
betterquesting.quest.NGG2rHQ4T4SInwXT8XTGSg.name=§6§lA Beginner's Guide to Particle Physics
betterquesting.quest.NGG2rHQ4T4SInwXT8XTGSg.desc=If you've built the Source Chamber already, you may have noticed that particles aren't produced as items, like GT++ ones are.%n%nInstead they're transmitted through Beamline Pipes from multi to multi, similar to real life.%n%nEach stream of particles transmitted, or "beam", has four properties:%n- §6Particle§r: the type of particle carried by the beam%n- §4Energy§r: the amount of energy the particles have%n- §9Focus§r: out of 100, how focused the beam is%n- §dAmount§r: a measure of the number of particles in the beam%n%nNote that you can see info about a multi's input and output beams by using a Tricorder on the controller.%n%nFor the recipes you'll be interested in, i.e. the ones that actually produce items, there'll be a threshold for allowed input beam energy, a minimum focus value, and an amount value which determines recipe time (more on that in the Target Chamber quest).%nTake a look some TC recipes for an example of this.%n%nHave a Higgs Boson. To hang on your wall.

# Quest: Producing Solar Panels in BULK!!
betterquesting.quest.NVgXYF-TQvqYnLn1NLM6pw.name=§6§lProducing Solar Panels in BULK!!
betterquesting.quest.NVgXYF-TQvqYnLn1NLM6pw.desc=[quest]The Solar Factory![/quest]%n%nThe structure has tiers, each of which allow greater production than the previous tier. %n%nRecipes in NEI display the minimum wafer tier required. %nWafer Tiers: %n%n§6Monocrystalline%nPhosphorous%nNaquadah%nEuropium%nAmericium%nPhotonically Prepared%nPhotonically Enhanced§r%n%nMachine parallels are based on Precise Casing Tier:%n%n§6MK-I: §c8x§r%n§6MK-II: §c16x§r%n§6MK-III: §c32x§r%n§6MK-IV: §c64x§r%n%n§lTier §b2:§r%n%n§aSupports Multi-Amp energy hatches§r%n§c25%%§r more outputs for every Wafer tier §oabove§r the minimum required.%nThe bonus to outputs occurs after parallels, but §9cannot be greater§r than §c100%%§r%nLV-LuV Solar Panels can be made without the previous panel, but at a higher cost.%n%n§lTier §b3:§r%n%n§aSupports Laser Energy hatches§r%nBonus per increased wafer tier is increased to §c50%%§r%nZPM-UV Solar Panels can be made without the previous panel, but at a higher cost.

# Quest: Synchrotron (No Relation to the Catalyst)
betterquesting.quest.QfQHCy0PRn-rABmKuvwQfw.name=§6§lSynchrotron (No Relation to the Catalyst)
betterquesting.quest.QfQHCy0PRn-rABmKuvwQfw.desc=To actually produce some light for photolithography, you'll need to accelerate your electrons in a Synchrotron. Like with the LINAC, providing it with coolant is necessary to keep it running.%n%nYou can increase the energy of the produced photons by increasing EU/t, or increasing the tier of all four Antenna Casings inside.%n%nTo improve focus, you can use a better coolant, and the output amount increases with both EU/t and antennae tier.%n%nYes, you need all four energy hatches.

# Quest: UXV Glass
betterquesting.quest.QpsC-ERsQHGoqzzSdWAx_A.name=§4§l§nUXV Glass
betterquesting.quest.QpsC-ERsQHGoqzzSdWAx_A.desc=The final, and by far most expensive tier of Borosilicate glass is Universium.%n%nEnjoy the bonus for gathering 32 ;)

# Quest: Stern-Gerlach, Perhaps?
betterquesting.quest.RLJR8nFySzSaZLeCRsabDg.name=§6§lStern-Gerlach, Perhaps?
betterquesting.quest.RLJR8nFySzSaZLeCRsabDg.desc=The Beam Splitter allows you to sort your particle beams. The LHC produces output particles randomly, and this machine allows you to sort them into different lanes using the Filtered Beamline Output Hatch. It also divides the Amount of any particle packet by the number of valid output spots.%n%n[note]For example, if you set one output to protons and two outputs to electrons, then a mixed input beam (with all particles having an Amount of 100) will be sorted into 3 beams - one of protons (Amount 100) and two of electrons (each Amount 50).[/note]

# Quest: Hundreds of Thousands of eV
betterquesting.quest.Y1kiJC_kRGKkW7h3qOPI8A.name=§6§lHundreds of Thousands of eV
betterquesting.quest.Y1kiJC_kRGKkW7h3qOPI8A.desc=A Linear Accelerator (LINAC) can be used to boost the energy of your beam, provided the beam's particles are charged. You'll need to constantly provide it with coolant for it to run, otherwise you'll have maintenance issues every time it runs dry.%n%nOutput energy can be increased by increasing EU/t (scales with the cbrt) or increasing length (scales linearly). The latter also decreases focus, however.%n%nFocus in turn can be improved by using a better/lower temperature coolant (options listed on tooltip).%n%nNote that Amount remains unchanged.

# Quest: Playing with Colors!
betterquesting.quest.Z_jn8qzFQr6FWHzmt2i3Aw.name=§6§lPlaying with Colors!
betterquesting.quest.Z_jn8qzFQr6FWHzmt2i3Aw.desc=Multiblock machines enforce input separation based on hatch color. Inputs from Input Buses and Input Hatches will only interact if they share the same color. Un-dyed inputs act as wildcards compatible with any color.
%n
%nColor can be applied using a Spray Can and removed with a Spray Can Solvent. An Infinite Spray Can becomes available later in progression.
%n
%n[note]There are a few other items which paint inputs. Check out [quest]Making Sense of Spaghetti[/quest] in the §lBuilding Better Bases§l§r tab for a complete list.[/note]
%n
%n[note]For more advanced users, note that the priority of dyed hatches is ordered exactly how the vanilla dyes are in NEI, from highest (black) to lowest (white).[/note]
%n
%n§6Now §2go §3have §4fun§5!!!

# Quest: Don't ask how this works
betterquesting.quest._xupoCqbT52qN_3zQonWNg.name=§6§lDon't ask how this works
betterquesting.quest._xupoCqbT52qN_3zQonWNg.desc=It's a mirror, it reflects stuff. Should this only work for Photons? %n%nMaybe. %n%n[note]But it works for all particles.[/note]

# Quest: Decay Warehouse
betterquesting.quest.bLz_cD33RE24mtOb2aLxXg.name=§6§lDecay Warehouse
betterquesting.quest.bLz_cD33RE24mtOb2aLxXg.desc=The Decay Warehouse stores a single type of radioactive isotope and allows it to decay over time. %n%nThe decay speed of the isotope is §adependent§r on its half-life.%n%nIsotopes will decay §9regardless§r of whether the warehouse is on or powered. %n%nThe Warehouse's capacity equals the chest's capacity divided by §c400§r.%n%nCapacity of the multiblock for each chest:%n%n§6Super Chest I:§r §c10,000%n§6Super Chest II:§r §c20,000%n§6Super Chest III:§r §c40,000%n§6Super Chest IV:§r §c80,000%n§6Super Chest V:§r §c160,000%n§6Quantum Chest I:§r §c320,000%n§6Quantum Chest II:§r §c640,000%n§6Quantum Chest III:§r §c1,280,000%n§6Quantum Chest IV:§r §c2,560,000%n§6Quantum Chest V:§r §c5,368,000§r%n%n[note]Right click the controller with a §aScrewdriver§r to dump stored isotopes into an output bus.%n%nRight click the controller with a §aPlunger§r to empty it. [/note]%n%n[warn]The Warehouse's contents are §nvoided§r when the controller is broken[/warn]

# Quest: Don't Lose That Multiblock Miner!
betterquesting.quest.b_Ll4zvSRfCMgmqiBa4Xkw.name=§6§lDon't Lose That Multiblock Miner!
betterquesting.quest.b_Ll4zvSRfCMgmqiBa4Xkw.desc=It's easy to lose Ore Drilling Plants. You're a busy engineer, you know? You can't be bothered to remember trifling things like "where, in what galactic backwater did I last place my miner." You could do something boring like "write down the location of the miner" or "put up a sign with the miner's location in my ore processing area," but there's a better way.%n%nEnter the Metrics Transmitter Cover. This cover, when attached to a multiblock miner (or any GregTech machine), spawns in a GregTech Advanced Sensor Card paired to the host machine. This card, when inserted into a NuclearCraft Industrial Information Panel, will receive runtime information transmitted by the host machine, including its current location. Additionally, it returns the same information that its lower-tech sibling, the GregTech Sensor Kit, provides. Unlike the GregTech Sensor Kit, the Metrics Transmitter Cover §nworks interdimensionally and at any range without the need of range upgrades.§r In addition, since covers remain on machines when they are dismantled, the paired sensor card §nwill continue to work even if the host machine is relocated, and never needs to be recalibrated.§r This makes it perfect for the Ore Drilling Plant and Oil/Gas/Fluid Drilling Rig, which are deployed in the field and often have to be relocated.%n%nHowever, like always, there's a catch. If the Metrics Transmitter Cover is detached from its host machine, §nthe paired sensor card will be destroyed.§r Maybe you shouldn't be using a crowbar around sensitive electronics...

# Quest: Using that Algae
betterquesting.quest.eur7SqfIT8GEE_NxscJj8Q.name=§6§lUsing that Algae
betterquesting.quest.eur7SqfIT8GEE_NxscJj8Q.desc=So you've created the Chemical Plant, and an Algae Farm, excellent! Time to make some use of it instead of letting it sit there collecting. There's quite a few recipes you can make with Algae, but we'll start with a more simple one.%n%nFor this you'll need some Brown Algae and some Green Algae. This means you need at minimum HV machine casings for the bottom of the Algae Farm. HV will produce up to 8 brown algae every 35 seconds, but can at worst case produce 2 in 105 seconds, while EV will produce at best 20 every 30 seconds, and at worst 12 in 90 seconds.%n%nOnce you have some Green and Brown Algae, you'll have to put them in a tier 2 Chemical Plant (steel based) with some distilled water, and you'll get back Sulfuric Acid. Cheap to produce once you have it all set up, a bit expensive to get there though! There's another Sulfuric acid recipe you can use as well later on, but it'll cost higher tier Algae and a higher tier Chemical Plant.

# Quest: A Little More Sigma (Squared)
betterquesting.quest.gkKzmpgkQguIfPwKqFB5Xg.name=§6§lA Little More Sigma (Squared)
betterquesting.quest.gkKzmpgkQguIfPwKqFB5Xg.desc=Eventually, your LHC will start making rarer and rarer particles. You may find that they appear in large bursts as single particle packets with very high Amounts, but not very often. The Beam Stabilizer allows you to capture these large packets and redistribute them over time as a continuous series of smaller packets with a lower Amount.%n%n[warn]This is particularly useful to ensure recipe checks work consistently for beam-consuming machines.[/warn]

# Quest: No More (IC) Engraving
betterquesting.quest.isBmh7T0Sr63O2m5N4pCIQ.name=§6§lNo More (IC) Engraving
betterquesting.quest.isBmh7T0Sr63O2m5N4pCIQ.desc=Now that you've reached ZPM, you're going to have to resort to means other than mere laser engraving for your photolithography needs.%n%nOf course, we're going overkill right away, requiring a full-on particle accelerator setup to produce the ultra-coherent ultra-high-energy light used to etch more advanced ICs.%n%nTo begin with, you'll need a Source Chamber to produce electrons (at pitifully low energies, of course). Check out NEI for the available recipes, you'll want the one with the hand-drawn icon.

# Quest: Digging Deep for Water
betterquesting.quest.jreOZVXRQa2sGXViV7-3Gg.name=§6§lDigging Deep for Water
betterquesting.quest.jreOZVXRQa2sGXViV7-3Gg.desc=Is the Water Tank not cutting it anymore? Have you set up in a dry biome and are in desperate need of more water? Fear not, for the Steam Water Pump can solve your issues! This Multiblock is able to produce large amounts of Water if fed with Steam (1500L/s).%n%nLike other Steam Multiblocks, it can be upgraded by using Steel Frame Boxes instead of Bronze ones, which doubles the Water output at no additional Steam cost.%n%n§4It is, however, still dependent on how humid the Biome you are in is, so keep that in mind.§r%n%n§9Hint: You can find small lead ore in the Nether or full ingots on the lowest floor of roguelike dungeons if you're lucky!§r%n%n[note]P.S. The optional quest item count includes the cost for the controller. [/note]

# Quest: UMV Glass
betterquesting.quest.m5N5Q9QEREyzF1B4eObk0Q.name=§c§l§nUMV Glass
betterquesting.quest.m5N5Q9QEREyzF1B4eObk0Q.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Hexanite.

# Quest: Filtered Beamline Output Hatch
betterquesting.quest.mqv5zPKRTdmfDUQH_-b1-A.name=§6§lFiltered Beamline Output Hatch
betterquesting.quest.mqv5zPKRTdmfDUQH_-b1-A.desc=The Filtered Beamline Output Hatch allows you to blacklist particles from appearing in the output of your Large Hadron Collider or Beam Splitter.

# Quest: Component Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.n7yjRSr0R7O2agebw73FGA.name=§6§lComponent Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.n7yjRSr0R7O2agebw73FGA.desc=Check the NEI pages to see all the nice recipes this machine can handle for you. Great to craft GT components in bulk.

# Quest: UEV Glass
betterquesting.quest.pbLvv9tvQaKGp2Y2usPMSw.name=§5§l§nUEV Glass
betterquesting.quest.pbLvv9tvQaKGp2Y2usPMSw.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Infinity.

# Quest: A Not So Useful Scanner...
betterquesting.quest.pd68ySXjTD6yW1MN6x6swg.name=§6§lA Not So Useful Scanner...
betterquesting.quest.pd68ySXjTD6yW1MN6x6swg.desc=...but a very useful meter.%n%nGT EU Meter will give you basic information about electricity in your cables and machines.%n%n[note]A more advanced version is available in MV and will allow you to gather much more data, so come back to this tab later to find it.[/note]

# Quest: Drones are not Drones!
betterquesting.quest.prKPwVNgSgOE1NGPiEEF-g.name=§6§lDrones are not Drones!
betterquesting.quest.prKPwVNgSgOE1NGPiEEF-g.desc=...but they can be as industrious as bees. These new electric friends are great companions for Multiblock machines: maintenance, control, management—they can do it all.%n%nThe §5§lDrone Centre§r is a newly designed machine. It doesn't need power; just put a drone into it and it will start running.%nOnce running, the drone will automatically scan for a '§lDrone Downlink Module§r' (replacing maintenance hatches on Multiblock machines) within a certain range and attempt to establish a connection with the host. If successful, you can remotely control this Multiblock machine from the Drone Centre GUI! Additionally, you can rename the machine for easier identification.%n%n[note]You can rename it either by right-clicking the Drone Downlink Module or in the Drone Centre GUI.[/note]%n%nPlacing more advanced drones will increase the range of the Drone Centre, with no limit on the number of drones.%n%n[warn]Note that drones may crash during operation—the probability decreases from Tier 1 to Tier 3, and Tier 3 Anti-Gravity Drones never crash.%nAdditionally, if the machine host is too far from the Drone Centre, the GUI remote control function will be disabled, but the turn-all-on/off button and maintenance functions will still work.[/warn]%n§6§l%nMaybe one day, our drones can control machines on other planets...drive engine online!§r%n%n[note]The Hempcrete can be any color![/note]

# Quest: UIV Glass
betterquesting.quest.qnXgpGxbRc-nHbshgUs1jA.name=§9§l§nUIV Glass
betterquesting.quest.qnXgpGxbRc-nHbshgUs1jA.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Transcendent.

# Quest: UHV Glass
betterquesting.quest.r9VceRoLQr-bpZq_EVu1Ig.name=§4§l§nUHV Glass
betterquesting.quest.r9VceRoLQr-bpZq_EVu1Ig.desc=The next tier of Borosilicate glass is Neutronium.

# Quest: Draconic Development
betterquesting.quest.rZCrzZ3QTni28BdPZf2-0w.name=§6§lDraconic Development
betterquesting.quest.rZCrzZ3QTni28BdPZf2-0w.desc=The Draconic Fusion Crafted has 5 tier of casings, each an upgrade of the previous tier.%n%nEach new tier of casings allows you to make better Cores, eventually ending at the Chaotic Core.%n%n[note]Each casing tier above recipe tier grants one perfect (4/4) overclock![/note]

# Quest: One Fluid Tank to Store it All!!
betterquesting.quest.tQecVBhjRRyfR3sqeNBrtA.name=§6§lOne Fluid Tank to Store it All!!
betterquesting.quest.tQecVBhjRRyfR3sqeNBrtA.desc=If you ever thought that the standard super tanks or quantum tanks were still too small then the YOTTank is the next option.%n%nThe YOTTank compared to the TFFT might only be able to store one fluid instead of 25 fluids. However it makes up for this downside by not having to share any of the fluid storage space with any other fluids. It also does not require any energy input or maintenance requirements.%n%nIf all you want to do is store a large amount of one fluid type then look no further then the YOTTank. It has a special ME input hatch for ae2 connections while having expandable storage blocks. The tank can be both upgraded with the fluid storage blocks and can be increased in height to hold any more fluid.%n%nSo if you want to store your fluid in style then look no further then the YOTTank.%n%n[note]If you're having issues searching for the fluid storage blocks for the YOTTank in NEI then search for: fluid cell block[/note]

# Quest: Tier 4 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.tXVcSBqQQnS4tF8VoMqr6Q.name=§6§lTier 4 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.tXVcSBqQQnS4tF8VoMqr6Q.desc=§lFinally, you have done it§r! You can now upgrade your QFT to the ultimate tier by replacing your §3Infinity Infused Manipulator§r casings with §3SpaceTime Continuum Ripper§r casings. This final upgrade unlocks all skips, including the §6bio cell skip, the kevlar skip and the radox + xenoxene skip§r.%n%nEven with all previous upgrades, the final leap remained out of reach. Chemical skips for foundational components used in the earlier stages of the QFT, such as bioware circuits, were still impossible - §ountil now§r. Reaching the theoretical limit of the QFT demands a material far beyond anything seen before, hidden deep within the second half of the Naquadah line.%n%nThe material you require will be your magnum opus - the §3Black Body Naquadria Supersolid§r. This extraordinary substance acts as a perfect black body - absorbing all radiation without reflection - and behaves as a supersolid, flowing like a fluid with zero viscosity. Combining these properties in a single material ensures stable, effortless quantum energy flow at any voltage level, even at the MAX tier!%n%nWith this breakthrough, your QFT is fully unlocked, capable of creating components up to the UHV tier.

# Quest: Tier 3 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.vK1Ed8HPTTms4QxfaA_P8Q.name=§6§lTier 3 Manipulating
betterquesting.quest.vK1Ed8HPTTms4QxfaA_P8Q.desc=With access to even more advanced materials, you can upgrade your QFT to tier 3 by replacing the §3Cosmic Fabric Manipulator§r casings with §3Infinity Infused Manipulator§r casings. This tier unlocks two powerful new skips: the §6final naqline skip§r and the §6stem cell skip§r.%n%nThis new casing requires even more advanced materials still, including the §3Superconductor Rare-Earth Composite§r, which can only be crafted in a tier 2 QFT. Unlike §3Hyper-Stable Self-Healing Adhesive§r, which focused on structural integrity, this composite is designed purely for energy transmission. With automatic self-repair now fully handled, we can shift our focus to increasing the energy flow between components and into the multi itself.%n%nStandard superconductors break down under quantum stress - but this composite eliminates all resistance across the outer shell. Its precisely layered rare-earth elements create such gradual transitions that quantum flow moves effortlessly, with no losses or destabilizing effects.%n%n§oWhat will you discover next?!

# Quest: More Algae Uses
betterquesting.quest.wgxwGsMBScCIIWzrgyfb8w.name=§6§lMore Algae Uses
betterquesting.quest.wgxwGsMBScCIIWzrgyfb8w.desc=Now that you have Titanium, why not make about 79 EV machine casings for some cheap Ammonia? The ratio is about 50mb to one Golden-Brown Algae. At EV you have a 10%% chance to get 8 about every 30 seconds. It also does not require a Chemical Plant, but it will require an MV Assembler and an MV Fluid Extractor at minimum.


## Quest Line: Mass Processing
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQ.name=Mass Processing
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAEQ.desc=This tab showcases new high-speed multiblocks to replace your old machines as they become available. Check back regularly!

# Quest: A Steam-Powered Whirl!
betterquesting.quest.0rUmaWIPQPaL93q-_pgKXw.name=§c§lA Steam-Powered Whirl!
betterquesting.quest.0rUmaWIPQPaL93q-_pgKXw.desc=How does one centrifuge rare materials in the Steam Age? The answer is by building and using the Steam Separator, of course! By using steam to create a spinning force, this Multiblock can separate different materials quickly and easily.%n%nIf you think separation is taking forever, the Steam Separator will speed things up!%n%n§3This Multiblock can process recipes up to LV Tier, and does accept an Output Hatch for recipes. But if you are looking to use recipes which require Fluid Inputs, you might have to build an LV Centrifuge in the future.

# Quest: Big Beautiful Brewery
betterquesting.quest.3SzKMSj0StOAOzVmInDjZQ.name=§5§lBig Beautiful Brewery
betterquesting.quest.3SzKMSj0StOAOzVmInDjZQ.desc=Start your own local brewery with the BBB! You can use it to make tons of potions, obscure alcoholic drinks, or, more likely, industrial quantities of lubricant.

# Quest: This Kinda Burns...
betterquesting.quest.4-HZ9i5AQ4qLN7cgSDaL3Q.name=§9§lThis Kinda Burns...
betterquesting.quest.4-HZ9i5AQ4qLN7cgSDaL3Q.desc=The §5§lIndustrial Chemical Bath§r will significantly increase the efficiency of your ore processing. It grants a §2§l5x§r speed boost and §6§l4§r parallels per voltage tier compared to its singleblock counterpart.

# Quest: Mass Processing at UV and Beyond!
betterquesting.quest.5L2m9tcsRgyf9aCp10E0eg.name=§2§l§nMass Processing at UV and Beyond!
betterquesting.quest.5L2m9tcsRgyf9aCp10E0eg.desc=Now that you've reached UV, you're going to start unlocking some extremely powerful processing multis. You'll want to create them as soon as possible because things are about to start getting very expensive...

# Quest: Fits The Mold
betterquesting.quest.6glle46JSyuwR6O4x7mLYA.name=§9§lFits The Mold
betterquesting.quest.6glle46JSyuwR6O4x7mLYA.desc=Making machines for every mold sounds tiring... fortunately, the Mass Solidifier multiblock can handle any number of molds by using §lSolidifier Hatches§r.%n%n[note]The Mass Solidifier also speeds up as it is running, making it more efficient to do large batches.[/note]

# Quest: T2 Maceration Stack 
betterquesting.quest.A4rEQOAXQsaa26Ib_nzkHg.name=§9§lT2 Maceration Stack 
betterquesting.quest.A4rEQOAXQsaa26Ib_nzkHg.desc=Upgrade your Maceration Stack by replacing all the casings with Maceration Stack Casings and then placing the Upgrade Chip into the slot in the controller.%n%nThe §5§lTier 2§r Maceration stack has §2§l4x§r the speed and §6§l4x§r the parallels compared to the T1!

# Quest: Smelt All The Things Stack-Wise...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVQ.name=§5§lSmelt All The Things Stack-Wise...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAVQ.desc=...with this great invention! Upgrade power and coils to smelt absolutely ridiculous amounts of items.

# Quest: Industrial Sledgehammer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABgg.name=§9§lIndustrial Sledgehammer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABgg.desc=The §5§lIndustrial Sledgehammer§r is a multiblock Forge Hammer. By default it processes recipes at §2§l2x§r the speed. %n%nThe tier of solenoid you use in the machine has a direct impact on how many parallels it has.%n%n§6§lParallels§r = §9Solenoid Tier§r * §cVoltage Tier§r * 6

# Quest: A Volcano For Your Base.
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABhQ.name=§9§lA Volcano For Your Base.
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABhQ.desc=The ultimate machine for cobblestone production. Or maybe to turn redstone into obsidian on a large scale for a renewable production of Silicon, Magnesium, Iron, and Oxygen.%n%nThe §5§lBoldarnator§r boasts a §2§l3x§r speed boost, §3§l25%%§r EU discount, and offers §6§l8§r parallels per voltage tier compared to the Rock Breaker.

# Quest: You Smell Like a Distillery!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADAA.name=§5§lYou Smell Like a Distillery!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADAA.desc=This bad boy will tremendously boost the byproducts of your cracked fuel or pyrolyse oven. This way you can make industrial TNT, polyethylene, polytetrafluoroethylene and other plastics more efficiently. You'll also need this for the platline.%n%nYou'll need to make EV circuits in a cleanroom to build this machine.%n%nFor hatches, you can choose your own tier. 1 MV energy hatch is enough for most of the useful recipes. 2 MV energy hatches or 1 HV energy hatch will cover almost all the rest. You will also need 1 input hatch, and at least 5 output hatches. An output bus will capture any solid outputs.%n%nNEI is not great for determining which cracked fuel option is the best. Instead, visit the Oil Cracking Unit wiki page linked below for a complete list of all the fractions in a nice, convenient format!%n%n[url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Oil_Cracking_Unit[/url]

# Quest: Bring Me My Vat of Polyethylene!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADbA.name=§5§lBring Me My Vat of Polyethylene!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADbA.desc=Tired of using small cells to process chemicals? Build a Large Chemical Reactor and you can just pipe in and out fluids. Or use the glorious large fluid cells to deliver and remove fluids from the hatches.%n%nYou can decide if the reactor should void any extra products when the outputs are full or not by toggling the void mode in the GUI!%n%nThere are also recipes specific to only the LCR, sometimes even allowing you to skip a step, so keep your eyes open for that.%n%nAdditionally, as a multiblock, LCR also counts as a cleanroom for any cleanroom recipes.%n%nYou will also need:%n1 Maintenance Hatch%n1-2 Energy Hatches%n0+ Input Bus (if a recipe has an item input. For full automation, you should probably use 1 for each material)%n0-1 Output Bus (if a recipe has an item output)%n2+ Input Hatch (use 1 for every fluid)%n1+ Output Hatch (same as above)%n%nYou can use a screwdriver on an output hatch to cycle through its modes. Use shift-right-click to go directly to specific fluid mode, then lock the fluid with a cell for easier automation. This works on more than just the LCR.%n%n[note]You can use any type of coil to form the structure, but there is no benefit accrued from using higher tiers.[/note]

# Quest: Hulk Smash!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjQ.name=§8§lHulk Smash!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjQ.desc=Mass destruction! Or at least, lots and lots of crushed ores. Build an §5§lIndustrial Maceration Stack§r to keep up with all the ores you are getting.%n%nThis processes items at §2§l1.6x§r the speed and with up to §6§l2§r parallels per voltage tier.%n%n[note]In IV you can upgrade the multi with an upgrade chip and better casings.[/note]

# Quest: The Rocks In The Washer...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjg.name=§8§lThe Rocks In The Washer...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjg.desc=...go round and round, all the live long day. A large ore washing plant gets your rocks nice and clean. %n%nThe §5§lOre Washing Plant§r gives a §2§l5x§r speed boost and §6§l4§r parallels per voltage tier compared to its singleblock counterpart.

# Quest: Dancing In Circles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjw.name=§8§lDancing In Circles
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFjw.desc=Spinning around, getting hot - sounds like a dance. Or a thermal centrifuge. Build a §5§lLarge Thermal Refinery§r to get the most out of your ores.%n%nUnlike with the singleblock, you get a base §2§l2.5x§r speed bonus and a §3§l20%%§r EU discount on all recipes. You unlock an extra §n§l5%%§r increase to both speed and EU discount per coil tier.%n%nAs a bonus, the LTR provides §6§l8§r parallels per voltage tier, and §6§l2§r additional parallels per tier of solenoid on top of that.%n%n[note]Glass tier is irrelevant; use what works best for you![/note]

# Quest: I Think I'm Going to be Sick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7A.name=§8§lI Think I'm Going to be Sick
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7A.desc=The §5§lIndustrial Centrifuge§r is the best solution for handling the thousands of ores being produced by the multiblock ore drill. You will eventually want to have an array of these running, though one or two is fine to start.%n%nThis multiblock gives you §6§l4-8§r parallels per voltage tier, operates at §2§l2-3x§r the speed, and grants a §3§l10%%§r EU discount. This makes it a far better alternative to both singleblock Centrifuges and the Steam Separator.%n%nThe parallel and speed modifiers start at their minimums and increase to their maximums as the Centrifuge gains momentum.%n%nThe Centrifuge will gain 1%% momentum every 10 ticks while running §3%n(50s to go from 0%% -> 100%%)§r%n%nOn the other hand, it will lose 2%% momentum every 5 ticks while idle%n§3(12.5s to go from 100%% -> 0%%)§r

# Quest: Bask In The Currents
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7Q.name=§d§lBask In The Currents
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7Q.desc=§r[warn]This multiblock always runs recipes at the same tier as the energy hatches in the structure. If the machine does not have enough power supplied, it won't turn on.[/warn]%n%nAlthough this multiblock is available in IV, we recommend building one §nafter finishing the Naqline§r.%n%n%nThis multiblock has 3 different modes: §3Normal§r, §4EBF§r, and §6Ore§r.%n%n%nIn §3Normal§r mode, this multiblock §3processes normal arc furnace recipes§r.%n%nIn §4EBF§r mode, this multiblock can process §4every EBF recipe regardless of coil tier requirement§r. This feature comes at the cost of §lbase recipe voltage being increased by 2 tiers§r.%n%nIn §6Ore§r mode, this machine can only process ores and raw ores that can be smelted in a normal furnace, giving molten metal directly.%n%n%nIn addition to the modes, this machine has 3 different processing phases.%n%n§lStartup:§r During this phase, the machine will use power equal to §lmaximum parallels * number of amps per parallel * (1 + startup penalty)§r. This phase lasts for 6 seconds before going to the processing phase.%n%n§lProcessing:§r During this phase, the machine behaves as any other multiblock. Its power usage is determined by the amps/parallel statistic on the electrode that is being used. If the machine fails to find a recipe that it can use, it goes into the shutdown phase.%n%n§lShutdown:§r The machine enters a 6 second phase during which it does not process any recipes and does not use any power. After the shutdown phase, it needs to go through startup again before processing recipes.%n%n%nStatistics of this multiblock are mostly dependent on the electrode that is being used. This ranges from speed, parallels, OCs, and even the amount of amps per parallel.%n%nIf the used electrode drops below 30%% durability, there is a 5%% chance that the machine will have to go through the startup phase again.%n%nIf the used electrode drops below 10%% durability, there is a 2%% chance that the machine will §lvoid ALL§r outputs.

# Quest: Bate Bate Chocolate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7g.name=§9§lBate Bate Chocolate
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7g.desc=Abuela, will you teach us the chocolate song?%nCon mucho gusto%nWill you sing the chocolate song with us?%nGreat, sing along with Abuela!%n%nBate bate chocolate%nBate bate chocolate%nBate bate chocolate%nBate bate chocolate%n%nMix your chocolate, chocolate%nMix your chocolate, chocolate%nBate bate chocolate%nBate bate chocolate%n%nAside from mixing chocolate, the Industrial Mixing Machine offers §6§l8§r parallels per voltage tier and an additional §2§l100%%§r speed boost per tier of Item Pipe Casing.%n%n[note]Eventually, when you unlock §9UIV§r tiered glass, this can be given multi-amp hatches![/note]

# Quest: Play-Doh For Big Girls and Boys
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7w.name=§9§lPlay-Doh For Big Girls and Boys
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH7w.desc=I never wanna grow up, I wanna play with my §5§lIndustrial Extrusion Machine§r. This machine offers a §2§l3.5x§r speed boost and §6§l6§r parallels per voltage tier.%n%nYou can use multiple input buses with a different extruder shape in each and then throw the items to extrude into the bus with the appropriate shape.%n%nAlternatively, you can also use an Extrusion Bus. These are more expensive but come pre-loaded with all of the extruder shapes so you can manually set them without needing to create one.

# Quest: Best Thing Since Sliced Bread
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8A.name=§9§lBest Thing Since Sliced Bread
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8A.desc=When all you have is a machine full of knives, everything starts looking like bread.%n%nIn order for the §5§lIndustrial Cutting Factory§r to function, it will need to have a sawblade put into it. The performance of the machine is directly correlated with the quality of the sawblade put in.%n%nThe first type of sawblade available to craft is the §lTungsten Titanium Carbide Sawblade§r. It gives you §6§l2§r parallels per voltage tier, a §2§l2.5x§r speed boost, and a §3§l10%%§r EU discount. %n%n

# Quest: ZzzZZZzzzZtt
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8g.name=§9§lZzzZZZzzzZtt
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8g.desc=Need lots of oxygen or hydrogen? Maybe you just want to rip apart materials for tons of aluminium? Both are perfect tasks for this multiblock.%n%nThe §5§lIndustrial Electrolyzer§r is much more effective than its singleblock variant. It offers §6§l4§r parallels per voltage tier, a §2§l2.8x§r speed increase, and a §3§l10%%§r EU discount on all recipes. Sounds like a good deal to me!

# Quest: Frozen Stiff
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8w.name=§9§lFrozen Stiff
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH8w.desc=The Cryogenic Freezer is a direct upgrade to the §5§lVacuum Freezer§r. It allows for §6§l16§r parallels, operates at §2§l3x§r the speed, and offers a §3§l10%%§r EU discount.%n%nSimilar to the Volcanus, it has a running cost. It will consume §c§l10L§r of cryotheum per second while in operation. It must be supplied with Cryotheum via a Cryotheum Cooling Hatch

# Quest: Hephaestus' EBF
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9A.name=§9§lHephaestus' EBF
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9A.desc=The Volcanus Advanced EBF will process items faster than you can believe. You'll need a constant supply of Pyrotheum to use it. And coils.%n%n[note]This multi is IV, but uses 2 ZPM circuits.[/note]

# Quest: Spools and Spools
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9Q.name=§9§lSpools and Spools
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9Q.desc=Need enough wire to go around the world? Here you go.%n%nThe §5§lIndustrial Wire Factory§r is the only Wiremill multiblock, delivering §6§l4§r parallels per voltage tier, a §3§l25%%§r EU discount, and a scalable speed bonus of §2§l+50%%§r per Item Pipe Casing tier, ranging from §2§l1.5x§r speed while using Tin to an impressive §2§l5x§r speed while using Black Plutonium.%n%n[note]Glass tier is irrelevant; use what works best for you![/note]

# Quest: Bender, More Bending!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9g.name=§8§lBender, More Bending!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9g.desc=When you need plates by the thousands you use the §5§lIndustrial Bending Machine§r. It grants §2§l6x§r the speed and §6§l6§r parallels per voltage tier compared to the singleblock.

# Quest: Bezos Would Be Proud
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9w.name=§9§lBezos Would Be Proud
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH9w.desc=The §5§lAmazon Warehousing Depot§r is the ultimate multiblock for all your packing needs. Got tiny and small dusts coming out of your ears? This is the machine for you.%n%nThe AWD offers a very generous §6§l16§r parallels per voltage tier, as well as a §2§l2-8x§r speed bonus (depending on item pipe casing tier) and a §3§l25%%§r EU discount on all recipes.%n%n[note]Glass tier is irrelevant; use what works best for you![/note]

# Quest: Mega is Betta
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH_A.name=§b§lMega is Betta
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH_A.desc=For someone who needs to blast a truly §lridiculous§r amount of stuff, the §5§lExothermic Hearth§r is the machine for you. This monster machine can handle up to §6§l256§r parallel recipes at a time.%n%nIf allowed to heat up fully, the machine will run with §6§l2x§r as many parallels (though that takes around 30 minutes). You can optionally provide it §c§l250L/s§r of Pyrotheum to speed up this process by §2§l6x§r.%n%nThe glass tier limits the energy hatch tier that you can use. You can even use multiamp hatches from TecTech! If you want to use laser hatches, however, you need at least §2§nUV§r glass.

# Quest: Frostbite!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH_Q.name=§b§lFrostbite!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH_Q.desc=The §5§lEndothermic Fridge§r can process up to §6§l256§r parallels! You can also optionally provide §9§l250L/s§r of Cryotheum to the machine to give it a §2§l5x§r speed boost.%n%n[note]Eventually, you will be able to upgrade this to its T2 variant.[/note]

# Quest: Empty The Oceans
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBQ.name=§9§lEmpty The Oceans
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBQ.desc=If you stuck with fish for bio diesel this long, you can now make the §5§lZhuhai Fishing Port§r to get cartloads of fish and other byproducts.

# Quest: Putting All Those Workers Out of Jobs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBg.name=§b§lPutting All Those Workers Out of Jobs
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIBg.desc=The large scale auto-assembler will put things together for you, in volume. This multi is available in ZPM.%n%n[note]While it unlocks much later, has much fewer parallels, and has no TT energy hatch support in contrast to the Precise Assembler, it has one upside: If you use two energy hatches you can craft items of the next tier.[/note]

# Quest: Tower of Babylon
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJEA.name=§d§lTower of Babylon
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJEA.desc=Well what might happen if you combine 64 Distillation Towers in one...? You know... you get a 61 Block tall Multiblock.%n%nThis can handle up to §6§l256§r Recipes at once and provides a different set of bonuses depending on which distillation mode is active.

# Quest: Circuit Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKKQ.name=§d§lCircuit Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKKQ.desc=You'll need all of this to create 4 CALs, enough for a single series of circuits. If you only want one (for the microprocessors for example), just divide by 4.%n%nAssuming you got the necessary imprints on the LuV tab, you can now craft the CALs for the crystal processor series. We're starting with 4 since you'll need one per circuit, the imprint is not removable. And yes this means you need one for every circuit type you want to make with the CAL.%n%nAs an Assembly Line, it generally works like the normal one, with different items in each bus, but since it's only one item per CAL, it's far easier to use, and the recipe is cheaper too.%n%nThe CAL uses 'wraps' to make 16 of a circuit at a time (aside from ULV and LV circuits), saving you time, EU, and Soldering Alloy (or Indalloy). You make the wraps in an Assembler with 16 of the item and Polyethylene.%n%n[note]BTW you can change out the Hatches and Buses for better ones, but you still need to keep ingredient order. Also, CAL grants 4/4 OC.[/note]

# Quest: Cool Guys Don't Look At Explosions
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxQ.name=§9§lCool Guys Don't Look At Explosions
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxQ.desc=They automate them instead.%n%nCompared to a regular Implosion Compressor, the §5§lDensity^2§r has §2§l2x§r the speed, and gives §6§l1 + (Tier/2)§r parallels.%n%n[note]This multi is IV, but uses platline materials and ZPM circuits.[/note]

# Quest: Let Me Fabricate a New Universe...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxg.name=§b§lLet Me Fabricate a New Universe...
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxg.desc=This multi is dedicated to producing UUM and Scrap. It is one of the hardest GT++ multis to craft, but you will be able to replicate many things if you get it working.%n%n[note]This multi is traditionally UV but can technically be made in ZPM.[/note]

# Quest: I Want SOLIDS Not LIQUIDS!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxw.name=§9§lI Want SOLIDS Not LIQUIDS!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKxw.desc=For when your ABS isn't the right machine. Also uses coils.%n%nNote that this is a multiblock version of the alloy smelter, not a solid version of the alloy blast smelter.

# Quest: Steamy Mincer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzA.name=§c§lSteamy Mincer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzA.desc=This is an upgraded version of your trusty ol' Steam Macerator. As a 3x3 Multiblock, it might seem expensive if you're in the Steam Age. However, the processing time per ore is so low that you can sustain your beginner's ore processing system with it!%n%nThe main reason to switch from this is the HV Macerator, which unlocks a slot for additional byproducts gained from the macerating step of ore processing. The Steam Grinder, in comparison, will only return the first item shown in the recipe output. However, this will do just fine until HV!%n%n§3The Steam Grinder can only process recipes up to LV Tier.

# Quest: MABS
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM1Q.name=§2§l§nMABS
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM1Q.desc=This unholy union between Mega and GT++ must be the work of some madman. It is the ultimate metallurgical furnace to make your alloys with up to 256 parallels. Using better coils and glass also boosts its speed and reduces energy costs!%n%nThe glass tier limits both the energy hatch tier and the recipe tier. As with other multis, UEV glass unlocks all tiers and UV glass is needed for lasers.%n%nGlass tiers gate recipe tiers, for example UHV recipes need UHV glass.

# Quest: Another Chemical Multiblock?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMig.name=§d§lAnother Chemical Multiblock?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMig.desc=You probably have built a lot of Large Chemical Reactors by now. With the powerful 4/4 OC it is one of the strongest multiblocks there is. But what if even that is not enough to satisfy your chemical needs? You can't make it faster after using your best energy hatches available.%n%nFear not, we have a solution for you: The Mega Chemical Reactor. It lets you do 256 parallels for your LCR recipes! And you can still overclock after that if you provide enough power.%n%nIt only unlocks in LuV as it needs 7 Fusion Coil Blocks. Check with your hologram projector to see how it is built and what you need.%n%nThe glass tier limits the energy hatch tier that you can use. You can even use multiamp hatches from TecTech! If you want to use laser hatches however you need at least UV glass.

# Quest: Mass Processing in LuV
betterquesting.quest.ECDllKcSQ4SONHHfkfO0yw.name=§d§lMass Processing in LuV
betterquesting.quest.ECDllKcSQ4SONHHfkfO0yw.desc=As you enter LuV, fewer mass processing multiblocks are available as you replace old setups with new systems and scale up the multiblocks you've already built - there are still some important upgrades in these higher tiers, though.%n%nDefinitely don't miss out on the Circuit Assembly Line or you'll be kicking yourself later.

# Quest: Clean Implosions?!
betterquesting.quest.IlCOpa8bR9WbOjSOPxZIlA.name=§4§l§nClean Implosions?!
betterquesting.quest.IlCOpa8bR9WbOjSOPxZIlA.desc=Introducing the bigger (and better) Implosion Compressor, the Electric Implosion Compressor.%n%nThe §5§lElectric Implosion Compressor§r does not need any explosive and only needs electricity, isn't that very nice!%n%nFurthermore it gains extra parallels §6§l4^(Tier - 1)§r based on the containment block used in the middle.%n%nTier 1: Neutronium Block%nTier 2: Infinity Block%nTier 3: transcendent Metal Block%nTier 4: Spacetime Block%nTier 5: Universium Block%n%n[note]The minimum allowed energy hatch tier is one tier below the recipe tier, so you'll want to start with at least 2 UHV energy hatches for now.[/note]

# Quest: Extraction Point
betterquesting.quest.Itn1KOiISHSbXzoDd2BB8w.name=§8§lExtraction Point
betterquesting.quest.Itn1KOiISHSbXzoDd2BB8w.desc=Nothing turns solids to liquids faster than the Large Fluid Extractor - not yet, anyways. You'll need to make both Heating and Solenoid Coils for this multiblock.%n%n[note]This multiblock is technically EV, but it will demand a lot of tungstensteel.[/note]

# Quest: More Steam, More Pressure!
betterquesting.quest.Plg8vg0gS9Ks2Ddc5sIVOg.name=§c§lMore Steam, More Pressure!
betterquesting.quest.Plg8vg0gS9Ks2Ddc5sIVOg.desc=How do you compress things in the Steam Age? Simple, putting a lot of steam in one place, under high pressure, can apply a force to compress things...%n%nLet's just make it bigger. With the Steam Squasher, you can have a Compressor in a much larger scale, similarly to the other Steam Multiblocks. If you feel like compressing recipes are taking too long, which they probably are, this is a good solution to your problems.%n%nOnce the multi forms, provide lots of steam to get lots of compressed items.

# Quest: Insane Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.RFgYQ7LAQD-p1gHMaeg5Sg.name=§9§lInsane Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.RFgYQ7LAQD-p1gHMaeg5Sg.desc=Upon reaching the land of IV machinery, you can put together even more multis and speed up your automation!%n%nMany of the multiblocks from IV tier onwards use special alloys, which either need to be cooked like any ingots you've used before (in a Furnace or EBF), but there are also alloys which have to be made in the Alloy Blast Smelter (ABS), as a fluid, which then needs to be solidified.%n%nThe multis that need ABS alloys are further down. To unlock their quests, you will first need to craft the ABS itself. However, there is a large assortment of machines you can craft without it, just by having the respective IV singleblock equivalent and some other resources.%n%nThose will be here... but you might be able to find some more, if you look closely through NEI. Good luck!

# Quest: L.A.T.E.X. Cable Coater
betterquesting.quest.RV7RYWwgRSaI4oNfhfZljw.name=§5§lL.A.T.E.X. Cable Coater
betterquesting.quest.RV7RYWwgRSaI4oNfhfZljw.desc=The §5L§raminated §5A§rpplication and §5T§rhermal §5E§rnclosure e§5X§rocoater (§5L.A.T.E.X.§r) is a multiblock dedicated to coating cables.%n%nYou will be making a LOT of cables during your playthrough... Why bog down your assembler when you can use the LATEX instead? The LATEX gives §2§l2x§r the speed with a §3§l15%%§r EU discount, and generously offers §6§l8§r parallels per voltage tier.%n%nIf that's not convincing enough, you also get an additive §2§l6.25%%§r rubber discount per Item Pipe Casing tier.%n%n[note]Once you eventually reach UV, you will be able to create an Elastic Singularity for additional perks![/note]

# Quest: The Form of the Former Former: Reformed
betterquesting.quest.UAy2m9SaSua5RZEb3ZENXw.name=§8§lThe Form of the Former Former: Reformed
betterquesting.quest.UAy2m9SaSua5RZEb3ZENXw.desc=Should you require a formidable former, for formatively forming formal forms, you'll want to create an §5§lIndustrial Forming Press§r. It grants §2§l6x§r the speed and §6§l6§r parallels per voltage tier compared to the singleblock.

# Quest: See You Lather
betterquesting.quest.VJN1qfd5SjCkm7CXVd9Pag.name=§8§lSee You Lather
betterquesting.quest.VJN1qfd5SjCkm7CXVd9Pag.desc=Just in time for the huge number of crystal rods you'll need to get your Applied Energistics system up and running, the Industrial Precision Lathe!%n%nThe number of recipes that can be processed in parallel by the IPL depends on the item pipe casing.%n§9(Parallel = Item Pipe Casing Tier * 8)§r%n%nAdditionally, it has 4x the speed on all recipes compared to the singleblock of that voltage and only consumes 80%% of the EU/t normally required

# Quest: Steam Blender?
betterquesting.quest.WEwrzX4ZRkSxJ3M6cBesfA.name=§c§lSteam Blender?
betterquesting.quest.WEwrzX4ZRkSxJ3M6cBesfA.desc=Why use fancy wiring and circuitry to blend dusts together when you can do the same thing with steam and pistons? The Steam Blender is the largest of these Steam Multiblocks and can handle your mixing needs for a while, having more parallel than an LV singleblock Mixer.%n%n[note]This Multiblock can only process recipes up to LV tier.[/note]

# Quest: Steam Fusing?
betterquesting.quest.WGhhKERfRTiJXKZEPoRf1Q.name=§c§lSteam Fusing?
betterquesting.quest.WGhhKERfRTiJXKZEPoRf1Q.desc=Singleblock Alloy Smelters not fast enough for you? Look no further than the Steam Fuser. This will make light work of your alloy smelter tasks at a fraction of the steam cost and a much faster speed. %n(Check out the tooltip for more info!)%n%nWhile the NEI requirements show borosilicate glass, you can substitute any HV tier glass in its place like warded glass, quite clear glass, or fused quartz. If you end up using borosilicate; boron can be obtained from electrolyzing borax.%n%n[note]Will only process up to LV tier recipes[/note]

# Quest: Taking Things Apart
betterquesting.quest.XA467S8MQtCEPy6L23eEEA.name=§5§lTaking Things Apart
betterquesting.quest.XA467S8MQtCEPy6L23eEEA.desc=You probably haven't thought about the extractor in a while. Is your steam extractor still collecting dust somewhere? Well, if you do find yourself needing to extract things quick, (processing industrial quantities of flowers, maybe?) pick up the Dissection Apparatus.%n%n[note]This multi gets additional parallels based on tier of item pipe casing, so use the best one you can get![/note]

# Quest: Advanced Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.ZIotzqvnRiKu1_1Hb9i1dg.name=§d§lAdvanced Assembly Line
betterquesting.quest.ZIotzqvnRiKu1_1Hb9i1dg.desc=This is the advanced assembly line from §6GigaGram§rFab.%n%nIt supports item pipelining. That is, it will mimic a real assembly line by consuming ingredients one by one instead of all at start. In effect, it offers a parallelism up to however many item inputs this recipe requires. You can think of an advanced assembly line as a collection of slices which are capable of processing each step independently from other slices. It will start processing once the input bus contents align with any stored data stick. The first slice will consume the input in Bus #1. After (recipe time/number of inputs) time, the first slice's work is concluded and will start the second slice. At the same time, first slice will look for input in input bus #1. If there are still enough input there slice #1 will start working again.%n%nThe terminal slice (the n-th slice, where n is number of item input in recipe) will put the recipe output in output bus when it has concluded its work. Whenever a non-terminal slice finished its work, it will try to pass the work onto next slice. If the next slice cannot find the materials in its input bus, the just-finished slice will remain in [warn]STUCK[/warn] state and hang the assembly line. To help locate these [warn]STUCK[/warn] assembly lines, the controller's front face will have its status light turned orange.%n%nThe EU/t cost of this machine is number of slices active multiplied by the original recipe EU/t. [warn]STUCK[/warn] slices do not consume power. It will use the worst energy supplying hatch's input voltage for recipe tier calculation and normal 2/4 OC. With exotic energy hatches, it can overclock beyond usual voltage tier, but will consume even more power than usual 2/4 OC. Every §2laser overclock§r will add 0.3 to the power exponent. 1 §2laser overclock§r will have 50%% recipe time and use 430%% power. 2 §2laser overclocks§r will have 25%% recipe time and use 1978%% power. Will not overclock beyond 1 tick. Machine first tries to parallelize, then normal 2/4 OC, then §2laser overclock§r.

# Quest: Advanced Autoclaving
betterquesting.quest._dFgSThoQTWgM696ykr2Gw.name=§d§lAdvanced Autoclaving
betterquesting.quest._dFgSThoQTWgM696ykr2Gw.desc=In LuV, you can make the Industrial Autoclave. This is a huge multiblock with many scaling factors - it is also extremely powerful. You'll definitely want to pick one of these up to process crystal chips quickly for the crystal circuit line.%n%n[note]Coils, pipe casings, and item pipe casings are all extremely important to this multi's scaling. Use the best ones you have![/note]

# Quest: Megalomania
betterquesting.quest.a6S75xGeQ4uu1qR1deuOfQ.name=§b§lMegalomania
betterquesting.quest.a6S75xGeQ4uu1qR1deuOfQ.desc=In ZPM, you now have the ability to construct very powerful mega machines. These absolute titans will boost your production to levels never-before-seen, at a price.%n%n[note]To get real benefit from these multis, you will want to use lots of power and take advantage of their extreme parallelization.[/note]

# Quest: ...With The Power of Science!
betterquesting.quest.bLAFkZX-RHGRFAz-C93aeQ.name=§b§l...With The Power of Science!
betterquesting.quest.bLAFkZX-RHGRFAz-C93aeQ.desc=This multiblock will allow you to use all that UU-Matter that your Matter Fabricator makes, not that you don't have anything else to do with it...%n%n[note]This multi is traditionally UV, but can technically be made in ZPM.[/note]

# Quest: You've Gotta Keep 'Em Separated
betterquesting.quest.bkEol9zuRiiCMwMUopFHhg.name=§9§lYou've Gotta Keep 'Em Separated
betterquesting.quest.bkEol9zuRiiCMwMUopFHhg.desc=When you need to polarize magnets or separate magnetic materials, look to the MFE! This multiblock requires an electromagnet to be inserted into its housing - better magnets, better bonuses. In IV, you'll be stuck with an Iron Electromagnet, though.%n%n[note]At the final tier of electromagnet, you can use TecTech multi-amp hatches. Might be good to remember when you're processing a certain magnetic material...[/note]

# Quest: Cracking the World
betterquesting.quest.d5Fxz8ClQQCXy9GN_m9BrA.name=§6§lCracking the World
betterquesting.quest.d5Fxz8ClQQCXy9GN_m9BrA.desc=How much oil do you need? Maybe you're after Naquadah Fuel or Radox. Either way, this massive structure can handle it, boasting §6§l256§r parallels.

# Quest: An End To Deforestation
betterquesting.quest.fLH_QDPRR6mgCK0PL5iWmA.name=§9§lAn End To Deforestation
betterquesting.quest.fLH_QDPRR6mgCK0PL5iWmA.desc=This multiblock is the perfect solution to high-speed tree farming. Do you need wood for charcoal or benzene power? Nuts for seed oil? Leaf blocks for decoration? Look no further!%n%nThe Tree Growth Simulator can farm almost any tree in the game, and produces all the items you would get by chopping it down normally. It does all this in a compact area, without any lag from growing a real tree.%n%nFirst, place any sapling in the controller slot of the multiblock. Then, insert tools appropriate for the part of the tree you want to harvest in an input bus. Give the machine power, turn it on, and be ready to get flooded by the outputs.%n%nDifferent tools are required to gather different parts of the tree:%n - Saw for logs%n - Branch Cutter for saplings%n - Shears for leaves%n - Knife for fruit%nBetter versions of the tools (Chainsaw, Grafter, ...) will increase the yield! Check the tooltip of the controller block for details.%n%nYou can even use multiple different tools together, and the machine will harvest several different products at the same time!%n%nNote that the tools used will slowly lose durability, so for long-term operation you might want to set up an automatic replacement system.%n%n[note]You can optionally use grass in place of the dirt blocks during construction.[/note]%n%n[warn]While this machine only requires IV, it is quite expensive to make early in the tier. You will need 16 ZPM circuits and some fancy alloys.[/warn]

# Quest: Can It!
betterquesting.quest.gMRufFtRRRa30LE21boFNQ.name=§5§lCan It!
betterquesting.quest.gMRufFtRRRa30LE21boFNQ.desc=If you've ever needed to wait on a Canning Machine to fill up your supply of tin cans, or  to make mountains of coolant, consider the TurboCan Pro. This multiblock acts as both machines and has significant bonuses - when the time comes that you decide you need it!

# Quest: Spinmatron-2737
betterquesting.quest.p4BZRIJZQKON4zmHeIqcoA.name=§b§lSpinmatron-2737
betterquesting.quest.p4BZRIJZQKON4zmHeIqcoA.desc=Tired of spamming Centrifuges already? %n%nAlas, with your newfound ZPM technology you can finally fabricate a Centrifuge with some real power; §5§lThe Spinmatron-2737§r!%n%nThe Spinmatron§r comes with a litany of advantages compared to the regular centrifuge multiblock, including a §2§l3x§r Speed boost, a §2§l30%%§r reduction in EU usage, and a malleable number of parallels.%n%nUnlike the generic turbine that comes stock in a normal Centrifuge, the Spinmatron§r graciously allows you to choose the quality of the turbines that go into the machine. You can add between §9§l2-8§r turbines depending on the machine tier, each turbine will increase the parallel amount by [§94 * Turbine Material Tier§r]. §3(You'll want to avoid using smaller, non-huge turbines!)§r%n%nThis efficiency comes at a cost however, and will require [§9Recipe Tier * 10§r] L/s of §5Kerosene§r in order to run. This can optionally be switched out with §5Biocatalyzed Propulsion Fluid§r for a §2§l1.25x§r parallel multiplier once you've reached §4UEV§r.%n%nAdditionally there are three modes that come unique to the Spinmatron:%n%n- §dLight§r -> Gives increased speed in exchange for only being able to process [§9Voltage Tier - 3§r] recipes%n%n- §6Normal§r -> No changes%n%n- §aHeavy§r -> Grants the ability to craft Heavy Mode dependent recipes in exchange for reducing your parallels by §c§l32x§r and consuming §5Biocatalyzed Propulsion Fluid§r.%n%n[note]Checkout the tooltip for more information![/note]%n%n[warn]Use the GUI for adding turbines; don't add them to the rotor assemblies.[/warn]

# Quest: High Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.pKSx6HEUS0WkL6qkwo742g.name=§5§lHigh Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.pKSx6HEUS0WkL6qkwo742g.desc=이제 규모를 좀 더 키울 시간입니다! HV 티어에선 여러 강력한 멀티블럭들을 접할 수 있습니다. 특히 눈독들여야 할 기계는,항상 완벽한 효율로 오버클럭이 적용되는 §l대형 화학 반응기(Large Chemical Reactor)§r와,결과물을 단 하나만 선택해서 뽑아내던 기존과 달리 증류되는 모든 부산물을 한 번에 얻을 수 있게 해주는 §l증류탑(Distillation Tower)§r을 눈여겨보시기 바랍니다.%n%n이 두 가지가 있겠네요. 이 말고도 여러가지 유용한 멀티블럭들이 있습니다.

# Quest: Under Pressure
betterquesting.quest.qDZZLi21TrmdWXwo_KimIw.name=§8§lUnder Pressure
betterquesting.quest.qDZZLi21TrmdWXwo_KimIw.desc=Bigger, better, faster. The Large Electric Compressor does about what you would expect.

# Quest: STEAM-POWERED BREAKTHROUGH
betterquesting.quest.quLxATDCQFWsrZRuh_gspA.name=§c§lSTEAM-POWERED BREAKTHROUGH
betterquesting.quest.quLxATDCQFWsrZRuh_gspA.desc=You should have quite the collection of single block Steam machines by now. While these may have gotten you through processing small amounts of materials, there will be a time when you will have to process a multitude of items. This is where Multiblocks come in.%n%nWhile these Multiblocks have a material cost that is way higher than their single block counterparts, they have certain bonuses: they use less Steam, and they can process recipes in parallel, which means that a single recipe cycle can craft multiple items at once, if the Steam provided is enough to sustain it.%n%nThey do however have some quirks that need to be taken care of:%n%n-These Multiblocks require §4§lvery specific§r I/O blocks, use only those that are part of the quest%n-They process up to 8 items, where the Basic Tier is made of Bronze and High Pressure Tier is made of Steel (checkout the Multiblock Preview in NEI which will show you different levels of tiers)%n-The Tier and amount of parallel processing can be seen via WAILA if you are looking at the Controller Block%n%n[note]With this quest, you have started your journey with Mass Processing. However, don't get too excited quite yet. While there are some Multiblocks accessible in the Steam Age, most of them only unlock in EV or later, including better versions of these Multiblocks.[/note]

# Quest: Thermic Heating Device
betterquesting.quest.rVvLhN6YTUKhminacygRVg.name=§9§lThermic Heating Device
betterquesting.quest.rVvLhN6YTUKhminacygRVg.desc=The §5§lThermic Heating Device§r is the multiblock edition of the Fluid Heater, offering §6§l8§r parallels per voltage tier at over §2§l2x§r the speed and for only §3§l90%%§r of the EU cost.%n%nThis can be useful now for Bauxite and Ruthenium processing but if you choose not to use it then definitely keep it in mind for later as you will eventually want it for Growth Catalyst!

# Quest: Steam Stomping!
betterquesting.quest.s6AEHSKiQe2XveT_oDZbZg.name=§c§lSteam Stomping!
betterquesting.quest.s6AEHSKiQe2XveT_oDZbZg.desc=While the Forge Hammer is quite fast already, why not build this upscaled version and make it even faster? With the Steam Presser, you can unleash the full force of steam on whatever material you feed it. Watch blocks break apart and rods get smashed together faster than ever-at least until you gain access to more advanced technology.%n%n§3The Steam Presser can only process recipes up to LV Tier.

# Quest: Engraving With Style
betterquesting.quest.uP_FwHb_QTyAPaoZ80u74A.name=§9§lEngraving With Style
betterquesting.quest.uP_FwHb_QTyAPaoZ80u74A.desc=Sick of having to swap out lenses or make tens of laser engravers for your cleanroom? The Hyper-Intensity Laser Engraver is here for you. This multiblock can handle all of your engraving needs.%n%nBy using more powerful §lLaser Source Hatches§r in the structure, you can gain more parallels and run higher tier recipes.%n%n[note]Laser source hatches are usually used for power transmission, but not here! No matter what laser hatch you use, it will NOT change the power input of HILE - it is determined by the standard energy hatch as usual.[/note]

# Quest: Extreme Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.w5O5rPL_Q_GDp8lxWMd0DQ.name=§8§lExtreme Voltage Multiblocks
betterquesting.quest.w5O5rPL_Q_GDp8lxWMd0DQ.desc=You might already have a Steam Multiblock or the Large Sifter. But in EV, IV, and the following tiers you unlock multiblocks for (almost) every GT machine. And some more on top of that!%n%nMost of them are made to do the same GT processing as the singleblock machines you've been using, but much faster. The multis can have up to three bonuses: energy savings, faster recipe time and parallels, which mean that a single recipe cycle can craft multiple items at once, if the power provided is enough to sustain it.%n%nThe variety of structures and intricacies of these new multis can go far beyond simpler multis like the EBF, LCR or VF. While some are simple cuboids, others come with more diverse mechanics and conditions to work properly. In return, they can be extremely powerful, so keep an eye out for them!

# Quest: Pressure Washing!
betterquesting.quest.zorY0c3BQuqLJp7ThOLG-g.name=§c§lPressure Washing!
betterquesting.quest.zorY0c3BQuqLJp7ThOLG-g.desc=If you have been processing the ores you have gathered until now, you will have come across a variety of crushed ores. Since these are quite dirty, you will have to clean them up to get certain byproducts. But how do you clean up this multitude of crushed ores? By using a Steam Purifier, of course! With a steady flow of Steam and a bit of Water, you can wash away impurities and get Purified Crushed Ores in no time.%n%nIf you're tired of waiting forever for your ores to clean up, this is your fix!%n%n§3This Multiblock has two modes, the default Washer Mode and a Simple Washer Mode. Simple Washers process ores considerably faster, but they do not give byproducts. Like other Multiblocks, the mode can be toggled by the respective button inside the GUI or by right-clicking the Controller with a Screwdriver. Since all ore washing recipes are LV, this Multiblock can run all of them.


## Quest Line: How to Generate Power
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQ.name=How to Generate Power
betterquesting.questline.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACQ.desc=If there's a way to generate EU, it'll be on this tab, so check back after a new milestone to see if anything became available.

# Quest: Marie Curium?
betterquesting.quest.3r7tJ7_bTuePzsh-B_jyIQ.name=Marie Curium?
betterquesting.quest.3r7tJ7_bTuePzsh-B_jyIQ.desc=It's like cured meat... no, not at all, many sacrifices were made on the path to understanding radioactivity, may they be remembered forever. This goes to you, Marie and Pierre Curie.%n%nThis is the only non-plasma produced in a fusion reaction in this entire chain. That's not the important part, though: the important part is that [warn]this is one of the bottlenecks of the chain.[/warn] For every reactor running the final recipe, you will need around 0.144 reactors of this, so you won't make it to a compact at the end with just one mk1 reactor. Expect to follow the count of the second-to-last recipe, the Advanced Nitinol one.

# Quest: XL Turbo Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.4HoSq97QT3G63VJFeV_0ZQ.name=§8§lXL Turbo Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.4HoSq97QT3G63VJFeV_0ZQ.desc=The first of the XL Turbines. Because this is the first, this quest will include an explanation for the mechanics shared across all XL Turbines.%n%nEach XL Turbine can hold 12 turbine items inside, but its total speed is 16x higher than the regular multiblock equivalent. Make sure all the turbine items inside are of the same material, and also that you can provide enough input to match the flow rate that the multi needs! If you need even more speed, you can enable Loose Mode with a screwdriver on the controller, which can greatly increase turbines' flow rate while decreasing the efficiency.%n%nThese huge turbines also support TecTech hatches, so you can use multi-amp dynamos with a much higher output amount than normal, or even laser outputs later on to sustain the hundreds of millions of EU/t that the strongest turbines can produce.%n%nEach of the 5 turbines takes in the same fuels as their smaller counterparts, with some exceptions that will be mentioned in the respective quest. This XL Steam Turbine only consumes Steam, as expected.%n%n[note]Glass can be any tier.[/note]

# Quest: Calcium Bottlenecking
betterquesting.quest.9j1Iwd3KRG6jqLI9m6YDKQ.name=Calcium Bottlenecking
betterquesting.quest.9j1Iwd3KRG6jqLI9m6YDKQ.desc=Craft yourself some bone-strengthening Calcium in plasma form.%n%nThis step is almost twice as fast as the Boron one, so you only need half the reactors, plus one, or the tier above the reactors on the Boron side. It would normally be a lot slower, but the next step needs only a small amount of Calcium.%n%nKeep in mind that, at the end of each of the three fusion chains, the plasma amount gets multiplied, which means that most of your bottlenecks will be near the end of the entire setup, if you're going for Celestial Tungsten Plasma.%n%nYou will need 2.13 reactors with this recipe to feed 1 reactor with the next step.

# Quest: Portable Clean Energy IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA2A.name=§9§lPortable Clean Energy IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA2A.desc=This is the IV version.

# Quest: MV Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWQ.name=§6§lMV Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAWQ.desc=Having moved up to MV, you can continue using Steam. However, it's not a great idea to stay here, and other fuel types will be more useful to you instead. This is because Steam Turbine efficiency drops quickly with every tier (this one is only 75%%), and the Steam itself needs big pipes to carry it around, compared to Benzene or Diesel.%n%nThat said, if you want to keep using this, then it's a good idea to build a Large Bronze Boiler or, later on, a Large Steel Boiler. You will need lots of solid fuel, probably Charcoal, so make sure you automate it! Definitely do not forget the water.

# Quest: Standard Nuclear Fuel: Uranium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAvw.name=§8§lStandard Nuclear Fuel: Uranium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAvw.desc=Just "regular" uranium fuel, nothing special about it. It produces 5x the power, and 4x the heat of thorium, while lasting 2/5 the time.%n%nMost fuel rods are basically this, but slightly modified. You generally get this from Mars and its moons, but you can get a little from centrifuging thorium if you want.%n%nBTW, one of the reactor types 'pulses' the reactor to turn it off once it gets too hot. You can pack in the rods and then cool it off for a while to get higher efficiency out of each rod. Try it if you like explosions.

# Quest: Tricky Nuclear Fuel: MOX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAwA.name=§8§lTricky Nuclear Fuel: MOX
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAwA.desc=Under normal conditions, produces the same amount of power as uranium, but MOX produces more power the more you let the reactor heat up. Try to come up with a heat-neutral design as close to the limit as possible to take advantage of this. It lasts 1/2 the time, and produces more heat once the reactor is over 50%%. A fuel for all the engineers out there.%n%n[note]You'll need to run a uranium reactor for a while to get some plutonium if you don't have another way to get it. Remember that there's more than 1 type![/note]%n%n[warn]Make sure to test in creative and/or use protection against explosions![/warn]

# Quest: Alternate Nuclear Fuel: Tiberium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAxg.name=§d§lAlternate Nuclear Fuel: Tiberium
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAxg.desc=They're the same as uranium but produce half as much heat. Given that there's no reactor designs floating around, and the fact that you need to go to Ross128ba, a T5 rocket (LuV) planet to get the tiberium, I'm gonna say they're probably not worth it. If you disagree, make a design and show it to people, 'kay?

# Quest: Obscenely Dangerous Nuclear Fuel: The Core
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB6g.name=§d§lObscenely Dangerous Nuclear Fuel: The Core
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAB6g.desc=For the truly insane mad scientists out there. Or people who can read a website (not guaranteed, trust me!). You HAVE to use coolant cells with it if you want power or to have it not explode after 1s.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at MV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD6w.name=§a§lPower of the Sun at MV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD6w.desc=The next solar panel you can make is the MV one. It gives 128 EU/t. You'll need to make some sunnarium first though.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 MV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7A.name=§a§lPower of the Sun 1x1 MV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7A.desc=Put those 128 EU panels on a block to make them placeable in the world.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at HV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7g.name=§9§lPower of the Sun at HV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7g.desc=The next solar panel you can make is the HV one. It generates 512 EU/t. First you need to produce enriched sunnarium by mixing irradiated uranium and sunnarium. The Avaritia 9x9 dire crafting table is required to make this and later panels.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 HV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7w.name=§9§lPower of the Sun 1x1 HV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAD7w.desc=Put those 512 EU panels on a block to make them placeable in the world.

# Quest: We Need Big Toys
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADDw.name=§5§lWe Need Big Toys
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADDw.desc=All your little turbines take up too much space? Are you running out of water? It's time to solve these problems. This Large Steam Turbine can help you produce a tremendous amount of energy. It will also distill water for you, so you can use the same water again inside your Large Boiler. Don't forget to make a rotor for the turbine and put inside the controller, otherwise this multiblock won't do anything.%n%nEach turbine has a specific optimal flow, the Steam flow that gives the highest fuel efficiency, the value shown on the turbine's tooltip. This is the flow you want to match, and you can use a Fluid Regulator as a cover to make it exactly what you want, but you can go beyond this flow to get an even higher EU/t value, at a loss of fuel efficiency. You can make turbines in 4 different sizes, with larger turbines producing more EU/t, but with varying amounts of fuel efficiency. Generally, Large is the best due to having the highest fuel efficiency and a good optimal flow rate%n%nWhen using turbines, be careful of flow rates. To find the optimal flow rate, you divide the optimal energy flow rate listed on the turbine, by the energy value for the plasma. You can also use the Large Turbine Calculator (there's a link on the main spreadsheet, which is linked to in discord), or scan the multiblock's controller while feeding it a minimal amount of plasma to see what the optimal flow is. Make sure to use a Fluid Regulator set to this flow rate for highest fuel efficiency, or go beyond it to get more EU/t at a cost to efficiency, with Steam Turbines being the worst at retaining efficiency beyond the optimal flow.%n%nIf you go beyond the optimal flow, you will get a higher EU/t value, but less fuel efficiency, and the maximum EU/t value depends on the turbine type and its Overflow Efficiency tier. For this type of turbine, tier 1 reaches the max at 150%% of optimal flow to produce 112%% of the EU/t, tier 2 reaches the max at 200%% of optimal flow to produce 133%% of the EU/t and tier 3 reaches the max at 250%% of optimal flow to produce 156%% of the EU/t. The closer you get to this maximum, the more fuel efficiency you're throwing away. Don't exceed your dynamo hatch's maximum EU/t output, though, or you will have problems!%n%nUse NEI with the appropriate long rod to find assembler recipes that will work for you. Or the spreadsheet. Long magnalium for small turbines, long titanium for normal turbines, etc.%n%nPre-moon, the best rotors are Shadow Metal or Vibrant Alloy.%n%nPost-moon, the best HV rotors are Shadow Metal or Oriharukon (this is IV-tier). Luckily, turbines are now fully functional with multi-amp dynamos, so give those a try if you need extra amps!%n%nFor additional choices, see the spreadsheet and Large Turbine Calculator.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at LV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADqA.name=§6§lPower of the Sun at LV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADqA.desc=The next solar panel you can make is the LV one. It generates 32 EU/t.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADqQ.name=§6§lPower of the Sun 1x1 LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADqQ.desc=Put those 32 EU panels on a block to make them placeable in the world. Use an MV assembler to combine the panel with an LV hull, a battery, and a robot arm. Now this panel will clean itself!

# Quest: Compressed Solar LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNA.name=§6§lCompressed Solar LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNA.desc=The power of the sun x10. This solar panel works like 10 regular ones, but costs only 8. How is this possible? Magic! NOTE: They give out GT EU. NO TRANSFORMER NEEDED!

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Potentia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNQ.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Potentia
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNQ.desc=Aren't you tired of voiding all that useless potentia essentia? Well here's the solution:%nA generator that consumes potentia and outputs GT EU NO TRANSFORMER NEEDED!

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Auram
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNg.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Auram
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNg.desc=This Generator is quite tricky. It requires Auram Essentia, that isn't that common, but its output is nice.

# Quest: Infused Solars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNw.name=Infused Solars
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFNw.desc=Compressed Solar Panels can be infused with Aspects for certain additional features. Check them out and choose one of them.

# Quest: Double Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOA.name=§6§lDouble Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOA.desc=100EU/t for 64x1EU/t Solars? Sounds like a good deal. Get one of these. They can be Infused as well.

# Quest: Even More Infused
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOQ.name=Even More Infused
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOQ.desc=You can infuse double or triple compressed solars as well.

# Quest: Triple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOg.name=§9§lTriple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOg.desc=Triple Compressed Solars. Yes, that's right. They are a bit more expensive than their lower counterparts, 512 Solars in total. But they give out 1,000 GT EU per tick and have no need to be cleaned. How so? Magic.

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Ignis
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOw.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Ignis
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFOw.desc=So, you got rid of the Potentia, maybe you don't want Ignis, but Potentia? Get this one to be able to burn Ignis.

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Arbor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPA.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Arbor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPA.desc=When using magical plants to get Praecantatio Essentia, you'll end up with a couple dozen of Arbor Essentia jars. But no worries! This generator runs on Arbor! Awesome!

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Aer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPQ.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Aer
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPQ.desc=Sugarcanes to power...? This generator runs on Aer Essentia, it might not be as powerful as its counterparts, but its fuel is cheap.

# Quest: Essentia Generator: Lucrum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPg.name=§6§lEssentia Generator: Lucrum
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFPg.desc=This highly-warped, high-power Essentia generator is a lifesaver, when you run out of energy. Just toss some gold into your Arcane Furnace and burn the Lucrum you get.

# Quest: HV Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFew.name=§5§lHV Steam Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFew.desc=Using Steam as your single power source in HV is pretty difficult. Your fuel automation will have to be very fast, your pipes will have to be very big and the final efficiency of HV Steam Turbines is 66%%, much lower than the other generators' 85%%.%n%nThis is best used with an efficient furnace, like the GT++ Advanced Furnaces, to power something specific like a farm. Powering your entire automation in your path to an EV, using only these, is a nightmare. If you want more efficiency out of your Steam, consider building a Large Steam Turbine.

# Quest: What Was That? I Can't Hear You Over the Engine!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFyQ.name=§9§lWhat Was That? I Can't Hear You Over the Engine!
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAFyQ.desc=The Extreme Combustion Engine is an upgrade to the Large Combustion Engine, the IV version that needs Tungstensteel instead of Titanium. The structure is essentially the same, and it's almost a 1:1 ratio between the two materials, so this is a good generator when you've accumulated several stacks of Tungstensteel.%n%nThe caveat is that it only accepts High Octane Gasoline. This is the last and most powerful type of combustion fluid made from Oil, and it has the longest processing line of them all. As a reward, it has an excellent §a2.5M EU per bucket§r, and you can burn it here alongside some Liquid Oxygen for almost §a4 IV amps per tick.%n%n§cThe Liquid Oxygen is very important, because it greatly boosts the speed of the multi and the fuel efficiency as well.§r It needs 40 L/s, so you will need more than one Vacuum Freezer to supply it continuously: for an ECE that is always running, you will need a double Vacuum Freezer, 1 EV and 1 HV. You can run fewer freezers if you overclock them, if the ECE isn't working all the time or if you upgrade to a Cryogenic Freezer,

# Quest: Power of the Sun at EV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGiA.name=§9§lPower of the Sun at EV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGiA.desc=The next solar panel you can make is the EV one. It generates 2048 EU/t.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGtw.name=§9§lPower of the Sun 1x1 EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGtw.desc=Put those 2048 EU panels on a block to make them placeable in the world.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at IV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGuA.name=§d§lPower of the Sun at IV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGuA.desc=The next solar panel you can make is the IV one. It generates 8192 EU/t. This is probably the last tier it's worth it to make solars, unless you just really like them.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGuQ.name=§d§lPower of the Sun 1x1 IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGuQ.desc=Put those 8192 EU panels on a block to make them placeable in the world.

# Quest: Do You Hear That Engine Revving?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGzA.name=§8§lDo You Hear That Engine Revving?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAGzA.desc=Your old and trusty combustion engines don't quite cut it anymore, not to mention they're polluting the place. If you want to keep burning liquids, you need to build a better engine. This multiblock can produce 1A of EV voltage by default and 3A if you supply it with oxygen. However, this power doesn't come for free - you need to supply the machine with small amounts of lubricant constantly (and oxygen if you want to boost both its efficiency and output).%n%nYou will also require 3 Input Hatches, a Muffler, and a Dynamo Hatch. Their tiers are up to you.%n%nCetane Boosted Diesel and High Octane Gasoline (HOG) are excellent fuel sources for this engine.%n%nYou will need to keep the area in front of the engine clear so it can pull enough air - not even torches.

# Quest: The Church of Benzene's Holy Altar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHTQ.name=§6§lThe Church of Benzene's Holy Altar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHTQ.desc=The MV Gas Turbine pairs excellently with Benzene, now that you can actually make it. Look at the "Bio for the Masses" tab for more details on how to go about it, or just check NEI. Benzene is renewable from trees, and it's a powerful source of EU that can keep you going for several tiers as long as you upgrade it with the new multiblocks you unlock over time.%n%nIt's a good idea to switch off Steam, since you need big pipes to carry that around and the fuel efficiency on Steam Turbines is lower. Instead, make a Pyrolyse Oven or an Advanced Coke Oven to make Charcoal faster, extract Benzene from it and run it through a few of these Gas Turbines.

# Quest: Diesel Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHTg.name=§6§lDiesel Power
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHTg.desc=The MV Combustion Generator burns Light Fuel faster than the LV version, but you can also automate Diesel and burn that instead, since it's even more powerful. It is arguably the easiest and most efficient way to generate lots of power for automation at this stage, and it'll last you a couple more tiers if you upgrade it as you go.%n%nAdditionally, Diesel can be used as fuel for the Copterpack, a good jetpack that makes it much easier to move around, inside and outside of your base. It's heavily recommended that you make one, if you have Diesel.%n%n[note]This will also unlock new quests in the Armors and Jetpacks tab.[/note]

# Quest: Fluid Regulator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHZQ.name=§6§lFluid Regulator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHZQ.desc=Turbines require precise amounts of fluids or else they will [warn]explode[/warn]. Use the fluid regulator on the pipe attached to the input bus to control the rate of fluids into the turbine. To raise the fluid limit, look at the right side of the regulator and:%n%n1L - Right-click with an empty hand%n16L - Right-click with a screwdriver%n256L - Right-click with a screwdriver while sneaking%n%nTo lower the fluid limit, do the same while looking at the left side. [note]If you shift-right-click on it you can use the interface which is more precise.[/note]%n%nUse the GTNH Power Planner linked below to find what to set it to, after deciding on a fuel. At GTNH, we do the math for you! For this at least.%n%n[url]https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1FTFdfmY_UWbTbFOyNzARKeI90pbHvPBH6M3JHJmaC-E/edit?usp=dsharing[/url]

# Quest: Gas Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHZg.name=§8§lGas Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHZg.desc=A Large Gas Turbine is more fuel-efficient than singleblock turbines, and can have lower pollution output with upgraded mufflers.%n%nYou will also need a Muffler and Dynamo Hatch to complete the multiblock. Don't forget to use a Fluid Regulator, to control the flow rate into the multi! It can usually be an LV Fluid Regulator, since the optimal flow is much lower here than in Steam Turbines.%n%nEach turbine material has a specific fuel efficiency (the higher, the more EU you get from the same amount of fuel), and the multi only reaches this efficiency if the fuel flow into it matches the optimal flow.%n%nIf you go beyond the optimal flow, you will get a higher EU/t value, but less fuel efficiency, and the maximum EU/t value depends on the turbine type and its Overflow Efficiency tier. For this type of turbine, tier 1 reaches the max at 150%% of optimal flow to produce 112%% of the EU/t, tier 2 reaches the max at 300%% of optimal flow to produce 180%% of the EU/t and tier 3 reaches the max at 450%% of optimal flow to produce 252%% of the EU/t. The closer you get to this maximum, the more fuel efficiency you're throwing away.%n%nFor the best turbine materials, see the spreadsheet and Large Turbine Calculator.

# Quest: Standard Nuclear Fuel II: Naquadah
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHaA.name=§9§lStandard Nuclear Fuel II: Naquadah
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHaA.desc=These are...not worth it. Go do something else with your enriched naquadah, like putting it in a naq gen if you want power. They work §oexactly§r the same as uranium other than materials cost/output.%n%n[note]PS: You can get Nq+ from both centrifuging Nq dust or processing the ore.[/note]%n%n[note]And why are they Naquadah rods when they're made of Enriched Naquadah?[/note]

# Quest: Tricky Nuclear Fuel II: Naquadria
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHaQ.name=§b§lTricky Nuclear Fuel II: Naquadria
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHaQ.desc=They're so not worth it I'm just going to give you back the materials. Like naquadah, they're the same as MOX other than materials.%n%n[note]PS: You can get Nq* from both centrifuging Nq or Nq+ dust, processing the ores, or thermal centrifuging the depleted Nq+ rods.[/note]

# Quest: Large Heat Exchanger - Fermat's Last
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHcQ.name=§8§lLarge Heat Exchanger - Fermat's Last
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHcQ.desc=The Large Heat Exchanger is a powergen multi that accepts a non-direct fuel, and doesn't output EU. What is it for, then? §7To heat up water with hot liquids, that's what!§r%n%nEffectively, it's a Steam Boiler that uses fluids instead of solids, but it's more complicated. The three sources of energy are Lava, Hot Coolant, and Hot Solar Salt. The salt is the most powerful, but hardest to get. Lava can be automated from Everburn Urns or a myriad of other options, Hot Coolant usually comes from Fluid Nukes, and Hot Solar Salt is produced in the Solar Tower.%n%nFor Lava, the LHE outputs §d160 L of Steam for every 1 L of Lava, up to 1000 L/s of Lava input§r (§a4000 EU/t§r at 100%% turbine efficiency). For Hot Coolant, the LHE outputs §d400 L of Steam for every 1 L of Hot Coolant, up to 800 L/s of input§r (§a8000 EU/t§r at 100%% turbine efficiency). For Hot Solar Salt, the LHE outputs §d2000 L of Steam for every 1 L of Hot Solar Salt, up to 160 L/s of input§r (§a8000 EU/t§r at 100%% turbine efficiency).%n%n§cIf you go above these input rates, the output becomes Superheated Steam, which needs to pass through a Large HP Steam Turbine before the regular Large Steam Turbine.§r The maximum input rate here is twice of what was before and the conversion rates are now §d1:80 for Lava§r, §d1:200 for Hot Coolant§r, and §d1:1000 for Hot Solar Salt§r. The energy output at 100%% turbine efficiency is §a12000 EU/t§r for Lava, §a24000 EU/t§r for Hot Coolant, and §a24000 EU/t§r for Hot Solar Salt.%n%n§6§lVery powerful, but complicated, and needs turbines!§r%n%nFor more information, visit [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Large_Heat_Exchanger[/url] or [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Fluid_Reactor[/url].

# Quest: Rocket Engine EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI9g.name=§8§lRocket Engine EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAI9g.desc=The Rocket Engine is a very dirty device which generates power out of rocket fuels at 80%% efficiency, and produces 250 to 2000 pollution/s.%n%n[note]There are 4 Rocket Fuels. Follow the Space Race tab quests to see how to make the rest. Expect to need more than one (probably several) Chemical Plants if you want to automate production.[/note]

# Quest: Kinetic Wind Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-A.name=§8§lKinetic Wind Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-A.desc=This is the EV version, it works the same.

# Quest: Kinetic Water Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-Q.name=§9§lKinetic Water Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-Q.desc=This is the IV version.

# Quest: Kinetic Wind Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-g.name=§9§lKinetic Wind Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-g.desc=This is the IV version.

# Quest: Kinetic Water Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-w.name=§d§lKinetic Water Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK-w.desc=This is the LuV version.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at LuV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK1g.name=§d§lPower of the Sun at LuV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK1g.desc=The LuV solar panel generates 32768 EU/t.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK1w.name=§d§lPower of the Sun 1x1 LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK1w.desc=This is the block version that doesn't need cleaning.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at ZPM Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2A.name=§2§l§nPower of the Sun at ZPM Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2A.desc=The ZPM solar panel generates 131072 EU/t.

# Quest: Power of the Sun at UV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2Q.name=§4§l§nPower of the Sun at UV Level
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2Q.desc=The UV solar panel generates 524288 EU/t.

# Quest: Power of the Sun 1x1 ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2g.name=§2§l§nPower of the Sun 1x1 ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2g.desc=This is the block version that doesn't need cleaning.

# Quest: Pocket Plasma EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2w.name=§d§lPocket Plasma EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK2w.desc=Assuming you don't want to set up something crazy every time you move your miners, you'll need some kind of SB to power them. This is one of the good options. You can just teleport the fuel instead.%n%n[note]You may note that the efficiency goes up rather than down as it goes up in tiers. Enjoy this small comfort, the multis are still way better.[/note]

# Quest: Pocket Plasma IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3A.name=§d§lPocket Plasma IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3A.desc=This is the IV version.

# Quest: Pocket Plasma LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3Q.name=§b§lPocket Plasma LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3Q.desc=This is the LuV version.

# Quest: Pocket Plasma ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3g.name=§b§lPocket Plasma ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3g.desc=This is the ZPM version.

# Quest: Pocket Plasma UV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3w.name=§2§l§nPocket Plasma UV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK3w.desc=This is the UV version.

# Quest: Rocket Engine IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4A.name=§9§lRocket Engine IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4A.desc=This is the IV version. It has 70%% efficiency, and produces 500 to 4000 pollution/s.

# Quest: Rocket Engine LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4Q.name=§d§lRocket Engine LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4Q.desc=This is the LuV version. It has 60%% efficiency, and produces 750 to 6000 pollution/s.

# Quest: How Many Forests Did You Cut Down to Power This?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4g.name=§5§lHow Many Forests Did You Cut Down to Power This?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4g.desc=This is the HV version, with the lowest efficiency so far of 85%%. You can offset that by just generating more Benzene, alongside Phenol and Toluene in a Distillation Tower, or use Naphtha instead... You have many options at this point, surely enough to fight the increasing power demands of your automation.%n%nBenzene doesn't get upgraded in HV, only in EV. You'll be able to make Nitrobenzene when you're there, and burn it in some turbines bigger than this one.

# Quest: Even Better Diesel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4w.name=§5§lEven Better Diesel
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK4w.desc=In HV, you unlock yet another generator, but also Cetane-Boosted Diesel. After a bunch of reactions, you can get a superpowered combustion fuel that is worth §a1M EU per bucket§r and run it for quite a while on these improved generators. You will also unlock the Distillation Tower here, so you might get even more fuel that you can burn in these generators.%n%nUnfortunately, the next fuel, unlocked in EV, doesn't come from Diesel. It's a completely different processing line, should you wish to tackle it later.

# Quest: Putting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5A.name=§2§lPutting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5A.desc=You've probably collected a ton of Creosote and have little to use it on. To fix that, build a Semifluid Generator and use it alongside Steam as a secondary power source! Singleblock generators will only use fuel if there is EU demand, so you might end up with a filled Creosote buffer if you aren't consuming enough EU.%n%nTo extract the Creosote from your Coke Ovens, you can use a Coke Oven Hatch and some fluid pipes of your choice.%n%nThere are other options to burn Creosote, like the Railcraft Liquid Boilers, but this is much cheaper and easier to set up, while still being efficient with Creosote (6x as efficient as Combustion Generators).

# Quest: Putting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators MV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5Q.name=§6§lPutting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators MV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5Q.desc=If you're still burning Creosote for power, you can get MV amps out of it with these machines. It won't last long, and definitely isn't a good main power source, but it'll give you some EU for your trouble.%n%nAlternatively, Heavy Fuel? It has the same EU per bucket as Benzene, 360k, and is the only semifluid with more than 100k per bucket. If you have it, and are not consuming enough for Diesel, you can use it this way.

# Quest: Putting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators HV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5g.name=§5§lPutting the 'Semi' Back Into Generators HV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5g.desc=If you've built Distillation Towers to improve your Oil or Benzene processing line, you might have ended up with some extra fuels that are semifluids, such as Heavy Fuel or Creosote. If you've accumulated them so much that they've started voiding, you can instead make an HV Semifluid Generator and get free power out of them!%n%nThe Creosote from one DT that is processing Wood Tar is enough to power the DT itself, depending on the fuel efficiency. One HV generator is just enough to power it.

# Quest: You Haven't Learned How to Separate Fluids Yet? Seriously?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5w.name=§8§lYou Haven't Learned How to Separate Fluids Yet? Seriously?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK5w.desc=This multi follows the same logic as the Large Combustion Engine, but it uses semifluids instead. If you have the need to burn any of those for power, like Heavy Fuel for example, you can put this together.%n%n[note]Check the Large Combustion Engine quest for more details.[/note]

# Quest: Acid Trip
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6A.name=Acid Trip
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6A.desc=This is the HV version. Will people really use this? Each stack of Redstone Dust is worth around 580k EU, so look at your storage and see what you have.

# Quest: Hallucinogenics Not Included
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6Q.name=§8§lHallucinogenics Not Included
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6Q.desc=This is the EV version. I hope you're not using this for primary power gen? At least, it has a pretty good efficiency of 88%% for an EV singleblock, and it's better than voiding the fluids that can be used as fuel here.

# Quest: Portable Clean Energy EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6g.name=§8§lPortable Clean Energy EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6g.desc=As long as you don't hold the fuel, that is. Very useful for your Mining rigs, the efficiency on these goes way up as they increase in tier. Though they require more Enriched Naquadah each tier (and Naquadria at ZPM).%n%n[note]The fuel is radioactive, dummy.[/note]

# Quest: Portable Clean Energy LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6w.name=§d§lPortable Clean Energy LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK6w.desc=This is the LuV version.

# Quest: Portable Clean Energy ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7A.name=§b§lPortable Clean Energy ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7A.desc=This is the ZPM version. It uses Naquadria now.

# Quest: Portable Clean Energy UV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7Q.name=§2§l§nPortable Clean Energy UV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7Q.desc=This is the UV version.

# Quest: Geothermal Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7g.name=§9§lGeothermal Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7g.desc=Turns lava into power, at very inefficient rates. Also, seems to produce way more pollution than it says. They also require you to be 2 tiers above the output amount, so, yeah.%n%n[note]Wasn't geothermal supposed to be environmentally friendly?[/note]

# Quest: Geothermal Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7w.name=§d§lGeothermal Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK7w.desc=The IV version. Almost certainly produces more pollution than it says.

# Quest: Geothermal Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8A.name=§2§l§nGeothermal Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8A.desc=The LuV version. Even if you use it with an Everburn Urn, would it even be useful?

# Quest: Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8Q.name=§8§lRadioisotope Thermoelectric Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8Q.desc=Runs forever on the fuel you give it. Puts out 1 EU/t, but doubles for each one added, up to 32 EU/t. Might be useful for a farm?

# Quest: Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8g.name=§9§lRadioisotope Thermoelectric Generator
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8g.desc=Runs for a reaaaally long time. Outputs an amount based on the fuel pellet given.%n%n241Am: 16 EU, 69875 days%n90Sr: 30 EU, 62640 days%n238Pu: 64 EU, 42982 days%n210Po: 480 EU, 34560 days

# Quest: Kinetic Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8w.name=§8§lKinetic Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK8w.desc=This is the EV version, it works the same.

# Quest: Kinetic Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9A.name=§9§lKinetic Power IV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9A.desc=This is the IV version.

# Quest: Kinetic Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9Q.name=§d§lKinetic Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9Q.desc=This is the LuV version.

# Quest: Kinetic Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9g.name=§b§lKinetic Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9g.desc=This is the ZPM version.

# Quest: Kinetic Water Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9w.name=§8§lKinetic Water Power EV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK9w.desc=This is the EV version, it works the same.

# Quest: Who Needs UV Solars When You Have Magic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJA.name=§5§l§nWho Needs UV Solars When You Have Magic
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKJA.desc=16,777,216 Solars!!! This single block can produce a maximum of 600m EU/t when in aqua form, that's balanced right... right?

# Quest: Kinetic Wind Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_A.name=§d§lKinetic Wind Power LuV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_A.desc=This is the LuV version.

# Quest: Kinetic Water Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_Q.name=§b§lKinetic Water Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_Q.desc=This is the ZPM version.

# Quest: Kinetic Wind Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_g.name=§b§lKinetic Wind Power ZPM
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_g.desc=This is the ZPM version.

# Quest: Quadruple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_w.name=§d§lQuadruple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAK_w.desc=4,096 Solars! Puts out 10000-32768 EU/t.

# Quest: This is Not How You Get Into Space
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKyg.name=§9§lThis is Not How You Get Into Space
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKyg.desc=This produces power out of Rocket Fuels. To see how to make them, look at the Space Race tab. These are specifically GT++ Rocket Fuels, and automating them for powergen in this multi will also provide you with endless fuel for your space travels.%n%nThe math regarding the Rocketdyne is complicated. Looking at the controller's tooltip helps, but the main gist of it is like this: provide Carbon Dioxide and make sure it doesn't run out, choose the EU/t you want to get, calculate the amount of fuel you need for the fuel you will use, and then provide enough Liquid Hydrogen to boost the multi, according to the EU/t value.%n%nYou will always want to have the Rocketdyne boosted, for several reasons. Assuming you have at least a buffered IV Dynamo Hatch, outputting close to the maximum on that hatch will lower the fuel efficiency, but not if it's boosted. Additionally, this multi doesn't consume fuel continuously, but with intervals of 1 second between consuming and not consuming, while generating power all the same. Boosting this consumption results in huge fuel efficiency, combined with the high fuel values of the Rocket Fuels.%n%n[warn]Beware, letting the dynamo overfill can lead to an explosion! Be sure you have a place to output the energy.[/warn]

# Quest: Deep Earth Heating Pump
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzg.name=§9§lDeep Earth Heating Pump
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKzg.desc=With the power of §cgeothermal energy§r, the Deep Earth Heating Pump can heat up Coolant or boil Distilled Water to create an energy source from the Earth's core.%n%nBy using a Heat Exchanger, you can convert the Hot Coolant into steam and use it in your turbines.%n%nAlternatively, you can make it output Superheated Steam directly, but only at 66%% of the efficiency the hot coolant can achieve

# Quest: UHT Resistant Mesh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL3g.name=§b§lUHT Resistant Mesh
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL3g.desc=§o*Slaps UHT Resistant Mesh* This bad boy can withstand so much heat!§r%n%nYou should probably automate this if you want to build and use the Dyson Swarm multiblock.

# Quest: Quintuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAA.name=§b§lQuintuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAA.desc=32,768 Solars! Puts out 100,000-131,072 EU/t.

# Quest: Sextuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAQ.name=§2§l§nSextuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAQ.desc=262,144 Solars! Puts out 1,000,000-2,097,152 EU/t.

# Quest: Septuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAg.name=§4§l§nSeptuple Compressed Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAg.desc=2,097,152 Solars! Puts out 10,000,000-33,554,432 EU/t.

# Quest: Toss Your Magic Junk in Here LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAw.name=§6§lToss Your Magic Junk in Here LV
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALAw.desc=And receive power in return. Especially good with Nether Stars if you've got a bunch. Or practically any magic material item (not crafted stuff mostly).

