# Quest: Hyper Acceleration!
betterquesting.quest.KM9gm3HCTa2OGPWlHHl4fw.name=Hyper Acceleration!
betterquesting.quest.KM9gm3HCTa2OGPWlHHl4fw.desc=Hyper-Acceleration cards are a faster version of the basic acceleration cards. %n%n[note]Hyper-Acceleration cards can only be placed in:[/note]%n%n§cME IO Port (3)%nME Fluid Import Bus (4)%nME Fluid Export Bus (4)%n%n§rIn an IO Port, the Hyper-Acceleration Card will transfer items at a rate of: %n%n§61x Cards: 4,096 items/tick%n2x Cards: 32,768 items/tick%n3x Cards: 262,144 items/tick%n%n§rIn ME Fluid Buses, the Hyper-Acceleration Card will transfer fluids at a rate of:%n%n§61x Cards: 4,096,000 mb/tick%n2x Cards: 32,768,000 mb/tick%n3x Cards: 262,144,000 mb/tick

# Quest: Advanced Neutronium Tech
betterquesting.quest.LsZndSrhSAGSi60QlbnDtg.name=Advanced Neutronium Tech
betterquesting.quest.LsZndSrhSAGSi60QlbnDtg.desc=Now that you've unlocked the neutronium energy cell, you can combine it with other objects to make powerful upgrades to your AE capabilities.%n%nCombining with an ME controller gives you a controller with infinite energy.%n%nCombining with a cable anchor & quartz fiber gives you a replacement for the quartz fiber cable that has infinite energy.%n%nCombining with an advanced card will give you an energy card that will allow you to upgrade your wireless terminal to have infinite energy, wherever you go.%n%n[note]It is HIGHLY recommended you use these tools wherever possible on main-nets and sub-nets as they are huge TPS savers[/note]

