betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ7w.name=§4§l§nWireless 3.0
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJ7w.desc=This upgrade allows unlimited range. You don't even need a Wireless Access Point!

# Quest: Obtaining Ender Pearls
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZA.name=§6§lObtaining Ender Pearls
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZA.desc=You can hunt endermen the Vanilla way to get a chance at Ender Pearls, you can purchase Endermen spawn eggs, or try your luck in the End.%n%nOr you can get cruel, and stuff one into a smeltery to melt it down into delicious Liquid Ender and cast pearls from it.%n%nYou monster.%n%nSome of the dungeons have Spawner of Enderman, so you can do whatever you want with it.%n%nTo prevent endermen from teleporting, make sure to cover the smeltery so they don't see the sky.%n%nIf you manage to put a regenerating endermen in there, tag it so it doesn't despawn, and make sure your smeltery is not in a claimed chunk on a server.%n%n[note]The Smeltery must contain liquid in it already in order to hurt the Enderman and generate liquid ender![/note]

# Quest: Numbers in the Corner?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZg.name=§9§lNumbers in the Corner?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJZg.desc=What's with the numbers in the corner? That is the In-Game Info (IGI) mod. Some of the info it gives is useful right away, some of it shines later on in progression.%n%nFor now, the most important thing it does is showing if you are in an ore chunk. Further quests will explain what it means.%n%nIf you want to hide it, type "/igi disable" in the chat. Type "/igi enable" if you want to turn it back on.%n%nThe command "/igi config" opens the configuration window to control its position, scale, and size.%n%nThe command "/xu_tps" from the mod Extra Utilities toggles numbers to measure ticktime in milliseconds and the TPS (Ticks Per Second). TPS is a measure of how well your server is running. The ideal TPS is 20.00 (meaning a ticktime of at most 50.00). If your TPS is less than 15, things are going to start lagging noticeably. At 10 or less TPS, it is going to be hard to play.%nThe tooltip shows three types of measurement: instantaneous, average, and worst-case. Each one first shows the ticktime and then the TPS in brackets.%n%nIf you need suggestions on solving TPS problems, feel free to ask for help in the GTNH Discord.%n%nWhile GTNH comes with recommended default settings, in particular when it comes to balance, there are many commands and configurations to customize your experience. They range from accessibility or debug tools to visual customization all the way to various cheats. You can find a small overview on [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Commands_and_Configurations[/url].

# Quest: Controlling Your Drawers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJaA.name=§5§lControlling Your Drawers
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJaA.desc=Now that you have MV Circuits and Stainless Steel, you can make the incredibly handy Drawer Controller. This block will make any drawers it connects to in a 4-block radius (including the y-axis) and 50 blocks at maximum as part of a multiblock that allows storage (and retrieval with the right setup) to any of the blocks that make it up. This will allow you to dump the contents of your mining trip into a storage system much easier. Just hold right-click on the Controller front for a second or two, and any items that match what's already in the multiblock will be deposited, while your tools and such won't. Just make sure to place your Controller last so it registers all the drawers.%n%nYou can feed into the Controller (and thus the rest of the drawers) with any kind of piping or hopper equivalent. If using it as part of a Multifarm or Mob Farm, make sure to set the contents of the drawers, and lock them with a key so that it properly stores everything in an organized manner. If the drawers' contents aren't set, it will start filling starting from the ones closest. If you wish to have more than one drawer full of an item, put a void upgrade on the drawer further from the Controller, and it will fill the first one, then the second.%n%nIf you want to go around corners, use the Trim Drawers to extend the multiblock. If you want to have a second point to dump items into, use the Controller Slave (one per multiblock, automation only). Note that you can use a key on the Controller to affect all drawers at once.%n%nOnce you have an ME Network, place a storage bus on the Controller, and the entire inventory will be accessible from the network, with both storage and retrieval. Just remember to set the priority higher than your ME Drives. If you haven't locked them yet expect all your drawers to fill with random items from your ME Network.%n%n[warn]Using the drawer controller with large amounts of I/O will tank TPS! If you're on a server, do not use drawer cubes, or expect the possibility of it being deleted or you getting banned.%n%nAdditionally, expect all non-backpack interactions to be DISABLED on the official servers. Congratulations, Drawer Cubists, you ruined it for everyone.[/warn]

# Quest: Bringing the Biome to You
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJbw.name=Bringing the Biome to You
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJbw.desc=So maybe you can't find a swamp or tropical forest for your crops or bees, or maybe they're too far away so they're inconvenient to get to, or maybe your base is in a colder climate and you have to deal with the constant howls of direwolves. Instead of packing up all your stuff and moving somewhere else, why not try changing the biome? There are a couple of different ways to do so in this modpack:%n%n§§§r§lUse the Arcane Terrestrial Reformer§r%n-Requires EV Circuits, Tungstensteel, Rocket Tier III%n-Also requires Infusion, Void Metal (sufficient warp), Energized Node for CV, lots of Essentia%n-16 block radius%n-Can only change to a few specific Vanilla or Thaumcraft biomes%n-Kind of slow%n%n§lUse Ritual of Gaia's Transformation from Blood Magic§r%n-Requires Void Metal, Infusion, Tungstensteel%n-Requires getting deep into BM (and the warp that comes with it)%n-Requires 1,000,000 LP, Master Blood Orb, Tier 4 Altar and Awakened Activation Crystal%n-10 block radius, can be exactly specified with bloodstone bricks (either type)%n-Cannot specify which biome you get, you can only change the temperature/humidity within the 0.0 - 2.0 range and hope%n-Some biomes may be impossible due to limited range and overlap%n-Adjust temperature/humidity with items on 8 plinths around the Master Ritual Stone%n-Need to relog to see changes%n-Very little documentation or explanation%n-Fast%n%n§lUse the Brew of Shifting Seasons from Witcher§ry%n-Small range, depends on the level of the brew (power, not dispersal extent)%n-Biome can be exactly specified%n-Crafted using the complicated custom brew system%n-Can add different ingredients to change range of the brew%n-At min changes a single block%n-At max has about a 3 block (circular) radius%n-Instant (once you use it)%n%n§lUse the Rite of Shifting Seasons from Witchery§r%n-Requires Stainless Steel, Greatwood Scepter or better for the Distillery%n-You have to do a bunch of Witchery stuff%n-Not hard once you've done it once%n-Extremely large range, 16/32/48 block (circular) radius%n-Biome can be exactly specified%n-Sometimes fails in specific chunks%n-Very fast%n%nIf you want to know how to use the Witchery methods, please go to the Look to the edges tab to continue.%n%nPSA: The IC2&Galacticraft Terraformers only change the surface, not the biome itself.

# Quest: Unlimited LP
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJlw.name=§4§l§nUnlimited LP
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAJlw.desc=This orb can hold (almost) unlimited LP. It also constantly refills itself §ofor free§r while it is in your inventory, or in an altar which has some blood in it.%n%nBut you still need blood for crafting, OK? (Look into the ritual §oCry of the Eternal Soul§r for a way around this.)

# Quest: Infinity Chest
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKEQ.name=§5§l§nInfinity Chest
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKEQ.desc=Stores up to 243 different items, each being able to stack up to 2,147,483,648. Useful if you want somewhere to put all those void miner ores.

# Quest: UV Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKGw.name=§4§l§nUV Solar
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKGw.desc=Produces 1A of UV voltage during the day. Useful if you live in a dimension with permanent day (Eg garden).

# Quest: Does Anyone Even Still Use These?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKng.name=§4§l§nDoes Anyone Even Still Use These?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKng.desc=If you do, they're now really good. I guess. They sound like it at least?

# Quest: Transform and...Stay Put Actually
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKqw.name=§b§lTransform and...Stay Put Actually
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKqw.desc=Active Transformers will transform power up or down at only a 0.004%% power loss, making using several in a row obsolete, if you can afford it. Unfortunately, it's kinda expensive. On the other hand, you can use it to turn your lasers from your laser hatches, which is probably a better use.%n%nIt doesn't need a Maintenance Hatch, just the I/O Hatches.

# Quest: What Even is This?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKyA.name=§d§lWhat Even is This?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKyA.desc=In addition to being a dehydrator multi, it's also a Vacuum Furnace, for which no singleblock exists. It's supposed to be used with the IsaMill Grinding Machine multi and the Flotation Cell Regulator multi for the purposes of ore milling, an advanced method of ore processing that needs a lot of infrastructure, but which gives many new outputs for each ore it supports.%n%n[note]This multi is LuV now![/note]

# Quest: Dyson Swarm Ground Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL3w.name=§9§l§nDyson Swarm Ground Unit
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL3w.desc=The Dyson Swarm Ground Unit multiblock is basically a solar panel, you just insert Dyson Swarm Modules (how many depends on how much energy you want) and get energy out. There are some complications though:%n- Each hour, n of m modules are destroyed according to this formula: n = m (2 * 0.066) / (exp(-0.00005 * (m - 1))+exp(0.00003 * cps)), where cps is computation per second,%n- Needs 3.6M L/h of Gelid Cryotheum.%n- Up to 10,000 modules can be inserted into a single Dyson Swarm.%n- Dyson Swarm can only accept up to 100k computation.%n%n[note]Note: TecTech's Multi-Amp Dynamo Hatches and Laser Source Hatches are supported.[/note]%n%nThe amount of each part on the right is only the minimum, depending on how many Dynamo Hatches, Input Buses, Input Hatches and Optical Reception Connectors you use, you may need more Energy Receiver Base Casings, Module Deployment Unit Base Casings or Control Center Base Casings.%n%nFun fact: The maximum output is 337B EU/t (limited by 10,000 Modules and the 3.37x dimension bonus of Horus)%n%n(If you don't want to calculate how many modules you need per hour, the number is 64 for max stats)

# Quest: Where Do I Build the Dyson Swarm?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4A.name=§9§l§nWhere Do I Build the Dyson Swarm?
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAL4A.desc=If you read the Dyson Swarm Ground Unit's tooltip carefully (which you should), you might have noticed, that it mentions a "dimension-dependent factor". The dimension you build the Dyson Swarm multiblock in can greatly affect the real power output.%n%n§lSorted by factor (descending):§r%n§2337%% - Horus%n231%% - Barnarda C%n228%% - Neper%n228%% - α Centauri Bb%n211%% - Mehen belt%n198%% - Maahes%n198%% - Seth%n198%% - Vega B%n194%% - Venus Space Stations%n181%% - Anubis%n176%% - Venus%n161%% - Mercury%n141%% - Barnarda E%n134%% - T Ceti E%n126%% - Barnarda F%n112%% - Ross128b, Ross128ba%n110%% - Earth Space Stations§r%n§6100%% - Overworld, Moon§r%n[warn]89%% - Mars Space Stations%n81%% - Mars, Phobos, Deimos%n61%% - Asteroids%n60%% - Ceres%n48%% - Jupiter Space Stations%n44%% - Europa, Io, Ganymede%n36%% - Saturn Space Stations%n32%% - Enceladus, Titan, Callisto%n25%% - Uranus Space Stations%n23%% - Oberon, Proteus, Miranda%n20%% - Neptune Space Stations%n18%% - Triton%n16%% - Pluto, Kuiper Belt%n15%% - Makemake, Haumea%n1%% - Garden, Mining and Void Worlds%n0%% - All other dimensions[/warn]

# Quest: Machine Interface Fluid I/O
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKg.name=§2§lMachine Interface Fluid I/O
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALKg.desc=Thanks to the tireless work of the devs, you can now use cells to I/O fluids directly from the interface of GT machines. Just click on the fluid while holding a cell or other fluid container item.%n%nPoints to consider:%n1) Left-click to attempt filling/emptying all fluid containers held on cursor.%n2) Right-click to attempt filling/emptying one fluid container held on cursor.%n3) All fluid containers that can be used in a standard gt tank (e.g. super tanks or the X voltage tanks) are supported, including but not limited to: water bottles, vanilla buckets, ic2 (universal and normal) cells, volumetric flasks, large fluid cells, pressurized fluid tanks, etc.%n4) Can fill/take less than one cell (1000L or 144L if molten) of fluid if the fluid container supports doing so.%n5) It won't check if it's a valid fluid for the machine/recipe, keep that in mind.%n6) EIO tanks need to be placed and picked up first before they can be used.

# Quest: 「 」
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALSA.name=§4§l「 」
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALSA.desc=If you somehow manage to connect to it, you can get a lot of aspect points, but can't become God. You don't disappear though, so it's probably a decent tradeoff.

# Quest: Making a Rapier
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUQ.name=§a§lMaking a Rapier
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALUQ.desc=Problems killing armored enemies? Just use a Rapier that ignores armor, but doesn't do a lot of damage.

# Quest: Here's Some Oil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALqg.name=§2§lHere's Some Oil
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALqg.desc=[note]Here the oil questlines diverge into two tabs - part about getting every possible output is in the LV tab, part about the usefulness of oil is in the Working with Oil tab, this quest is part of the latter.[/note]%n%nWelcome! This is the questline that shows the path through oil processing towards all the useful items and fluids that can be obtained from it. Working with this black liquid involves a lot of steps that range from LV (Low Voltage), all the way to IV (Insane Voltage), and outputs that are useful at those tiers and beyond.%n%nOil is useful both for generating power, and to automate a lot of chemicals that are important for progression. As you progress, you will be able to get more of it, and get it faster, as well as process it in new ways that improve on the setup that you were using before. It is not a required path for progression in the pack, but it is a very useful one, should you choose to follow it.%n%nThe best way to start working with oil is to extract it from the surface. Oil spouts are visible without having to dig down, and they can be interacted with by using a Pump placed above them, alongside a generator that feeds it some power. You can use some of the Oil to generate this power for now.

# Quest: Nano Forge Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM0A.name=§4§l§nNano Forge Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM0A.desc=Carbon Nanites are good first workers, but they don't have much in the way of working with more complex systems as they have a very basic nanite network. So a new more advanced nanite will be needed to produce complex nanites.%n%nThe neutronium nanite is an in-between of the two tiers able to produce tier 2 nanites, which have other uses.%n%n[note]When putting the neutronium nanite in the controller, you will need to wait for the structure check to happen again or break and replace the controller with a neutronium nanite inside. Allows the Nano Forge to make tier 2 nanites.[/note]

# Quest: Nano Forge Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM0Q.name=§9§l§nNano Forge Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM0Q.desc=Neutronium nanites are slow moving, but that allowed them to have a complex nanite network. If there was a material that could move itself it could allow for an even more complex nanite with great speeds... Thankfully with the DTPF fully functional we can make it, transcendent metal.%n%n[note]Same thing as the neutronium nanite, but this nanite allows for tier 3 nanites to be made in the nano forge.[/note]

# Quest: Chemical Pseudo-Altercations
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM1w.name=§5§l§nChemical Pseudo-Altercations
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAM1w.desc=Learning more about the world and its ways is a sign of wisdom. However, the truly wise are the ones who know what is unimportant and can be skipped. For a true breacher of technology, the constraints of physics and chemistry are not essential. To skip past their technicalities, the Quantum Force Transformer comes into play.%n%nThis multi is meant to replicate the most popular and important processing lines in the pack's progression, mostly those related to chemistry. Because of recursion in recipes, where earlier tier materials are required to craft higher tier equivalents, there are a lot of early processing lines that stay up through progression. Even worse, they often need more and more machines to keep up with increasing speed demands. To save on lag, this multi will do those processing lines in one step and without most of the extra chemicals that are added to purify the inputs into the outputs.%n%nThe Quantum Force Transformer (QFT) is unlocked in UEV, after Optical Mainframes have been crafted, and with the addition of a single Eternal Singularity and other materials. It's a tall, 15x15 multiblock with many different casings, including two that are upgradable and decide the two tiers of the multi. Although it's available in UEV, the upgraded casings require more and more expensive materials, while also unlocking skips for more advanced processing lines. For example, a platline skip can be done in the earliest QFT tier, whereas a Kevlar skip can only be done in the last tier.%n%nEach recipe that the QFT has represents a single processing line or a big part of a line. The inputs for the early plastic skip, for example, are the basic components of the plastics on a molecular level (Carbon, Hydrogen, Oxygen, etc.), and not the multi-step chemicals that were used half a dozen tiers earlier. All recipes have 3 or more outputs, and every output has a chance to appear: the chance for each is 100%% divided by the number of outputs. To increase it, there are additional mechanics that can be used.%n%nSimply put, the QFT uses huge amounts of energy and quantum field stabilization to disassemble simple molecules and assemble them into more complex ones, without needing additives or constrained processes. The only addition to the base inputs that the multi requires is a specific catalyst, which the smart circuits use to guide the materials into what they ultimately transform into, but they are never consumed or lost in any way.%n%nThis direct process simplifies long processing chains to one step, but it has two consequences: it makes the process expensive, given the extreme conditions needed to undergo the transformation (in a similar way to fusion), but it also generates many different outputs at once, none of which are guaranteed, and it's impossible to choose between them without adding something else into the setup to alter the conditions inside the QFT in some way. Throwing more energy into the multi won't do anything, and better materials don't seem to work, so what is the next step? That is what the next two quests will answer.%n%n[note]Tip: Use multiple Bulk Catalyst Housings to run additional QFT recipes within the same structure[/note]

# Quest: Precise Assembler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMEg.name=§9§lPrecise Assembler
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMEg.desc=The Precise Assembler has two modes: Precise and Normal.%n%nPrecise mode is used to make certain advanced components, whereas Normal mode works as multiblock version of the Assembler.%n%n[note]You can't skip tiers with this. You'll need either a singleblock Assembler or a Large Scale Auto-Assembler multi to make your first Energy Hatch, then you can use it on the Precise Assembler.[/note]

# Quest: Industrial Coke Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMOQ.name=§8§lIndustrial Coke Oven
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMOQ.desc=Your EV endeavors might push you into a GT++ multiblock, despite most of those being IV-tier. This happens because the special alloys used to put them together need to be crafted in an Alloy Blast Smelter, which is IV, but the §5§lIndustrial Coke Oven§r (ICO) does not!%n%nWhat does it do? It's in the name, it's a really fast Coke Oven. So fast, in fact, that it can replace a few dozen Pyrolyse Ovens. It actually takes its recipes from that multi, so you also get the additional fluid, such as Charcoal Byproducts, alongside the greatly increased processing speed. The caveat is that this multi needs Titanium, Platinum, and a little bit of Tungsten. You can get unprocessed Platinum from Nickel or Meteoric Iron & you can get Tungsten from processing End Stone Dust, Ender Goo or Moon Dust.%n%nIn EV you'll have to stick to the heat resistant casing, which offers §616§r parallels. When you unlock HSS-S in IV however you can upgrade to the heat proof casings for an upgrade to §632§r parallels.%n%nOptionally, you can add up to 15 slices to each Coke Oven for a boost in parallels. §6+8§r per slice when using Heat Resistant Casings, and §6+16§r per slice when using the Heat Proof Casings.%n%n[note]For now, coil tier is irrelevant to the machine's performance, but later on, upgrading to Infinity Coils+ allows for multi-amp hatches, and using Eternal Coils allows for unlimited slice addition.[/note]

# Quest: Bet On The Distillus
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMQQ.name=§9§lBet On The Distillus
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMQQ.desc=IV brings forth GT++ multis, including an upgrade for the Distillation Tower called the Dangote Distillus. Its structure is exactly the same as the DT, but it requires a muffler hatch and uses a different controller with a more expensive recipe.%n%nIt's also locked behind an IV Chemical Plant, which makes it a very expensive craft if it is the only use you have for that plant.%n%nThat said, it solves the issue of DTs being slow, and those are the backbone of many renewable setups. How many quad DTs are you going to need for reliable IV/LuV power, you might ask? Just go for it.%n%n[note]You can also use it to do single block Distillery recipes that can't be done in the DT, like making Sodium Potassium. However, that requires a max height tower.[/note]

# Quest: Faster Basic Crops
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMRg.name=§6§lFaster Basic Crops
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMRg.desc=Welcome to my TED Talk, today we talk about the §6§lExtreme Industrial Greenhouse.§r%nIt is the most advanced and §l§nLAG FREE§r crop farm that will allow you to supply the amount of tea you need.%nThe machine starts at §5EV§r, and can no longer farm CropsNH crops (The Industrial Farm now handles them).%nTo see the structure, place the controller on the ground and use a structure hologram to build.%nThe glass tier limits the energy tier until [note]UV[/note]. With [note]UV[/note] glass you can have an energy tier as high as you want.%nThere are 3 modes to manage your crops (change with screwdriver):%n%n§lSetup mode (input):§r%nIn this mode you can plant your crops in the machine.%nJust put them in the input bus and enable the machine with a soft mallet.%nWhen the bus is empty, just disable it and change the mode.%nKeep in mind that there is limited space of slots for your crops depending on the voltage.%nWith normal crops you start with 1 slot and that multiplies by 2 every tier past §5EV§r, every slot can take 64 crops of the same type.%n%n§lSetup mode (output):§r%nThis mode allows you to move your Greenhouse or upgrade your crops.%nWhen the machine is running in this mode it will output all planted crops in the output bus.%n%n§lNormal operation:§r%nWith normal crops it is a straightforward process. Base processing time is 5 seconds, at the end of operation all crops are grown and the outputs are added to the output bus. Additionally the time is lower every tier past §5EV§r §o(The time is divided by the number of tiers past §6HV§r§o, minimum 1 second. WOW)§r%n%nIf you want to grow your crops even faster, then you can use a fertilizer (up to §l400%% more drops§r!). Machine will take fertilizer from the input buses on start of the operation and will be applied to that operation only. Each fertilizer gives +200%% per crop. The bonus is applied evenly on crops. Examples:%nNormal mode, 3 wheat seeds, 1 tea seed, you insert 1 fertilizer, you will get +150%% wheat drops and +50%% tea drops.%n%nAdditionally, all your crops need water to grow. Every single crop drinks 1000L per operation. So for example if you have planted 576 tea seeds at [note]UV[/note] voltage you will need 576000 L per second.%n%n§lLast notes:§r%nThe animation can't be disabled.%nThe lamps can be inverted.%nThe dirt must be tilled.%nIf you encounter any issue or have any suggestion please open an issue on GitHub and ping §l@kuba6000§r.%nThis MB was created to farm tea because I wanted to.%nThe glass tier limits the energy input tier.

# Quest: UV Power Per Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMXQ.name=§b§lUV Power Per Turbine
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMXQ.desc=Once you progress enough in ZPM to make ZPM Dynamo Hatches, you can increase each turbine's output to 524,288 EU/t. At this number, you'll be a lot less limited by the turbine material, and it's possible to increase the total power output of one Fusion Reactor considerably. You can cover the total Helium Plasma output from one reactor with 3 Plasma Turbines, if you choose the right materials:%n%nLarge High Durability Compound Steel 235%% 473,759 EU/t%nLarge Atomic Separation Catalyst 206%% 409,663 EU/t%nLarge Adamantium 206%% 413,280 EU/t%nLarge Draconium 175%% 220,500 EU/t (durable)%nLarge Neutronium 165%% 249,480 EU/t (very durable)%n%nThe power output and final efficiency can vary a lot, based on which turbines you're using. Some of them, like Ichorium and Neutronium, last basically forever, while others will need to be replaced from time to time but offer higher efficiency. If you want to get more power per turbine, to reach closer to the dynamo's limit, you can increase the flow of plasma to the turbine, but be careful! You can't go beyond the dynamo's limit, and you will also lose efficiency as you increase the flow amount. More concrete values for efficiency loss can be found in the Plasma Turbine quest in the LuV page.%n%n[note]Also, check out the XL Plasma Turbine.[/note]

# Quest: High Temperature Gas-cooled Reactor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMbg.name=§6§lHigh Temperature Gas-cooled Reactor
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMbg.desc=Have you heard of gas-cooled reactors? Have you heard of Pebble Bed reactors? Well now you have both!%n%nThe High Temperature Gas-cooled Reactor (HTGR) uses specially prepared fuel pellets to heat coolant gas (helium) that's pumped in a closed loop through the reactor and heat exchangers. The reactor requires a constant supply of helium gas and power in order to power the pump that keeps the coolant loop working.%n%nThis reactor allows breeding of rare resources (§5Indium§r,§9Osmium§r), fissile materials (§aU235§r,§cPu239§r,§4Pu241§r), can supply you with §dLutetium§r and also unlocks alternative recipes for §dEuropium§r and §7Americium§r via the elusive §2Promethium§r.%n%nThe disadvantage of this reactor is it's expensive nature. Pebble reactors work by stuffing the reactor full of pebbles, none of which require rare resources but rather a large amount of common ones. Even though a lot can be recycled, you still need to keep the reactor filled to get decent speed. As a reward for this upkeep cost, you get a decent production for many different outputs.%n[note]%nNotes:%n%nHTGR has an internal buffer for fuel and gets faster the more fuel you put inside according to the formula §6eff=1-(1-x)^3§r%n%nThis multi consumes 0.2A IV when operating and this amount increases when lacking helium gas. %nThe amount of Helium gas increases with the amount of helium gas stored.%n%nReactor speeds up immensely when supplied with either/both IC2 Coolant or Water, if the amount of supplied fluid is not full the bonus speed is applied linearly.%n%nBy typing HTGR in NEI, you can see all the items that are related to this multiblock.%n%nFor exact numbers visit HTGR-Controller-Tooltip.as/always%n[/note]

# Quest: Two Million Turbines
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMcw.name=§2§l§nTwo Million Turbines
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMcw.desc=Hopefully, not more than a handful. The objective here is for each of them to output close to 2 million EU/t.%n%nHow can you get there? Look at the UV Dynamo Hatch's recipe and you have your new objective. When you arrive there, each turbine that is equipped with that impressive block will be able to output up to 2,097,152 EU/t, which again opens you up to new turbine opportunities. Some good choices at this point are as follows:%n%nLarge Cosmic Neutronium 225%% 1,360,800 EU/t%nLarge Ichorium 225%% 1,360,800 EU/t (very durable)%nLarge Awakened Draconium 195%% 491,400 EU/t%nLarge Trinium 185%% 1,451,840 EU/t%n%nAt this point, you might consider building more t1 Fusion Reactors to process other materials. Even if you stop the reactor you're using to generate this plasma, the EU cost of restarting it is less than 1 bucket of plasma, so it's probably not that big of a deal.%n%n[note]At this point, you really should be looking into the XL turbine chain, from XL supercritical to dense to normal steam.[/note]

# Quest: Infinite Turbines
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMeA.name=§4§l§nInfinite Turbines
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMeA.desc=Some turbine materials are not available for you, either because you don't have the material itself or because the Dynamo Hatch in the turbine cannot handle the power output from plasma. It will be a different story in UHV, when you can once again quadruple the max output of each turbine, and also unlock Infinity as an option for turbines.%n%nHuge Infinity 300%% 6,451,200 EU/t%nHuge Infinity Catalyst 231%% 1,236,480 EU/t%n%nYes, that's basically it. You can use any material from the previous turbine quests, but when you make the t8 rocket and can mine Infinity Catalyst, these are the two options. Obviously, Infinity is much better, but also much more expensive. If you stick with fusion, you will need several of those to push through the endgame. Remember that you can input plasma beyond the optimal flow, and get more out of each turbine at the cost of fuel efficiency.

# Quest: Hypogen Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkg.name=§9§l§nHypogen Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkg.desc=Forged from the blood of an ageless dragon, and melded together by the power of fusion beyond what you thought was the reality. No natural element, or combination of elements, could match up to this glowing orange material, not even the Awakened Draconium you got your hands on before.%n%nWhat is this blood made of?%n%nWhat truly happened inside that Mk4 Fusion Reactor? What §ois§r this material? It moves on its own, moving as if it is made of slime, however it is boiling to the touch. Despite moving as if it is soft and squishy, Hypogen is hard to the touch and is incredibly hard to cut or work. It feels out of this world, and it is obvious to you what needs to be done with it.%n%nWhat were they feeding these dragons?%n%nIt absorbs and radiates energy without any effort, but it would be stupid to attempt making coils out of this without assistance. Wetware wasn't good enough anymore, and only the most advanced living circuit could withstand the erratic behavior Hypogen demonstrates.%n%nProvides 12601K heat. Almost certainly, this will end up on your DTPF.

# Quest: Eternal Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkw.name=§9§l§nEternal Coil Upgrade
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMkw.desc=Beyond spacetime, beyond reality. You have peered into what never existed and brought into a fluid, and then a solid. It has been stabilized, against all odds. When you look at it, you think that you could hold the entire universe in your hand.%n%nIn the past, you were able to combine almost all materials into one, through an Eternal Singularity, an infinitely dense sample of the universe. However, automating this at the scale of the DTPF proved ridiculous, which would have stopped your progress altogether if not for the discovery of the Energized Tesseract. To physically manifest spacetime itself, you first needed to manifest the fourth spatial dimension, and that is what the Tesseract is: a 4-dimensional cube.%n%nCubes! Almost everything around you is made out of cubes. You have only glimpsed at the reality of the 4-dimensional world, but you have successfully used it to condensate spacetime, which can be arbitrarily molded into the complete Eternal mixture. Needless to say, living circuits will not suffice to maintain an infinitely dense, infinitely stable, multi-dimensional material.%n%nCurrently, the final upgrade with 13501K. This really makes your DTPF shine!

# Quest: Power in the Ether
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMow.name=§9§l§nPower in the Ether
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMow.desc=These new hatches allow you to wirelessly store and receive energy from any location in any dimension. They can be placed in any existing multi block structure and will function as normal energy hatches. %n%nAdditionally, the wireless covers can be used for singleblock machines such as a World Accelerator or a BioLab.%n%nThe wireless network can store a total of 2^(2^31) EU, far exceeding even a max tier LSC.%n%nYou can share a wireless network with others by adding them to your network with §5/gt global_energy_join §3user1§r §2user2§r. This will make §3user1§r use §2user2's§r energy when interacting with the global network. You can leave a network at any time by doing §5/gt global_energy_join§r §4your_name your_name§r.%n%nYou cannot connect wires to these blocks. These are also designed to be highly lag efficient, meaning EU is added at large intervals to prevent needless calculations from occurring. This will also save you some TPS lag from vast wire networks.%n%n[note]If your calculator is giving up, 2^(2^31) is a number with 646,456,994 digits.[/note]

# Quest: PCB Factory
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyQ.name=§2§l§nPCB Factory
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyQ.desc=Using a Chemical Reactor to create circuit boards has become quite inefficient... it's time for a proper solution! After some research you have found a more efficient method; a factory designed to print out circuit boards.%n%nThe PCB Factory is able to use a wide range of plastics to create circuit boards ready to be used. The printing mechanism overheats when it tries to overclock currently, so I will have to find a way to make that work later. Boards with neurons on them will also require a modification before they can be made, but that shouldn't be hard to achieve.%n%n§2Trace size: the trace size represents the lines between components, which are needed to transmit the electrical signals on the circuit. One can make it smaller to slow down the machine, but use less resources, or make it bigger to make it faster, but use more resources.%n%n§1Formulas:%n- 10000/(TraceSize/100) Production%n- RecipeDuration/TraceSize^2 Time§r%n%n[note]Similar to the water line, additional modules of the PCB Factory can connect to one another using a Data Stick[/note]

# Quest: Bio Chamber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyg.name=§2§l§nBio Chamber
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyg.desc=With new technology comes the need for adaptation! In order to create §9Wetware§r & §cBioware§r boards you need a chamber that is capable of properly maintaining the neurons while they are installed to the board. Fortunately, the §5§lBio Chamber§r is a simple upgrade and doesn't require many resources. %n%nAfter its construction, you can link it to the PCB Factory by left-clicking the PCB Factory Controller using a Data Stick, and right-clicking that data stick onto the Bio Chamber Controller. One Bio Chamber can connect to any number of PCB Factories within a §216§r block radius.%n%n[note]You can use any tier of glass.[/note]

# Quest: Liquid Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyw.name=§4§l§nLiquid Cooling Tower
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMyw.desc=Starting to hit the production limit of the PCB Factory? Let's install a §5§lCooling Tower§r; this will allow any PCB Factory within its range to overclock with §22x§r Speed in exchange for §c4x§r EU and §910L/s§r of §nDistilled Water§r while running.%n%nYou can connect this to the PCB Factory by first left-clicking the PCB Factory Controller and then right-clicking the Cooling Tower Controller. One Cooling Tower can connect to any number of PCB Factories within a §216§r block radius.%n%n[note]The input hatch is placed in the bottom center of the Liquid Cooling Tower.[/note]

# Quest: PCB Factory Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzA.name=§4§l§nPCB Factory Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzA.desc=With the Nano Forge built, we can upgrade our production of circuit boards using Silver Nanites. Due to the nature of the nanites however, you will need both new structure casings and a special §5Nanite Containment Bus§r.%n%nFor the structure casings, you find that using infinity as a frame and enriched holmium as the protection layer works well. It can be allowed to let through nanites to go into the printer base so that extra material can be directly removed instead of trying to go slower.%n%nWith this new upgrade you can finally use §3Tier 2 recipes§r. Additionally, by placing extra nanites into the Nanite Containment Bus, you can boost your parallel amount by §2Amount^.75§r up to §2256§r parallels.%n%n[note]P.S. For those who don't feel like doing math, that's §n1638§r nanites to reach the maximum parallel amount.[/note]

# Quest: Liquid Cooling Tower Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzQ.name=§c§l§nLiquid Cooling Tower Tier 2
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzQ.desc=With your newfound ability to manipulate spacetime you have found a way to sustain cosmically low temperatures. It is now possible to make an even better cooling unit. A casing able to keep its room temperature very low and nanites which can transfer heat effectively because of their small bodies. You will still need coolant, though water won't cut it any longer given its high freezing point. If only there was some kind of super... coolant...%n%nThe §5Tier 2§r Coolant Tower now allows for a §24x§r Speed boost for the same §c4x§r EU cost, making it possible to speed through recipes much quicker. It requires §910 L/s§r of §nSuper Coolant§r to operate while running.%n%n[warn]This upgrade is incompatible with its lower tier predecessor.[/warn]

# Quest: PCB Factory Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzg.name=§9§l§nPCB Factory Tier 3
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzg.desc=Why use a small nozzle to print out the conductor on the board when you can just build it using nanites? Unfortunately, the Silver Nanite isn't rigid enough for that so a §6Gold Nanite§r will be needed... and so will new casings. Celestial tungsten should be a good candidate for a frame, and Quantum can be used for the protection for all these nanites flying around inside.%n%nThe structure will need to be bigger and taller to fit this more advanced technology, hopefully you prepared enough space!%n%n[note]Works the same as the Tier 2, with the advantage of requiring less resource intensive Gold Nanites.[/note]

# Quest: Nano Forge Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzw.name=§2§l§nNano Forge Tier 1
betterquesting.quest.AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAMzw.desc=There must be a way to make a nano scale robots to work in a machine. Carbon ones can be made in an assembly line, but very inefficiently. There must be a better way.%n%nWhat about a Nano Forge, able to cut up blocks into nano-thin sheets and then creating the first nanite, which helps create thousands of them in mere seconds.%n%n[note]The Nano Forge is a big multiblock requiring lots of power over the course of a couple minutes. It is able to use TT energy hatches (including lasers). The controller must have a carbon nanite inside to make tier 1 recipes.[/note]%n%n[note]Despite what NEI might claim there are no minimum voltages for the Nano Forge recipes. If you want to do a recipe you just have to achieve the minimum EU/t required, no matter the voltage[/note].

# Quest: Prototype Matter Manipulator
betterquesting.quest.AVth34rQQ3iuYeQaKrsSQg.name=§5§lPrototype Matter Manipulator
betterquesting.quest.AVth34rQQ3iuYeQaKrsSQg.desc=The §1§lMatter Manipulator§r is an extremely powerful tool that you can use during your entire playthrough. It is essentially a survival version of world-edit that is custom made for the GTNH player's convenience.%n%nAs you might expect, the §1§lPrototype Matter Manipulator§r is the least powerful, most rudimentary version. You can only use the §5§lGeometry Mode§r to create and manipulate shapes for use in building. You will [warn]not[/warn]§r be able to remove blocks until you install an upgrade unlocked in EV.%n%nYou can find detailed information from the developer on: [url]https://github.com/RecursivePineapple/MatterManipulator/blob/master/README.md[/url]%n%nBut the best way to learn about it is to use it! Experiment with the UI and become familiar with how it works.%n%n[note]Checkout the Building Better Bases tab for the complete Manipulator questline.[/note]

# Quest: Matter Manipulator MKII
betterquesting.quest.D6AFvlXcQbqDncL9y2HXEw.name=§d§lMatter Manipulator MKII
betterquesting.quest.D6AFvlXcQbqDncL9y2HXEw.desc=The MKII is the penultimate upgrade in the Matter Manipulator line. It is much more powerful, storing §210x§r the power, with a range of §2128 Blocks§r, and the ability to place §2256 Blocks/Second§r. In addition to all of the MKI features you now unlock §5§ltwo powerful new modes§r:%n%n- §5§lCopy / Paste§r: Copy a selection of blocks and paste it as many times as you'd like. Works best with GT & AE2.%n%n- §5§lMove§r: Similar to Copy / Paste, but will physically relocate something already built.%n%nHere is a short list of things that are copied / moved with the MM, the more complete list is on the Readme, but this should give you a general idea of how versatile it is.%n%n§3§lGregTech:§r%n- Pipe/Cable connections%n- Machine color%n- Machine front & output directions%n- Basic machine settings (auto outputs, etc)%n- Hatch settings (sorting, stack limiting, etc)%n- Multi machine settings (void protection, batch mode, etc)%n- Multi rotation%n- Covers%n- Strong redstone output%n- Custom names%n- Ghost circuits%n- Bus/hatch item/fluid lock%n- Modes (for machines that use the new mode system)%n- Data stick data%n- TecTech machine input parameters%n- ME output bus/hatch capacity%n%n§3§lAE2:§r%n- Any coloring%n- The orientation%n- The configuration%n- The upgrades%n- Custom names%n- Any stored cells (will also automatically configure cells & install their upgrades)%n- Any patterns (will encode but not decode patterns)%n- Priority Settings%n- P2P Settings%n- OreDict / Regular Filter%n%n§9§3§lAdvanced Copy Options:§r %n%nWhen in Copy / Paste mode, the radial menu has an §5§lAdvanced Options§r sub-menu with two powerful toggles:%n  - §5§l§5§lLink to External Hubs§r: When copying wireless connectors that are linked to a hub outside of the copy region, the pasted connectors will stay linked to that original hub.%n  - §5§lAuto-P2P Interfaces§r: Replaces ME Interfaces in the copied region with P2P ME tunnels, automatically placing matching tunnels at the source for seamless item routing.

# Quest: Ozonation
betterquesting.quest.E9atHD5uR9CC0G1qEeFDmQ.name=§d§lOzonation
betterquesting.quest.E9atHD5uR9CC0G1qEeFDmQ.desc=Want even more speed on your wafer processing? Using Grade 2 Purified Water, made by ozonation, you can now reduce processing time by 50%%. To run this machine, you will need to make large amounts of Ozone Gas by bombarding air with a strong laser. If you haven't already, you should definitely make the Hyper-Intensity Laser Engraver multiblock to speed up this process.%n%n[note]This multiblock is very picky about where the ozone input hatch goes. If you can't figure out why it's not forming, chances are you forgot to place this hatch in the correct location. Use the hologram projector to see where it goes.[/note]

# Quest: A Portable Barrel?
betterquesting.quest.EDtFbLVvQX2Y5mQp84W9bw.name=§2§lA Portable Barrel?
betterquesting.quest.EDtFbLVvQX2Y5mQp84W9bw.desc=As an upgrade to the barrels, EFR also adds the ever-familiar shulker box! The shulker box allows you to comfortably tote around its contents. You can find the research for them in the New Horizons tab of the Thaumonomicon.%n%nThese have seven additional tiers much like the barrels and chests that give you additional storage space. %n%nYou can dye any tier by shapelessly crafting them with a dye, and undye them by shapelessly crafting them alone. They §nwill§r retain their inventory. %n%n[note]There are many ways to obtain shulker shells:%n1. Fighting Shulkers in the Twilight Forest Lich & Ghast Queen Towers.%n2. Fighting Shulkers from the eggs you get from the Vending Machine.%n3. Manually crafting the shells.[/note]

# Quest: Infinity Egg
betterquesting.quest.EUgSnkUkT-6CHxpWCNWrbg.name=§4§l§nInfinity Egg
betterquesting.quest.EUgSnkUkT-6CHxpWCNWrbg.desc=The Infinity Egg is the best power source available for the Witchery altar.%n%nYou can also use it to unlock more efficient recipes in the DEFC.  

# Quest: Superdense Casting Basins
betterquesting.quest.EWAWhpFvQY6nvgVeXSZoNQ.name=§5§l§nSuperdense Casting Basins
betterquesting.quest.EWAWhpFvQY6nvgVeXSZoNQ.desc=The §5§lSuperdense Casting Basin§r (SCB) module is one of the first three modules you unlock right away for use in the §nExo-Foundry§r.%n%nThe SCB adds §312§r parallels per voltage tier and reduces the minimum number of Foundry casings by §236§r, giving you space for more inputs. %n%nIf this module is paired with the §5Streamlined Casters§r (SC) module, you will unlock "§6Optimum Production§r", a bonus giving §36§r extra parallels per voltage tier and a §275%%§r speed increase.

# Quest: Infinite Water Cell
betterquesting.quest.GR94tIXOQvC2w5SttlezrQ.name=§2§l§nInfinite Water Cell
betterquesting.quest.GR94tIXOQvC2w5SttlezrQ.desc=The ME Fluid Infinity Water Storage provides §24.5P§r water directly to your AE system, That's the equivalent of 2.25 million reservoir hatches, all conveniently packaged into one drive. %nMight come in handy...

# Quest: Gold Barrel
betterquesting.quest.GuylOTxSSraeAtj16fZ9-w.name=§c§lGold Barrel
betterquesting.quest.GuylOTxSSraeAtj16fZ9-w.desc=The Gold barrel has 81 slots.

# Quest: Heliocast Reinforcement
betterquesting.quest.JCfcbke6SGO9KCPqXsTyaQ.name=§9§l§nHeliocast Reinforcement
betterquesting.quest.JCfcbke6SGO9KCPqXsTyaQ.desc=The §5§lHeliocast Reinforcement§r (HR) module is the final §nExo-Foundry§r module unlocked in §9§lUIV§r. %n%nThe HR module finally allows you access to §9§lUIV+§r Fluid Solidifier recipes. Now you can cool higher tier materials or create advanced reinforced glass types using the Foundry.%n%nThe HR module is also unique in being able to pair with itself. Having two or more §5HR§r modules on your Foundry will unlock "§6Superstable Core§r" and give these bonuses:%n%n- Two or more HR modules grant §2+75%%§r speed & §c-10%%§r EU per HR%n- Three or more HR modules grant §3+6§r Parallels per voltage tier & §2+0.1§r overclock factor per HR%n- Four total HR modules grant §2+2§r full overclocks%n%n[note]Note these are compounding effects; e.g. having three HR modules will grant those listed bonuses in addition to the bonuses attained from two HR modules.[/note]

# Quest: Celestial Gateways
betterquesting.quest.OWIeO5C1RheNGaVsrwmPJg.name=Celestial Gateways
betterquesting.quest.OWIeO5C1RheNGaVsrwmPJg.desc=Celestial Gateways are a bit expensive, but they provide very convenient travel within a dimension.%n%nShift-click with a celestial pearl on a celestial gateway to attune the pearl to that specific gateway and insert that pearl into the slot of another.%n%nShift when standing above a celestial gateway to get the teleportation menu. It makes sense to name the pearls in an anvil if you want to easily identify the different locations.

# Quest: Diamond Barrel
betterquesting.quest.PjAewUoJTnilPpIT-Ce0tA.name=§2§lDiamond Barrel
betterquesting.quest.PjAewUoJTnilPpIT-Ce0tA.desc=The Diamond barrel has 108 slots.

# Quest: Large Molecular Assembler
betterquesting.quest.Q10xj-OrTE67wsWuTNCAAQ.name=§9§lLarge Molecular Assembler
betterquesting.quest.Q10xj-OrTE67wsWuTNCAAQ.desc=The §5Large Molecular Assembler§r is exactly how it sounds; a very quick molecular assembler with a much bigger inventory for crafting patterns. %n%nThis can handle up to 1024 crafts per second at the maximum energy usage making it up to 100x faster than a molecular assembler. Check out the Wiki for specifics: [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Large_Molecular_Assembler[/url]%n%nThe LMA controller hooks up directly to your main network in order to function, and all recipes must be placed inside either an input bus or a Crafting Pattern Provider bus in order to be recognized. Will not require an output bus.%n%nAdditionally, you must place a §2Data Orb§r inside of the controller or else it won't function.%n%n[note]It's recommended you use a Crafting Pattern Provider bus since it has more pattern slots and gets recognized by an interface terminal unlike a regular input bus.[/note]%n%n[warn]This machine can absolutely wall-share, but be careful about the placement of your input bus or all machines may not be used.[/warn]

# Quest: Compact Storage
betterquesting.quest.QNsm_wc0QO2g9C6_-vj2fA.name=§a§lCompact Storage
betterquesting.quest.QNsm_wc0QO2g9C6_-vj2fA.desc=Now that you are starting to find more and more copper, you feel your wood chests are too small to hold all the stuff.%n%n[note]It's time to upgrade your wooden chests to copper chests! Higher tiers of chests can be upgraded cheaply by using upgrade items, but not all tier chests can be upgraded directly this way. You can also try the "Wood to Copper Chest Upgrade", but upgrading from wood to a tiered chest will not be any cheaper.[/note]%n%n[note]Upgraded chests cannot be connected into double chests.[/note]

# Quest: Sentient Overclocker
betterquesting.quest.Rg0l66VnRsKlUZ0VTO3ilA.name=§c§l§nSentient Overclocker
betterquesting.quest.Rg0l66VnRsKlUZ0VTO3ilA.desc=The §5§lSentient Overclocker§r (SO) module is the sixth module of the §nExo-Foundry§r, and the only one unlocked in §c§lUMV§r.%n%nThe SO module, as you might imagine, increases the overclock factor of the Foundry by §20.35§r. This means that for every overclock provided to this machine, it will give a §235%%§r speed boost. %n%nFor example, if your Foundry has 1 overclock it should run at §32x§r base speed. However with this module it would instead run at §22.35x§r base speed (235%%). This then compounds if another overclock is added, so instead of running at §32x§r the speed of the first overclock, it will run again at §22.35x§r the speed of the first overclock, bringing it to a total of §25.52x§r speed (552%%).%n%nAdditionally, this module can pair with the §5Proto-Volt Stabilizer§r (PVS) module to unlock "§6Harmonic Efficiency§r" giving the Foundry a §c50%%§r EU discount and an additional §20.1§r overclock factor (2.45x§r instead of 2.35x).%n%n[warn]Only one of these modules may be installed per Foundry.[/warn]

# Quest: Large Hadron Collider
betterquesting.quest.TL8RVz_HTBO5LvkI6SQi6A.name=§2§l§nLarge Hadron Collider
betterquesting.quest.TL8RVz_HTBO5LvkI6SQi6A.desc=In order to obtain more exotic particles than simple protons, neutrons, and electrons, you will need the Large Hadron Collider. You can use any charged particle as input, sourced from any other beam-like multiblock such as the Source Chamber.%n%nThe LHC's four modules can each produce a different set of particles. For a specific particle to start appearing in the outputs, the §bCollision Energy§r must be greater than the particle's §dRest Mass§r, shown on its tooltip in NEI.%n%nThe LHC has two modes: §lAccelerator§r and §lCollider§r. %n%nFirst, in §lAccelerator§r mode, it accelerates the input beam to a higher energy. It does this in 1-second cycles, with the beam energy increasing once per cycle by a fixed amount based on how much EU is consumed that cycle. The power draw increases quadratically as the §9Number of Completed Cycles§r increases, and linearly if the §cAmount§r increases. %n%nYou can set a target §6Beam Energy§r and a maximum §9Number of Cycles§r in the UI. If your beam reaches the target §6Beam Energy§r before reaching the maximum cycle count, further completed cycles will repeatedly multiply the beam's current §cAmount§r by 1.1, which also increases your power draw. Once the maximum §9Number of Cycles§r is reached, the LHC automatically switches to §lCollider§r mode.%n%n%nIn §lCollider§r mode, the beam is collided with itself to generate all kinds of particles. Each LHC Module is able to detect and capture a certain subset of particles, depending on which Fundamental Force the particle can interact with. This also means some particles appear in multiple modules. You can blacklist particles from appearing by using the Filtered Beamline Output Hatch.%n%n§l[note]§lThe §b§lCollision Energy§r §lis §l2x§l§  the accelerated §6§lBeam Energy§r. [/note] %n%n%n

# Quest: Steel Chest?
betterquesting.quest.V4jinTYRSueIrEqn90dRzQ.name=§c§lSteel Chest?
betterquesting.quest.V4jinTYRSueIrEqn90dRzQ.desc=While being significantly more expensive than a gold chest, the steel chest has less capacity but it can be used in some specialized crafting recipes.

# Quest: The future is here!
betterquesting.quest.V9BupH47RI6RWX6vff5dpw.name=§c§lThe future is here!
betterquesting.quest.V9BupH47RI6RWX6vff5dpw.desc=EFR adds with it vanilla Barrels (not to be confused with JABBA barrels). These are essentially like chests, but they can be placed next to each other and opened with a block above them. And you can upgrade them! Great for those compact machine setups.

# Quest: A Toolbox For All Your Tools
betterquesting.quest.VAZfRG1BQt6JwqRQ_PNP0g.name=§2§lA Toolbox For All Your Tools
betterquesting.quest.VAZfRG1BQt6JwqRQ_PNP0g.desc=As your factory grows, you will need to use your tools to build, configure, and dismantle machines. Crafting a toolbox to hold your tools will help.%n%nThe Field Engineer's Toolbox allows you to use a tool inside for building and configuring without taking the tool out of the box. Right click to open the toolbox and put tools in. Then, press the Pick Block bind (default: middle mouse button) to open a radial menu and select a tool. You can then use the toolbox as if it was that type of tool. Pressing Pick Block while looking at a block will also choose an appropriate tool for the job, skipping the radial menu. Sneak and press Pick Block to deselect a tool quickly.%n%nLater on, you can upgrade the toolbox with a battery. This allows the toolbox to recharge electric tools and unlocks the ability for machines and wireless chargers to charge the entire toolbox.%n%nToolboxes can also fix maintenance hatches, using the tools inside. Deselect the equipped tool (if any), then right click the maintenance hatch with the toolbox. All of the tools inside will be applied to the maintenance hatch, fixing any problems it might have.%n%nThe toolbox requires polyethylene, which is a fluid you likely haven't made before. It's up to you to figure out how to get it. Here's a hint: the black gushers of oil found around the world may be the key...

# Quest: The Quest for Holy Water
betterquesting.quest.WPoaCPPwTBSyn2dmh5DcBA.name=§5§l§nThe Quest for Holy Water
betterquesting.quest.WPoaCPPwTBSyn2dmh5DcBA.desc=You got to take a well deserved break from the waterline in UHV, but now that you are going to be making optical circuits, your Grade 6 Purified Water will no longer be enough. Using the Degasser, you can remove all the leftover decontaminants from previous processes and make even more pure water, pure enough for Optical Circuits.%n%nThe tooltip and list of requirements looks intimidating. Try breaking it down into small, digestible units of logic and you will quickly arrive at a solution.

# Quest: High Energy Laser Purification
betterquesting.quest.WqDynhbQQ4GdNMKm0BlbcQ.name=§2§l§nHigh Energy Laser Purification
betterquesting.quest.WqDynhbQQ4GdNMKm0BlbcQ.desc=For even more pure water, you will need to use strong lasers to precisely bombard the water and remove impurities. As usual with the waterline, this multiblock presents you with a complex automation puzzle to solve.

# Quest: Neutronium Compressor
betterquesting.quest.XKKP2E5ORG-ju42dSDd3sw.name=§2§l§nNeutronium Compressor
betterquesting.quest.XKKP2E5ORG-ju42dSDd3sw.desc=In order to compress singularities and eventually infinity catalysts, you'll need the strongest compressor yet: the Neutronium Compressor. This multiblock channels and controls extreme amounts of pressure through carefully calibrated Active Neutronium Casings, but the sheer magnitude of pressure is too much to produce blocks or superdense plates, as any regular material inserted into the device will be compressed down to a singularity. More advanced singularities should be possible in theory, but you'll need something even stronger...%n%n[note]Note that singularity recipes require extreme amounts of items! Consider using Compressed Buses, Quantum Buses, or ME Stocking Input Buses to fit everything in there.[/note]

# Quest: Matter Manipulator MKI
betterquesting.quest.Y4bRCOWFTgyxdTJXWXjFfA.name=§9§lMatter Manipulator MKI
betterquesting.quest.Y4bRCOWFTgyxdTJXWXjFfA.desc=The MKI is where you really start unlocking the potential of the Matter Manipulator. It has a §264 Block§r range and a §264 Block/Second§r speed limit.%n%nUnlike it's prototype predecessor, you now have §5§l3 modes§r available:%n%n- §5§lGeometry§r: Places standard blocks in a selected and configurable shape.%n%n- §5§lCable§r: Allows you to place AE and GT cables & pipes in lines (and connect them automatically).%n%n- §5§lExchange§r: Allows you to swap large swaths of blocks like the TC Equal Trade Focus.%n%nAdditionally, the MKI can connect to your AE network to automatically transfer items and liquids. You can link the tool in your security terminal and use it while within wireless range.%n%nWhen something is placed in the world, the tool will §lpull§r from inventories in this order:%n1 - ME system%n2 - Player's inventory%n3 - Uplink§r%n%nWhen something is removed from the world, the tool will §lpush§r into inventories in this order:%n1 - ME system%n2 - Uplink%n3 - Player's inventory%n4 - The Ground (Items Only)%n%n[note]The MKI also comes with the ability to remove blocks, so there is no need for another excavation upgrade.[/note]

# Quest: Universal Collapser
betterquesting.quest.ZUdnzN4GSxmaxY7xZIgNTg.name=§4§l§nUniversal Collapser
betterquesting.quest.ZUdnzN4GSxmaxY7xZIgNTg.desc=The §5Universal Collapser§r (UC) module is the final module unlock for the §nExo-Foundry§r.%n%nThe UC module grants a 2/4 OC to the Foundry and increases the minimum number of casings by 20, leaving space for only 5 inputs (without an SCB module installed).%n%nThis becomes much more powerful if paired with the §5Hypercooler§r (HC) module to achieve "§6Realized Potential§r", giving a partial 2/2 OC and allowing eternity to be used as a coolant which grants an additional §23§r 2/4 OCs for doing so.%n%n[warn]Only one of these modules may be installed per Foundry.[/warn]

# Quest: Matter Manipulator MKIII
betterquesting.quest._zwtTNh-SG6B4wp221XPcQ.name=§b§lMatter Manipulator MKIII
betterquesting.quest._zwtTNh-SG6B4wp221XPcQ.desc=The MKIII is the final upgrade in the Matter Manipulator series, and grants you access to it's most heightened capabilities. With §210x§r the EU storage as the MKII, it also boasts an §5§lunlimited§r block range and can handle placing §21024 Blocks / Second§r.%n%nThe MKIII comes with all of the features of the MKII, except now with the ability to also use the §5§lQuantum Uplink§r, though you won't be able to build that multiblock until UV.%n%n §3§lAdvanced Copy Options:§r%n%nThe MKIII unlocks an additional toggle in the §5§lAdvanced Options§r sub-menu:%n%n- §5§lAuto-Proxy CRIBs§r: Replaces Crafting Input Buses in the copied region with Crafting Input Proxies linked back to the original CRIB.

# Quest: Creative Flight With MagLev
betterquesting.quest.a-g__0y_SGyed_E6IkIrsg.name=§6§lCreative Flight With MagLev
betterquesting.quest.a-g__0y_SGyed_E6IkIrsg.desc=Getting annoyed trying to reach pipes and conduits around your base? Look no further than the §5§lMagLev Harness§r!%n%nWith the MagLev, you can have creative flight whenever you are within range of a MagLev Pylon and have the Harness equip.%n%nThis will work at half of the range when unpowered, you unlock the full range when it's given §21A§r of it's corresponding tier of power. The MagLev will only draw power while you are in-range, not passively. A Harness can only be tethered to one Pylon at a time, but a Pylon can attach to any number of Harnesses. Will only consume 1A §nregardless§r of how many Harnesses are tethered to the Pylon§r.%n%nThe §6MV Pylon§r has a §c16§r block radius (33x33x33 cube centered around the pylon)%n%nThe §5HV Pylon§r has a §c32§r block radius (65x65x65 cube centered around the pylon)%n%nThe §8EV Pylon§r has a §c48§r block radius (97x97x97 cube centered around the pylon)

# Quest: Powerfail Notifications
betterquesting.quest.a59175-ZS16kxwUW_BCuEQ.name=§6§lPowerfail Notifications
betterquesting.quest.a59175-ZS16kxwUW_BCuEQ.desc=Congratulations on your first EBF!%n%nThroughout your GTNH gameplay you will end up creating hundreds of multiblocks, and will very likely run into a multitude of power failures at some point. %n%nFortunately, we have a dedicated system for helping you stay informed of exactly when and where these power failures occur §3(though the 'why' portion is up to you to figure out!)§r.%n%nWhen a multiblock powerfails, you will receive a notification in §5chat§r, in addition to a visible icon on §5screen§r, and an icon visible on your §5map§r. %n%n§lYou can clear these notifications by§r:%n- Clicking into the multiblock that has powerfailed%n- Deleting the notification in JourneyMap%n- Typing §4/powerfails clear§r%n%nFor those playing §2multiplayer§r, anyone who is on your §2team§r will receive the §2same notifications§r. §2§nOne person§r clearing a notification should clear it for§2 §nall players§r.%n%n[note]This feature uses the same team system as wireless EU. Use <§c/sp invite§r §1[Player Name]§r> to team up.[/note]%n%nAll of these features can be turned off in the gregtech config. If you want the on screen icon to disappear use §4§l/powerfails hide§r. For all in-game options use §4§l/powerfails help§r.

# Quest: Absolute Purity
betterquesting.quest.bNVzOxCORxuo_lhAh13r0A.name=§5§l§nAbsolute Purity
betterquesting.quest.bNVzOxCORxuo_lhAh13r0A.desc=Absolute Baryonic Perfection! This multiblock allows you to create water that is pure even on the subatomic level. Not a single quark is out of place in Grade 8 Purified Water. Thanks to this purity, even more advanced processes are possible, starting with reducing the processing time of Optical Boules and increasing yield on Optical Chips.%n%nWhile the tooltip is certainly a lot less intimidating than the one of the Degasser, automating this process will not be an easy challenge. Have fun solving the puzzle!

# Quest: Crafting Input Proxy
betterquesting.quest.cEFNSTdoRvysoNgmtDLdvg.name=§9§l§nCrafting Input Proxy
betterquesting.quest.cEFNSTdoRvysoNgmtDLdvg.desc=You have mastered both interdimensional transportation and wallsharing, why not combine them?%n%nYou can link both crafting input bus/buffer to proxies with data sticks and use it to process patterns with multiple machines, as if you are wallsharing them, but without actually wallsharing them.%n%n[note]Maybe this can reduce lag?[/note]

# Quest: The Everlasting Guilty Pool
betterquesting.quest.cejGOPB2QiuW5833Z5ontA.name=§4§l§nThe Everlasting Guilty Pool
betterquesting.quest.cejGOPB2QiuW5833Z5ontA.desc=Mana for all of your needs, endless amounts of mana. 

# Quest: pH Neutralization
betterquesting.quest.eon8hLumTS-E7MYJ4TFT3w.name=§b§lpH Neutralization
betterquesting.quest.eon8hLumTS-E7MYJ4TFT3w.desc=If you want to process your Europium-Doped Wafers with a significant speed boost, this machine is for you. Using the pH neutral water you get from this machine, you can process wafers twice as fast.%n%nThis is the first real complex automation challenge in the waterline, it's up to you to figure out how you want to deal with the pH neutralization process. Have fun!%n%n[note]This multiblock is very picky about where its hatches for acids and bases go. If you can't figure out why it's not forming, chances are you forgot to place these hatches in the correct location. Use the hologram projector to see where they go.[/note]

# Quest: Silver Barrel
betterquesting.quest.fhzjYvdATJuUQTMUO1pVvA.name=§c§lSilver Barrel
betterquesting.quest.fhzjYvdATJuUQTMUO1pVvA.desc=The Silver barrel has 72 slots.

# Quest: Hypercooler
betterquesting.quest.h4k6r6ohQp2DJl07w8Boog.name=§9§l§nHypercooler
betterquesting.quest.h4k6r6ohQp2DJl07w8Boog.desc=The §5§lHypercooler§r (HC) module is the first §9§lUIV§r tier module you unlock for the §nExo-Foundry§r.%n%nThe HC module will require one of three different types of coolant be supplied to it via input hatch in exchange for giving overclock bonuses to the Foundry. The input hatch can be set in replacement of any Cryogenic Casing.%n%nAllowed Coolant Types:%n1. Supercoolant (§c100L/s§r) -> §21§r Overclock%n2. Spacetime (§c50L/s§r) -> §22§r Overclocks%n3. Eternity (§c25L/s§r) -> §23§r Overclocks%n%n[note]Eternity can not actually be used as a coolant unless paired with another module unlocked later in UXV.[/note]%n%n[warn]Only one of these modules may be installed per Foundry.[/warn]

# Quest: Multiblock Revolution
betterquesting.quest.hEsmeH74S4aOOrROI1AHxQ.name=§c§lMultiblock Revolution
betterquesting.quest.hEsmeH74S4aOOrROI1AHxQ.desc=The steam machines you have been using until now have served you well, but there will be a time when you need to process even more items. That's where the so-called multiblocks come in. There's a variety of steam multiblocks available to you - go have a look at the Mass Processing quest tab!
%n
%nThis tab introduces you to a wide range of extremely powerful multiblock machines that can replace your old, worn-out singleblocks (and some that can replace your old multiblocks!). Many of these new machines will require you to handle additional mechanics and requirements, but it will be worth it!
%n
%nHere are some terms you should be familiar with as you enter the world of multiblocks:
%n
%n§lOverclock (OC):§r
%nWhenever a machine is running a recipe of a lower tier than it's energy hatch it will gain a speed boost at the cost of more energy usage.
%n
%n§lImperfect Overclock§r (aka. Normal, 2/4 OC):
%nFor each tier above recipe machine will be 2x faster at the cost of 4x energy (2/4 OC)
%n
%n§lPerfect Overclock§r (Often phrased as "Does not lose efficiency when overclocked", 4/4 OC):
%nSome machines conditionally (or unconditionally) perform perfect overclocks. In this case, the machine will be 4x as fast, but it will run at 4x the EU/t (4/4 OC), leading to both increased speed and no net increase in the total EU usage!
%n
%n§lParallel§r (Often phrased as "Processes x items"):
%nMachines which parallel act as if they are running multiple of themselves - that is to say, they are able to perform multiple of the same recipe at the same time, using the recipe's EU/t multiplied by the number of parallels. Machines which parallel will [warn]PRIORITIZE[/warn] this behavior over overclocking, which is good for you! Parallels are more efficient.
%n
%n§lInput Separation:§r
%nRefers to a machine's behavior when choosing inputs for a recipe. With Input Separation on, you must have all required items for a recipe in one bus. With Input Separation off, you can split item inputs of a recipe between multiple busses.
%n
%n[note]When working with multiblocks, if power is interrupted during operation, your inputs will be lost forever... careful![/note]

# Quest: Nano Forge Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.hUEbNbngSA6JxT_Pjq8DNw.name=§4§l§nNano Forge Tier 4
betterquesting.quest.hUEbNbngSA6JxT_Pjq8DNw.desc=The Transcendent nanite has the required complexity and speed to create most nanites, but lacks the strength required to handle the exotic, hyper-dense, magnetic forms of matter you need to manipulate in order to advance. Fortunately with Eternity, you have found an ample replacement that should be up to the task... But you suspect that you'll need a far more complicated structure to be able to contain such a process.%n%n[note]Grants the ability to create §lMagmatter Nanites§r in addition to a greater speed at the cost of assembling a more expensive structure.[/note]

# Quest: NEI Next Level Recipe Search
betterquesting.quest.hmQlN9vLSEOyCnCSOOXz7Q.name=§a§lNEI Next Level Recipe Search
betterquesting.quest.hmQlN9vLSEOyCnCSOOXz7Q.desc=There are even more NEI search options!%n%nIf you are scrolling through recipes, you might have noticed the magnifier symbol on the top, left to the page number. Clicking it opens the §lrecipe search field§r. A search term you enter here will filter all the current recipes to the ones where an input or output matches the term. An easy way to narrow down all screwdriver recipes to just the one from a particular material you want!%n%nIf you use "extended+" search mode the recipe search becomes even more powerful!%n%nHere backticks `` are used around the search queries, but you don't need them when searching.%n%nBy default the search works like in the extended mode, searching in §lany§r of the inputs and outputs of a recipe. So if you search a recipe by `§1-§rdust`, it will return all recipes where there's at least one item that doesn't have §o"dust"§r.%n%nLet's say you want to search only in §linputs§r. Put §a<§r before your search query to do that. For example: `§a<§riron` returns all the recipes with §o"iron"§r in one of the §linputs§r, `§a<§rsteel§5@gregtech§r` returns the recipes with at least one item from any mod containing §9Gregtech§r in their name, using §o"steel"§r.%n%nBut then, if you search by `§a<§1-§rdust` it still returns the recipes with §o"dust"§r on the left. Why is that? Because §a<§r searches among §lall§r items. So if there's one item that doesn't have §o"dust"§r, then it would still match the recipe, even if the rest of the inputs are dusts.%n%nTo solve this, use §a<&§r instead. Like this: `§a<&§1-§rdust`. It returns §lall§r the recipes without §o"dust"§r among the inputs! §a<&§r sets a §lstrict§r condition on §lall§r inputs, unlike §a<§r that sets a condition on §lany§r input.%n%nTo filter the §loutputs§r use §a>§r and §a>&§r. They work the same way, but allow you to filter the §loutputs§r of a recipe. So `§a>§rgold` gives you the recipes with at least one §loutput§r with §o"gold"§r. And `§a>&§rgold` gives you the recipes with §o"gold"§r in every outputted item.%n%nWant to combine multiple conditions? Sure, just put them one after another in any order. E.g. you could search for `§a<§riron§a>§rsteel`, `§a<&§r §1-§b$dust§r §a<§r cell`, `§a>&§1-§rdust cell`.%n%nOr even for `dust§a>§rcell`. Here the non-prefixed part works like default, searching among §lall§r items from the inputs and outputs. So this query returns the recipes with §o"dust"§r in one of the inputs or outputs and §o"cell"§r in one of the outputs.%n%nIn some recipes you might have items that don't belong to inputs or outputs. In order to filter them use `§a^§r` and `§a^&§r` respectively.%n%nYou can add spaces for readability too, because (unless you have space mode on) spaces can be used anywhere while in extended+ mode.

# Quest: Never Hungry Again
betterquesting.quest.hvukogcPRX-hht60vc0Zgw.name=§2§lNever Hungry Again
betterquesting.quest.hvukogcPRX-hht60vc0Zgw.desc=Congratulations! You have gracefully served your penance; no longer shall you be bound by the woes of hunger. %n%nWith this new trinket (equipable in a baubles slot) you will automatically have your hunger and saturation replenished, so long as the nanobooster stays charged.%n%nAdditionally it will do its best to keep you healed, though it cannot ward off death completely on its own.%n%n[note]P.S. Upgrading your wireless charger might be a good idea![/note]%n%n[note]P.P.S. Advanced Nitinol can be made out of blocks of Nitinol 60 with a Quantum Anomaly in a Laser Engraver, or you can go the plasma method once you unlock MKIII fusion.[/note]

# Quest: Quantum Uplink
betterquesting.quest.jZURYQZlSuitTiiasN4J8A.name=§2§l§nQuantum Uplink
betterquesting.quest.jZURYQZlSuitTiiasN4J8A.desc=The §5§lQuantum Uplink§r is a multi made specifically for the Matter Manipulator that is unlocked with the aid of UV tech. %n%nThis allows the Matter Manipulator to connect to your ME system over an infinite range, and across dimensions. The tool can be linked by placing it into the controller while the uplink is active. The uplink will take a continuous 1A of ZPM power to function.%n%nAdditionally, you can now use it to create fake ME patterns upon selecting an area. This will make it quick to order all of the parts needed for Copy & Pasting in an area. %n%n[warn]The Uplink is powerful, but at a cost. Moving all items / fluids from the AE system will cost a small amount of plasma per transfer. %n%nSpecifically: 16k EU of plasma per item / per 1000L of fluid[/warn]

# Quest: NEI Next Level Search
betterquesting.quest.kR1YVSq2R4WFu9KNM9lCZQ.name=§a§lNEI Next Level Search
betterquesting.quest.kR1YVSq2R4WFu9KNM9lCZQ.desc=NEI search got improved even further!%n%nSelect a search mode extended+ to try it out!%n%nExtended+ works pretty much like extended, but it doesn't support * and ? expanding in the names. Also the following symbols have to be escaped with a `\`: `-` (dash) `<` and `>` (less-than and more-than) `^` (caret) `{` and `}` (curly brackets) `|` (vertical bar) `\` (backslash) ` ` (space) `"` (quote) alongside with the prefixes that you have enabled like §5@§r or §b$§r.%n%nExamples: §5@§oElectro\-Magic§r, §oiron\ ingot§r, §oPB\&J§r.%n%nExtended+ adds some QoL to your everyday search experience and an improved recipe search (next quest). In the following backticks `` are used around the search queries. You don't need them when searching.%n%nWant to search for something without having to put a backslash before every other symbol? Use quotes! You could use a quote inside quotes too, but you would have to escape it. Like this: `§6"§r\"§6"§r`.%n%nUse curly brackets §7{}§r to group conditions. Searching for `§7{§rmytryl§7|§rmanasteel§7}§r hammer head` would show you hammer heads made out of mytryl or manasteel.%n%nSpace is no longer necessary to use. So `§7{§rmytryl§7|§rmanasteel§7}§rhammer` works too!%n%nThere's a space mode support, so if you want your spaces to work literally turn it on!%n%nQuotes no longer require a closing quote. So you could search for `§6"§riron ingot` and it would work! You still do need a quote if you want your quotes to end though.%n%nRegex syntax got simplified (though the old one is still supported). Now instead of `§br/§rsome regex§b/§r` you could search for `§b/§rsome regex` and it would work too! You still do need a slash if you want your regex to end. Regex doesn't require escaping, the same way quotes don't, with the only exception being the `/`. So to find a slash with a regex you would search with `§b/§r\/`.%n%nYou can use quotes or regex after prefix to search with them instead of a plain text. For example, use `§5@§6"§5chest minecarts§r` to search for items from the §9Iron Chest Minecarts§r mod. Or `§5@§b/§5chest minecarts§r` to do the same with a regex.

# Quest: Clarifier
betterquesting.quest.mMCFuGqxQTuuLnJgEldztA.name=§d§lClarifier
betterquesting.quest.mMCFuGqxQTuuLnJgEldztA.desc=The first step in the water purification process is the clarifier. Operating this machine is a simple task, you will just need to maintain a steady supply of Activated Carbon for the filters. Using this machine, you will be able to make Grade 1 Purified Water, which can speed up processing of Naquadah-Doped Boules and Wafers by 25%%.

# Quest: Iron Barrel
betterquesting.quest.ne_onBK6TP2F_ySPabM7Lw.name=§c§lIron Barrel
betterquesting.quest.ne_onBK6TP2F_ySPabM7Lw.desc=The Iron barrel has 54 slots.

# Quest: Purifying Water With Plasma
betterquesting.quest.pMGI_sXdQSKWWFFxTunqvA.name=§2§l§nPurifying Water With Plasma
betterquesting.quest.pMGI_sXdQSKWWFFxTunqvA.desc=As usual, before you can make use of your Americium to make better wafers, you will need better water. This time, we're going to use plasma to rapidly heat up the water and then cool it back down.%n%nSome of the mechanics may seem similar to how you set up the pH neutralization process, maybe you can expand on what you learned there?%n%n[note]This multiblock is very picky about where its plasma and coolant input hatches go. If you can't figure out why it's not forming, chances are you forgot to place these hatches in the correct location. Use the hologram projector to see where they go.[/note]

# Quest: NEI is EVEN MORE POWERFUL NOW?
betterquesting.quest.pl7uw8oSRhe6L4DmTRfrOQ.name=§a§lNEI is EVEN MORE POWERFUL NOW?
betterquesting.quest.pl7uw8oSRhe6L4DmTRfrOQ.desc=NEI now automatically collapses similar items into one slot making browsing much faster! To collapse/uncollapse a group use ALT+LMB.%nYou can also create your own presets with custom groups!%n%n[note]You can disable this functionality in NEI settings.[/note]%n%nAlso now NEI has JEI-like Advanced Search:%n%n@ - search by mod (@minecraft)%n%n[note]There are even more special characters that you can use but most of them are off by default (e.g. no need to use # to search in tooltip), below are all the special characters, check which ones are on/off in NEI settings.%n%nSpace is used as a logical AND between different conditions%n# - search by tooltip (#UV-Tier)%n& - search by id: (extratrees:door)%n$ - search by ore dictionary ($ore)%n%% - search by subsets (%%block)%n| - logical or. multi-item search (wrench|hammer)%n- - logical not. exclude items that match the following expression (-@minecraft)%n" - multiple words wrapped in quotes are treated as one condition rather than several ("White Stained Glass")%n%nSearch Mode (apply on search parts, not full string):%nPlain - simple string%nExtended - allow only ?, * rules (by default)%nRegex - allow full regex%n%nIn Extended Search Mode:%n? - any character (@min?craft)%n* - any few characters (@m*ft = @minecraft)%nr/.../ - standard java regex (@r/m\w{6}ft/ = @minecraft)[/note]%n%n[note]You can disable this functionality in NEI settings.[/note]%n%nYou can add bookmarks with the A key while hovering over an item, also:%nHold SHIFT to bookmark the whole recipe%nHold CTRL to bookmark number of items%nHold SHIFT + CTRL to bookmark both recipe and all the number of all the items it contains

# Quest: Flocculation
betterquesting.quest.sZ9d2SzSSLSc9tccXG_L4g.name=§b§lFlocculation
betterquesting.quest.sZ9d2SzSSLSc9tccXG_L4g.desc=You want to start using your new Europium to make even better wafers, but it turns out that your old methods of creating purified water are no longer enough. You will need to use the Flocculation Purification Unit to make even better purified water first. To run this machine, you will need large amounts of Polyaluminium Chloride, but luckily you can get all your Chlorine back if you properly recycle the waste liquid.

# Quest: Dark Steel Chest
betterquesting.quest.t6xRGFm_S2SG6_-xNh8mwQ.name=§6§lDark Steel Chest
betterquesting.quest.t6xRGFm_S2SG6_-xNh8mwQ.desc=After embracing the dark side you get access to the new even bigger dark steel chest... perhaps another upgrade will be available in the future?%n%n[note]Just as with the previous chests you can also upgrade with a fitting upgrade item.[/note]

# Quest: Crafting, but with Beams!
betterquesting.quest.xTkeDXIZSlmRkde8LZgzLw.name=§b§lCrafting, but with Beams!
betterquesting.quest.xTkeDXIZSlmRkde8LZgzLw.desc=The Beam Crafter allows you to craft items using two beam-like inputs! If you are familiar with the Target Chamber, this works the same way, but with two beams instead of one.%n%nEach Beam Crafting recipe requires two particle inputs. You must provide enough of both types of particles to finish the craft. The progress of a craft in the Beam Crafter depends entirely on the number of provided particles, but will draw power the entire time. %n%n[note]This also means that the speed of the craft is entirely dependent on how quickly you can provide particles, and as a result the WAILA estimate is likely inaccurate.[/note]%n%nFailing to provide particles consistently is not an issue! The machine will continue to draw power while it waits for more particles, but you will not lose crafting progress.%n%n[note]If enough of one of the input particles is provided, providing more of that particle has no effect on the progress of the craft.[/note]

# Quest: Thaumometric Essentia Cell
betterquesting.quest.xdiDnTdpTgW6POwCuDlPgg.name=§9§l§nThaumometric Essentia Cell
betterquesting.quest.xdiDnTdpTgW6POwCuDlPgg.desc=After meddling with the 4th Dimension, you've finally discovered a way to access its unlimited Essentia supply. The Thaumometric Essentia Cell is your tool for extracting Essentia from this boundless source—think of it as your unlimited magic credit card.

# Quest: Creative Mana Tablet
betterquesting.quest.ykz6BsyOTl2m_xfS28ofXA.name=§4§l§nCreative Mana Tablet
betterquesting.quest.ykz6BsyOTl2m_xfS28ofXA.desc=This tablet holds the power of gaia in your hands, it gives infinite mana to any tool you have...

# Quest: Exo-Foundry
betterquesting.quest.ziczkJstQ7C0LgmnzTUTeA.name=§5§l§nExo-Foundry
betterquesting.quest.ziczkJstQ7C0LgmnzTUTeA.desc=You didn't think we were going to force you to use the Mass Solidifier for the rest of the game, did you? Imagine being compelled to make hundreds of those for gate... that would just be cruel!%n%n§lIntroducing the Exo-Foundry!§r %n%nThe §5§lExo-Foundry§r is a direct upgrade to the §5Mass Solidifier§r, and just a few of them will be powerful enough to support your infrastructure for the rest of the game. But let's start off with one for now.%n%nThere are three separate tiers, and seven different modules. Each tier allows you to place more modules on the machine, starting with two at T1 and ending with four at T3. Each module has its own special set of abilities, and you can combine them in unique ways to get a Foundry that best fits your infrastructure.%n%nThe questbook will explain the function of each module type, but the best way to view all of the information together is to use the GUI of the Foundry itself and the tooltips visible on the individual blocks. %n%n[note]For even more information regarding the precise mathematics of module combinations and interactions, you can also check out the Wiki: [url]https://wiki.gtnewhorizons.com/wiki/Exo-Foundry[/url][/note]


